INSERT INTO `daily_reports` VALUES (86,27,'1. Spent the morning hours up to 10:30 am following up on my leads and scheduling site visits.\n2. Went to source for the Golden Mansion apartments in Muthithi road and got a consent.\n3. Went to source for ready units at the Misty Springs apartments and found there are 1 and 2 BR available for sale from Kshs 8.5M.\n4. Spent the afternoon following on my hot leads for viewing apartments, villas, and plots and waiting for their feedback.','2025-11-07','Almost closing','2025-11-07 13:47:32','2025-11-07 13:47:32'),(88,24,'Made follow up calls to the existing inquiries.\nHeld a meeting with Mr.Danish regarding the Luminara Project.\nSent and offer letter for the 1.6acres Arwings Kodhek property for 450Million.  ','2025-11-07','','2025-11-07 15:15:30','2025-11-07 15:15:30'),(89,27,'WEEKLY REPORT QUESTIONNAIRE FOR THE SALES TEAM\n1. Targets & Performance\n•	What were your specific targets for this week?\n1.	Follow up with Gladwell Wanjiru, my lead who viewed 1050 residences in Kilimani and Astra Bay in Lower Kabete. To get an offer letter from her.\n2.	Benter Okonji has scheduled a viewing for this Wednesday to view an apartment for investment in Riverside, Lavington, and Kileleshwa – Kaputiei.\n3.	Secure consents from Golden Mansion in Westlands, and Synina developers for their two developments: Synina residency and Beacon.\n4.	Source for my hot leads’ properties in Kiambu road, Westlands, Spring Valley, Riverside, and Lavington.\n5.	Follow up on Mr Bogale on his interest in an apartment within the blue zone area.\n•	How many have you achieved so far?\nTwo of the above:\n1.	I got a consent from Golden Mansion apartment developers in Westlands\n2.	Sourced for some apartments in Westlands especially ready 1 and 2 bedrooms.\n•	How many site visits did you complete (with clients)?\nNONE\n•	How many new property leads did you source (with full details and consent letters)?\n1.	Golden Mansion apartments in Westlands, Muthithi road.\n•	How many new client inquiries did you receive, and how many are still active/following up?\nI received 3 new clients for Luminara, and I am actively following up on two of them: Ken and Hitesh\n•	Did you meet or exceed your area coverage plan (Kilimani, Kileleshwa, Lavington)?\nNo. This week I covered Westlands.\n2. Lead Follow-Ups & Client Handling\n•	How many old leads did you contact or follow up with this week?\n5 old leads.\n•	Please list the names or initials of the clients you followed up with and their current status (e.g., interested, viewing scheduled, not responding, closed).\n•	\n1.	Mr Jack – Interested in Villa in Kiambu.\n2.	Mr Wilson – Interested in a ready 1 bedroom in Westlands.\n3.	Mr Bogale – Interested in buying an apartment close to Gigiri.\n4.	Benter Okonji – Interested in an investment unit in Riverside, Lavington, and Kileleshwa.\n5.	Mrs Gladwell Wanjiru – Interested in a 2 bedroom in 1050 residency, Kilimani.\n•	Which clients have pending follow-ups that need attention next week?\nNONE\n•	Have any clients gone silent, and what’s your next step to re-engage them?\n5 leads have gone silent, and my next step is to engage them via WhatsApp and texts until they respond.\n•	How many viewings were conducted, and what was the client feedback on the properties?\nNONE\n•	Did you share live locations or updates during viewings and sourcing as required?\nYes.\n3. Achievements\n•	What was your biggest achievement or win this week?\n1.	Reactivating one of my old leads, Mr Wilson and getting to probe him again on his enquiry and he is interested in a ready 1 bedroom to live in Westlands.\n2.	Mrs Gladwell is ready with Kshs2M as deposit for a 2-bedroom in 1050 residency. We are waiting for her offer to be accepted.\n3.	Benter Okonji is now looking for a 3 bedroom to live or invest in Riverside, Langton or Kileleshwa. This is after she went cold.\n•	Any new listings or clients you’re proud of securing?\nYes. Ken who is interested in investing in Luminara.\n•	Any property owners you built a new relationship with or got consent from?\nYes, Golden Mansion apartments in Muthithi road, Westlands.\n•	Any positive client feedback worth noting?\nYes. Our consultancy advice is top notch.\n4. Challenges\n•	What were your biggest challenges this week (e.g., client responsiveness, location access, consent letter issues, pricing)?\n1.	Getting rentals in Parklands, Kileleshwa, and Westlands.\n2.	Scheduling viewings with leads and then they end up postponing.\n•	What support or resources do you need from the team or management to overcome these?\nCurrently none. To be determined.\n•	Any listings or developments that were difficult to get information or access to?\nYes, Tassa apartments in Kilimani.\n5. Next Week Planning\n•	What are your key focus areas or priorities for next week?\n1.	To get the consents for the 5 new listings I sourced in this and last week.\n2.	Follow up with all my Village Market leads.\n3.	Achieving my target of 3 viewings with the leads.\n4.	Closing either a sale or a rental.\n•	Any specific clients or properties you plan to push or close?\nYes:\n1.	Mr Bogale – 3-bedroom apartment to buy and live in.\n2.	Capt Atandi – Syokimau Villa.\n3.	Benter Okonji – Wants a 3br apartment for living in or for investment.\n4.	Michael – wants a Villa in Lavington.\n\n•	Which days are you planning for fieldwork or viewings?\nWednesdays and Saturdays.','2025-11-09','Hi Caroline. This is the weekly report that we are supposed to submit.','2025-11-09 15:37:05','2025-11-09 15:37:05'),(91,22,'This is a summary of my report from 3rd-7th November 2025\nMonday;  Spent the day in the office, preparing for the week and finalising on my weekly report, Later went to a site visit in Tigoni with Joy and Brian.\nTuesday; attended morning office meeting, did a followup calls with clients and land owners, later met with a clients to finalise on a four bed villa at Amalia springs in Kamiti road which final scenario will be determined by 15th Nov 2025. with the same property owner we  went to Kitengela Chuna estate to view three more of his properties on sale.\nWednesday; Attended the morning office meeting and later proceeded to viewpoint Limuru ,Lari for a video shoot  with the media team and also a client of same came for viewing, waiting for her feedback within the month of November.\nThursday; Met a client interested in two acres of land in Cianda area Kiambu, we later went ahead to meet the land owner in  Two- rivers mall, negotiation still ongoing hopefully to get to closure within the month. later that afternoon went for sourcing and got two properties in mirema drive and thindigua. still following up with the owners.\nFriday; Spent the day in the office doing follow up calls and getting new leads also compilling my weekly report and later in the afternoon went for viewing in Ruiru Kamakis.  ','2025-11-10','','2025-11-10 07:36:46','2025-11-10 07:36:46'),(92,23,'Went for sourcing. Got 1 three bedrooms apartment for rent on Hatheru. \n1 apartments for sale Princess park. 13M 3 bedrooms\nOnly 1 lead assigned on Saturday by media team\n15 previous leads follow up on\n\nSourcing on Hatheru amd Valley arcade and along Gitanga road.\n1 SV conducted\nNew project in Kilimani. Fountain residency for sale.\nVillage market activation on Friday, Saturday and Sunday.\n\nNext week plan is to follow up on all 32 leads acquired i village market activation through out the weekend. Presentation by fountain residency to the team amd site viewings.','2025-11-10','','2025-11-10 08:22:45','2025-11-10 08:22:45'),(93,12,'Last week\'s report \n\nI managed the following targets:\n15 follow ups with previous clients \n1 new sourcing for a property in Karen \n4 site visits with clients on site \nFor the site visits\nTamara -viewed 3 br in kilimani and later proceeded to syokimau to view varieties \nLetty -viewed the 10 acre land in Tigoni \nBrian -Viewed 3 br apartment in blossom ivy \nIan - viewed 3 br apartment in syokimau \nThere was no new lead provided by the media team last week.\nApart from the followed and completed viewing appointment above for the 4 clients,I also handled;\nBrian: my previous client who will be available next week to view 1 br apartment to invest in , along Ngong\' road \nMike: I shared a land options with him since he declined the mansiontte in Kitusuru having been smaller ,he asked to view the option upon return to Kenya from Germany by early December \nDan: I followed up with Mr Dan concerning the 2 br he\'s looking to buy in Westland ,he is available next week to view a few options \nRiley: I managed to share Luminara project with her , it\'s relevant to the option she\'s looking for in Westlands for investment purpose \nBeatrice:she asked to be viewing over next weekend,for the 5 br mansionatte in syokimau \nFor next week ,I need to follow up with the following client \nTamara,so she share an update concerning the viewing \nBrian:he mentioned he will send a representative to take forward for the blossom ivy 3 br unit ,they considered buying \nBeatrice,open for a viewing appointment over next weekend \nLetty, she\'s working on her offer letter for the 10 acres land in Tigoni \nAlso for the silent clients \nMr Arthur: I will share Luminara project to follow up with him concerning the 2 br he\'s looking to buy for investment \nPriyesh: I will visit diplomat project and share the progress on ground,also I will share Luminara project as well \nDan: I will give him a call and invite him for a viewing appointment for the Luminara project \nAndrew: I\'ll give him a call again this week and share with him other upcoming project in syokimau \nFor next week I already have 2 clients who have confirmed their viewing appointment \n1 . Beatrice for the 5 br mansionatte in syokimau \n2. Mercy ,2 br apartment for azure apartments in syokimau','2025-11-10','','2025-11-10 13:56:36','2025-11-10 13:56:36'),(94,27,'1. I took my half day of today from 8:30 to 1:00pm and reported back to the office at 1pm.\n2. Wilson reached out to me and would like to view a 1Br apartment which is ready to move in. He was to come to the office at 3pm, but he didn\'t make it today. Maybe tomorrow.\n3. Followed up with all my 5 assigned Luminara leads and 2 are serious. They are scheduling to view Luminara this week.\n4. Followed up with all my other BEKE leads.','2025-11-10','Almost there on a closure.','2025-11-10 14:36:57','2025-11-10 14:36:57'),(95,15,'Went for shooting of the in  villa in Karen,\n\nFinished on the edit for limuru\nManaged to generate 6 leads for the luminara ','2025-11-10','','2025-11-10 17:45:45','2025-11-10 17:45:45'),(96,13,'I uploaded two projects from carol and Denis, 1 for sale and 1 for rent.\nI helped some of my colleagues to understand the CRM better.\nI uploaded my clients on the CRM as requested; I am yet to do follow up with others before i can add them as well.\nI got in touch with the website developer in regard to some changes that needed to be made, and he worked on them as requested.\n\n\n','2025-11-10','','2025-11-10 18:00:37','2025-11-10 18:00:37'),(98,12,'Today I managed to call 2 leads provided by Rashid,one of the lead was offline so I sent the details for Luminara on WhatsApp waiting for his feedback \nThe other client was traveling and I didn\'t manage to share all the details via call ,so I proceeded and shared on email \n\nLater I managed to call my leads generated from village Market,three of them calls made were positive with what they wanted,one of them had scheduled from r a viewing next week \nThe other who\'s looking for 1 br along othaya road also is planning to view over this week ','2025-11-10','','2025-11-10 18:58:02','2025-11-10 18:58:02'),(99,23,'-Morning meeting\n-Followed up on leads thats I got from village market.\n- 2 have confirmed for luminara viewing for Saturday and the other one has scheduled for Tuesday next week.\n-1 person has scheduled to view land in Migaa 1/8 acre going for 6.5\n- 1 is interested in Angani gardens 3 bedrooms apartment going for 19.5M. They are yet to confirm their availability to view the property.','2025-11-11','','2025-11-11 06:10:36','2025-11-11 06:10:36'),(100,22,'-Attended the morning office meeting.\n-Finished on my last weeks report.\n-Did follow up calls to clients and land owners.\n-Went sourcing for two properties , one in outering road 1 acre going for 210m and the other in tatu city 0.5acres  going 24m\n','2025-11-11','','2025-11-11 06:22:50','2025-11-11 06:22:50'),(101,20,'i went for sourcing along ngong road for 1 acre as a request for the client where i presented to him and scheduled for Friday viewing \nfrom 2pm i went for sourcing on upperhill where i got 2 acres for sale where thy requested for client to sign for concents','2025-11-11','','2025-11-11 06:30:46','2025-11-11 06:30:46'),(102,9,'今天拜访了永盛装饰冷总，了解到他们有几个工厂，包括铝材加工，铁艺加工，腻子粉工厂，在肯尼亚有15年，主要与国家，央企接工程比较多。也有做一些私企的装修，相对来说比较有经验。有几套房子也需要BEKE转销售，同时谈未来BEKE接单旧房改造装修与永盛合作之事。','2025-11-11','','2025-11-11 14:06:42','2025-11-11 14:06:42'),(103,23,'-Team meeting\n-Calls to leads that have been assigned by Rashid.\n-Follow up on leads that I got from Village Market.\n-Some clients from Village market wanted options in Syokimau and Kitengela So i worked on sending them options with a budget of 10-12M.\n-Scheduled a meeting with AAD to pitch Fountain Residency.\n-Put in customers to the CRM.\n','2025-11-11','','2025-11-11 14:10:21','2025-11-11 14:10:21'),(104,27,'1. After the early morning meeting, I followed up with my Luminara leads for a scheduled site visit. Two of them have scheduled for this weekend.\n2. Followed up with my lead who is interested in a fully furnished apartment in Kileleshwa, Kilimani, and Lavington.\n3. Later went for sourcing and viewing of Purple Haze and Riara One for furnished apartments and found options for my lead, of which I am sharing with him.\n4. Back to the office and following up with my leads.','2025-11-11','Working out on finding the right property that fits my leads.','2025-11-11 14:11:41','2025-11-11 14:11:41'),(105,22,'A. Attended the morning office meeting\nB. Met with a client and the land owner at Ridgeway mall for the purpose of renegotiating the initial deposit of 2acres in Cianda, Kiambu. It was not conclusive for the land owner asked for more time to consult his family-he is to give a feedback before the end of the week.\nC. Met another client interested with a four bed villa at Amallia springs in Kamiti Road, we were to get a go ahead to give an offer letter from the landlord after the client previously proposed a mode of payment that  the landlord was hesitant to accept. So after talks today the landlord declined. \nD. Went for sourcing and I got 0.5acre land in Muthithi estate with a three bed bungalow going 75m.\n','2025-11-11','','2025-11-11 14:31:27','2025-11-11 14:31:27'),(106,19,'Sent out all daily reports (except for one)\nCompleted all assigned tasks on time. \nRestocked the office with necessary supplies. \nWent sourcing with Musa (Managed to get a total of 20 leads)\nScheduled a follow up with an agent, \n\n','2025-11-11','none . ','2025-11-11 17:06:04','2025-11-11 17:06:04'),(107,13,'1. Today I uploaded 2 projects for land from Dominic, I was promised others tomorrow by my colleagues since  they are still waiting for the consent letters to be signed.\n2. I called one client Lilian and updated in the CRM I also shared with her a few options in the areas she had requested, I will be getting back to her tomorrow to follow up if she liked the options I had shared.\n3. I worked on a few changes on the website; editing locations and also changing photos where necessary.\n4.I had a small sharing with Carol on writing the real estate insights, she was to share a few topics which i could add on the website, I also did some research from other real estate websites and also articles. I will be adjusting ours tomorrow.\n5. I worked on the google business reviews; I finished setting up the account as requested by google and am now waiting for their feedback.\n\n\n','2025-11-12','Hoping that the website will soon start bringing in leads which will convert into sales','2025-11-11 17:17:02','2025-11-11 17:17:02'),(108,15,'Editing of the limuru land for boosting.\nEditing of the Karen villas shot yesterday.\n\nGenerated 2 leads for the sales team ','2025-11-11','','2025-11-11 17:53:10','2025-11-11 17:53:10'),(109,20,'I went for a viewing with client for the 2.4acres along Ngong road where he requested for a meeting next week when he will be available \nI went to search for a JV in Kilimani as a request from a client where I got 1 but it had alot of challenges to access on the ground ','2025-11-11','','2025-11-11 18:46:47','2025-11-11 18:46:47'),(110,12,'Today early in the morning,my client Ian rescheduled for the site revisit for sunpark,for Friday, he\'s planning to confirm available units and also detailed payment plan \n\nI followed up with Joyce, concerning the Luminara project,she didn\'t respond to call, thereafter I messaged her on WhatsApp,I sent her more information for the project on her Whatsapp \nI also followed up with Brian whom I took last week for viewing,he mentioned he had shared my number with so we proceed to site , they\'re open to purchase two units of 3 bedrooms are blossom ivy \nI later managed to transfer my previous clients into the new CRM \n','2025-11-11','','2025-11-11 18:51:06','2025-11-11 18:51:06'),(111,24,'8:35-9:10\nHeld the meeting with the team where we discussed out targets and shared the leads and requests from Village Market for our perusal.\n\n9:30-10:30\nHeld another meeting with the Team Leaders and Mr.Ken to discuss how we can use the CRM to monitor the progress of each client and daily tasks of each individual.\n\n10:30-1:50\nMade follow up calls to my previous clients and the ones i got from Village Market.\n\n2:10-3:45\nMade follow up calls to confirm  tomorrow\'s meeting and availability of various properties.\nFollowed up on three leads that were shared today by various agentswhich included sourcing for them new properties.\n\n3:50-6:10 \nHeld a meeting with Juma,Lawyer for 1.6acres for Hurlingham to discuss progress of the purchase. The Client\'s lawyer requested for the updated  Title deed with deceased landowner\'s name.','2025-11-11','','2025-11-11 19:36:21','2025-11-11 19:36:21'),(112,11,'	1.	I led the morning team meeting from 8:30 to 9:00 a.m., attended by Dennis and Desmond. We discussed each person’s plan for the day and reviewed progress on the Luminara project.\n	2.	I continued reaching out to my Village Market clients regarding Luminara and successfully shared project details with all contacts I hadn’t managed to reach yesterday.\n	3.	Later in the day, I left the office for a meeting with my business partner, which went on until late in the evening.','2025-11-11','','2025-11-11 20:58:27','2025-11-11 20:58:27'),(113,9,'今天拜访了内罗毕设计师公司老板Mutahi，他代表地主与买家洽谈JV合作，地主需要先给5亿先令，其它再JV，基本达成双方意愿。同时邀请设计公司下次进入我们网站服务商。','2025-11-12','','2025-11-12 08:50:38','2025-11-12 08:50:38'),(114,23,'Weekly Report\n\nActivities This Week:\n\nSourcing:\n\n-Conducted sourcing along Hatheru, Valley Arcade, and Gitanga Road.\n\n-Identified 1 three-bedroom apartment for rent on Hatheru. asking price is 100k per month.\n\nIdentified 1 three-bedroom apartment for sale at Princess Park (Ksh 13M).\n\nLeads & Follow-ups:\n\n1 new lead assigned by the media team on Saturday.\n\n15 previous leads followed up on.\n\nSite Visits:\n\n1 site visit (SV) conducted. David. A client wanting 3-bedroom apartment but did not like the option that i had gotten. too old and not well maintained.\n\nNew Projects:\n\n-Introduced Fountain Residency, Kilimani — apartments for sale.\n-Princess Park for sale.\n-Hatheru apartments for rent.\n\n\nActivations:\n\nParticipated in Village Market activation on Friday, Saturday, and Sunday.\n\nPlans for Next Week:\n\n-Follow up on all 32 leads acquired during the Village Market activation.\n\n-Attend Fountain Residency presentation to the team.\n\n-Conduct site viewings for potential clients.','2025-11-12','','2025-11-12 10:37:21','2025-11-12 10:37:21'),(115,19,'Sent out all daily reports (except for one)\nCompleted all assigned tasks on time. \nRestocked the office with necessary supplies.\nScheduled another follow up with an agent, \nManaged to secure a new listing for the agency called: HEPHE PALACE','2025-11-12','','2025-11-12 12:11:16','2025-11-12 12:11:16'),(116,22,'1.I had a meeting with a client for viewing at Ruiru KAMAKIS by 9:30Am but she was late by almost 2hrs, she finally showed up but didn’t like the parcel she wants me to another nearer to the Eastern ByPass.\n2. Had another client for Migaa Estate by noon  but due to lateness of my morning client I had to reschedule the time of our meeting to 4pm. He liked the parcel and willing to give an offer letter by the beginning of next month when his money will be ready. \n3. I was unable to attend the Luminara office meeting because of time challange\n\n','2025-11-12','','2025-11-12 16:25:20','2025-11-12 16:25:20'),(117,15,'Finished on the Karen villas ,was approved by Joseph and so I posted it \n\n2 . Leads was rolled today and assigned to Brian and caro respectively, on the same not two agent and a owns owner also massaged and I asked them to visit our offices.','2025-11-12','','2025-11-12 16:53:32','2025-11-12 16:53:32'),(118,17,'Attended the morning meeting at 8:30am,\nPrepared two scripts for Friday shoots.\nPrepared texts for the Karen villa videos.','2025-11-12','','2025-11-12 18:31:32','2025-11-12 18:31:32'),(119,13,'1.Today I uploaded 1 project for land\n2.I called my client Lilian and she liked Vienna garden as I had shared it with her,I am looking forward to her going for a viewing soon.\n3 .I had a meeting with Mr Ken and the developers in the afternoon.\n4.We went to Luminara in the evening.','2025-11-12','','2025-11-12 18:56:56','2025-11-12 18:56:56'),(120,20,'I went to view a plot along kitusuru which was 2acres \nI proceeded to Kikuyu gatune area and viewed the 5 acres but the client declined the area because we were informed it is on gikambura\nLater I went to Kilimani with an agent to have a meeting with the advocate to discuss the matter of a land as the client demands which will be attended tomorrow ','2025-11-12','','2025-11-12 19:26:21','2025-11-12 19:26:21'),(121,12,'\nClient Follow-Up Summary (Today):\n\nMr. Andrew: Followed up regarding his previous inquiry for a 1-bedroom apartment along Mombasa Road. He confirmed availability for a viewing appointment on Friday at 10 AM.\n\nAjay: Reached out to discuss his interest in a 4- or 5-bedroom penthouse. I identified a suitable option in General Mathenge and will be recording a house tour video to share with him. He expressed strong interest, with a budget of KSh 65 million.\n\nLetty: Followed up on the Tigoni land; she’s currently drafting an offer letter.\n\nLynne: Presented the Luminara project to her. She requested that I follow up on Friday for further discussion.\n\nMr. Anthony: Contacted regarding his search for a 2-bedroom apartment in the upmarket area for residential use. Shared several options, and he requested a follow-up on Friday for feedback.\n\nStellato: Scheduled an appointment to discuss entering into an agreement for their commercial spaces available for sale and rent.\n','2025-11-12','','2025-11-12 19:27:27','2025-11-12 19:27:27'),(122,23,'-Morning departmental meeting \n-Got a draft agreement for fountain residency \n-presentation by AAD on fountain residency by Damaris in the office.\n-9 follow up calls to clients. \nPresentation at luminara office','2025-11-12','','2025-11-12 19:35:41','2025-11-12 19:35:41'),(123,27,'1.Early morning meeting as our sales team to recap on yesterday\'s day’s working plan, and today’s work plan.\n2.Then spent the other early morning following up on my hot leads along with their sourcings.\n3.Went for sourcing at Centum Real Estate and was oriented on all their projects in Nairobi, Vipingo, and out of Kenya and bargained for a commission of 2.5%. Awaiting the draft consent to be sent to us.\n4.Came back to the office for my lead’s follow up.\n5.Then we as BEKE went to Luminara for another orientation and for a birthday celebration for Brian and Evans.','2025-11-12','All is well.','2025-11-13 06:11:13','2025-11-13 06:11:13'),(124,19,'Sent out all daily reports (except for one)\nCompleted all assigned tasks on time. \nRestocked the office with necessary supplies.\nScheduled another follow up with an agent,  \nManaged to secure a new listing for the agency called: HEPHE PALACE\n\nUpdate : \nRashid got to Hephe Palace before i joined BEKE. ','2025-11-13','Tough work day : (','2025-11-13 13:17:20','2025-11-13 13:17:20'),(125,27,'1. Spent the morning in the office following up with my Luminara and my previous BEKE leads.\n2. Updated my CRM by entering my leads and will have keyed-in all of them by tomorrow.\n3. Managed to book our shooting session at Golden Mansion tomorrow at 11am.\n4. Took madam Benter to view Riverside One apartments for investment.\n5. Back in the office on more leads\' follow up.','2025-11-13','A closure is loading','2025-11-13 14:43:16','2025-11-13 14:43:16'),(126,15,'1.Majored in the training for meta business suite for marketing \nObjectives\nI. Campaign targeting lookalike audience for the formerclient engaged with previously using client list.\nii.targetiing core audience for purposes of getting qualified leads \niii. Targeting Kenyan clients in the abroads countries who are likely to convert as qualified leads .\n\n2. Attended the evaluation meeting which was geered to restructuring and making sure that BEKE admin tea m responsibility is keenly noted to each team member .\n\nRolled three leads for sales team and 1 agent who was looking to partner ','2025-11-13','','2025-11-13 17:26:23','2025-11-13 17:26:23'),(127,13,'1.Today I attended the meta training which took long from morning to the afternoon,we did the theory part and also the practical part of the session which was quite engaging.\n2.I received a consent letter from Dennis and took it for stamping,I am still waiting for the feedback before I can upload it.\n3.Carol shared with me some content for the blog, though I wasn\'t able to upload much of it ,I will be working on it fully tomorrow.\n4.I attended the evening meeting with Mr Ken and the administration team where we had some new changes in the department in regards to the leads generation processes.','2025-11-13','','2025-11-13 17:38:12','2025-11-13 17:38:12'),(128,12,'\n\nToday, I followed up with Beatrice, who had expressed interest in the 5-bedroom maisonette in Syokimau. She has scheduled a viewing appointment for this coming Saturday and requested that I get in touch tomorrow to confirm the exact time.\n\nI also shared details of the 5-bedroom penthouse at Sunstone, General Mathenge, with Mr. Jay as requested. He mentioned that he will be available for viewing next week, as he is currently out of town. Mr. Jay is specifically looking to purchase a 5-bedroom penthouse.\n\nAdditionally, I followed up with Mr. Andrew, who has scheduled a viewing appointment for the 1-bedroom apartment at the Azure project in Syokimau.\n\nLastly, I reached out to Letty regarding her offer letter for the 10-acre land in Tigoni. She later shared the letter; however, it was not accepted by the landowner, as the terms did not align with the owner’s conditions.\n','2025-11-13','','2025-11-13 18:59:19','2025-11-13 18:59:19'),(129,24,'Took my client to view 0.66acres for lease at 700,000 per month for 30years along 4th Parklands. He liked and was ready to give an offer. However the landowner declined the offer since his son had already signed a lease with a Chinese client  yesterday evening. I got another property around the same area and scheduled to view it tomorrow at 9a.m.\n\nMade follow up calls to my previous clients.\nReceived 2 inquiries for a lease and purchase of 1acre along mpaka road.','2025-11-13','','2025-11-13 19:05:16','2025-11-13 19:05:16'),(130,11,'I chaired the team meeting, where Brian, Desmond and Dennis were in attendance. \nThe main agenda of the meeting was to discuss each team member’s plan for the day and review progress on our current targets for Luminara. So far, none of us have attained our set targets, but we are optimistic that by tomorrow and Saturday, some viewings will take place.\nI spent most of the day following up with all my Village market leads and updating my CRM list.\nOne of the clients I spoke to is Eric, a lead I met during the Village Market Expo. He has shown interest in Luminara, and I’m hoping to meet him tomorrow.','2025-11-13','','2025-11-13 20:06:15','2025-11-13 20:06:15'),(131,22,'1. Attended morning office meeting.\n2. Made follow up calls to clients and landlords.\n3went for viewing with a client t at kiranyaga Rd, Muthaiga North and Cianda','2025-11-13','','2025-11-13 20:23:16','2025-11-13 20:23:16'),(132,19,'Sent out all daily reports (except for one)\nSent out daily report to Joseph reason being; WhatsApp login on my laptop has crashed. \nGot done with his assigned task on time. \nGot done with an \"about us presentation\" will share final results with Joseph.\nRestocked the office with necessary supplies.\nScheduled another follow up with an agent,  \n','2025-11-14','None. ','2025-11-14 13:45:26','2025-11-14 13:45:26'),(133,27,'1. Early morning meeting and progress follow up.\n2. Leads\' follow up.\n3. Had a meeting with Kelvin and Lucy whom I met during our Village Market activation. They are interested in buying a home in Peponi, Redhill, or around Westlands, to lease a commercial space for a coffee and leather shop and wish to move from their current apartment to another one with a budget of Kshs150K per month.\n4. Visited Golden Mansion again and for the shooting follow up.\n5. Back in the office and on my leads\' follow up.','2025-11-14','My leads are responding and scheduling site visits','2025-11-14 13:51:19','2025-11-14 13:51:19'),(134,13,'1.I  received three projects from Dennis ,I uploaded 2 one is still pending as it has not been stamped yet.\n2.I attended a meeting with Mr Ken and the website developers at the office,we had discussions on the changes that need to be made in the website.\n3.I called my client Lilian, she was to have a viewing tomorrow but she has not confirmed so I am still waiting for her feedback.\n4.I did some editing on the previous projects as some prices had been adjusted by the developers,I updated them according to the current prices.\n5.I did other office duties as requested by Joseph.\n','2025-11-14','Hoping to get quality leads at the village market tomorrow.','2025-11-14 16:54:32','2025-11-14 16:54:32'),(135,22,'1.Attended the office morning meeting .\n2. Went for activation at village market\n3.Met a lawyer with a client and the land owner.','2025-11-14','If the client and the land owner agrees on the location where the two acres will be subdivided from the 10 acres. This will be a successful deal ','2025-11-14 17:28:18','2025-11-14 17:28:18'),(136,12,'\nToday, I accompanied my client, Andrew, for a viewing at the Azure Sky project in Syokimau. He expressed interest in a 1-bedroom apartment with a balcony and gave a verbal cash offer of KSh 4.8M for a unit priced at KSh 5M. He requested that I present this offer to the developer for consideration.\n\nAfter the viewing, Andrew took me to his property in Utawala, which he intends to sell. He confirmed that he is willing to sign an agreement with our company to allow us to market the house on his behalf.\n\nLater in the day, I followed up with Beatrice regarding her scheduled viewing of the KSh 35M Syokimau maisonette, which is set for tomorrow morning.\n\nI also checked in with Anthony concerning the Luminara project. He requested additional time to review the documents I shared with him on Wednesdays \n','2025-11-14','','2025-11-14 17:36:15','2025-11-14 17:36:15'),(137,23,'-Morning meeting\n-1 lead assigned by Rashid that  i followed up on.\n- 10 follow up calls to previous clients and leads\n-went to village market for the activation','2025-11-14','','2025-11-14 18:10:55','2025-11-14 18:10:55'),(138,17,'Attended the morning meeting at 8;30am\nLeft the office for a property shoot at Muthithi road then reported back to the office by 1;30pm.\nmassaged  some of the influencers as requested by my manager Mr. Joseph Wanguo, managed to get two responses yet to engage others tomorrow and finalize my research.','2025-11-14','','2025-11-14 19:28:02','2025-11-14 19:28:02'),(139,12,'\n\nWeekly Report\n\n1. New Agreements & Client Assignments\n\nSuccessfully secured one agency agreement for a house in Karen.\n\nReceived four new clients assigned by the social media team.\n\n\n2. Client Engagements & Site Visits\n\nConducted a successful site visit with a client at the Azure Sky Project in Syokimau.\n\nVisited General Mathenge to source a 5-bedroom penthouse at Sunstone Apartments for a client who plans to view it next week.\n\nFollowed up with 10 additional previous clients.\n\n\n3. Individual Client Updates\n\nMr. George – Interested in Luminara; shared detailed project information. He requested a follow-up on Monday.\n\nMr. Andrew – After viewing the Azure project, follow-ups continued over the weekend. The developer is open to negotiating his offer upon a meeting. The client plans a meet-up next week; I will follow up for an exact date.\n\nMr. Antony – Met at Village Market Expo; showed interest in Luminara and requested a follow-up on Monday after discussing with his spouse.\n\nMr. Jay – Interested in the 5-bedroom penthouse in General Mathenge; shared a virtual tour, and he is open to visiting next week. I will coordinate to confirm the date.\n\nMr. Dan – Previously inquired about a 2-bedroom investment unit in Westlands, but preferences changed after discussing with his spouse, who is now considering Mombasa as the preferred location.\n\nJoyce – A client referred by the social media team; still unresponsive to calls and messages regarding her Luminara inquiries.\n\nMitchell – Requested a visit to Luminara next week once she returns from Congo; an online presentation has already been conducted.\n\nBeatrice – Scheduled to view a 5-bedroom maisonette in Syokimau but went silent on the viewing day. A follow-up is pending to reschedule.\n\nLetty – Submitted an offer letter for the 10 acres in Tigoni; the offer was rejected, but she is reviewing and adjusting her terms to align with the landlord’s conditions. Follow-up is ongoing.\n\n\n4. Key Achievements\n\nSuccessfully followed up and progressed Letty’s offer letter for the Tigoni land.\n\nConducted a successful viewing with Andrew in Syokimau, and he is planning a meeting with the developer next week to negotiate his offer for the one-bedroom apartment.\n\n\n\n---\n\n','2025-11-16','','2025-11-16 18:13:32','2025-11-16 18:13:32'),(140,23,'WEEKLY SALES REPORT\n1. Targets & Performance\nWeekly Targets\n\n50 new leads\n\n25 follow-up leads\n\n2 agent meetings\n\n1 client meeting in the office\n\n2 site viewings with clients\n\nAchievements\n\n4 new leads assigned\n\n28 leads followed up on\n\n2 client viewings completed\n\nSite Visits Completed\n\n2 site visits with clients\n\nNew Property Leads Sourced\n\n\nNew Client Inquiries\n\n6 new inquiries received\n\nAll 6 are still active\n\n2 clients completed viewings over the weekend\n\nArea Coverage Plan\n\nN/A\n\n2. Lead Follow-Ups & Client Handling\nNew Leads Contacted or Followed Up\n\n4 new leads\n\nClient Follow-Ups & Status\n\nVivian – Personal client (BnB business); viewed Luminara on Saturday; traveling out of the country and will give feedback after returning.\n\nJemimah – Lead from Village Market; interested in land in Migaa; viewed a 6.5M property on Sunday; consulting stakeholders before making a decision.\n\nPending Follow-Ups for Next Week\n\n11 clients\n\nSilent Clients & Re-engagement Plan\n\n8 clients have gone cold\n\nPlan: Follow up next week with calls and messages\n\nClient Feedback From Viewings\n\nVivian – To provide feedback after travel\n\nJemimah – Stakeholder consultation ongoing\n\nNo additional feedback provided\n\nLive Locations/Updates During Viewings/Sourcing\n\nYes, \n\n3. Achievements\n\nCompleted 2 successful viewings:\n\nLuminara (Saturday)\n\nMigaa, Kiambu (Sunday)\n\nAdditional Client Feedback Worth Noting\n\nNone\n\n4. Challenges\nChallenges Faced\n\nClient responsiveness issues\n\nClients canceling viewings at the last minute\n\nSupport Needed from Management\n\nNone\n\nListings/Developments With Access or Information Difficulties\n\nNone\n\n5. Next Week Planning\nKey Focus Areas\n\nLuminara\n\nSpecific Clients/Properties to Push or Close\n\n(Not specified—can be added if needed)\n\nPlanned Fieldwork/Viewings Days\n\nFriday','2025-11-17','','2025-11-17 07:37:59','2025-11-17 07:37:59'),(141,27,'DK WEEKLY REPORT QUESTIONNAIRE FOR THE SALES TEAM\n1. Targets & Performance\nWhat were your specific targets for this week?\n1.To pursue three pending consents, two from Synina and one from Lilydale Riverside apartments.\n2.To source for ready apartments within Westland’s radius and about for my two serious leads.\n3.Plan and prepare for Kelvin and Lucy’s meeting to be held on this Thursday at the office.\n4.Source for a 1- or 2- bedroom fully furnished and serviced apartment for my own source lead.\n5.Source for listings for my fellow team members especially 1-, 2-, and 3-bedroom apartments.\n6.Follow up with all my previous Village market leads.\nHow many have you achieved so far?\nFive of the above:\n1.I got all the three consents mentioned and had them listed in our website.\n2.I got only one option for my lead who was looking for a ready apartment; Misty Springs.\n3.Kelvin and Lucy came to the office and we had a lengthy discussion on their properties of interest which is a 2Br for rent along Peponi road and Thigiri area for immediate moving in, two, they are in need of a commercial space to set up their leather items for sale, and lastly a 2- or 3- townhouse or villa for them to move in permanently which is in their long-time plans.\n4.Found several options of the 1- or 2- bedroom furnished apartments for long term rent in Kilimani, Riverside, and Kileleshwa.\n5.Only found one suitable listings for my team mates.\nHow many site visits did you complete (with clients)?\nTWO; \n1.One with Benter and we viewed Riverside One 3 bedroom apartment. She doesn’t prefer Chinese projects and prefers Indian’s and locals’ projects.\n2.One with Mr Bogale and we viewed Emaar residence and he liked the 3bedroom on the 13th floor and he is viewing it again this Wednesday.\nHow many new property leads did you source (with full details and consent letters)?\nTwo from Synina Properties for Synina Residency and Beacon by Synina apartments both in Kileleshwa, and Lilydale Riverside aprtments.\nHow many new client inquiries did you receive, and how many are still active/following up?\nI received 2 new leads and actively following on one who would like to buy and live in Luminara.\nDid you meet or exceed your area coverage plan (Kilimani, Kileleshwa, Lavington)?\nNO, this week I traversed Riverside to meet my lead’s enquiry.\n2. Lead Follow-Ups & Client Handling\nHow many new leads did you contact or follow up with this week?\n3 new leads\nPlease list the names or initials of the clients you followed up with and their current status (e.g., interested, viewing scheduled, not responding, closed).\n1.Dennis Mutuku for Luminara who is not responding.\n2.David Mukabi for Luminara and is responding and will come to our office tomorrow.\n3.James, who is my own lead, and is hunting for a 2Br fully furnished and serviced in Kilimani, Kileleshwa, and Lavington.\nWhich clients have pending follow-ups that need attention next week?\nFive; Dennis, Bashir, Jack, Andrew, and Evans.\nHave any clients gone silent, and what’s your next step to re-engage them?\nYes, 1 client have gone silent. I have already engaged them via WhatsApp and sms.\nHow many viewings were conducted, and what was the client feedback on the properties?\nTWO viewings. The Emaar residence requires some customization and changes to fit his need.\nDid you share live locations or updates during viewings and sourcing as required?\nYes, I shared the live locations for my viewings of Riverside One and Emaar residency.\n3. Achievements\nWhat was your biggest achievement or win this week?\nI was able to have two site visits with my hot leads who have been postponing the scheduled viewing.\nAny new listings or clients you’re proud of securing?\nYes, the potential and serious lead for Luminara apartment who will view it tomorrow.\nAny property owners you built a new relationship with or got consent from?\nYes, Mr Abdul from Synina properties.\nAny positive client feedback worth noting?\nWe take their enquiry seriously and we usually give them options that fits their need.\n4. Challenges\nWhat were your biggest challenges this week (e.g., client responsiveness, location access, consent letter issues, pricing)?\n1.This week my challenge was to source the right properties that fits my clients enquiries.\n2.My leads who keep on postponing our scheduled viewings.\nWhat support or resources do you need from the team or management to overcome these?\nTo conduct an analysis of our BEKE leads and base our sourcing on their needs.\nAny listings or developments that were difficult to get information or access to?\nYes, Riverside One apartments.\n5. Next Week Planning\nWhat are your key focus areas or priorities for next week?\nTo push for a sale for the two clients; Benter and Bogale who have already viewed the apartments of their choice.\nAny specific clients or properties you plan to push or close?\nYes, Mr Bogale and Madam Benter.\nWhich days are you planning for fieldwork or viewings?\nThursday, Friday, and Saturday.','2025-11-16','','2025-11-17 11:47:42','2025-11-17 11:47:42'),(142,19,'Sent out all daily reports (except for one)\nSent out daily report to Joseph reason being; WhatsApp login on my laptop has crashed. \nGot done with his assigned task on time. \nGot done with an \"about us presentation\" will share final results with Joseph.\nRestocked the office with necessary supplies.\nScheduled another follow up with an agent','2025-11-17','','2025-11-17 12:04:42','2025-11-17 12:04:42'),(143,27,'1. Early morning meeting where we strategized and planned for increasing the Luminara sales and how to meet our targets.\n2. Today, I spent time in the office following up on my Village market hot leads.\n3. Entering my new leads in the CRM.','2025-11-17','A closure is close by','2025-11-17 13:33:07','2025-11-17 13:33:07'),(144,17,'Attended the morning meeting at 8;30am,\nCreated a spreadsheet for leads , updated and shared on the group\nCame up with a script for tomorrows shoot at Luminara.\nContacted few more influencers both in Instagram and tik tok, but managed to get a response from one , she\'s yet to share her rate card.\nAdded one client I got from village market last saturday on my followup list ,  will continue following up tomorrow.','2025-11-17','','2025-11-17 16:12:49','2025-11-17 16:12:49'),(145,13,'1. I uploaded 1 project for sale from Dennis ,I am still waiting for others to submit their projects for stamping so that I can upload them.\n2.I did a follow up with the clients I got at village market on Saturday, two responded and one showed more interest towards Luminara,I have shared photos and also the price list with her,she said I call her tomorrow for her feedback,I was trying to convince her to go for viewing at the site,I also updated her in the CRM for more follow ups.\n3.I was deleting poor quality photos and replacing with new ones that\'s I had traced from other websites and also adding more photos for those that I couldn\'t add initially.\n4.I got in touch withe the developer in regards to some changes that he needed to make and also the challenges that my colleague had faced while  using the CRM he promised to sort them soon.','2025-11-17','Trying to push my clients from village market so that I can get a sale soon.','2025-11-17 17:08:44','2025-11-17 17:08:44'),(146,23,'-3 leads assigned by Rashid that I followed up with\n-8 leads from village market that I followed up with\n-5 previous leads that I followed up with. 1 is available from 10 January amd another from 29th.\n','2025-11-17','','2025-11-17 17:45:42','2025-11-17 17:45:42'),(147,15,'1. Closely followed up with the lead generated in village market \nAnd updated the responsive 3 in the CRM \n2.Generated leads for the sales team and a total of 11 leads were assigned as per 5 pm .\n3. Oriented the new videograpia and editor to ensure that all the equipment we have are upto power with him .','2025-11-17','','2025-11-17 17:52:48','2025-11-17 17:52:48'),(148,24,'13Th November 2025:\nHad a viewing with a client for the 0.75acres at Westlands but the client didn’t like it due it terms.\nMade follow up calls to the clients interested on the Luminara and Cartier Villa project.\nHad a meeting with Danish an Agent regarding various prorperties he has and his support to market Luminara.\nHeld a meeting with Chairman regarding the various JV Properties I have where I managed to share a few and organize for site visits.\n14th November 2025:\nActivation at Village Market.\nGot 8leads for Luminara and 8leads for other properties and Zero for Cartier Villas.\n15th November 2025:\nHad a meeting with other team managers regarding the progress of the leads we got and challenges we are facing.\nWent to source at Muthaiga 5acres for Holistic Mission property for sale per 50Million per half acre.\n17th November 2025:\nDid a follow up of the leads I got from Village Market on Friday.\nWorked on sourcing of Houses for UN Staff a request I got over the weekend and planned for viewing on 18th November 2025 2.P.M.\nHeld a meeting with my team as we planned on the weekly targets and requests we need to work on.\nMade follow up calls and text messages to the Luminara leads, two of which promised to view on Wednesday.\n','2025-11-17','','2025-11-17 18:42:59','2025-11-17 18:42:59'),(149,22,'A. Attended the morning office meeting\nB. Made follow up calls with clients, land owners and agents.\nC. Went to Kiambu rd to show a client 0.5acre land suitable for petrol station and Later went with the same client to Lari viewpoint for 1acre suitable for the same. ','2025-11-17','','2025-11-17 18:55:08','2025-11-17 18:55:08'),(150,20,'I attended a meeting early today regards  to 0.24h where both advocates were present and negotiation are on going waiting for the next step tomorrow \nI made call follow up on my clients where most of them responded positively towards their interested land\nI went to mpaka road for a viewing where I shall meet the owner tomorrow ','2025-11-17','','2025-11-17 19:01:54','2025-11-17 19:01:54'),(151,12,'\n\nI followed up with several clients. Jay confirmed he is planning a site visit tomorrow to view the 5-bedroom penthouse at Sunstone as well as the 5-bedroom townhouse in Peponi.\n\nChristian confirmed his viewing appointment for Luminara on Saturday at 11:00 AM.\n\nMichelle, who is currently in DRC, mentioned that she will update me once she returns this week so we can proceed with viewing Luminara and other similar investment projects.\n\nI also contacted the three newly assigned leads. One of them responded positively; he is looking for a 3-bedroom unit with a DSQ on the 4th floor or below. I presented the Greenville project in General Mathenge, and he is open to a viewing this Saturday','2025-11-17','','2025-11-17 19:49:50','2025-11-17 19:49:50'),(152,19,'Got done with primary responsibilities then proceeded to get supplies for the office. \nSent out all daily reports (except for one).\nRestocked the office with necessary supplies.\nScheduled another follow up with an agent.\n\n','2025-11-18','none. ','2025-11-18 12:14:59','2025-11-18 12:14:59'),(153,13,'1.Today I was replacing photos in the website,the photos that didn\'t look good I tried to look for them and replace so as to improve photo quality on the website,I will be replacing one by one once I get better ones.\n2.I did a follow up with my client Irene from Yesterday,I texted her but she hasn\'t responded yet. I will be doing a third follow up tomorrow via call.\n3.I had a meeting with Mr Ken and Joseph in regards to the website progress,he shared some changes which I will be sharing with the developer.\n','2025-11-18','Am planning on how the website can have better photos as we progress.','2025-11-18 15:35:52','2025-11-18 15:35:52'),(154,24,'Had a meeting with the HK Developer in their office at Mirage where we made a few changes with the existing project to suit the landowners expected value of 30%.\nMade follow up calls to the Luminara clients to which two confirmed viewing tomorrow.\nMade follow ups to the other clients of land in Tigoni and Old Muthaiga.','2025-11-18','','2025-11-18 15:37:46','2025-11-18 15:37:46'),(155,17,'Attended the morning meeting at 8:30pm at the office.\nPrepared and left the office to go to Luminara  for two shoots, got back at the office at 4:20pm.\nCompiled and shared the leads template on the Beke group.','2025-11-18','','2025-11-18 17:16:43','2025-11-18 17:16:43'),(156,23,'-Morning meeting\n-followed up with previous leads.\n- 1 has confirmed viewing for Luminara tomorrow\n-worked to get details on Migaa architectural approvals for a client who saw land on Sunday as well as clarification on other outgoing costs\n-1 lead wanted an alternative for Cartier villas. Managed to get details on Sage villas going for 80M as an alternative.','2025-11-18','','2025-11-18 17:43:10','2025-11-18 17:43:10'),(157,15,'Accompanied mia and paddy for shooting at luminara where we did two video creative shoots .\nBack at the office and did the lead assigning and filtering agent from real leads and assigned them to the sales team . A total of 6 leads were assigned.','2025-11-18','','2025-11-18 17:51:30','2025-11-18 17:51:30'),(158,12,'\nToday, I accompanied Mr. Jay for viewings at Sunstone Apartments, where we toured the 4- and 5-bedroom penthouses. He appreciated the spacious layout but was not satisfied with the finishes.\n\nWe then proceeded to view the 4-bedroom townhouse at Sage on Peponi Road, which he really liked. The owner, who is relocating to London, is reselling the unit and is open to a short-term payment plan. Mr. Jay mentioned he would discuss the option with his family and share his feedback thereafter.\n\nLater in the day, I followed up with my client searching for a commercial space to purchase in Westlands. I successfully identified a suitable option, which she has already shared with her husband. I am expecting a callback from him starting tomorrow.','2025-11-18','','2025-11-18 18:57:30','2025-11-18 18:57:30'),(159,22,'1. Attended the morning office meeting\n2. Made follow up calls in the office till midday.\n3. Met two potential clients in their offices about Luminara project.\n4. Went sourcing at Mirema drive 0.5 acre suitable for apartments ','2025-11-18','','2025-11-18 19:19:44','2025-11-18 19:19:44'),(160,10,'Good evening. Hope you all had a lovely day. As for my team, let me start with Rashid. As of today, Rashid, Mia, and Paddy went to Luminara to take videos and do more shoots to promote Luminara and create more content. Paddy was learning more ways to work, getting acquainted with what the media team does. At the same time, Rashid shared four leads with several sales team members, namely Carol, Dominic, Joy, and Brian. He\'ll also be looking into more sharing of leads as they come in. At the same time, he\'s assisting Paddy in getting more acquainted with the work he\'s supposed to be doing. \n\nAs for Mia, she also participated in the video shoots today. She also compiled data regarding Luminara leads and sent them to me and Mr. Ken. She is still compiling information about other influencers and their charges.\n\nAs for Diana, she is working on the website and getting acquainted with Google Ads. We are now discussing which team members will manage which platforms: Rashid will manage Meta Ads, Mia will manage TikTok, and Diana will manage Google Ads. Paddy also has to get acquainted with what we do, so that is a work in progress. \n\nAs for myself, I was working on getting more acquainted with TikTok Ads. I learned where to upload and what to do next to find more information regarding getting more leads. At the same time, I also managed to discuss Luminara, the marketing, and the potential clients with other teams. We are hopeful that, from tomorrow onward, we will bring in more information, data, and clients to invite them to see the project. I also had meetings with Mr. Ken and the team managers, where we discussed better ways to encourage the team to be more productive. Tomorrow morning, I have a meeting with Mr. Huang on Limuru Road. He\'s an agent who has clients who want to buy our Cartier villas. We\'ll meet them at their office at 11.00am. After that, I\'ll meet with my team members, the sales team, the project property manager, and the land manager to discuss more ways to invite more clients to Luminara.\n','2025-11-18','Hope to improve on where I\'m falling short. ','2025-11-18 20:42:56','2025-11-18 20:42:56'),(161,27,'1. Early morning BEKE meeting as a whole team.\n2. Follow up with my Village Market leads, and my hot leads too, especially my two Luminara leads who postponed their viewing to Saturday.\n3. Entering my leads into the CRM and sharing our project details to some of the leads.\n4. Follow up on my consents from some developers.','2025-11-18','Apologies for the late report writing as the site was down yesterday.','2025-11-19 07:49:37','2025-11-19 07:49:37'),(162,11,'1. Morning Activities\n\nAttended a 9:30 AM client meeting in Karen that went all the way to the afternoon.\n\nConducted multiple rental viewings in Karen for the client.\n\n2. Afternoon to Evening till around 4pm – Lavington Client & Viewings\nReceived another client seeking a townhouse for rent in Lavington. Conducted the following property tours:\n\nK Villas (Convent Drive) – Ksh 350,000\n\nZalig Villas (Lavington) – Ksh 450,000\n\nManyani Road townhouse – Ksh 550,000 (Client did not like this option)\n\n3. Evening Activities\n\nReturned to the office for the scheduled managers’ meeting.\n\n4. Summary\nA productive day focused on client meetings and townhouse viewings in both Karen and Lavington, ending with internal management discussions.','2025-11-18','','2025-11-19 08:07:42','2025-11-19 08:07:42'),(163,27,'1. Early morning departmental meeting with our sales team members where we shared our hot lead\'s enquiry and we were sourcing as a team.\n2. Continued with my leads follow up and sharing project details with them.\n3. Went to source at Broadwalk Mall Residential where they have furnished apartments from USD 1,500. My leads are yet to respond on their feedback.\n4. Back to the office with more leads follow up.','2025-11-19','All good for now.','2025-11-19 13:53:53','2025-11-19 13:53:53'),(164,24,'Held the morning meeting with my team where we shared various leads that we had and the team went sourcing and client visits.\nMade follow up calls to Luminara clients but the two who were viewing today postponed to tomorrow same time.\nGot two leads from social media but they turned out to be agents.\nGot two enquiries for half acre JV for GM and 80% Financing option for a project at Riverside.\nSourced for new properties of JV in General Mathenge.\n','2025-11-19','','2025-11-19 16:27:41','2025-11-19 16:27:41'),(165,23,'Morning meeting. \nFollowed up with 2 leads assigned by Rashid\nFollowed up with previous clients\nViewing at Luminara with a client\nMeeting at the office with agent','2025-11-19','','2025-11-19 16:32:22','2025-11-19 16:32:22'),(166,13,'1.I was replacing some bad quality photos for various projects with better ones.\n2. I did some research about google ads and also watched some useful tutorials on u tube as requested by Joseph.\n3. Joseph took me through some insights about google ads using the companies account,we did a practical and we will be doing a test before we can run an actual campaign since we needed to be very sure about some aspects.\n4. I did other minor office duties as they arised.\n5.I took the new staff through the CRM as he will be using it to write his reports.\n','2025-11-19','Our WiFi network needs an upgrade as now it is becoming Abit slow,also we have increased in number; meaning the people using it are many making it even more slower.','2025-11-19 17:11:20','2025-11-19 17:11:20'),(167,15,'Shooting of the staff portrait photos for the website \nRolled up 5 leads for the sales team \n','2025-11-19','','2025-11-19 18:03:44','2025-11-19 18:03:44'),(168,17,'Attended the morning marketing meeting at 8:30am\nPrepared two scripts for Fridays shoot\nCompiled and shared the daily leads excel sheet.\n','2025-11-19','','2025-11-19 18:09:37','2025-11-19 18:09:37'),(169,12,'\n\nToday’s Report\n\nI accompanied a client for rental property viewings. She initially sought a 2-bedroom unit in Westlands with a budget of KSh 130,000, but later adjusted her budget to KSh 180,000. We managed to view two options in Westlands and an additional two in Kileleshwa. She was particularly impressed with Marquis. She mentioned she is open to viewing one final option before making her decision, as she plans to move in by 1st December.\n\nI also followed up with Mr. Anthony, who is looking for a 1-bedroom unit for investment. Although he did not consider Luminara, he was quite impressed with Galaxy 1 along Raphta Road. He mentioned he will create time before Saturday for a viewing appointment.\n\nAdditionally, my client Jay provided feedback regarding the 4-bedroom townhouse he viewed in Peponi yesterday. He is interested in a similar concept but larger, with a budget of up to KSh 95 million','2025-11-19','','2025-11-19 18:53:32','2025-11-19 18:53:32'),(170,20,'I went a viewing with client on parklands 0.5acres where he liked the land and later we held a meeting with the client inclusive his lawyer and requested to meet the land owner \nLater I went to Ngong road where I had a client representative for a viewing where they are requesting for deedplan so they can do the search','2025-11-19','','2025-11-19 19:44:28','2025-11-19 19:44:28'),(171,22,'1.Attended the office morning meeting\n2.Did customer follow-up reports and also made follow up calls to clients, landlords and agents.\n3.Met a potential client for Luminara project.\n4.Went for a meeting with the owner of 0.5 acres land in Kiambu road suitable for a petrol station. The intention was to get the consent to sell for i am having a potential client.','2025-11-20','','2025-11-20 06:28:52','2025-11-20 06:28:52'),(172,24,'Took a Luminara client to site at Mogotio Road.\nMade follow up calls to to my previous clients and new leads i got yesterday.\nHeld a meeting with my agent where he shared more new properties and requests from different clients.\nHeld another meeting with an agent who is charge of a hotel request i got on sale by an Arab Client\nHeld another meeting with the agent and client for Luminara 1Bedroom.\nMade follow up calls to my previous clients.','2025-11-20','','2025-11-20 14:47:05','2025-11-20 14:47:05'),(173,11,'- Morning meeting with the team, Brian, Dennis and Desmond\n- Met with Henry\'s partner and went viewed Perry West which he liked and settled for.\n-Came back to the office and followed up with my team, i got reports on the feedback they got from the clients they have followed up with today. i also assisted in sharing options of listings they didn\'t have.\n','2025-11-20','','2025-11-20 15:01:03','2025-11-20 15:01:03'),(174,22,'A. Attended the morning office meeting\nB. Did follow up calls on clients, land owners and agents.\nC. Did my pending reports\nD. Took a client for viewing of 0.25acre at Ngara and later went for viewing with a developer interested in 1 acre at Kirigiti ','2025-11-20','','2025-11-20 16:07:16','2025-11-20 16:07:16'),(175,23,'Morning meeting\nCalls to 6 leads assigned by Caro\nFollow-up with previous leads \nLiaise with Migaa management on concerns by client who wants to buy\n1 lead has confirmed viewing for Tuesday. Rental client.\n','2025-11-20','','2025-11-20 16:33:47','2025-11-20 16:33:47'),(176,13,'1.Today I attended the meta class training together with the marketing team,the class was very insightful as it was also the final class ,we did a recap of the previous classes and also today\'s lesson which was quit engaging,we had a chance to do practicals on the lead froms and also scaling,we also had time to ask practical questions.\n2.I was able to upload 1 project for sale from Brian.\n3.I did other office duties as the arose.','2025-11-20','Everyday is a learning day.','2025-11-20 17:33:58','2025-11-20 17:33:58'),(177,27,'1. Early morning departmental meeting with our sales team where we shared our hot leads\' enquiries and the options, we have of serving them.\n2. Thereafter, leads\' follow up and they were responsive and sharing their needs.\n3. Sourcing in General Mathenge and Parklands.','2025-11-20','All is faring on well.','2025-11-20 17:59:40','2025-11-20 17:59:40'),(178,15,'Meta training training which took the better part of my day\n\n leads rolled to the sales team , and shared to one each .\nFor both ,Brian , Desmond, denis , domnic and caro, the excel sheet will be updated tomorrow morning as soon as I give them to mia ','2025-11-20','','2025-11-20 18:01:40','2025-11-20 18:01:40'),(179,12,'\n\nToday\'s Report\n\nI shared additional rental options with Bernice, and she confirmed her availability to view them tomorrow before making her final decision.\n\nI also contacted the three leads forwarded by the social media team:\n\nPamela is looking for a ready 1-bedroom unit or one nearing completion within the next 6 months. I sent her several available options, and she requested that we touch base again tomorrow. She also mentioned she has units for resale at Capital Heights and Alba Garden.\n\nSekani is searching for a 2-bedroom apartment to buy for her own residence, with a budget of 6–8M. She is open to units under construction and prefers locations on the outskirts of Nairobi CBD, such as Kitisuru and Mombasa Road.\n\nInden is looking for a ready 2-bedroom unit. He noted that he has already viewed several properties, so I will need to cross-check my available options with him.\n\n\nAdditionally, Mr. Anthony confirmed his availability for next week Tuesday to visit the Azure Sky project in Syokimau for a meeting with the developer regarding his offer ','2025-11-20','Upon confirmation,I will take Bernice for a viewing to the available rental options\nI Will later proceed to village Market ','2025-11-20 18:25:02','2025-11-20 18:25:02'),(180,20,'I went to parklands for viewing with client where he will have to visit to the office of the advocate tomorrow for documents viewing \nI went to upper Hill to a law farm office for a follow up on for a sourcing letter for a property that a client requested along Ngong road where I got it in order to present to a land owner to produce the required documents for further engagement ','2025-11-20','','2025-11-20 19:16:35','2025-11-20 19:16:35'),(181,28,'I edited team photos that I had taken with Rashid on Wednesday. After which I embarked on creating caroussel designs for Luminara, 4 slides of those. I later did a short opening montage for Luminara.','2025-11-20','','2025-11-21 03:21:36','2025-11-21 03:21:36'),(182,27,'1. Early morning BEKE staff meeting led by Joseph.\n2. Emmanuel from Stanbic Bank oriented to us and pitched their mortgage products, and as well shared our proposal for a win-win partnership.\n3. Leads follow up especially for Golden Mansion, Luminara, and Cartier Villas for scheduled viewing.\n4. Sourcing at SAGE Real Estate for their projects and met Ruth who pitched and shared their project details.\n5. Back to the office for project sharing with my leads and preparing my sales materials for my hot leads.','2025-11-21','All good for now.','2025-11-21 13:55:16','2025-11-21 13:55:16'),(183,29,'Had a morning training from the Stanbic staff. We then headed for the ground breaking ceremony at Luminara, shot some videos. ','2025-11-21','','2025-11-21 13:59:04','2025-11-21 13:59:04'),(185,13,'1. I went to village market with Desmond,I had 8 clients and 4 were interested in Luminara,I shared with them my card and also invited them to the office next week,I hope they keep their word and come as agreed,the rest I will still follow up.\n2.I attended the short session at the office with the visitor from Stanbic bank.\n3.I engaged with the developer in regards with his progress and also he shared an excel where they tick a task once they have completed it so that we can also confirm.','2025-11-21','','2025-11-21 17:21:31','2025-11-21 17:21:31'),(186,15,'Attended the short briefing by the Stanbic bank representative \n\nProceeded to luminara and had the shoot for the ground breaking they were having.\n\nRolleds 9 leads for the luminara project and devided them equally to the sales team .\n\nLater , had a zoom meeting with the marketing consultant (Joseph )and set another ad for meta which runs across Facebook and Instagram this is purposed to help get more lead and client for luminara.','2025-11-21','','2025-11-21 17:23:45','2025-11-21 17:23:45'),(187,23,'Morning meeting\nStanbic meeting\nVillage market activation','2025-11-21','','2025-11-21 17:41:10','2025-11-21 17:41:10'),(188,12,'\nRephrased Report:\nEarlier today, I followed up with Mr. Christian. He confirmed that he will come to the office tomorrow morning to discuss the ready 2-bedroom apartment he is looking to purchase. We will review the available options and then proceed for viewings.\n\nLater, I took Bernice for rental viewings, where we looked at four different options. During the process, she also expressed interest in purchasing a 3-bedroom unit, so I took her to view Blossom Ivy. She will share her feedback on both the rental and purchase options by Monday.','2025-11-21','','2025-11-21 18:49:06','2025-11-21 18:49:06'),(189,22,'-Attended morning office meeting\n-Did follow up calls with clients, land owners and agents. Got a client coming in on Thursday 27th November for Luminara project.\n- Met a client at Ngara at midday and we later proceeded for viewing in Kiambu rd and View point ','2025-11-22','','2025-11-22 07:39:44','2025-11-22 07:39:44'),(190,29,'Delivered the groundbreaking video.  Afterwards I designed three Luminara  E-Card designs for our socials','2025-11-22','','2025-11-23 01:39:00','2025-11-23 01:39:00'),(191,27,'WEEKLY REPORT QUESTIONNAIRE FOR THE SALES TEAM\n1. Targets & Performance\n•	What were your specific targets for this week?\n1.	Sourcing for rentals in Westlands, Kilimani, Kileleshwa, and Riverside for mine and my team’s lead.\n2.	Follow up on my Golden Mansion and Luminara leads on their scheduled viewings for this weekend.\n3.	One of my Village Market leads is looking for a 2-bedroom or a 3-bedroom for investment around Runda, Nyari, Peponi road, and Gigiri. Sourcing for his need\n4.	Finding out more about Broadwalk Mall residency rates and for our partnership.\n5.	Following up on all my given TikTok leads and sharing the apartments and Villas they were looking for.\n•	How many have you achieved so far?\nFour of the above:\n1.	Followed up on all my Golden Mansion and Luminara leads and they postponed the viewing to this coming weekend.\n2.	Sourced for several rentals and shared with my leads.\n3.	Broadwalk Mall rates are on the higher side and they have furnished and serviced apartments only\n4.	All my tiktok leads are now well oriented in their respective project details and are considering scheduling a site visit.\n•	How many site visits did you complete (with clients)?\nNONE\n•	How many new property leads did you source (with full details and consent letters)?\nNONE\n•	How many new client inquiries did you receive, and how many are still active/following up?\nI received 17 new client enquiries, and I am only actively following 5 leads who are responding to the project that I have pitched to them.\n•	Did you meet or exceed your area coverage plan (Kilimani, Kileleshwa, Lavington)?\nNo. This week I covered Westlands, and Parklands.\n2. Lead Follow-Ups & Client Handling\n•	How many old leads did you contact or follow up with this week?\n2 old leads.\n•	Please list the names or initials of the clients you followed up with and their current status (e.g., interested, viewing scheduled, not responding, closed).\n•	\n1.	Mr Shay, whom I met in Village Market last week and is interested in a 2- or 3-bedroom apartment for investment.\n2.	Mr Bogale, who has already viewed Emaar Residency and was ready to pay for the 3-bedroom he picked only for him to inform me they have decided to invest elsewhere.\n•	Which clients have pending follow-ups that need attention next week?\n3 clients have pending follow up for next week\n1.	Lucy and Kelvin for their rental in Peponi rd or Nyari.\n2.	Gladwell Wanjiru for her interest in 1050 2-bedroom unit.\n3.	Benter who is looking for a 3-bedroom for investment.\n•	Have any clients gone silent, and what’s your next step to re-engage them?\n7 leads have gone silent, and my next step is to engage them via WhatsApp and texts until they respond.\n•	How many viewings were conducted, and what was the client feedback on the properties?\nNONE\n•	Did you share live locations or updates during viewings and sourcing as required?\nYes.\n3. Achievements\n•	What was your biggest achievement or win this week?\n1.	Followed up with my cold lead, Shay, who now is interested in an investment apartment.\n2.	Lucy and Kelvin are interested in the apartment for rent that I had shared with them. They would like to view it on Monday\n•	Any new listings or clients you’re proud of securing?\nYes. Shay whose interest is buying an apartment for investment.\n•	Any property owners you built a new relationship with or got consent from?\nYes, Lilydale apartments.\n•	Any positive client feedback worth noting?\nYes. We have a pool of properties they can choose from.\n4. Challenges\n•	What were your biggest challenges this week (e.g., client responsiveness, location access, consent letter issues, pricing)?\n1.	Getting rentals in Parklands, Kileleshwa, and Westlands.\n2.	Scheduling viewings with leads and then they end up postponing.\n•	What support or resources do you need from the team or management to overcome these?\nCurrently none. To be determined.\n•	Any listings or developments that were difficult to get information or access to?\nYes, Elegant properties and the consents from their developments.\n5. Next Week Planning\n•	What are your key focus areas or priorities for next week?\n1.	To get the consents for the Elegant Properties developments\n2.	Follow up with all my previous cold leads and all my Village Market leads.\n3.	Schedule more viewings with my leads.\n4.	Closing either a sale or a rental.\n•	Any specific clients or properties you plan to push or close?\nYes:\n1.	Gladwell – The 2 bedrooms in 1050.\n2.	Capt Atandi – Syokimau Villa.\n3.	Benter Okonji – Wants a 3br apartment for living in or for investment.\n4.	Shay – wants an apartment for investment.\n\n•	Which days are you planning for fieldwork or viewings?\nTuesdays, Thursdays, and Saturdays.','2025-11-22','Hi. Here is my weekly report.','2025-11-23 15:17:42','2025-11-23 15:17:42'),(192,23,'\nWEEKLY REPORT QUESTIONNAIRE FOR THE SALES TEAM\n1. Targets & Performance\n•	What were your specific targets for this week? \n-50 new leads, \n- 25Follow up leads. \n-2 site viewings with clients.\n•	How many have you achieved so far?\n-12 new leads assigned.\n-9 leads followed up on\n-2 viewings\n\n•	How many site visits did you complete (with clients)?\n-2. \n1 in Luminara the other rental in Shangrila.\n\n\n•	How many new client inquiries did you receive, and how many are still active/following \nup?\n-2 clients that are new leads worth follow up on. \nKepha  is a rental client that wants a 2 bedroom for rent in westlands.  With a budget of 100k. Has scheduled a viewing on Tuesday to view options that I shared. \nHilda, a personal client who wants something for investment but wants something ready so as to finance the off plan projects that she has already committed to. She is to view Grand premier in Lavington. Once she confirms with Sacco about financing on Monday.\n2. Lead Follow-Ups & Client Handling\n•	How many new leads did you contact or follow up with this week?\n-12 new leeads\n- 9 follow up\n•	Please list the names or initials of the clients you followed up with and their current status (e.g., interested, viewing scheduled, not responding, closed).\n- Kepha  is a rental client that wants a 2 bedroom for rent in westlands.  With a budget of 100k. Has scheduled a viewing on Tuesday to view options that I shared. \n-Hilda, a personal client who wants something for investment but wants something ready so as to finance the off plan projects that she has already committed to. She is to view Grand premier in Lavington. Once she confirms with Sacco about financing on Monday.\n-Jemimah, Lead from Village market. Interested in Land in Migaa. Got a piece of land going for 6.5M. Confirmed that the week was very busy for her so to follow up next week.\n-Mina. Village Market lead. Foreigner in Kenya who wants to invest in Kenya Real estate. is interested in Luminara.\nMoses. Interested in Luminara but wants a virtual presentation on Luminara. To be scheduled between 7.30 and 9.30 AM. Village market lead.\n\n•	Which clients have pending follow-ups that need attention next week?\n-9 clients\n\n•	How many viewings were conducted, and what was the client feedback on the properties?\n-	2 viewings conducted.\n-Lynn. Her mother and Aunty want to invest in Kenya but are currently in The US, to view once they fly in in December.\n-Khali. Rental client interested in 2 bedrooms. Viewed Shangrila. To confirm with the husband on way forward.\n\n\n3. Achievements\n•	What was your biggest achievement or win this week?\n-2 viewings 1 for Luminara and one for rental in westlands..\nve client feedback worth noting?\n-No\n4. Challenges\n•	What were your biggest challenges this week (e.g., client responsiveness, location access, consent letter issues, pricing)?\n-	 \n-	\n•	What support or resources do you need from the team or management to overcome these?\n-None\n•	Any listings or developments that were difficult to get information or access to?\nNo\n5. Next Week Planning\n•	What are your key focus areas or priorities for next week? \n-2 potential viewings in Luminara.\n-1 meeting with a client in AAD\n-\n•	Any specific clients or properties you plan to push or close?\n-Mina\n-Moses\n-Mbabu\n-Jemimah\n','2025-11-23','','2025-11-23 16:14:36','2025-11-23 16:14:36'),(193,12,'\n\nWeekly Report\n\nThis week, I achieved the following targets:\n\nMade 18 calls, including both new prospects and previously engaged clients.\n\nConducted 3 successful viewing appointments.\n\nCompleted 15 follow-ups through calls and WhatsApp.\n\n\nSite Visits & Client Engagements\n\nBernice:\nI took Bernice to view several rental options. She was initially looking for a 3-bedroom unit with a budget of KES 130–160k. She later indicated that she is also open to purchasing a 2-bedroom unit, and I managed to show her suitable options as well.\n\nJay:\nI accompanied Jay to view a 4-bedroom townhouse on Peponi Road. He felt the house was smaller than expected and mentioned he is willing to adjust his budget up to KES 95 million for a bigger option. I shared the Oak and Ivy project with him and will follow up next Monday.\n\nMr. Chris and his friend:\nI took them to view multiple 2-bedroom units for investment purposes. They were particularly impressed with Pinecrest in Kilimani. They are yet to provide final feedback, and this will be a key follow-up item next week.\n\n\nFollow-Ups Conducted\n\nGeorge:\nHe previously showed interest in Luminara but later clarified he is looking for a 2-bedroom unit with mortgage payment options and nearing completion.\n\nMr. Anthony:\nOut of the projects shared, he preferred Galaxy 1 and is open to a viewing next week.\n\nMr. Andrew:\nHe viewed a 1-bedroom apartment in Syokimau and is open to a revisit on Tuesday or Wednesday next week.\n\n\nNew Leads Contacted\n\nNaseem:\nLooking for a 3-bedroom unit with DSQ. I will record and share a video tour of Greenville on General Mathenge as requested.\n\nSekina:\nSearching for a 2-bedroom residential unit. I shared options along Mombasa Road and will follow up with her on Monday.\n\nPamela:\nLooking for a 1-bedroom unit for investment. She also mentioned having resale units at Capital Heights, Kilimani and Alba Garden, Kilimani.\n\nMr. Prahlad:\nOpen to off-plan projects in Westlands for residential use. I will follow up with him on Monday.\n\n\nNext Steps\n\nContinue following up with pending clients and those who viewed properties last week to work towards closing.\n\nReconfirm viewing appointments scheduled for next week.','2025-11-23','','2025-11-23 19:51:27','2025-11-23 19:51:27'),(194,13,'1. Today i attended a session with Mr Paul from Stanbic bank, he shared some of the programs that they have which could bring us clients.\n2. I worked with the developer since there were some changes he needed to make in the CRM for customer follow ups,he has completed and i have confirmed that it is ok. There were also some small changes that e has done and they are ok.\n3. I added some content for blog on the home page .\n4.I was editing some locations for projects which were not correct.\n5. I was updating the prices for various projects as the developers had revised them.\n\n','2025-11-24','','2025-11-24 14:08:39','2025-11-24 14:08:39'),(195,27,'1. Today, I took my half day off from the Sunday\'s Village Market activation and reported back to work at 1pm.\n2. In the afternoon, I followed up with all the leads I was allocated during the weekend and shared their respective project details.\n3. Previous leads\' follow up too.','2025-11-24','All is good for now.','2025-11-24 14:42:43','2025-11-24 14:42:43'),(196,24,'21st November 2025:\nHeld a meeting with my Team where we discussed how to use the CRM for customer follow up Icon.\nWent sourcing for a 2.5acres processional way for a Chinese Developer.\nHeld a meeting with the agent for Luminara to assist in Marketing the project.\nMade follow up calls to the previous clients and two leads assigned for Luminara. \n22nd November 2025:\nActivation at Village Market.\nGot 5leads for Luminara and 8leads for other properties and Zero for Cartier Villas.\n24th November 2025:\nDid a follow up of the leads I got from Village Market on Saturday.\nWorked on the CRM to follow up reports of my team.\nHeld a meeting with my team member as we planned on the weekly targets and requests we need to work on.\nWent for a meeting at Tilisi, Tigoni with the Developer and the Lamdowner of 5acres.\nHeld a meeting with an agent who wants to assist in marketing Luminara Project.\nMade follow up calls and text messages to the Luminara leads, one of which promised to view on Wednesday Afternoon.\nHeld a meeting with Chairman where we were able to share two properties in Karen 24acres and Kileleshwa 8acres. We planned for an introduction meeting on Wednesday 12noon.','2025-11-24','','2025-11-24 15:19:51','2025-11-24 15:19:51'),(197,17,'Attended the morning meeting at 8:30am\nLeft the office to shoot the  Cartier villa long video, we managed to cover five sites in total, village market, two rivers mall, Durham international school,  sabis  international school, Rossly mall, evergreen garden we could not shoot because you have to pay to get access.','2025-11-24','','2025-11-24 16:19:05','2025-11-24 16:19:05'),(198,23,'Morning meeting\nStanbic meeting\nFollow up with 8 leads from village market. \nFollow-up to confirm this weeks viewing. 1 confirmed for tomorrow Westlands.\nFollow-up with 8 previous leads from last week.\n1 new lead assigned by Rashid.','2025-11-24','','2025-11-24 17:42:47','2025-11-24 17:42:47'),(199,12,'\nToday’s Report\n\nToday, I was assigned three new leads. I contacted all of them as follows:\n\nMr. Frank was responsive and requested an online presentation for Luminara.\n\nI followed up with Pamela, who is looking to buy a 1-bedroom unit. She mentioned that she will confirm a day this week for us to view the options I previously shared with her.\n\nI also followed up with Mr. Naseem, who is searching for a 3-bedroom unit with a DSQ. I conducted a virtual presentation of Greenville Garden and Sunstone, both in General Mathenge. He did not prefer Sunstone but is currently considering Greenville Garden.\n\n\nAdditionally, I called Mr. Andrew for a follow-up. He confirmed his availability on Thursday to visit the Azure project office to negotiate his offer for the 1-bedroom apartment.','2025-11-24','','2025-11-24 17:59:14','2025-11-24 17:59:14'),(200,15,'Today I accompanied paddy and mia for the Cartier be villas commercial since we had prepared the scenes together just to put paddy up to speed and make sure we deliver befores month ends so we took footages at:\nSabis school\nDurham school \nPorterhouse school \nRosslyn mall \nVillage market \nTwo rivers mall \nFor purposes of making the content.\n\nThe meta ads money ran out to I requested Mr chui to add the account and keep the ads which were paused running which was also payed at 3 pm .','2025-11-24','','2025-11-24 18:51:03','