harmonize the NDA for commission and progress of the project. The meeting is set on 2nd of December 2025 at the office of the Land Owner in Westlands.\n','2025-11-26','','2025-11-26 16:29:55','2025-11-26 16:29:55'),(219,22,'-Attended the morning office meeting.\n-I was expecting a Luminara client to visit the office today at 11Am but he came and preffered I do the presentation for both him and his wife so went to the wife\'s work place in ASL industrial area. It was successful but they\'re hesitant they\'d want to wait for completion in 2028.\nThey later took me to Alina ridge in kileleshwa where they\'ve bought a two bed  and they wanted help in finding a tenant.\n-Around 3pm went to Eden ville for viewing with a client for rent, he liked the place and he promised to get back over the weekend. ','2025-11-26','','2025-11-26 17:13:41','2025-11-26 17:13:41'),(220,11,'1.	Chaired the morning meeting with Brian, Desmond, and Dennis in attendance.\n	2.	Followed up with my clients and shared the property options they had requested.\n	3.	Conducted a site visit at Escada Apartments with a client.','2025-11-26','1.	I’m happy with the team’s progress so far.\n	2.	We’ve all been actively attending viewings, and we’re optimistic about closing .','2025-11-26 18:09:25','2025-11-26 18:09:25'),(221,11,'1.	Chaired the morning meeting, with Brian, Desmond, and Dennis in attendance.\n	2.	Followed up with my clients.\n	3.	Updated my CRM.\n	4.	Accompanied Desmond for his client viewing at Luminara.','2025-11-25','None at the moment.','2025-11-26 18:33:17','2025-11-26 18:33:17'),(222,12,'\nToday I followed up with my previous clients.\n\nI spoke with Mr. Andrew, and we have scheduled a site revisit tomorrow afternoon in Syokimau.\n\nI later took Mr. Frank for a viewing at the Golden Mansion project. He liked the development and plans to revisit tomorrow for further detailed confirmations.\n\nI also followed up with Mr. Naseem; he is yet to confirm the viewing of the 3-bedroom unit with DSQ at Greenville Garden.\n\nAdditionally, I followed up with Mr. George, who will be visiting the 2-bedroom resale in kilimani ','2025-11-26','','2025-11-26 19:58:37','2025-11-26 19:58:37'),(223,23,'Morning meeting\nCalls to leads assigned by rashid in the evening. 2 of them\nFollow-up call T previous leads\nMeeting in the office with agent who has someone interested in Cartier villa\nPresentation at Luminara with agent who has a client','2025-11-26','','2025-11-26 20:16:26','2025-11-26 20:16:26'),(224,29,'Edited the Cartier villa video, to be presented tomorrow.','2025-11-26','','2025-11-27 00:03:58','2025-11-27 00:03:58'),(225,27,'1. Early morning meeting with all the staff members chaired by Mr Ken where we discussed what is expected from us.\n2. Spent the whole day following up with leads and was able to share project details with them.\n3. Reached out to developers for sourcing of their properties.','2025-11-27','All is good for now.','2025-11-27 13:53:00','2025-11-27 13:53:00'),(226,13,'1.I attended a meeting with Joseph in the afternoon since we were sharing on how to improve the quality of our videos so that we can get quality leads, we came up with some strategies which we will be working on.\n2.I n the morning I was working on the short descriptions  as per the new website requires both short and long description of projects.\n3.The developer made some changes on the map ,I am now able to pin locations manually as requested.\n4. I updated the task tracker on excel as we still have some tasks the developer hasn\'t completed, he can now work on them as well.','2025-11-27','I am trying to make progress everyday.','2025-11-27 14:03:43','2025-11-27 14:03:43'),(227,24,'Worked on the CRM to check on my teams reports which showed a great improvement in terms of sharing details for each client.\nOrganized for a site visit with the client to Two Rivers at 9a,m for purchase of 5acres.\nOrganized for viewing at Redhill, Tilisi for a client at 11a.m.\nSourcing along Eastern Bypass 10acres and 40acres along Kangundo Road.\nSent and received negotiation emails regarding the Arch.Walia Westlands 0.25acres JV Property.\n','2025-11-27','','2025-11-27 14:38:16','2025-11-27 14:38:16'),(228,15,'Recup of yesterday\'s where I hoped into meta ads settings after being paid the fees for marketing by Mr chui and set up two ad creative purpose for ensuring that more advers run across social media .\n\nManage assign 7 leads to the sale team including two for tiktok .','2025-11-27','','2025-11-27 16:41:52','2025-11-27 16:41:52'),(229,20,'I attended morning meeting with a client Ali who was interested On a 0.25 acres along muthithi where he viewed the property and requested we have the meeting tomorrow around 2 on presence of the owner \nLater I went a viewing with the client Mike along ABC where we  had a request of the land owner to be present in order to verify the document due to its a distress land and promised to be present \n','2025-11-27','','2025-11-27 17:51:32','2025-11-27 17:51:32'),(230,23,'Morning meeting\nFollow up with leads assigned by Rashid\nPrepared PowerPoint presentation for clients\nCrm update\nClient follow up ','2025-11-27','','2025-11-27 17:58:27','2025-11-27 17:58:27'),(231,22,'Attended the office morning meeting.\n- Did follow up calls with clients, land owners and agents\n-went for land viewing at muthithi rd\n- Later went to Murang\'a -  Makuyu ridge iwith Mr Julius for viewing ','2025-11-27','','2025-11-27 18:12:07','2025-11-27 18:12:07'),(232,12,'\nToday, I followed up with Albi, and he confirmed that he will be available for the Luminara project presentation next week on Tuesday.\n\nI also followed up with Mr. Andrew regarding his planned visit to the Azure project in Syokimau. He rescheduled the visit to Sunday when his wife will be available.\n\nAdditionally, I contacted Mr. Raphael, a lead assigned from the social media team. He is looking for a 2-bedroom apartment in Westlands. I shared several available options with him, and he mentioned he would review them and get back to me.\n\nI also reached out to Mercy, a lead generated from Village Market who had inquired about Luminara. She stated that she will share the information with her husband and revert.','2025-11-27','','2025-11-27 19:11:45','2025-11-27 19:11:45'),(233,29,'Finished up on the Cartier villas video and submitted.','2025-11-27','','2025-11-27 19:16:49','2025-11-27 19:16:49'),(234,11,'Attended the morning joint BEKE meeting.\nFollowed up with my clients \nI went to meet a client at Purple Haze \nI attended the launch of Luminara at the JW Marriot','2025-11-27','','2025-11-28 10:00:34','2025-11-28 10:00:34'),(235,13,'1. Today I was editing the locations of projects and also pinning the correct location on the map as required.\n2. I worked on the short description of the sale projects since they were not displaying as required.\n3. I did a follow up with the developer since changes needed to made from yesterday, he has worked on most of them.\n4.In the evening Mr. Ken shared with me some few changes that needed to e made on the website and I communicated with the developer, he also assigned Nana and I a new task that we will be working on together immediately.','2025-11-28','Am trying my best to adjust to the new changes that keep on arising.','2025-11-28 13:54:34','2025-11-28 13:54:34'),(236,27,'1. Early morning sales team BEKE meeting where we strategized on closing on our hot leads.\n2. Spent the morning in the office following up on my leads.\n3. Waiting on my Luminara lead to confirm our scheduled meeting in Westlands at Noon.\n4. In the afternoon following up on my leads and confirming scheduled viewings.','2025-11-28','All is well.','2025-11-28 13:57:11','2025-11-28 13:57:11'),(237,22,'-Attended the morning office meeting\n-Made some follow up calls with clients and landlords.\n- spent the rest of the day in Village market for a activation, I was  able to get four leads that I will be following up from next week. ','2025-11-28','','2025-11-28 16:06:03','2025-11-28 16:06:03'),(238,15,'Accompanied mia and paddy in ensuring that more content are produced before we can set campaign for more leads by Monday , so paddy is tasked with ensuring that before Monday I have 3 videos to run campaign with on Monday \n\nOn the other hand I managed to assign 8 leads as per 8.30pm today six of which has been recorded by mia .\n','2025-11-28','','2025-11-28 17:37:27','2025-11-28 17:37:27'),(239,17,'\n\n- Attended morning meeting at 8:30 am\n- headed to Kitisuru for the first  shoot at 10:30 am\n- Went to the second location at 2:30 pm in Westland\'s.\n- Headed to the office at 4:30 pm\n- Updated and shared the leads Excel sheet on the Beke business group.','2025-11-28','','2025-11-28 18:09:42','2025-11-28 18:09:42'),(240,19,'Got done with primary responsibilities then proceeded to get supplies for the office. \nSent out all daily reports (except for one).\nRestocked the office with necessary supplies.\nScheduled another follow up with an agent.','2025-11-28','None ','2025-11-28 18:25:00','2025-11-28 18:25:00'),(241,12,'\nToday, I accompanied Mr. Frank for a site review at the Golden Mansion project. He had anticipated that ground-breaking would have commenced, but the works have not started yet.\n\nI later took him to Luminara for a presentation. However, he was in a bit of a hurry, so he requested that I share the remaining details with him on WhatsApp.\n\nI also followed up with Mr. Bingh, who is looking for a ready 2-bedroom unit in Westlands. He requested that I give him a follow-up call on Tuesday next week.\n','2025-11-28','','2025-11-28 19:01:15','2025-11-28 19:01:15'),(242,11,'I chaired the sales team morning meeting.\nWent to Village Market activation, where we all managed to get a total of 9 clients.\nI still managed to follow up with some of my clients','2025-11-28','','2025-11-29 06:32:49','2025-11-29 06:32:49'),(243,27,'WEEKLY REPORT QUESTIONNAIRE FOR THE SALES TEAM\n1. Targets & Performance\n•	What were your specific targets for this week?\n1.	Sourcing for rentals in Kileleshwa, Kilimani, Westlands, and Lavington for my hot leads looking for a furnished and unfurnished 1- and 2-bedroom apartments.\n2.	Following up again on the TikTok leads I was given by BEKE and Joseph who for some are hot leads looking around for a unit to buy or rent.\n3.	Prepare the 2-bedroom option for rent, unfurnished to view with Lucy and Kelvin who would like to move around Westlands and the areas.\n4.	More sourcing for properties that fits my leads ‘enquiries and share with them the options.\n5.	Prepare to host some leads in our office to discuss their options and view the listings of their choice.\n•	How many have you achieved so far?\nThree of the above:\n1.	Sourced for very nice and modern furnished and unfurnished apartments for my leads, and as well shared with them the options.\n2.	Successfully engaged all the TikTok leads and they are yet to schedule their viewings of the options they have picked.\n3.	Managed to view the 2-bedroom option at Sunstone apartments with Lucy and Kelvin available on the 4th Floor. They would like to view more in 2 weeks’ time.\n•	How many site visits did you complete (with clients)?\nONE. Sunstone apartments.\n•	How many new property leads did you source (with full details and consent letters)?\nNONE\n•	How many new client inquiries did you receive, and how many are still active/following up?\nI received 7 new client enquiries, and I am only actively following 4 leads who are responding to the project that I have pitched to them.\n•	Did you meet or exceed your area coverage plan (Kilimani, Kileleshwa, Lavington)?\nYes. This week I covered Westlands, Kilimani, and Kileleshwa.\n2. Lead Follow-Ups & Client Handling\n•	How many old leads did you contact or follow up with this week?\n15 old leads.\n•	Please list the names or initials of the clients you followed up with and their current status (e.g., interested, viewing scheduled, not responding, closed).\nName	Current Status	Interest	Priority	Source\nSood	Not responding	Apartment	B	social\nElijah Wahome	Not responding	Apartment	B	social\nDavid Mukabi	Interested	Apartment	C	social\nDevi Shah	Interested	Apartment	C	social\nMbugua	Not responding	Apartment	C	social\nLotoom	Not responding	Apartment	C	social\nYakub	Viewing scheduled	Apartment	B	social\nIshwar	Viewing Scheduled	Apartment	B	social\nJoan	Interested	Apartment	B	social\nEmmanuel	Interested	Apartment	C	social\nVaite	Not responding	Apartment	C	social\nTricia	Viewing scheduled	Apartment	B	social\nAlisha	Interested	Apartment	B	social\nMoses	Interested	Apartment	C	social\nFriend	Interested	Apartment	C	social\n•	Which clients have pending follow-ups that need attention next week?\n3 clients have pending follow-up for next week. They are the ones who have scheduled viewings stated in the table above.\n•	Have any clients gone silent, and what’s your next step to re-engage them?\n5 leads have gone silent, and my next step is to engage them via WhatsApp and texts until they respond.\n•	How many viewings were conducted, and what was the client feedback on the properties?\nONE. The views of the apartment will infringe on their privacy, because it is facing the gate and the access road where all the traffic comes in and out of the apartment.\n•	Did you share live locations or updates during viewings and sourcing as required?\nYes.\n3. Achievements\n•	What was your biggest achievement or win this week?\n1.	My nonresponding leads are engaging back with their preferred property that fits them.\n2.	Lucy and Kelvin viewed the Sunstone apartment for rent that I had shared with them. They would like to see others in two weeks’ time.\n•	Any new listings or clients you’re proud of securing?\nYes. Two, who directly filled up our TikTok enquiry form on their enquiry and are considered very hot leads.\n•	Any property owners you built a new relationship with or got consent from?\nYes, AMANI residence, and TATU city.\n•	Any positive client feedback worth noting?\nYes. We have very great properties on our listings.\n4. Challenges\n•	What were your biggest challenges this week (e.g., client responsiveness, location access, consent letter issues, pricing)?\n1.	Getting rentals furnished and unfurnished Kilimani and Lavington.\n2.	Scheduling viewings with leads and then they end up postponing.\n3.	Clients who have viewed our listings and then try to engage the developer directly.\n•	What support or resources do you need from the team or management to overcome these?\nCurrently none. To be determined.\n•	Any listings or developments that were difficult to get information or access to?\nYes, Elegant properties and the consents from their developments.\n5. Next Week Planning\n•	What are your key focus areas or priorities for next week?\n1.	To get the consents for the Elegant Properties developments and TATU city.\n2.	Follow up with all my previous cold leads and all my Village Market leads.\n3.	Schedule more viewings with my leads.\n4.	Closing either a sale or a rental.\n•	Any specific clients or properties you plan to push or close?\nYes:\n1.	Yakub, especially on his interest in Luminara apartments.\n2.	Triciah would like to buy an apartment for investment before the year ends.\n3.	Alishia who is looking around for a 2 bedroom to buy and live in.\n4.	Yakub is interested in a 1 bedroom for investment in Westlands.\n•	Which days are you planning for fieldwork or viewings?\nTuesdays, Thursdays, and Saturdays.','2025-11-30','','2025-11-30 06:51:51','2025-11-30 06:51:51'),(244,12,'\n\nWeekly Report\n\nThis week, my targets were as follows:\n\nFollow up with previous week’s clients\n\nCall 20 new leads\n\nConduct 5 site visits with clients\n\n\nI managed to call 15 new leads, including those assigned from social media.\nI also conducted the following site visits:\n\nAlbi – Luminara\n\nMr. Frank – Luminara\n\nMr. Sam – Pinecrest and Capital Garden in Kilimani\n\n\nFrom the assigned leads, the following clients were responsive, and I was able to establish their specific interests:\n\nMr. Frank:\nHe inquired about Luminara and also showed interest in the Golden Mansion project along Muthithi Road. I conducted a site visit with him. He expressed concern about Golden Mansion since construction has not yet started. I will continue following up with him on the available options.\n\nMr. Bhangra:\nHe is looking for a ready 2-bedroom unit in Westlands. I shared several options, and he requested that I follow up with him on Tuesday.\n\nYodit:\nShe inquired about ready 2-bedroom units in Westlands. After sharing the available options, she went silent. I will follow up with her next week.\n\nMr. Raphael:\nHe inquired about Luminara but later noted that the project is located in Parklands rather than Westlands. He requested ready or near-completion 2-bedroom units for residential use. I shared options, but he has since gone silent. I will continue following up.\n\nMr. Timothy (from the US):\nHe inquired about Capital Garden. I shared the full details, but he has not responded. I will follow up with him next week.\n\n\nKey Achievement of the Week:\nMy client, Christian, made a decision to purchase the larger one-bedroom unit at Luminara. An offer letter was drafted for him, and he intends to proceed with payment after completing his due diligence. He emphasized the importance of securing the unit before the current discount Expires ','2025-11-30','','2025-11-30 19:54:31','2025-11-30 19:54:31'),(245,23,'-Morning meeting\n-went to Luminara on some updates that a client wanted. the client had viewed last week. Mina.\n-Lead follow up. For those assigned by Rashid and Joseph. 2 by Joseph on Sunday and 3 by Rashid.\n-follow up with previous clients.','2025-12-01','','2025-12-01 14:03:28','2025-12-01 14:03:28'),(246,27,'1. Early morning BEKE meeting where we discussed our leads, and targets for the month of December 2025.\n2. In the office following up leads and sharing their respective project details.\n3. Working on and update BEKE\'s CRM.','2025-12-01','All is well.','2025-12-01 14:11:38','2025-12-01 14:11:38'),(247,24,'Held a meeting with my team members and I followed up on the clients submitted to the CRM.\nMade follow up calls and text messages to the leads and I got over the weekend and site visit made on Saturday.\nMade follow up calls to the existing clients.\nWorked on the CRM to follow up reports of my team.\nMade follow up calls and texts to my previous clients and updated in the CRM.\nOrganized for viewing of two properties tomorrow in Donyo Sabuk and 6th Parklands 10a.m and 2P.M respectively.\n','2025-12-01','','2025-12-01 15:11:25','2025-12-01 15:11:25'),(248,17,'\n\n1. Meeting Attendance: Attended the morning meeting to discuss ongoing projects and priorities.\n2. Content Creation: Developed a script for a new month video, which was successfully produced in-house.\n3. Location Shoot: Conducted a shoot at Runda from 12pm to 3:30pm.\n4. Lead Management: Updated and shared leads generated from TikTok and Meta on the Beke group.','2025-12-01','','2025-12-01 17:19:52','2025-12-01 17:19:52'),(249,15,'Assigned 17 leads as per 8.30pm  , 13 of which mia has recorded in the daily excel sheet for meta leads ,\nDid a monthly general team engagement post for market.\nAccompanied mia and paddy to shoot Caro\'s land in runda ','2025-12-01','','2025-12-01 17:35:32','2025-12-01 17:35:32'),(250,22,'Attended the office morning meeting.\n-Made follow up calls from nine leads I had gotten from village market, Rashid and Joseph. Only one client was interested with Luminara and he requested as soon as he breaks for holidays he will come. We scheduled our next conversation on 16th December 2025.\n- I went for viewing at kileleshwa Gold park homes 2bed for sale 13. 5m and Kiambu rd 1acre land for sale respectively. ','2025-12-01','','2025-12-01 18:53:24','2025-12-01 18:53:24'),(251,13,'1.Today I edited some projects on the website I continued from last week\'s work ,I was coming up with better descriptions and adding more important details.\n2. Joseph gave me 1 lead from TikTok and I called and also updated on the CRM I am yet to do more follow ups as the client responds.\n3.I was working with the developers as they needed to make some changes on the developers page, hopefully tomorrow we will have better feedbacks so that I can upload some content,they had not published some functions yet , though I was able to do tests of creating accounts for a developer as they register and it was successful.','2025-12-01','1. I will be doing major follow ups with the developer in regards to their progress overnight as they have promised.\n2.Working in the developers content once everything is sorted out.','2025-12-01 18:56:09','2025-12-01 18:56:09'),(252,12,'\n---\n\nToday I followed up on the leads assigned from TikTok and Meta by Rashid. Out of these leads, five were responsive.\n\nMr. Islen is looking for a 2-bedroom unit to buy in Westlands, preferably on the higher floors.\n\nMr. Timothy, who is based in the USA, inquired about Capital Garden and requested a callback at a suitable time.\n\nMayende from TikTok asked for a callback tomorrow morning when she will be available.\n\nDavid Too, also from TikTok, inquired about the Luminara project and mentioned he is creating time for a viewing appointment.\n\n\nI also visited the Luminara project to verify a few changes requested by my client who intends to proceed with the offered luxury one-bedroom unit.\n\nAdditionally, I followed up with Mr. George, who requested to view the 2-bedroom resale unit at Capital Rise last week. The owner confirmed that the unit will be vacant for viewing on Wednesday. I am yet to reconfirm the schedule with the client','2025-12-01','Follow ups with pending yesterday\'s client \n\nSharing more options with Albi who declined Luminara project \nCalling Mr Bhangra who had requested for a call back on Tuesday ','2025-12-01 19:04:08','2025-12-01 19:04:08'),(253,11,'1. Attended the morning BEKE team meeting.\n2. Went for a viewing with a personal client at 10:30 AM. Peter is looking for a 6–7 bedroom townhouse to buy, and we viewed two options—one in Lang’ata and another in South C.\n3. Visited a property for sale in Karen, a listing shared by an agent friend.\n4. Returned to the office and made two follow-ups.\n5. Met Josie at her Ngong Road property in Santack Estate, which she’s selling. I was able to take photos for marketing.\n6. Returned to the office by 4:30 PM.\n','2025-12-01','','2025-12-01 20:47:41','2025-12-01 20:47:41'),(254,23,'9 leads assigned last week by Rashid\n\n2 leads assigned by Joseph \n\n10 follow up calls to previous clients\n\n2 site visits conducted \n\nMarijan from village market viewed Luminara and meeting regarding Cartier villas in the office\n\nMicheal, meta lead. Interested in 2 bedroom for investment. Viewed capital garden and amber bay on Saturday \n\n2 clients have confirmed vieweing for this week. \n\nPlan for the week\n\nPushing for an offer letter from Jemimah by end of the week.\nFollow up u with Mina after sharing other options','2025-12-02','','2025-12-02 04:37:23','2025-12-02 04:37:23'),(255,19,'Got done with primary responsibilities then proceeded to get supplies for the office. \nSent out all daily reports (except for one).\nRestocked the office with necessary supplies.\nScheduled another follow up with an agent.\nIn the process of wrapping up an assignment\nSend out all the daily reports\n','2025-12-02','','2025-12-02 12:37:03','2025-12-02 12:37:03'),(256,24,'Made follow up calls with my previous clients. Was not able to record in the CRM since the customers updated in the system are not accessible.\nUpdated new clients from Tik Tok in the system.\nMade follow up calls to the offer letters to be shared on 3rd December.\nRescheduled meetings for that were planned today to Thursday since the landowners were not available.','2025-12-02','','2025-12-02 13:20:22','2025-12-02 13:20:22'),(257,27,'1. Early morning BEKE office meeting for the sales department staff team strategizing on closures for this month.\n2. Leads follow up and pitching our listings to them.\n3. Went for sourcing around Westlands for my leads looking for an apartment in Westlands and visited four projects.\n4. I came back to the office for leads\' follow up.','2025-12-02','All is going on well.','2025-12-02 13:41:36','2025-12-02 13:41:36'),(258,13,'1. I was testing the new changes made in the website, I have started with the developers page as requested I was able to do two tests using Nanchong and also Luminara but the outcome wasn\'t that good, some adjustments still need to be made by tomorrow.\n2. I attended the presentation  from the golden mansion team with the my colleagues at the office.\n3.I  updated the changes that needs to bee made by the developer , I highlighted to them the changes that needed to be made.\n4. I followed up with the client from tiktok that Joseph gave me and updated the follow up details on the CRM,','2025-12-02','Some changes need to made for me to be able to do a good job  in the developers page, suppliers page and the contractor page as well.','2025-12-02 13:45:32','2025-12-02 13:45:32'),(259,22,'- Attended the morning office meeting.\n-Did follow up calls 2leads from Rashid had requested me to call them today, one said he is not interested with an off plan project and the other one told me to keep sending him options he will tell me when he is ready over the December holiday.\n- Later went for sourcing for twenty acres in Karirana going for 15m per acre. ','2025-12-02','','2025-12-02 16:29:49','2025-12-02 16:29:49'),(260,29,'I edited two videos that we shot on Friday at the Kitisuru Duplexes.','2025-12-02','','2025-12-02 16:41:18','2025-12-02 16:41:18'),(261,23,'Morning meeting\n1 lead assigned by Rashid\n10 follow up leads\n1 meeting with butterfly palace developer','2025-12-02','','2025-12-02 17:21:58','2025-12-02 17:21:58'),(262,15,'Today was majorly based on the analysis for the leads assigned in November this would now help us strategize interms of number of leads per day on both meta and TikTok\nAnd the summary was the best performing campaign is to be left running, the final report will be given by caro for the lead assigned to his team , so that we can launch a campaign which should give us both numbers and quality leads For December.\n\nI majorly adjusted the post which have already been approved to all our social media platform.\nAlso 6 leads from meta and 4 from TikTok was assigned ','2025-12-02','','2025-12-02 17:49:53','2025-12-02 17:49:53'),(263,17,'Attended the morning meeting at 8:30am\nPrepared two scripts for tomorrows shoots for Luminara and a Greenview villas in Kiambu.\nupdated and shared the leads spreadsheet.','2025-12-02','','2025-12-02 18:10:37','2025-12-02 18:10:37'),(264,20,'I manage to visit to a land in muthithi Westland  with a client where he requested the land owner for the process to proceed \nLater I had a client who I took to Kilimani for a viewing on the 1.6acres where he liked the land and requested for the deed plan  for a search and later procided to Lavington for a search of a JV as a client request','2025-12-02','','2025-12-02 18:56:54','2025-12-02 18:56:54'),(265,12,'\n\nToday, I managed to share alternative options from reputable developers with Albi, who had earlier declined Luminara after finding out that the developer has limited completed projects.\n\nI also followed up with Mr. George regarding the planned viewing of the 2-bedroom resale unit at Capital Rise. The landlord rescheduled the viewing to Saturday, and the client has confirmed availability for that day.\n\nAdditionally, I followed up with Mr. Andrew. He confirmed that he will be available on Saturday to view the available 3-bedroom options in Syokimau when his wife is also available.\n\nLater in the day, I took a client to view the 3-bedroom unit for letting at Grand Premier. She did not prefer the open-plan kitchen layout. I have since shared other suitable options with her and will be following up tomorrow for her feeback','2025-12-02','','2025-12-02 19:11:21','2025-12-02 19:11:21'),(266,11,'1. Lead the sales team meeting , in attendance was Brian, Desmond  and dennis\n2. i Followed up with most of my clients from Saturday last week to date. Some were responsive some were not. I had like 10 leads shared by Rashid that i called but they didn\'t pick up. i will be following up with them tomorrow.\n3. attended the Golden mansion presentation by the golden mansion team\n4. i was only able to update leads that were responsive to the CRM. after i have called my leads again tomorrow i will input them to the CRM','2025-12-02','','2025-12-02 20:56:40','2025-12-02 20:56:40'),(267,27,'1. Early morning sales team meeting and we discussed about actualizing our sales\n2. Mr Jonas from Luminara came to understand our challenges and also empower us with proper selling skills.\n3. Leads follow up in the following way:\n      a) I received 3 new leads from Rashid, where two leads; Eve and Sandeep are serious leads looking for apartment to buy, while Hassan is an Agent. Scheduled viewings is what I am waiting from them.\n      b) I followed up on my 11 old/previous hot leads who are mostly Luminara and also invited them to this Saturday\'s Clients\' Open day. Also, waiting for their confirmation.','2025-12-03','All is faring on well.','2025-12-03 13:47:28','2025-12-03 13:47:28'),(268,24,'Held a morning meeting with my team where we went through various clients submitted in the system for more than a month without traction and asked them to delete.\nHeld a meeting to discuss the progress of Dominic so far.\nTook a client to view two 0.9acres in Lavington. Promised to come with the business partner tomorrow at 10a.m for viewing and meeting with the landowner.\nTook another client to Jacaranda Lavington to view 5Bedroom villa at 150Million. The client liked it but he wanted a ready unit.\nHeld a meeting with the Danish who shared the new properties in the market.\nWorked on the CRM to update my follow up customers and meetings.\n','2025-12-03','','2025-12-03 14:26:33','2025-12-03 14:26:33'),(269,13,'1. I attended a meeting with Mr Jonas CEO from Luminara ,he had some details that he wanted to share with us.\n2. I uploaded 1 project in the website,for sale from Carol.\n3. I  was in touch with the developers, giving feedback from yesterday and also the changes that needed to be made,they are working towards them and we will see great improvement asap.\n4. I managed to get better photos as requested so that we can improve the photos on the landing pages of the different pages in the website,I shared with the developer he is to replace them.\n5. I was doing various testing functions in the website and the are ok I gave a feedback.\n\n','2025-12-03','I am pushing so that we can have great improvements in the website so that the clients can have very easy time navigating through the website, hoping to get there soon ,as we are improving everyday.','2025-12-03 15:24:53','2025-12-03 15:24:53'),(270,22,'Attended the office morning meeting.\n-Attended the Luminara CEO talk.\n-Updated CRM and follow up list to date.\n-Made follow up calls the leads from the marketing team.\n-went sourcing in Kiambu rd for 4bd villa in Eden ville ','2025-12-03','','2025-12-03 17:26:37','2025-12-03 17:26:37'),(271,15,'Assigned 6 leads from meta  , Joseph asked me to analyze the two ads which are currently running and so i majored on that , by doing this it would enable us to plan for which one to be stoped and which one to continue , which I also did and stoped one .\nFollowed up with my luminara client and so instead of Friday I the client is going to attend the clients day at luminara.','2025-12-03','','2025-12-03 18:01:28','2025-12-03 18:01:28'),(272,20,'I managed to make follow up on my clients where most of them responded positively and 2 of them we shall hold meeting with them tomorrow and 1 is waiting for the lawyer to draft the authority for the client to proceed on negotiations ','2025-12-03','','2025-12-03 18:22:20','2025-12-03 18:22:20'),(273,17,'Attended the morning meeting at 8:30am,\nLeft the office for property shoot at Kiambu road and Lavington,\nReturned to the office at 3pm,\nupdated and shared the leads spreadsheet on the Beke business group.','2025-12-03','','2025-12-03 18:48:04','2025-12-03 18:48:04'),(274,23,'Morning meeting\nLuminara session\n2 new leads assigned that I called\nFollow up calls from previous leads\nInvitation for client opening celebration for Luminara on Saturday. 2 are likely to come','2025-12-03','','2025-12-03 19:05:27','2025-12-03 19:05:27'),(275,29,'Went for a shoot at Greenview villas in Kiambu, unfortunately they\'re still in the completion process, so we\'ll revert at alter date. We then headed to the Fountain project in Lavington and did a video on the offplan project.','2025-12-03','','2025-12-03 19:07:08','2025-12-03 19:07:08'),(276,12,'\nToday, I made follow-up calls to the leads assigned from both TikTok and the media team.\n\nFrom TikTok, one of the leads was an agent representing a client looking for a ready 1-bedroom unit in Westlands with a budget of KES 8M.\n\nFrom the media team, out of the two leads assigned, one appeared serious. He is a lawyer and mentioned he would get back to me after his court session, but unfortunately, he didn’t. I will follow up with him tomorrow morning.\nThe second client did not respond to my call and will also be a follow-up case for tomorrow.\n\nI additionally followed up with Mr. Bhangra, who is scheduled to view Sunstone, Emaar, and Greenville tomorrow starting from 11 a.m','2025-12-03','','2025-12-03 19:31:12','2025-12-03 19:31:12'),(277,13,'1. Today I attended a morning meeting with My boss Mr. Ken and the website developer as they had come to give an overview of their progress: they were given a feedback and the changes that they were to work on so that the developer, contractor and suppliers page would look more appealing for our customers.\n2. I called the lead that Joseph gave me from TikTok and updated on the CRM , I invited the client to the Luminara event on Saturday. I  also called my client Terez and invited her to the Saturday event.\n3. I  was making a few changes on the website just to correct the errors that I could trace and then work on them one by one.\n4. I helped Joseph call his client as he was busy , I also sent an invitation to her, we also prepared some policies to be used on the website.\n','2025-12-04','I am doing more follow ups to invite clients to come to Luminara on Saturday.','2025-12-04 13:32:19','2025-12-04 13:32:19'),(278,27,'1. Early morning BEKE Sales team meeting with our manager on how to boost our sales.\n2. Today, I followed up on my 13 Luminara hot leads and invited them to the Clients Open Day this Saturday. Only one has confirmed and will tag along with two others making three the number of confirmed attendances as of today.\n3. Project, and apartment familiarization to share with my leads who are looking out for studios and one bedroom for investments. I have identified 3 projects that I will view and have them as our sourcing tomorrow.\n4. In the afternoon, I followed up with 9 of my old leads, and 2 of them would like to view Capital Gardens next week.','2025-12-04','','2025-12-04 13:37:08','2025-12-04 13:37:08'),(279,19,'Got done with primary responsibilities then proceeded to get supplies for the office. \nSent out all daily reports (except for one).\nRestocked the office with necessary supplies.\nScheduled another follow up with an agent.\nIn the process of wrapping up an assignment\nSend out all the daily reports','2025-12-04','','2025-12-04 14:21:34','2025-12-04 14:21:34'),(280,24,'Started with viewing of the property with a client along the Eastern Bypass 10acres at 9a.m. Client liked it but wanted only 4acres. The owner of the land is reluctant to subdivide the parcel to smaller portions. Shared a different property to the client and organized for viewing on 7th Dec 2p.m.\nWent for a second viewing at 10.40a,m with a Somali Developer 2 0.9acres opposite Lavington Equity.\nThe client liked both properties and we set a meeting on Saturday 10a.m with the landowner at the property.\nCame back to the office and worked on the CRM as I made follow up calls to the existing clients and new leads I got.\n','2025-12-04','','2025-12-04 15:21:40','2025-12-04 15:21:40'),(281,29,'I edited and submitted the Runda Mumwe video. I then edited a property video for the luckyinn residence. I did and submitted a luminara clip before close of business.','2025-12-04','','2025-12-04 17:02:34','2025-12-04 17:02:34'),(282,23,'Morning meeting\nCalled leads that were assigned\nFollow up calls to previous leads\nSending invites for Luminara Saturday clients event\n1 site visit rescheduled ','2025-12-04','','2025-12-04 17:31:04','2025-12-04 17:31:04'),(283,15,'Today was just implementation on the campaigns for leads generation \n1 .campaign for property carrying three ad creative for more volume and wide coverage to bring in more leads daily \n2. Land which was aimed at promoting lands properties that we have to also bring in more leads for the lands department.','2025-12-04','','2025-12-04 17:46:41','2025-12-04 17:46:41'),(284,17,'Attended the morning meeting at 8:30am\nCalled one lead I was given but unfortunately she\'s not in Nairobi\nprepared a script for tomorrows shoot at the office\nupdated and shared the leads spreadsheet.\n ','2025-12-04','','2025-12-04 18:37:06','2025-12-04 18:37:06'),(285,22,'Attended the office morning meeting.\n-Made follow up calls with leads from meta and TikTok.\nMet a client interested in 1acre in Thindigua but  declined due to the topography of the land.\n-Went sourcing an alternative parcel along Kiambu Road. ','2025-12-04','','2025-12-04 18:42:02','2025-12-04 18:42:02'),(286,12,'\nToday, I made follow-up calls for the assigned leads:\n\nMary: She mentioned she is looking to buy land in Meru. I am currently in touch with the land team to confirm if they have suitable options available for her.\n\nMr. Nicholas: He was unresponsive to calls. I will reach out to him again tomorrow to understand his exact requirements.\n\nMr. Bhangra: He had initially scheduled a site visit at Sunstone but has now rescheduled it to next week Tuesday.\n\nSam: I followed up with him regarding the Capital Garden viewing he attended over the weekend. He requested a follow-up on Sunday as he will have made a decision by then.\n\nMr. David Too: I contacted him to invite him to the Luminara Saturday event, but he informed me that he has travelled upcountry.','2025-12-04','','2025-12-04 19:05:57','2025-12-04 19:05:57'),(287,20,'I managed to hold a meeting in upper Hill with a client and the land owner for a land on Kilimani where they agreed on the terms of the land where they will have a viewing on Saturday  and next week follow by paper work and payments.\nLater went back to Westlands along gtc for a viewing  with client  fora JV and ready to book for a meeting with land owner next week \nI went in parkland for a viewing with a client for 1 acre where we viewed   and decided to give feedback on Monday ','2025-12-04','','2025-12-04 20:38:23','2025-12-04 20:38:23'),(288,11,'1. Morning Activities\nToday, I chaired the morning Sales Spec Team meeting from 8:30 a.m.–9:30 a.m. The meeting focused on:\n* Ongoing active clients close to conversion this month\n* Challenges faced by team members (e.g., lack of suitable listings, client objections, delays in decision-making)\n* Sharing available listings across the team to match client needs\n* Supporting team members where difficulties arise between them and their clients\n\nTeam members in attendance:\nBrian, Desmond, Dennis, and we were joined by Dominic and David from the Lands Department.\n2. Client Engagements & Follow-Ups\n Followed up with Lawrence, a Village Market lead who had not responded previously.\n Contacted several clients to invite them for the Luminara Clients’ Open Day on Saturday.\nBrenda confirmed attendance.\nRod also confirmed attendance.\nContinued engagement with older clients while sourcing options aligned with their preferences.\n\n3. Team Assistance & Support**\nAssisted Desmond in sourcing listings in **Mombasa** for one of his clients.\nHelped to resolve a challenge he had after his client opted out of Luminara.\n\n4. Management Meeting**\nAttended a meeting called by Mr. Ken regarding:\n* Progress of the sales team\n* Estimated closures before the 20th of this month\n* Current performance trends\n\nOutcome of the meeting:\n> I will be sharing weekly reports for the entire sales team, inclusive of individual weekly targets','2025-12-04','','2025-12-04 21:31:17','2025-12-04 21:31:17'),(289,13,'1. I followed up with the clients I invited to come to Luminara tomorrow.\n2. I uploaded 1 project for sale from Desmond.\n3. I was editing  for spelling errors from previous projects and also adding additional details where necessary.\n4. I did a follow up with the developer in terms of the progress and they will be giving me a feedback in the evening.\n','2025-12-05','','2025-12-05 13:49:08','2025-12-05 13:49:08'),(290,24,'Held my morning meeting with the team where we went through the targets set earlier on the week to which most haven\'t been met. \nWent for viewing with a client at Arwings Kodhek 1.6Acres and 1acre. The client liked the two properties and promised to meet the landowner on 10th Dec for further discussion.\nHeld another meeting with the client and land owner where the developer gave his proposal and the landowner requested for time to go through the document. Next meeting is on Monday 8th 1pm.\nMade follow up calls tomy clients and set up meetings for next week.\nWorked in te CRM.','2025-12-05','','2025-12-05 15:52:38','2025-12-05 15:52:38'),(291,27,'1. Early morning BEKE Sales Team meeting on our individual follow ups and sharing strategies on how tomorrow\'s Luminara Client Open Day will be a success. \n2. I followed up on two potential leads: Tricia and Lameck who are looking out for apartments to buy for a 2- and 3-bedroom respectively. They are scheduling a site visit tomorrow.\n3. Went for sourcing in the Projects listed below and got properties that fits my clients needs. Like a 4-bedroom all ensuite with a dsq, spacious 2-bedroom plus dsq, and off plan projects with studios and one bedroom apartments. ','2025-12-05','All is well for now','2025-12-05 17:05:06','2025-12-05 17:05:06'),(292,23,'Morning meeting\n1 lead assigned by Joseph\nFollow up calls to previous clients\nConfirmation for clients attendees\nSourcing for Kazuri.','2025-12-05','','2025-12-05 17:32:40','2025-12-05 17:32:40'),(293,15,'Assigned 8 leads to the sale team \nWent for rental property shoot in lavington grand premier apartments 1,2 and 3 bedroom duplex .\nFollowed up with my client and confirmed for the tomorrow client meeting day \n','2025-12-05','','2025-12-05 17:41:07','2025-12-05 17:41:07'),(294,17,'Attended the morning meeting at the office,\nLeft the office at 11am for the shoot in Lavington for the rentals,\nUpdated and shared the daily leads spreadsheet.\n','2025-12-05','','2025-12-05 17:46:54','2025-12-05 17:46:54'),(295,20,'I managed to  attend two meetings with the lawyer and the buyer representative for Ngara and arwings kodhek plot where they promised their clients are willing to have a meeting with the lawyer  next week\n Later  we had a client representative with joy for  1.6and 1acre where they viewed  and promised for the client to have a  viewing next week \nAt 1 I went for sourcing for 1 acre as a request from a client along Kilimani where I got 1 and later I had viewing for the same with the client representative ','2025-12-05','','2025-12-05 18:10:12','2025-12-05 18:10:12'),(296,12,'\n\nToday, I made a call to the assigned lead, Mr. Nicholas, who had shown interest in Luminara. I shared the project details with him via WhatsApp and will follow up with him tomorrow.\n\nI also followed up with Mr. Sam, who confirmed his viewing appointment for the 2-bedroom resale unit in Kilimani.\n\nMr. Andrew confirmed his viewing appointments for the Syokimau 1-bedroom unit as well as a residential 3-bedroom option.\n\nLater in the day, I secured a viewing appointment for Mr. Anthony for both Luminara and Galaxy 1 so that he can make a comparison','2025-12-05','','2025-12-05 20:40:19','2025-12-05 20:40:19'),(297,22,'Attended the office morning meeting.\n-Made follow up calls with leads I have received this week both from meta and TikTok.\n-Updated the CRM to date.\n-Took a Client /developer to 7.5 acres in Kahawa sukari next to AMREF University.\n-Later went to View 2acres in Twiga farm Toll station in Ruiru with the same developer. ','2025-12-06','','2025-12-06 04:08:02','2025-12-06 04:08:02'),(298,29,'Went for the 1,2,3 BR Duplex shoot in Grand Premier, Lavington','2025-12-05','','2025-12-06 15:40:21','2025-12-06 15:40:21'),(299,29,'Submiited the Fountain residence edited video. Went to the Luminara event for a few minutes and went back to start editing the Duplex videos for Grand Premier, needed to run an ad campaign.','2025-12-06','','2025-12-06 15:44:42','2025-12-06 15:44:42'),(300,19,'Got done with Primary office responsibilities first \nSent out the necessary reports \nMet up with a client \nGot done with an assignment i was given \n','2025-12-06','','2025-12-07 11:59:06','2025-12-07 11:59:06'),(301,19,'Sent out all daily reports (except for one)\nSent out daily report to Joseph reason being; WhatsApp login on my laptop has crashed. \nGot done with his assigned task on time. \nGot done with an \"about us presentation\" will share final results with Joseph.\nRestocked the office with necessary supplies.\nScheduled another follow up with an agent','2025-11-15','','2025-12-07 12:00:45','2025-12-07 12:00:45'),(302,19,'Sent out all daily reports (except for one)\nSent out daily report to Joseph reason being; WhatsApp login on my laptop has crashed. \nGot done with his assigned task on time. \nGot done with an assignment given to me by : Mr.Ken \nRestocked the office with necessary supplies.\nScheduled another follow up with an agent','2025-11-19','','2025-12-07 12:02:44','2025-12-07 12:02:44'),(303,19,'Sent out all daily reports (except for one)\nSent out daily report to Joseph reason being; WhatsApp login on my laptop has crashed. \nGot done with his assigned task on time. \nGot done with another assignment given to me by : Mr.Ken \nRestocked the office with necessary supplies.\n\nScheduled another follow up with an agent\n\n','2025-11-20','','2025-12-07 12:06:01','2025-12-07 12:06:01'),(304,19,'Sent out all daily reports (except for one)\nSent out daily report to Joseph reason being; WhatsApp login on my laptop has crashed. \nGot done with his assigned task on time. \nFollowed up with a referral client\nRestocked the office with necessary supplies.\n\nScheduled another follow up with an agent','2025-11-21','','2025-12-07 12:08:37','2025-12-07 12:08:37'),(305,19,'Sent out all daily reports (except for one)\nSent out daily report to Joseph reason being; WhatsApp login on my laptop has crashed. \nGot done with his assigned task on time. \nRestocked the office with necessary supplies.\n\nScheduled another follow up with an agent','2025-11-22','','2025-12-07 12:11:07','2025-12-07 12:11:07'),(306,19,'Sent out all daily reports (except for one)\nSent out daily report to Joseph reason being; WhatsApp login on my laptop has crashed. \nGot done with his assigned task on time. \nFollowed up with another referral client, feedback was positive.\nRestocked the office with necessary supplies.\n\nScheduled another follow up with an agent','2025-11-23','','2025-12-07 12:12:58','2025-12-07 12:12:58'),(307,19,'Sent out all daily reports (except for one)\nSent out daily report to Joseph reason being; WhatsApp login on my laptop has crashed. \nGot done with his assigned task on time. \nFollowed up with a project and made the necessary adjustments to the contract \nRestocked the office with necessary supplies.\n\nScheduled another follow up with an agent','2025-11-24','','2025-12-07 12:14:15','2025-12-07 12:14:15'),(308,19,'Sent out all daily reports (except for one)\nSent out daily report to Joseph reason being; WhatsApp login on my laptop has crashed. \nGot done with his assigned task on time. \nFollowed up with a referral client for Luminara, (did not manage to close the deal), he was interested in other projects\nRestocked the office with necessary supplies.\n\nScheduled another follow up with an agent','2025-12-04','','2025-12-07 12:16:41','2025-12-07 12:16:41'),(309,19,'Got done with primary responsibilities around the office first\nFollowed up with clients / assignment\'s , and agents\nGot done with an assignment given to me to complete \nGot done with his assigned task on time. \nFollowed up with a referral client\nRestocked the office with necessary supplies.\n\nScheduled another follow up with an agent','2025-12-05','','2025-12-07 12:19:15','2025-12-07 12:19:15'),(310,23,'Weekly Report\n1. Lead Allocation\nTotal Leads Received: 12\nFrom Rashid: 9 leads\nFrom Joseph: 3 leads\n2. Responsive / Active Clients\na. Meena\nRequirement: Studio or 1-bedroom unit\nBudget: 6–7M\nTimeline: Needs to occupy before end of next year\nAction Taken: Viewing scheduled for Monday at Minara Heights\nStatus: Actively responsive\nb. John Mark\nInterest: Eternity Duplexes, Kitisuru\nAction Taken: Viewing scheduled for Tuesday\nStatus: Actively responsive\n3. Follow-Ups & Pending Clients\na. Mbabu\nNote: Confirmed for Luminara event on Saturday but did not attend\nAction: Follow-up initiated; awaiting rescheduling or feedback\nStatus: Requires continued follow-up\nb. Amish\nRecent Activity: Viewed Marina Bay\nFeedback: Found the pricing too high\nNext Step: Viewing scheduled for Azure in Syokimau next week\nStatus: Ongoing engagement\nc. Michelle\nNote: Was out of town and unable to attend the Luminara event\nAction: Pending follow-up for new availability\nStatus: Pending response\nd. Kazuri\nActions Taken: Shared several options, including Luminara and additional alternatives\nAwaiting: Feedback on whether she will pursue Luminara or other viewed options\nExpected Update: Next week\nStatus: Awaiting final feedback\ne. Jemimah\nRecent Activity: Viewed Migaa\nFeedback: Concerned about affordability as the gradient increases construction cost\nAction Taken: Shared more affordable options provided by Dominic\nStatus: Awaiting decision or further discussion\n Went for sourcing for several projects including\nMarina Bay\nMinara heights\nDolce Vita\nHimalaya Horizon','2025-12-07','','2025-12-07 13:59:50','2025-12-07 13:59:50'),(311,12,'\nWeekly Report\n\nThis week, I successfully conducted two site visits with clients.\nI took Sam to view the 3-bedroom unit with DSQ for letting at Grand Premier. I have been following up with him, but he is yet to respond. I will give him another follow-up call on Monday next week.\n\nI also accompanied Mr. George to view the 2-bedroom resale unit at Capital Rise. He liked the unit and requested a second visit with his wife on Monday next week.\n\nClient Follow-Ups:\n\nMr. Bhangra – Initially scheduled to view the Sunstone project. He has rescheduled the visit to Tuesday next week.\n\nMr. Andrew – Due to his tight work schedule, he requested that we stay in touch and plan viewings for the 3-bedroom Syokimau options based on his availability.\n\nJudy – After sharing various 2-bedroom options in Westlands, she went silent on both calls and WhatsApp. I will follow up again on Tuesday next week.\n\n\nLead Assignments:\n\nI was assigned 12 leads, out of which 4 responded:\n\nMr. Zach – Inquired about the Eternity Duplex on behalf of his brother who is abroad. He confirmed he will be available next week for a viewing.\n\nMr. David – Interested in the Luminara project. He traveled upcountry and missed the Saturday event, but mentioned he will create time next week for a site visit and a detailed presentation.\n\nMargaret – Has a client looking for a ready 1-bedroom unit to buy in Westlands with a budget of KSh 8M. I advised her to confirm if the client can also consider an off-plan option nearing completion.\n\nSixter – Confirmed that he will make time to view the Luminara project on Wednesday next week.\n\n\nUpcoming Scheduled Appointments for Next Week:\n\nMr. George – Revisit to Capital Rise with his wife\n\nMr. Nicholas – Luminara viewing on Monday (awaiting confirmation)\n\nMr. Bhangra – Sunstone viewing on Tuesday\n\nMr. Antony – Galaxy viewing on Saturday\n\nSixter – Luminara viewing on Wednesday','2025-12-07','','2025-12-07 15:12:26','2025-12-07 15:12:26'),(312,19,'Got done with Primary office responsibilities first, this included the office maintenance  as well, restocked the necessary supplies first. \nSent out the necessary reports such as : Daily report and the Minutes report. \nFollowed up with a tik tok lead, the so called client was not a client rather a curious person. \nGot done with an assignment I was given by, Mr.Ken. \nFollowed up with personal leads, hopefully feedback is positive. \n\n','2025-12-08','','2025-12-08 13:43:07','2025-12-08 13:43:07'),(313,13,'1. I updated the developer progress task tracker and shared in the group, so that no task is forgotten, they are now up to date with all the major changes we need made.\n2.I corrected the map locations of land projects as some maps were not well updated, I am yet to finish though I have worked on a big number of them, some projects had blank maps  which made the website look un professional.\n3.I deleted some of the projects that had very bad photos and I couldn\'t trace them as they make the website look bad  .\n4. I made follow ups with the developer as he is to publish the changes he had worked on over the weekend, he will be sharing the progress link in the evening so that we can approve and then progress from there. ','2025-12-08','Everyday is a learning day :from the meetings with my colleagues and also from my own personal experiences in the company.','2025-12-08 13:48:10','2025-12-08 13:48:10'),(314,24,'Had a morning meeting with Landowner for 30acres Two Rivers and Markem Developer, Johnson for introduction and exchange of documents.\nWent for a photoshoot for Villas at Jacaranda in Lavington.\nWorked on social media clients and posted in the CRM.\nWorked on the CRM for my previous clients.','2025-12-08','','2025-12-08 14:34:48','2025-12-08 14:34:48'),(315,11,'1. Morning Activities\nParticipated in the morning BEKE team meeting chaired by Mr. Ken and Joseph.\n\n2. Property Owner Meeting – Lavington\nMet with the property owner in Lavington at 11:00 a.m. as scheduled. The listing is a 5-bedroom townhouse priced at KES 67 million.Shared the details with Rashid, and the media team is scheduled to shoot next week.\n\n3. Follow-Ups and Lead Management\nReturned to the office and conducted follow-ups on leads shared between Saturday and today.\n\n4. Status of Follow-Ups\n*Everlyn: Currently disposing of several properties before she proceeds with purchasing an apartment for her daughter. She has received offers and is awaiting client commitment.\n*Ivy Burale: Requested that property details be sent via WhatsApp, and the details have been shared.\n*Willson (Developer): Has a client looking for a 3-bedroom unit for rent. He requested a follow-up call on Monday at 9:30 a.m.\n* Natasha: has confirmed viewing for Wednesday.','2025-12-08','','2025-12-08 16:49:12','2025-12-08 16:49:12'),(316,12,'\nToday, I was assigned 9 leads. Out of the 8 I managed to contact, 3 were responsive:\n\nBhatma showed interest in the duplex in Kitisuru. I shared all the relevant details, and she mentioned she will review the information and give her feedback.\n\nVendanda also expressed interest in the duplex. She is currently going through the detailed information and will share her feedback regarding a potential viewing.\n\nMr. Martin showed interest in the 3-bedroom duplex at Grand Premier. He mentioned he will confirm his viewing appointment tomorrow.\n\n\nClient Visits:\n\nI took Mr George for a revisit of the 2-bedroom resale unit at Capital Rise. He really liked it and is planning to meet the owner to discuss the ROI as well as negotiate the price.\n\nMr George also viewed two additional options—Jade Residence and Pinecrest View—to compare with the 2-bedroom unit at Capital Rise.','2025-12-08','','2025-12-08 17:02:07','2025-12-08 17:02:07'),(317,15,'Assigned leads to the sales teams , a total of 28 leads was assigned to the sales team which each member receiving as per the regulations of the company .\n\nAccompanied paddy and mia to do content shoot for the marina bay 2 , this would see paddy having time to come up with as much creative and content as possible, ','2025-12-08','','2025-12-08 17:12:20','2025-12-08 17:12:20'),(318,27,'Today\'s Report\r\nWEEKLY REPORT QUESTIONNAIRE FOR THE SALES TEAM\r\n1. Targets & Performance\r\n• What were your specific targets for this week?\r\n1. To identify my Luminara hot leads and persist on a scheduled viewing with them for a closure.\r\n2. Source for my BEKE leads that I have been allocated by Rashid and Joseph on the property that fits them and which is not in our listings.\r\n3. Improve my viewings with the client to one per day to achieve our targets of 20 leads per month.\r\n4. Identify agents who can partner and sell properties on our behalf.\r\n5. Have to source for rentals which are faster to close than a sale both furnished and unfurnished properties.\r\n• How many have you achieved so far?\r\nTwo of the above:\r\n1. I managed to get three leads who confirmed viewing of Luminara this Saturday, 6th December 2025.\r\n2. Successfully sourced for properties for sell and for rent that fits some of my leads. The properties are Comfy Residences, Aria Capital, Express View Apartments, and Sakarya.\r\n• How many site visits did you complete (with clients)?\r\nTWO for Luminara apartments on Saturday.\r\n• How many new property leads did you source (with full details and consent letters)?\r\nFIVE. Comfy Residence, AMANI apartments, Express View Apartments, Maylan apartments, and Aria Capital of which I am getting the consents this week.\r\n• How many new client inquiries did you receive, and how many are still active/following up?\r\nI received 14 new client enquiries, and I am only actively following 7 leads who are responding to the project that I have pitched to them.\r\n• Did you meet or exceed your area coverage plan (Kilimani, Kileleshwa, Lavington)?\r\nYes. This week I covered Westlands, Kilimani, and Kileleshwa and sourced the above mentioned consents.\r\n2. Lead Follow-Ups & Client Handling\r\n• How many old leads did you contact or follow up with this week?\r\n5 old leads.\r\n• Please list the names or initials of the clients you followed up with and their current status (e.g., interested, viewing scheduled,\r\nnot responding, closed).\r\nName Current Status Interest Priority Source\r\nBenter is responding Apartment B social\r\nKen is responding Apartment B social\r\nBen Interested Apartment C social\r\nYakub interested Apartment B social\r\nTricia interested Apartment B social\r\n• Which clients have pending follow-ups that need attention next week?\r\n1 client has pending follow-up for next week. They are the ones who have started responding.\r\n• Have any clients gone silent, and what’s your next step to re-engage them?\r\n9 leads have gone silent, and my next step is to engage them via WhatsApp and texts until they respond.\r\n• How many viewings were conducted, and what was the client feedback on the properties?\r\nTWO. The Luminara apartments are beautiful, though it lacks the basic amenities like the full back up generator heating the bathroom shower, and having a mixer taps in the kitchen and bathroom. They would like to see more options.\r\n• Did you share live locations or updates during viewings and sourcing as required?\r\nYes.\r\n3. Achievements\r\n• What was your biggest achievement or win this week?\r\n1. My non responding leads are engaging back with their preferred property that fits them.\r\n2. My clients who are abroad at the moment are set to view their preferred properties of choice before the 20th December.\r\n• Any new listings or clients you’re proud of securing?\r\nYes. Four, who are all from our social media pages and after our first phone call did schedule viewings of the properties we discussed about.\r\n• Any property owners you built a new relationship with or got consent from?\r\nYes, Comfy residence, and Express View Apartments.\r\n• Any positive client feedback worth noting?\r\nYes. We have very great properties on our listings.\r\n4. Challenges\r\n• What were your biggest challenges this week (e.g., client responsiveness, location access, consent letter issues, pricing)?\r\n1. Getting rentals furnished and unfurnished Kilimani and Lavington.\r\n2. Scheduling viewings with leads and then they end up postponing.\r\n3. Clients who pay attention to details of the properties we have viewed.\r\n• What support or resources do you need from the team or management to overcome these?\r\nCurrently none. To be determined.\r\n• Any listings or developments that were difficult to get information or access to?\r\nYes, still Elegant properties and the consents from their developments.\r\n5. Next Week Planning\r\n• What are your key focus areas or priorities for next week?\r\n1. To get the consents for rentals in Westlands, Lavington, and Kileleshwa.\r\n2. Follow up with all my previous cold leads and all my Village Market leads.\r\n3. Schedule more viewings with my leads.\r\n4. Closing either a sale or a rental.\r\n• Any specific clients or properties you plan to push or close?\r\nYes:\r\n1. Simon and his friend Mr John, especially on their interest in Luminara apartments.\r\n2. Triciah would like to buy an apartment for investment before the year ends.\r\n3. Alishia who is looking around for a 2 bedroom to buy and live in.\r\n• Which days are you planning for fieldwork or viewings?\r\nTuesdays, Thursdays, and Saturdays.\r','2025-12-08','','2025-12-08 17:35:31','2025-12-08 17:35:31'),(319,23,'\nTotal leads received: 10\nHighly responsive leads: 6\nOverall engagement from today’s leads was strong, with the majority responding promptly and showing clear interest in available listings.\nClient Activities & Follow-ups\n1. Natasha – Rental at Grand Premier\nConducted an in-person viewing at Grand Premier.\nClient expressed concern regarding the small pool size.\nShe has not yet made a decision; awaiting her feedback.\nNext Step: Follow up for her final thoughts and propose suitable alternatives if needed.\n2. Aman – Eternity (3 Bedroom Penthouse)\nInterested in viewing the 3-bedroom penthouse at Eternity.\nViewing scheduled for tomorrow.\nNext Step: Prepare unit details and confirm appointment logistics.\n3. Foreign Student – 1 Bedroom Near Strathmore\nLooking for a 1-bedroom rental near Strathmore with move-in planned for January.\nCurrent listings are above their budget.\nNext Step: Continue scouting options within the required price range; update client once suitable units become available.\n4. Michael – Investment Unit at Luminara\nInterested in the 2-bedroom unit at Luminara for investment purposes.\nWill confirm viewing before end of next week.\nNext Step: Follow up mid-week to secure viewing date and prepare investment highlights.\n5. Regina – 3 Bedroom Rental (Budget 100k)\nSearching for a 3-bedroom rental with a budget of 100,000 KES.\nShared one available option with her.\nAwaiting her feedback on the listing.\nNext Step: Expand search for more units within budget while awaiting her response.\n6. Utsav – Eternity (Kirawa) + Additional Options\nInterested in viewing Eternity in Kirawa.\nRequested more options; shared Greenview and Kitusuru Terraces.\nOrganizing a viewing later this week.\nNext Step: Finalize viewing schedule and send detailed comparisons.','2025-12-08','','2025-12-08 17:35:41','2025-12-08 17:35:41'),(320,27,'1. Early morning BEKE Africa meeting and strategising on how to close the year strongly. \n2. Leads\' follow up and especially Simon\'s request of viewing other projects after view Luminara on Saturday.\n3. Viewing with Simon a total of 3 projects: Capella Residency in Westlands, Golden Mansion in Westlands, and Marina Bay Phase 2 in Westlands.\n4. Back to the office to work on my BEKE CRM. ','2025-12-08','I am pushing for a closure or rental before the 20th December','2025-12-08 17:44:54','2025-12-08 17:44:54'),(321,17,'\n\n- Attended morning meeting at the office at 8:30am\n- Left the office at 12pm to Marina Bay 2 property for a shoot\n- Headed to Lavington for Nova Villa shoot at 2:30pm\n- Left Lavington at 4:30pm\n- Updated and shared leads spreadsheet on the Beke business group.\n\n- Attended morning meeting at the office at 8:30am to discuss ongoing projects and daily tasks.\n- Left the office at 12pm to conduct a photo shoot at Marina Bay 2 property.\n- Proceeded to Lavington at 2:30pm for a photo shoot at Nova Villa.\n\nTasks Completed:\n\n- Conducted photo shoots at Marina Bay 2 property and Nova Villa.\n- Updated leads spreadsheet with latest information.\n- Shared updated leads spreadsheet on the Beke business group.\n\n*Timeline:*\n\n- 8:30am - 12pm: Attended morning meeting at the office\n- 12pm - 2:30pm: Conducted photo shoot at Marina Bay 2 property\n- 2:30pm - 4:30pm: Conducted photo shoot at Nova Villa\n- 4:30pm: Left Lavington\n- 5:00pm: Updated and shared leads spreadsheet on the Beke business group\n','2025-12-08','','2025-12-08 17:57:40','2025-12-08 17:57:40'),(322,20,'I had a site visit around mid morning with a client representative at Kilimani for the 1.6 acre along arwings kodhek where they viewed and promised to arrange the client date for viewing \nI managed to make a meeting with land owner where the client had requested for aplot he can purchase     \nI attended a meeting with lawyer who holds the client where he requested for some documents and will be delivered to on Wednesday in order to facilitate for the offer writing ','2025-12-08','','2025-12-08 21:28:41','2025-12-08 21:28:41'),(323,29,'We kickstarted the week with our weekly general meeting where we got to review our last week\'s targets and tasks. After the meeting I delved into creating scripts to be used in the Villa Novo in Lavington stand alone residence. at 12:30 we left for Marina Bay 2 to do a corresponding shoot as we awaited confirmation from  Villa Novo to proceed. We did two shoots, a talking a video and general property shoot of the showhouse. We got confirmation from Villa Novo to proceed at 2. We then shot two videos, a talking video and general house tour. We were done by close of buiness.','2025-12-08','','2025-12-09 01:39:47','2025-12-09 01:39:47'),(324,22,'-Attended the morning office meeting.\n- Made follow up calls with, leads, clients and landlords from the previous week.\n- Went for a land owner meetup who signed consent for one acre in Ikinu - Kiambu.\n-Later went sourcing and got 5acres behind Spur mall for 250m','2025-12-09','','2025-12-09 02:53:43','2025-12-09 02:53:43'),(325,24,'Held the morning meeting with my team where we discussed various ways of getting new properties including Law Firms, Pension Funds and Saccos. This we will provide new ways to get new leads.\nMade follow up calls to new leads provided by Media Team.\nWorked on the CRM to update new clients and follow up clients.\nMeeting with landowner for 0.25acres Westlands road to discuss the JV terms.\nViewing with a Chinese client for the 0.25acres Westlands Road.\nOrganized for meetings tomorrow at Westlands Road 0.25acres 10a.m ','2025-12-09','','2025-12-09 13:26:41','2025-12-09 13:26:41'),(326,19,'Got done with Primary office responsibilities first, this included the office maintenance  as well, restocked the necessary supplies first. \nSent out the necessary reports such as : Daily report and the Minutes report. \nFollowed up with a personal lead, feedback was minimal and not positive. I will be sure to scout for more potential clients and agents during the week.\nGot done compiling the development map list , will forward the result to  dept manager (Joesph)\nFollowed up with personal leads again, hopefully feedback is positive. \nManaged to maintain the office successfully , managed to get done with office duties/ reports as well. ','2025-12-09','none , tough day :(\n','2025-12-09 13:42:45','2025-12-09 13:42:45'),(327,13,'1. Today I was doing tests on the website , there  were changes that had been made yesterday and I had to confirm how they had been done by doing tests and I also gave a feedback.\n2. I was working with the developer via a call as I was giving him the feedback on the immediate changes that he needed to make. Some he has already made and he will be progressing overnight.\n3. In the evening we had a small meeting with Joseph we came up with ideas to share with the developer tomorrow as he will be coming for a meeting tomorrow and he needs to come after he has worked on some of those ideas.\n','2025-12-09','Hoping that the website changes come to an end soon so that I can add data.','2025-12-09 13:57:45','2025-12-09 13:57:45'),(328,11,'Last Week Team Summary Report\nBrian - Weekly Summary\nBrian conducted two main client viewings and progressed several new leads.\n•	Took Sam to view the 3-bedroom at Grand Premier; awaiting feedback after follow-up.\n•	Accompanied Mr. George for 2BR resale at Capital Rise; second viewing with spouse scheduled next week.\n•	Managed 12 leads assigned; four were actively responsive and scheduled for presentations/visits.\n•	Key active prospects include: Mr. Zach (Eternity Duplex), Mr. David (Luminara), Margaret (ready 1BR), and Sixter (Luminara).\n•	Several follow-ups and scheduled appointments already lined up for next week.\nDesmond - Weekly Summary\nDesmond handled 12 assigned leads, conducted follow-ups, and scheduled multiple viewings.\n•	Active engagements include: Meena (Minara Heights), John Mark (Eternity Duplex), and Amish (Azure next week).\n•	Jemimah’s decision pending after Migaa review; more options shared.\n•	Client Mbabu missed Luminara event; follow-up initiated.\n•	Undertook sourcing across Marina Bay, Minara Heights, Dolce Vita, and Himalaya Horizon.\nWeekly Focus: Move active clients to viewing and decision stage, especially Jemimah (push for offer) and Mina follow-up after Monday.\nDennis - Weekly Summary\nDennis focused on sourcing new inventory and reviving non-responsive leads.\n•	Confirmed three Luminara viewings for the weekend.\n•	Sourced new properties for sale and rentals-Comfy Residence, Aria Capital, Express View, AMANI, and Maylan.\n•	From 14 new enquiries, seven remain active and responsive.\n•	Built new relationships and progressed consents for listed options.\nWeekly Focus: Confirm and execute scheduled viewings, finalize consents and push at least one closure (sale or rental).\n\nCombined Weekly Plan\nTo be implemented by all three agents:\n1.	Push viewings and convert active prospects into firm decisions.\n2.	Execute confirmed site visits and collect detailed feedback same day.\n3.	Close decisions on revived leads and ongoing discussions (priority: Jemimah, George, Christian, Mina).\n4.	Finalize consents for newly-sourced properties to widen match options.\n5.	Re-engage silent clients and confirm rescheduled appointments for next week.\n','2025-12-09','Last week Summery Report','2025-12-09 13:58:51','2025-12-09 13:58:51'),(329,29,'After our morning marketing team meeting. I started editing the Villa Novo video. We then did an office shoot of the BEKE team talking about what we do. I submitted the Villa Novo video and started working on the office shoot video. I submitted the edited video by close of business.','2025-12-09','','2025-12-09 14:07:51','2025-12-09 14:07:51'),(330,11,'1. Morning Activities\nAttended the morning sales team meeting.\n\n2. Client Viewing – Chinese Client\nConducted property viewings with the Chinese client.\nViewed available options in Langata and three different units in Karen.\nThe client showed strong interest in the Bogani option.\nThey will revert on Thursday with their decision.\n\n3. Lead Follow-Up\nReturned to the office and followed up on three clients obtained today.\nOne lead from Rashid: The client has requested a follow-up call at 7:00 p.m.\nTwo leads from Joseph: One client is currently unresponsive; follow-up attempts continue.','2025-12-09','','2025-12-09 14:15:49','2025-12-09 14:15:49'),(331,17,'1. Marketing Meeting: Attended the morning marketing meeting to discuss ongoing projects and strategies.\n2. Video Production: Created a video showcasing Beke Real Estate Company\'s services and projects, which was edited and shared by Mr. Paddy Odit.\n3. Script Preparation: Prepared two scripts for tomorrow\'s shoot, focusing on [insert topics or projects].\n4. Lead Spreadsheet Update: Updated lead spreadsheet with latest information and shared it on the Beke','2025-12-09','','2025-12-09 16:58:15','2025-12-09 16:58:15'),(332,15,'I assigned 11 leads to the sales team for their further persual and they are responsible for the updates in their CRM for clients follow up \n\nTook park for the office shoot ,which majorly included the whole team for the purpose for makng it visible for the social media more about Beke .','2025-12-09','Will just be doing follow ups with the campaigns and creating one for the office shoot that was done today \n','2025-12-09 17:09:17','2025-12-09 17:09:17'),(333,27,'1. Early morning BEKE Sales Team meeting and we focused on the viewings we had yesterday.\n2. Went for sourcing and familiarisation of apartments in Westlands which are; Luminara, Luckinn Ivy, Citi Rise apartments sourcing for 1 and 2 bedrooms to buy.\n3. Followed up with the following leads:\n a. Faith Wanjiku - Eternity apartments\n b. Winney - Rentals\n c. Evans - Rentals\n d. Margaret - To buy.\n e. Grace - to buy.\n f. Martin - To buy. \n g. Omondi - Rentals. \nThe above will entered into the CRM tomorrow.\n4. Back to the office with projects familiarisation. ','2025-12-09','All is well.','2025-12-09 17:35:35','2025-12-09 17:35:35'),(334,23,'Daily Report\n1. Follow-up Calls to Clients\nAman\nHad been scheduled to view Eternity today but rescheduled.\nInquired about I&M Bank mortgage options; confirmed with the developer that I&M financing is acceptable.\nShared the various mortgage plans with him.\nJohn Mark\nConducted viewings at Eternity Heights and Minara Heights.\nEternity Heights: Not suitable for him due to the distance.\nHis sister is interested and would like to schedule her own viewing for Eternity.\nMinara Heights: He liked the project; follow-up is required\nFollowed up with Mina who was interested in Luminara. Asked whether she will still pursue Luminara and she confirmed that she is still interested but is currently out of France for work and will be back on Sunday. Still subject to follow up','2025-12-09','','2025-12-09 18:15:02','2025-12-09 18:15:02'),(335,12,'\nToday I was assigned 4 leads, and 2 of them turned responsive.\n\nNina is looking to purchase a 1-bedroom residential unit with a budget of Ksh 8M. She mentioned she is open to off-plan options and is available for a site visit next week.\n\nWinfred, an agent, has a client interested in the 2-bedroom duplex at Eternity Heights in Kitusuru. She is yet to confirm the viewing appointment scheduled for tomorrow at 2 PM.\n\nI also followed up with previously pending clients:\n\nMr. Sam Muga requested more time to review the information I had shared earlier.\n\nBhatma, whose son is looking for a 3-bedroom 