o provide,I resized them with the help of Paddy and then Uploaded them.\n2. I uploaded the data for 3 developers after getting their logos and creating a profile for them,the photos of their different projects , their History ,their location and also their gallery.\n3. I did a test on the developers page adding some data to see the final look,some changes still need to be made.\n','2025-12-11','I am trying my best so that I can finish uploading the developers then start with the suppliers and contractors.','2025-12-11 18:43:20','2025-12-11 18:43:20'),(356,12,'\nToday I was assigned two leads.\n\nCeline did not respond to my calls regarding her inquiry about the Kitusuru Eternity Heights project. I shared the detailed information on her WhatsApp and will follow up with her.\n\nTaran inquired about the Syokimau townhouse and requested that the details be shared via WhatsApp, which I have done.\n\nI took Mr. Greyson for a viewing of the available 5-bedroom villa options in Lavington; however, the units were above his budget. I am currently sourcing alternative options for him.\n\nI also followed up with Mr. Anthony regarding his weekend viewing appointment. He confirmed that he is available to view on Saturday','2025-12-11','','2025-12-11 20:18:45','2025-12-11 20:18:45'),(357,22,'-Had a successful 9:30Am meeting with a client that led to a second viewing at 5acres in Ruiru.\n- Later in the afternoon we met the land owner of the above parcel in Mbs Rd Syokimau area where he had suggested the venue of the meeting to be. The meeting was productive for the buyer got all the necessary documents required for due deligence and subsequently another meeting on 6th January 2026 .\nLate in the evening I took a client to view 2bed at Kilimani Alina ridge. ','2025-12-12','','2025-12-12 03:37:52','2025-12-12 03:37:52'),(358,29,'After our morning marketing team meeting, I submitted the Hephe palace launch event video. Afterwards I did caroussel designs for a first time buyer: 5 slides. I then did and E-card for the incoming Jamhuri day. I later did another E card design of a real estate trivia quiz intended to spark some engagement.','2025-12-11','','2025-12-13 02:26:52','2025-12-13 02:26:52'),(359,29,'I edited a property video of the 5BR townhouse in Lavington to be submitted early Saturday morning.','2025-12-12','','2025-12-13 02:29:06','2025-12-13 02:29:06'),(360,27,'DK WEEKLY REPORT QUESTIONNAIRE FOR THE SALES TEAM\n1. Targets & Performance\n•	What were your specific targets for this week?\n1. To source for more listings that will fit my leads ‘enquiries especially for the rentals in Kitisuru and Peponi road.\n2. Follow up with all my new allocated leads and share their specific projects of interest.\n3. Arrange for more viewings of apartments suitable for investments for Mr Simon Munene after we viewed Luminara last week.\n4. Follow up with my hot leads for a scheduled viewing this week.\n•	How many have you achieved so far?\nAll of the above\n1. Out of the targeted 8 consents, I managed to get two consents for Maylan and Express View apartments.\n2. I followed up with all my hot leads and managed to get three scheduled viewings for next week.\n3. We viewed three new projects with Mr Simon Munene; Capella Residency, Golden Mansion, and Marina Bay Phase 2 and 3. He is assessing all of them and will revert on the apartment of interest.\n4. I managed to get two new rentals in Parklands. They are both 4-bedrooms with DSQ for Kshs110K/M and Kshs270K/M respectively.\n•	How many site visits did you complete (with clients)?\nTHREE.\nTo Capella Residency, Golden Mansion, and Marina Bay Phase 2 and 3.\n•	How many new property leads did you source (with full details and consent letters)?\nTwo from Maylan Apartments in Kileleshwa, and Express view apartments in Kilimani.\n•	How many new client inquiries did you receive, and how many are still active/following up?\nI received 18 new leads and actively following on 12 new leads who would like to buy or rent a property within their specified areas of interest.\n•	Did you meet or exceed your area coverage plan (Kilimani, Kileleshwa, Lavington)?\nYES, this week I traversed and covered Kileleshwa, Kilimani, and Parklands to source for my lead’s enquiries.\n2. Lead Follow-Ups & Client Handling\n•	How many new leads did you contact or follow up with this week?\n18 new leads\n•	Please list the names or initials of the clients you followed up with and their current status (e.g., interested, viewing scheduled, not responding, closed).\n1. Faith Wanjiku – Viewing scheduled.\n2. Elvis – Interested.\n3. Winney – Interested.\n4. Evans – Interested.\n5. Maggie – Interested.\n6. Munjal Shah - Interested.\n7. Grace – Interested.\n8. Omondi – Viewing scheduled.\n9. Martin – Interested.\n10. Gladys - Viewing scheduled.\n11. Deborah - Viewing scheduled.\n12. Martin – Interested.\n•	Which clients have pending follow-ups that need attention next week?\nFive; Mr. Deep, Anthony Muhoro, Justin, Eunice Karanja, and Jane Nyawira.\n•	Have any clients gone silent, and what’s your next step to re-engage them?\nYes, 6 clients have gone silent. I have already engaged them via WhatsApp and SMS.\n•	How many viewings were conducted, and what was the client feedback on the properties?\nTHREE viewings. We noticed poor workmanship in some of the upcoming apartments where the water piping was crisscrossed with the power lines. The layouts for some of the units were not appealing as one could see the bedroom from the main door.\n•	Did you share live locations or updates during viewings and sourcing as required?\nYes, I shared the live locations for my viewings of Capella Residency, Golden Mansion, and Marina Bay apartments.\n3. Achievements\n•	What was your biggest achievement or win this week?\nI was able to have three site visits with my hot leads who have been postponing our scheduled viewings this is after my persistent follow-ups with them\nI was also able to get more scheduled viewings from my cold leads for next week, namely Mr. Ben and Mr. Ireri.\n•	Any new listings or clients you’re proud of securing?\nYes, the Express view apartments, which is mostly within the budget of my leads based on their pricing and location.\n•	Any property owners you built a new relationship with or got consent from?\nYes, Joy of Maylan Apartments, in Kileleshwa.\n•	Any positive client feedback worth noting?\nWe have enough various options for them.\n4. Challenges\n•	What were your biggest challenges this week (e.g., client responsiveness, location access, consent letter issues, pricing)?\n1. This week my challenge was to source the right rentals for my leads especially that their budget is lower than the market rates.\n2. My leads have postponed our scheduled viewings.\n•	What support or resources do you need from the team or management to overcome these?\nTo have our current CRM to be able to have the features we have discussed about. Like grouping our CRM leads in their rightful properties enquired and the stage they are currently in the sales process.\n•	Any listings or developments that were difficult to get information or access to?\nYes, Aria Capital and Tassa apartments.\n5. Next Week Planning\n•	What are your key focus areas or priorities for next week?\nTo persistently follow up on all my scheduled viewings with my leads especially for Westlands and Parklands leads.\nTo get the remaining 6 consents from the property developers\nTo push for Mr Simon and Munjal to pay for Luminara apartments since both are out for an investment unit in Westlands.\nClose the year with a sale or a rental.\n•	Any specific clients or properties you plan to push or close?\nYes, Mr. Simon and Mr. Munjal.\n•	Which days are you planning for fieldwork or viewings?\nTuesday, Wednesday, Thursday, and Friday.\n','2025-12-13','','2025-12-13 12:23:29','2025-12-13 12:23:29'),(361,23,'Weekly Sales & Client Activity Report\nLead Allocation Summary\nLeads allocated by Rashid: 15\nLeads allocated by Joseph: 5\nTotal leads received: 20\nSite Visits Overview\nTotal site visits conducted: 4\nClient Viewings & Feedback\nUtsav\nProperty viewed: Kitusuru Terraces\nFeedback: The house lacks sufficient natural light.\nStatus: Client is not fully convinced but may still consider the property.\nNatasha\nProperty viewed: Grand Premier\nInterest: 1-bedroom unit\nConcerns: Swimming pool is relatively small and limited alternatives available.\nStatus: Client to revert after further consideration.\nJohn Mark\nProperty viewed: Eternity Heights (on behalf of his sister)\nAdditional Requirement: Interested in selling their townhouse located along Naivasha Road.\nAsking Price: KES 28M\nStatus: Viewing completed; potential sales listing opportunity identified.\nJames (Lead from Village Market)\nProperty viewed: Eternity Heights\nFeedback: Positive interest.\nStatus: Client will revert after the festive period.\nGeneral Observations\nEternity Heights attracted multiple viewings, indicating strong interest.\nSome clients expressed concerns around property features (natural lighting, amenities), highlighting the need for alternative options.\nPotential new listing opportunity identified along Naivasha Road.\nAction Points for the Coming Week\nFollow up with Natasha and Utsav to address concerns and present alternative options.\nRe-engage James after the festive season.\nDiscuss and possibly onboard John Mark’s townhouse listing along Naivasha Road.\nContinue nurturing allocated leads to increase site visits and conversions\n2 clients have already confirmed viewing for next week. One for Luminara and the other for eternity heights','2025-12-14','','2025-12-14 09:03:47','2025-12-14 09:03:47'),(362,29,'I edited and submitted a property video for Villa Novo and Marina Bay 2. ','2025-12-13','','2025-12-14 17:58:35','2025-12-14 17:58:35'),(363,12,'\n\nWeekly Report\n\nLast week, I conducted four (4) site visits with clients:\n\nI took Mr. George to view a resale property at Capital Rise. He also viewed Pinecrest View and Jade Residence.\n\nMr. Christian revisited the Luminara project, where he made an additional payment.\n\nI took Mr. Greyson to view a 5-bedroom villa to let in Lavington.\n\nI took Mr. Anthony to view the Galaxy One project.\n\n\nDuring the week, I was assigned 16 leads, out of which 6 turned responsive.\n\nClient Follow-ups and Plans for Next Week:\n\nMr. Joe requested a site visit next week for a Syokimau maisonette.\n\nI am working on planning site visits based on the requests received last week.\n\nWinfred, an agent with a client interested in viewing Eternity Heights, Kitusuru, later became unresponsive.\n\nNina is looking for a residential unit within an 8M budget. She is open to off-plan projects and is available for a site visit next Tuesday.\n\nVendana showed interest in the Eternity Heights, Kitusuru project and is available for a site visit next Saturday.\n\nMumbi is looking for a residential unit and is open to an office visit next week to further discuss and clarify her requirements.\n\nAdeel expressed interest in viewing Eternity Heights, Kitusuru but suggested Sunday, when the site is closed. I am following up to confirm his availability for a weekday visit next week.','2025-12-14','','2025-12-14 19:46:37','2025-12-14 19:46:37'),(364,13,'1. Today I was able to create profiles for 5 developers, I will be able to add their data as well so that the profile  is complete. I included their logos and also their history, location and the projects they have done.\n2. I submitted two consent letters to Mr Yi for stamping, I will be uploading the projects after the stamping has been done .\n3. Joseph and I went through the excel task tracker from the developers and we approved some of the tasks they have completed and we updated the ones that are still pending, they will be working on the pending ones.','2025-12-15','I am trying to beat my deadline despite the short period that is remaining.','2025-12-15 13:51:56','2025-12-15 13:51:56'),(365,29,'After our weekly Monday meeting as the marketing team, we headed for a shoot at Sohail Gardens in Gatanga road. We managed to shoot two videos, a talking a video and a general house tour of the place.','2025-12-15','','2025-12-15 13:54:18','2025-12-15 13:54:18'),(366,27,'1. Early morning BEKE Sales team meeting to plan and strategise on how we are all going to push for a closure of either a rental or sale.\n2. Follow up on the following leads:\na. Rashid - Interested in viewing Eternity apartments in Kitisuru.\nb. Elvis - Interested in viewing Shangri-la 1-bedroom apartment for rent.\nc. Esther - New lead and seems to be a diaspora lead looking for an investment unit in Westlands.\nd. Felix Kemboi - New lead interested in a 1-bedroom apartment for rent in Lavington.\ne. Dr David Waruingi - Interested in a rental apartment in Lavington.\nf. Evans - An agent with a lead for rental.\ng. Martin Kitur - Looking for a rental in Lavington.\n\n3. Thereafter, I went for viewing and to meet Rashid in Eternity apartments in Kitisuru. He was not able to come, especially after I sent him the PIN and found the apartments to be far beyond his location limit.\n4. Back to the office to familiarise with new projects for listing.','2025-12-15','All is well.','2025-12-15 14:42:38','2025-12-15 14:42:38'),(367,11,'1. Chaired the morning team meeting, attended by Desmond, Brian, Dennis and Reachel.\n2. Went for a viewing in Lavington, with Brian\'s Client. we only maneged to view one option, we will meet again tomorrow.\n3. I also went to Karen to attend a meeting between the client and the landlord. Happy to state that the client will be taking the house and will pay before end of this week. The meeting was schedules for 3pm ','2025-12-15','','2025-12-15 14:55:02','2025-12-15 14:55:02'),(368,24,'Held a morning meeting with my team where we shared various requests received over the weekend.\nMade follow up calls with my clients in the CRM to check on the progress of the negotiations.\nReceived two request for a JV on Muthithi Road 31 0.5acres and sale of 24acres in Karen that i got the properties and planned for viewing on 16th Dec.\nCalled 3leads assigned to me from social media and got one positive feedback for Luminara.\nHeld two meetings ith the developers agents regarding the 0.25acres Wetlands JV to discuss commission.\nWorked the CRM to get Dominic\'s clients and follow ups. \n\n','2025-12-15','Thank you for introducing the reminder button of the expiry session of the CRM.','2025-12-15 14:58:53','2025-12-15 14:58:53'),(369,15,'Managed to assign 20 leads which rolled from Sunday noon in addition to 8 leads which rolled to day as from 7am  from meta ads \n\nCrosse checked the campaigns with the the consultant and In that I decided to ad one creative to maximize on the adspend since we had three .\nWas majorly analyzing our social media content and seeing on where to adjust to maximize on the hooks .where Joseph the consultant also said he would share some scripts too .','2025-12-15','','2025-12-15 16:49:06','2025-12-15 16:49:06'),(370,17,'Meetings and Tasks:\n\n- Attended the daily morning marketing meeting to discuss ongoing projects, strategies, and initiatives, ensuring alignment with team goals and objectives.\n- Updated the daily leads spreadsheet with assigned leads, ensuring accurate tracking, follow-up, and seamless collaboration among team members.\n- Conducted a standalone shoot in Lavington from 12pm, which was successfully completed, capturing key footage and assets for upcoming marketing campaigns.\n- Returned to the office by 3:30pm and updated the leads form, sharing it on the Beke marketing group to facilitate team information and follow-up.','2025-12-15','','2025-12-15 17:07:03','2025-12-15 17:07:03'),(371,12,'\n\nToday, I took Mr. Kush for a site visit to view a 3-bedroom apartment at Emaar, as well as an option at Greenville Gardens along General Mathenge. He expressed interest in Emaar, with a few concerns that I need to confirm and revert with feedback.\n\nLater in the mid-afternoon, I received a call from Judy, who requested a site visit to the Amara project in Syokimau. She viewed the project and indicated that she would share her feedback before the end of the week.\n\nI was assigned seven new leads, which are subject to follow-up calls tomorrow morning, as I had limited office hours today.\n\nAdditionally, I followed up with Mumbi, who confirmed her availability on Saturday to further discuss the purchase options she is considering.\n ','2025-12-15','','2025-12-15 19:18:17','2025-12-15 19:18:17'),(372,23,'Summary of Activities:\nReceived 8 new leads from the Marketing Department.2 leads have schedule for viewing before the end of the week. Still subject to follow up for viewings and those who were not reaponsive,\nConducted 4 follow-up calls with existing prospects.\nClient Updates:\nAman: Informed that he has secured an alternative property in Westlands.\nNatasha: Requested to review another option before committing to Grand Premier.\nWanja: Scheduled a viewing at Luminara for tomorrow.\nMina: Reached out regarding Luminara; currently awaiting feedback.\nRaabi: Conducted a property viewing for investment purposes. Viewed Eternity and Luminara. Client indicated she is comparing two additional options and will revert on whether to proceed with Luminara.\nNext Steps:\nFollow up with Mina for feedback on Luminara.\nConduct scheduled viewing with Wanja.\nAwait Raabi’s final decision after her comparisons.\nContinue nurturing remaining leads from marketing.','2025-12-15','','2025-12-15 19:38:02','2025-12-15 19:38:02'),(373,20,'I managed to to attend morning viewing with client in kilimani and he liked the plot and requested after holiday he will meet the owner \nLater we viewed another 2 quarters with another client where in kilimani where he will be back tomorrow for viewing paper work\nI went sourcing a town house for a client who was in need of it and I got it later in the noon we went for viewing  añd the client decided it was not on the best position he needed ','2025-12-15','','2025-12-15 20:56:54','2025-12-15 20:56:54'),(374,13,'1. Today I was able to create 6 Developer profiles, I was able to get their logo images , resized them and then created a profile for them, I included their locations and also their history information, I will be working on the different data for the projects they have done tomorrow.\n2. Joseph and I tested the bulk sms sending using our own contacts, we are still waiting for thee team to sort out the pending issues for the sms to reflect before they can be sent to the agents.\n3.I did a follow up with the website developer , he was to include the transfer of customers from one agent to another and also include the account disabling function , I have done a test since he had already worked on them and these two functions are now possible.','2025-12-16','','2025-12-16 13:41:32','2025-12-16 13:41:32'),(375,27,'1. Early morning BEKE Sales Team meeting to push for a sale or rental before this Saturday.\n2. Sourcing a town house at Dennis Prit Road and Mvuli road for my leads.\n3. I was able to follow up on my yesterday\'s leads and share projects with them.\n4. Today was a queit day for me.','2025-12-16','All is well, though today was a quiet day for me.','2025-12-16 14:53:29','2025-12-16 14:53:29'),(376,17,'\n\n- Attended the morning marketing meeting to discuss ongoing projects, strategies, and initiatives.\n- Wrote two scripts in preparation for tomorrow\'s shoot for rental properties, ensuring alignment with project objectives.\n- Participated in creating fun reels with the team to increase interactions on our social media pages. The two videos were submitted by Mr. Paddy for review and approval.\n- Submitted the property shoot done yesterday in the Beke marketing group for team information and feedback.\n- Updated and shared the leads spreadsheet on the Beke marketing group, ensuring team alignment and progress tracking.','2025-12-16','','2025-12-16 15:55:06','2025-12-16 15:55:06'),(377,15,'Assigned 18 leads to the sales team this included 7 leads which were Majorly for the syokimau stand alone and the rest for various apartments that are running I the ad \nWe did an upcoming office content shoot which was angaging all the team members .\nI stopped running the ad campaign for the kitusuru duplexes since it was not bringing any leads while at the same time consuming daily budget .','2025-12-16','','2025-12-16 16:36:35','2025-12-16 16:36:35'),(378,12,'\n\n> Today, I followed up on the assigned leads through calls.\n\nMr. Brian confirmed his availability to view Eternity Heights on Saturday.\n\nMehreen mentioned that she will be available to visit Eternity Heights in January next year.\n\nLinda was responsive and requested that I share the details of a 5-bedroom maisonette in Syokimau via WhatsApp.\n\nMr. Kioko indicated that he is looking to purchase a 1/8-acre plot in Syokimau to develop his personal home.','2025-12-16','','2025-12-16 18:31:32','2025-12-16 18:31:32'),(379,29,'We had our morning departmental meeting, after which I edited two videos of the previous\'s day shoot at Sohail Gardens in Lavington: A talking video and a property video. In the afternoon we did two light office shoots, edited and submitted by close of business.','2025-12-16','','2025-12-16 18:33:53','2025-12-16 18:33:53'),(380,20,'I attended meeting with the land owner and the buyer regards on a plot on muthithi Westland  where they agreed on each terms where they exchanged documents in order for the search to be conducted for a period of 2 days where the meeting will proceed on Thursday if the documents are clean ','2025-12-16','','2025-12-16 18:50:57','2025-12-16 18:50:57'),(381,23,'Daily Work Report\nReceived 4 leads: 2 from Rashid and 2 from Joseph.\nMost of the leads were foreign numbers, so I engaged them via WhatsApp. Some have responded and are pending follow-up.\nFollow-Ups & Calls\nWanja: Unable to meet as scheduled due to a personal engagement. She requested to reschedule the Luminara presentation to either Thursday or Friday.\nJohn Mark: Requested more details on Eternity, specifically regarding rental yield. He asked that I follow up after the festive period and also expressed interest in viewing Eternity on friday with the sister who wants to purchase for investment\nSaid: wants to view eternity and a gani gardens on Thursday.\n\nI have a meeting with Amto serviced apartments in Westlands in their offices on sports road and 1 viewing at golden mansion in the afternoon\n','2025-12-16','','2025-12-16 19:01:52','2025-12-16 19:01:52'),(382,11,'Consolidated Weekly Sales Team Report\n1. Team Lead Allocation Summary\n•	Leads allocated by Rashid and Joseph: 100\n2. Site Visits & Client Engagement Overview\n•	Total site visits conducted (team): 14\n•	Strong client turnout recorded, particularly for Eternity Heights – 2-bedroom duplexes in Kitisuru, indicating sustained buyer interest in the project.\n3. Individual Agent Performance Summaries\nBrian – Weekly Performance Summary\n•	Conducted four (4) site visits:\no	Capital Rise (resale), Pinecrest View, Jade Residence – with Mr. George\no	Luminara revisit with Mr. Christian (additional payment made)\no	5-bedroom villa to let in Lavington – Mr. Greyson\no	Galaxy One project – Mr. Anthony\nClient Follow-ups & Planned Actions:\n•	Mr. Joe – Syokimau maisonette viewing scheduled\n•	Nina – 8M budget, open to off-plan; viewing scheduled next Tuesday\n•	Vendana – Eternity Heights viewing next Saturday\n•	Mumbi – Office meeting planned to clarify requirements\n•	Adeel – Interested in Eternity Heights; weekday viewing to be confirmed\n•	Winfred (agent) – Became unresponsive after initial inquiry\nDesmond – Weekly Performance Summary\nActive Clients:\n•	Meena – Studio/1-bedroom (6–7M); viewing at Minara Heights scheduled\n•	John Mark – Eternity Duplexes, Kitisuru; viewing scheduled\nOngoing Follow-ups:\n•	Mbabu – Missed Luminara event; follow-up ongoing\n•	Amish – Marina Bay viewed; Azure Syokimau scheduled\n•	Michelle – Pending availability\n•	Kazuri – Reviewing Luminara and alternative options\n•	Jemimah – Viewed Migaa; affordability concerns; alternatives shared\nProject Visits Conducted:\n•	Marina Bay\n•	Minara Heights\n•	Dolce Vita\n•	Himalaya Horizon\nDennis – Weekly Performance Summary\n•	Received 18 new leads; actively following up on 12\n•	Conducted three (3) site visits:\no	Capella Residency\no	Golden Mansion\no	Marina Bay Phases 2 & 3\nKey Achievements:\n•	Secured 2 new consents (Maylan Apartments, Express View Apartments)\n•	Arranged 3 scheduled viewings for next week\n•	Sourced 2 Parklands rentals (4BR + DSQ at KES 110K & KES 270K)\nChallenges Identified:\n•	Rental budget constraints vs market pricing\n•	Postponed viewings by clients\nFocus for Next Week:\n•	Push for Luminara investment units (Mr. Simon & Mr. Munjal)\n•	Close either a sale or rental before year-end\n4. Sales Manager – Client & Revenue-Focused Activities\n•	Conducted targeted follow-up calls with Village Market and social media leads, successfully re-engaging dormant clients.\n•	Personally conducted four (4) client site visits, including a Karen viewing with a Chinese client, resulting in a positive outcome and strong purchase interest.\n•	Provided direct sales support to Brian by:\no	Sourcing suitable townhouse rental listings for a client with a KSh 400,000 budget\no	Personally accompanying the client for a site viewing\n•	Attended a performance review meeting with Mr. Ken, aligning on:\no	Overall pipeline strength and deal viability\no	Closure targets to be achieved by the 20th of the month\no	Implementation of weekly consolidated team reports tracking targets, progress, and conversions\n5. Key Observations \n•	Strong interest in Eternity Heights (Kitisuru) signals high demand for well-priced duplex investment units.\n•	Client concerns around amenities and natural lighting highlight the need for alternative inventory readiness.\n•	Identified potential new listing opportunity along Naivasha Road.\n6. Action Points for the Coming Week\n•	Push offer letters, deposits, and confirmations for Luminara and Eternity Heights\n•	Convert all scheduled second viewings\n•	Secure additional rental and resale inventory\n•	Intensify follow-ups on all warm and active leads\n•	Target at least one sale and one rental closure to maintain momentum\n','2025-12-16','Consolidated weekly report for last week','2025-12-16 22:06:00','2025-12-16 22:06:00'),(383,11,'I chaired the morning sales team meeting.\n\nI rushed for a viewing with a client in Lavington who is looking for a 5–6 bedroom villa for rent. He did not prefer the option I showed him, so I will be sourcing additional alternatives.\n\nSince the client wants a house he can move into soon, I went ahead and sourced listings in Kyuna, Spring Valley, and Lavington. I identified three options in total  two for rent and one for sale.\n\nI was back in the office by 3:45 pm, then headed to Parklands (City Park Road) to collect the market study report Edmond had requested. Unfortunately, due to time constraints, most places had already closed.','2025-12-16','','2025-12-16 22:25:36','2025-12-16 22:25:36'),(384,27,'1. Early morning meeting with the BEKE Sales Team on pursuing a closure of any kind.\n2. Sourcing in Upper Hill and viewed Luarel Hills suites, Anjoy apartments, and ARIA Capital which is under construction.\n3. Back to the office and I followed up on the following leads:\n1) Kelvin - Interested in a 2Br rental.\n2) Gladys - Interested in the Syokimau house/Villa.\n3) Dr Obadiah - Interested in a Rental.\n4) Saloni - Interested in a Rental.\n5) Stephanie - Interested in a Rental.\n6) Ben - Interested in Luminara.\n7) Saloni - Interested in a Rental.\n8) Ian - Interested in a 1-bedroom apartment for investment.\nI have shared with them their respective property of choice and waiting for their feedback.','2025-12-17','All is well and pushing for a closure.','2025-12-17 14:22:19','2025-12-17 14:22:19'),(385,24,'Had a viewing with a client in Lavington where the landowner shared the documents for the search to be done and next meeting to be held on Friday.\nHeld a meeting with the Lawyer regarding our commission of the JV Project on Westlands road and made a few corrections which are going to be rectified tomorrow and shared accordingly.\nTook another client, Pauline, to site at Plainsview in Juja to show the location of the project. She liked it and requested for the payment plan details to see whether it will be accepted by the bank.\nDid sourcing of 43acres up for JV at Guru Nanak.\nCalled the leads assigned to me and sourced properties in Kitisure 1acre as per the request and organized for viewing  on Friday 19th 9a.m.\nWorked on the CRM on my follow up clients.','2025-12-17','','2025-12-17 14:43:24','2025-12-17 14:43:24'),(386,13,'1.Today I was able to add some data for 5 developer profiles that I had already created.I was uploading the projects they have done, adding the units those particular projects have and also adding photos for their galleries as required.\n2.I did a follow up with the developer,I still had some challenges since some photos were not displaying,he has worked on a few,others he will be working on tonight and I will confirm tomorrow.\n3. I assisted in some of the office duties since we still don\'t have the receptionist,Mia and I stepped in.\n4.I updated the excel for the developers progress tracker,as they have already made some changes which they were to make by today .','2025-12-17','Try to do better than yesterday.','2025-12-17 15:07:57','2025-12-17 15:07:57'),(387,17,'Summary of todays  Activities:\n1. Morning Meeting:\n    - Attended the daily morning marketing team meeting at 8:35am at the office, located at Broadwalk Mall, Westland\'s, Nairobi.\n    - The meeting aimed to discuss ongoing projects, address challenges, and align team efforts.\n    - Key takeaways and action items were documented and shared with the team via the Beke Marketing group.\n2. Property Shoot:\n    - Left the office at 11:20am with Mr. Paddy and Mr. Rashid and proceeded to Dolce Vita, Parklands, for a property shoot.\n    - The shoot was conducted from 11:30am to 1:10pm, capturing necessary visuals and data for marketing purposes.\n3.Site Shoot:\n    - Left Dolce Vita, Parklands, at 1:10pm and headed to Galaxy One offices for a meeting and site shoot.\n    - conducted the site shoot as scheduled.\n    - Left Galaxy One offices at 3:15pm and returned to the office at Broadwalk Mall.\n4. Administrative Tasks:\n    - Updated the leads spreadsheet with the latest information and progress and shared on the Beke marketing group.\n    - Identified and brainstormed ideas for the next shoot, scheduled to take place  tomorrow.\n\nAccomplishments:\n- Successfully conducted a property shoot at Dolce Vita and Galaxy one in Parklands.\n- Updated leads spreadsheet and identified new ideas for future shoots, enhancing the team\'s pipeline and creative direction.\nUpcoming Tasks:\n- Prepare for the next shoot, scheduled for this week, ensuring all logistics and resources are in place.\n- Follow up on leads and respond to inquiries, providing excellent customer service and driving business growth.\n\nChallenges/Concerns:\n\n- None reported','2025-12-17','','2025-12-17 16:31:58','2025-12-17 16:31:58'),(388,15,'I assigned 14 leads to the property sales team , the clarification of syokimau mansion is that the owner the house is allowing visits from clients accompanied by Brian because they had an exclusive arrangements given the arrangements they had in the exclusive consent for selling.\nI accompanied mia and paddy and came up with a meta priming video which will be used to create a custom audience for the period that we will be in the break .\nI uploaded 2 content as shared by paddy earlier in the morning hours .','2025-12-17','Compiling content shot today together with Joseph the consultant for purposes of utilizing it\'s priming for meta ads \n\nAssigning lead got over today\'s night ','2025-12-17 16:55:36','2025-12-17 16:55:36'),(389,12,'\n\nToday, I successfully contacted all the assigned leads.\n\nMr. Joseph has scheduled a visit to the office tomorrow, after which we will proceed to the site at Eternity Heights, Kitusuru.\n\nMr. Chadamba expressed interest in the 5-bedroom maisonette in Syokimau and mentioned that he will create time on Saturday for a viewing appointment.\n\nMr. Harold indicated that he is looking for a one-bedroom apartment to rent in Westlands and plans to move in by mid-January.\n\nI took Mr. Greyson to view a villa in Lavington. He would like to explore more options before settling on one.\n\nAmanda, who was scheduled to view the Syokimau maisonette, rescheduled the viewing to tomorrow','2025-12-17','','2025-12-17 20:30:27','2025-12-17 20:30:27'),(390,12,'\n\nToday, I successfully contacted all the assigned leads.\n\nMr. Joseph has scheduled a visit to the office tomorrow, after which we will proceed to the site at Eternity Heights, Kitusuru.\n\nMr. Chadamba expressed interest in the 5-bedroom maisonette in Syokimau and mentioned that he will create time on Saturday for a viewing appointment.\n\nMr. Harold indicated that he is looking for a one-bedroom apartment to rent in Westlands and plans to move in by mid-January.\n\nI took Mr. Greyson to view a villa in Lavington. He would like to explore more options before settling on one.\n\nAmanda, who was scheduled to view the Syokimau maisonette, rescheduled the viewing to tomorrow','2025-12-17','','2025-12-17 20:30:28','2025-12-17 20:30:28'),(391,20,'I had viewing on the morning hours with a client on a plot on Ngara where he liked the plot and requested for time to do his due diligence l\nLater I went to Kilimani for a viewing with a developer and viewed where he requested for the paper work in order to request a search \nI later went to Westland for a viewing but the developer didn\'t show up where he requested for the viewing to be held tomorrow ','2025-12-17','','2025-12-17 20:35:21','2025-12-17 20:35:21'),(392,11,'Attended the morning Sales team meeting for both the Residential and Lands departments, chaired by Mr. Ken. The discussion focused on year-end wind-up, pending closures, targets to be closed before year-end, and performance expectations for the team.\n\nProceeded to Parklands to conduct market research on developments around City Park Road at the request of Edmond. While several projects were stalled and on-site teams lacked sufficient information or reliable contacts, I was able to gather available insights and compiled a research report, which was shared with Edmond.\n\nAccompanied Brian\'s  client to Lavington to view the property that i had sourced for a property viewing priced at 450,000. The clients have a budget of 400,000, and negotiations with the owner are ongoing but challenging. The clients have expressed interest in exploring additional options within their budget.\n\nTraveled to Karen to meet Mr. Luo (Chinese client) for property viewings. Three options were viewed in collaboration with a Karen-based agent. The client liked all three properties, with a strong preference for the final option. The landlord was present during the viewing, discussions were held on-site, and the engagement appears promising. He will give me feedback on his decision tomorrow.','2025-12-17','','2025-12-17 21:01:27','2025-12-17 21:01:27'),(393,23,'Lead Engagement & Follow‑Ups\n1. Actively Responsive Lead\n\nRequirement: 3‑bedroom apartment\n\nBudget: KES 15M\n\nStatus: Actively engaged\n\nAction Taken: Options shared\n\nNext Steps: Ongoing engagement and awaiting detailed feedback from the client to narrow down preferred options.\n\n2. Kazuri\n\nStatus: Follow‑up completed\n\nClient Request: Details on Gemini\n\nAction Taken: Information on Gemini shared\n\nNext Steps: Client to confirm availability for a possible viewing on Friday.\n\n3. Michelle\n\nRequirement: 2‑bedroom apartment\n\nTimeline: Available from next year\n\nStatus: Warm lead\n\nNext Steps: Viewing planned for January when the client becomes available.\n\n4. Other Follow‑Ups\n\nStatus: Contacted\n\nOutcome: Availability yet to be confirmed\n\nNext Steps: Continued follow‑ups to lock in viewing dates.\n\nBusiness Development & Viewings\nAMTO – Serviced Apartments\n\nActivity: Site visit conducted\n\nDiscussion: Potential collaboration where we assist with sales\n\nStatus: Initial engagement completed\n\nNext Steps: Follow‑up discussions to define scope and terms of collaboration.\n\nMarina Bay – Rental Viewing\n\nClient: Natasha\n\nProperty: 1‑bedroom apartment (rental)\n\nStatus: Viewing completed\n\nNext Steps: Active follow‑up to close or address client feedback.\n\nOverall Status\n\nOne highly active sales lead progressing well.\n\nTwo warm leads with clear future timelines (Kazuri and Michelle).\n\nOngoing follow‑ups with remaining leads to confirm availability.\n\nOne potential new collaboration opportunity identified (AMTO).','2025-12-18','','2025-12-18 07:06:45','2025-12-18 07:06:45'),(395,29,'We went for a shoot at Dolce Vita where did a talking video and a general house tour of the residence. We also went ahead to Galaxy one residence, an off plan project and did an informative video shoot','2025-12-17','','2025-12-18 07:14:58','2025-12-18 07:14:58'),(396,13,'1. Today I created 3 developer profiles, I included their logo images, the different projects that they have done and also the different types of units they have within their projects.\n2. I added data for 4 developer profiles that I had created earlier but I still did not have the correct data, I included photos for their gallery, the different projects they have done and also the different units within the projects they have done to make their profiles complete and informative.\n3. I assisted in other office duties as Mia and I are the ones stepping in as receptionists for the meantime.\n4. I had a session with Joseph in regards with the website developer progress , he requested if they could come tomorrow which they have not yet confirmed.','2025-12-18','Working to become better each day.','2025-12-18 13:46:16','2025-12-18 13:46:16'),(397,27,'1. Early morning meeting with the BEKE Sales team and we discussed our previous\' days\' work plan, viewings, and the hot leads we have. Also, we discussed about our today\'s work plan.\n2. All my scheduled viewings were postponed to tomorrow and Monday next week.\n3. In the office and followed up with 13 of my hot leads and pushed for viewings with them after pitching to them their preferred projects. Below are the 13 leads:\n\nName	Phone	Interest	Priority	Source	Country	Agent	Created	Actions\n	Esther Nurse	+254 702 916320	Apartment	B	social	Kenya	Dennis Kimani	18 Dec 2025	\n	Felix Kemboi	+254 729 974989	Apartment	B	social	Kenya	Dennis Kimani	18 Dec 2025	\n	Dr David	+254 721 994598	Apartment	B	social	Kenya	Dennis Kimani	18 Dec 2025	\n	Jacky Samuel	+211 929 489 491	Apartment	B	social	Kenya	Dennis Kimani	18 Dec 2025	\n	Ricky Derrick	+254 771 450475	Apartment	B	social	Kenya	Dennis Kimani	18 Dec 2025	\n	Charles \"Ëternity\"	+254 786 581990	Apartment	C	social	Kenya	Dennis Kimani	18 Dec 2025	\n	Victoria Kerubo	+254 742 470028	Apartment	C	social	Kenya	Dennis Kimani	18 Dec 2025	\n	Bol Chienguon	+254728806008	Apartment	C	social	Kenya	Dennis Kimani	18 Dec 2025	\n	Dr Obadiah	+254 790 037892	Apartment	C	social	Kenya	Dennis Kimani	18 Dec 2025	\n	Luqman	+254 717 467110	Apartment	B	social	Kenya	Dennis Kimani	18 Dec 2025	\n	Stephanie	+254 717 600811	Apartment	C	social	Kenya	Dennis Kimani	18 Dec 2025	\n	Ian Kabui	+254 702 439618	Apartment	C	social	Kenya	Dennis Kimani	18 Dec 2025	\n	Yassin Omer	+254743274555	Apartment	B	social	Kenya	Dennis Kimani	18 Dec 2025	','2025-12-18','I am pushing for a sale or a rental.','2025-12-18 13:56:50','2025-12-18 13:56:50'),(398,24,'