ive season.\nHilda: Requested follow-up in January (specific date provided).\nMichelle: Requested follow-up in January (specific date provided).\nMbarack: Requested follow-up in January (specific date provided).\nNext Steps:\nSchedule follow-up with Marco in early January.\nSet reminders for January follow-ups with Hilda, Michelle, and Mbarack.','2025-12-18','','2025-12-18 16:41:20','2025-12-18 16:41:20'),(402,17,'Summary of todays Activities:\n\n1. Meeting Attendance:\n    - Attended the daily marketing meeting at 8:35am, ensuring alignment with team objectives and updates.\n2. Meeting Minutes:\n    - Wrote and shared the morning marketing meeting minutes on the Beke marketing group, disseminating key discussions and action items to the team.\n3. Shoot Preparation:\n    - Created two scripts for tomorrow\'s shoot, enhancing preparedness for upcoming marketing activities.\n    - Collaborated with Mr. Paddy on new ideas to execute tomorrow, fostering team synergy and innovative approaches.\n4. Lead Management:\n    - Updated and shared the daily leads spreadsheet on the Beke marketing team, ensuring accurate tracking and follow-up.\n\nAccomplishments:\n\n- Successfully shared marketing meeting minutes, keeping the team informed and aligned.\n- Prepared scripts and ideas for tomorrow\'s shoot, contributing to operational readiness.\n\nUpcoming Tasks:\n- Support tomorrow\'s shoot and follow up on leads, driving business growth and customer engagement.\n','2025-12-18','','2025-12-18 17:07:32','2025-12-18 17:07:32'),(403,12,'\nMy day was productive.\n\nI managed to update the CRM with this week’s clients early in the morning.\n\nIn the mid-afternoon, I had a scheduled site visit with Mr Joseph; however, he went silent and did not respond to calls. I plan to follow up with him again tomorrow.\n\nLater in the afternoon, I made calls to the assigned leads and received some positive responses. One client is planning to view the 5-bedroom maisonette in Syokimau on Saturday.\n\nI also followed up with last week’s clients who had gone silent. One of them responded and mentioned she will be available for a viewing in early January. Another client, who is looking to purchase a 3-bedroom residential unit, also indicated that he will be available after the festive season.','2025-12-18','','2025-12-18 19:07:13','2025-12-18 19:07:13'),(404,11,'1. Morning Meeting\n\n   * Attended the morning meeting chaired by Rachel.\n\n2. Client Follow-ups & Lead Management\n\n   * Conducted follow-ups with leads and existing clients throughout the day.\n   * Secured four serious clients interested in viewing properties within the month.\n   * Updated the CRM with all client calls, feedback, and next actions.\n\n3. Scheduled Viewings\n\n   * Viewings planned for tomorrow with:\n\n     * Amos – Interested in Kitisuru duplexes (Eternity Heights).\n     * Wamuyu – Interested in Kitisuru duplexes (Eternity Heights).\n     * Wangui – Interested in Kitisuru duplexes (Eternity Heights).\n   All three clients requested a confirmation call tomorrow morning to agree on viewing times.\n\n4. New Client Requirement\n\n   *Bridget\n\n     * Looking for a 1-bedroom apartment for rent in Kilimani.\n     * Budget: 55,000 ksh.\n     * Move-in timeline: January (relocating from Kisumu to Nairobi for a new role).\n\n5. Chinese Client Update\n\n   * Communicated with the Chinese client and successfully connected him with the landlord.\n   * Both parties are currently in direct communication.','2025-12-18','','2025-12-18 20:09:55','2025-12-18 20:09:55'),(405,29,'We had our morning team meeting, after which I submitted the first video for Dolce vita. I started editing a property video on the same and submitted in the afternoon. We also did a fun  POV office shoot with Mia and submitted by close of business.','2025-12-18','','2025-12-19 01:52:42','2025-12-19 01:52:42'),(406,20,'I managed to have a viewing with a client along Westland where he declined to purchase due to the neighbors