artments and Emaar Residence.\n2. Went for site visit to the above two mentioned apartments and they will consider the options we have viewed and give feedback. Mr Sam and Mrs Joyce Wamboi.\n3. Back to the office on more leads follow up for tomorrow\'s site visit.','2025-12-30','Pushing for a closure and a sale.','2025-12-30 13:59:07','2025-12-30 13:59:07'),(413,27,'1. Reported to the office on the last day of the year and followed up with my leads listed below:\n 1) Joyce Wamboi who viewed two apartments yesterday and liked Emaar Residence.\n 2) Winny Williams who is interested in a 2-bedroom apartment for rent.\n 3) Tarik Aden who is interested in a 1-bedroom furnished apartment for rent.\n 4) Linda Gachie interested in a unit for investment.\n 5) Yassin Omer interested in a furnished apartment in Kamakis.\n 6) Ian Kabui intrested in buying an apartment for investment.\n 7) Luqman interested in buying a 2–3-bedroom apartment for living in\n\n2. Sharing project details with my potential leads.\n\n3. Updating my CRM.','2025-12-31','New Year of 2026 looks promising, and sales are almost coming in.','2025-12-31 13:32:40','2025-12-31 13:32:40'),(414,27,'1. Reported to the office and followed up on my leads, especially the ones who were to view today.\n2. Later on, went for viewing with my lead who was interested in The Summit apartments.\n3. Back to the office and followed up with all my allocated leads from BEKE:\n   1) Grace interested in Eternity Apartments,\n   2) Mr Langat interested in a Villa in Lavington,\n   3) Dishon Ratego interested in the Syokimau Villa,\n   4) Caroline interested in a 3Br for rent along Waiyaki Way,\n   5) Josephine interested in a stand-alone house for rent in Ruiru.\n   6) John interested in a 1 to 2-bedroom furnished apartment for rent.','2026-01-02','All is going on well.','2026-01-02 14:03:22','2026-01-02 14:03:22'),(415,11,'Daily Summary\n	•	Client Follow-ups: Re-engaged and followed up with existing clients whose matters were pending before the holiday break.\n	•	Property Viewings (Rent): Conducted two viewings in Kileleshwa for a client seeking a 2-bedroom rental unit.\n	•	Property Viewing (Rent): Viewed a 5-bedroom townhouse in Kapute Gardens, Kileleshwa, listed at KSH 300,000.\n	•	Client Feedback: Client expressed interest but requested to view additional options before making a decision.\n	•	Next Action: Source and schedule further suitable property options for client consideration.','2026-01-02','','2026-01-02 21:13:45','2026-01-02 21:13:45'),(416,27,'1. Report to the office as usual and follow up with my leads.\n2. Viewing of Eternity apartments with Grace K\n3. Back to the office and sourced two projects: Super WestView Apartments and Super WestBury Apartments.','2026-01-03','All is well for now.','2026-01-03 12:47:59','2026-01-03 12:47:59'),(417,24,'Started with the morning meeting with the team where we shared various strategies to execute the vision for 2026. Its important to note that the team was still working even while still on holiday.\nHeld a meeting with the Land Department team where we set targets for seasoned property collection and had a viewing at Raphta Road with a client.\nMade follow up calls  and Whatsapp messages to the previous clients wishing them a Happy New Year and polite reminders.\nOrganized for viewing tomorrow with a client along Muthithi Road at 10a.m. 0.25acres.\nHeld a meeting with agents that have various properties to which they are willing to sell through us.','2026-01-05','','2026-01-05 14:26:23','2026-01-05 14:26:23'),(418,17,'OFFICIAL DAILY REPORT\n\n-Meeting Attendance: Attended the morning meeting at 8:30am and actively participated in discussions\nTasks Completed:\n    - Wrote and shared the meeting minutes with the team\n    - Prepared a script for the scheduled Wednesday shoot\nClient Engagement:\n    - Left the office at 3:15pm to attend a viewing with a client in Lavington, he was not satisficed with the house will source another property and share with him in the course of this week.\n    \n','2026-01-05','','2026-01-05 17:21:23','2026-01-05 17:21:23'),(419,23,'Daily Report\nLeads & Assignments\nReceived 1 lead from Rashid interested in a 2-bedroom apartment in Westlands for a 2-month stay. Her name is June. They have a budget of 150k per month\nJune has reviewed the options sent and scheduled a viewing for one of the units tomorrow.\nClient Follow-ups\nFollowed up with previous clients.\nFrom the follow ups, Michelle Banju has scheduled a viewing for a 1-bedroom apartment for sale in Lavington.\nStatus Summary\nActive leads progressing to viewings.\nContinued engagement with previous clients showing positive outcomes.','2026-01-05','','2026-01-05 17:46:51','2026-01-05 17:46:51'),(420,13,'1.Today was the opening day where we were reporting back to work,we had a morning meeting which was chaired by Joy,we motivated ourselves after sharing the challenges we had last year and the new attitude we need for this new year.\n2. I created a profile for 1 developer and added the data to make the profile complete as required.\n3. I did a test on the suppliers page but I had a small challenge which I already communicated with the developer and he promised to sort it out by tomorrow so that I can proceed.\n4. I had a meeting with Paddy since he was requested to assist me come up with better photos for the website,he shared his strategy and we agreed that we will begin working tomorrow since we still needed the exact dimension of the size of the photos that will be suitable for different landing pages in the website.','2026-01-05','','2026-01-05 18:04:27','2026-01-05 18:04:27'),(421,15,'Resumed campaign which had been paused for the holidays, and managed to do the eternity duplexes , grand premier rental and off plan in kirichwa road , however there was network issue so Joseph assistance was very helpful, a total of 23 leads had been rolled so far  today .','2026-01-05','','2026-01-05 18:06:17','2026-01-05 18:06:17'),(422,29,'Reported to work and joined the first meeting of the  year. After meeting, I finished up on some corrections for the Galaxy one video, then submitted.  I then designed two E card designs.','2026-01-05','','2026-01-05 18:31:27','2026-01-05 18:31:27'),(423,27,'1. Early morning BEKE meeting led by Joy and we schemed on how we are going to make 2026 our year by raking in more sales and rentals.\n2. Followed up with my OWN 6 personal leads:\nSuzzane, Shahid, Stacy, Halima, Ma Fahima, and Abdiaziz and from their enquiries they are hunting for apartments for sale and for rent in Westlands and Kileleshwa both for living in and for investment. Suzzane would like to view Shangri-la tomorrow and Abdiaziz would like to view Sunstone. I am following up on the same.\n3. We went for viewing of SOHAIL Gardens with Zhu Yi and Chairman as they are looking out for a Villa on its own compound sitting on 1/2 an acre. They would like to view more options today.\n4. Back to the office and followed up with my leads up to 8:15pm and I had to because there were hot leads.','2026-01-05','I wasn\'t able to write my report as I was handling a hot lead who wanted to view Villas in the afternoon.','2026-01-06 07:31:26','2026-01-06 07:31:26'),(424,13,'1.Paddy assisted to resize different photos using the dimensions given by the developer for the different landing pages, I then did a test using the resized photos and I had to delete them since they still weren\'t good enough they still appeared stretched , we have shared a new idea with the developer which will at least bring a positive change once he works on it as soon as possible. \n2. I added some data to the already created developers profiles, the process is  slow but I am trying my best to have data in all the already created profiles.\n3.I noticed some error problems on different pages and I communicated them to the developer and he sorted some, some are still pending but he promised to sort them soon, I will be pushing for the same.\n\n','2026-01-06','','2026-01-06 13:40:11','2026-01-06 13:40:11'),(425,24,'Held the morning meeting with the team where they requested for notebooks and an upgrade for the Internet. Also Brian managed to close on one client for Luminara.\nWent for a site visit at Luminara with a client for two 2Bedrooms.He will communicate by 8th Jan if he is going to make an offer or not.\nWent for another site visit at Kileleshwa 2.7acres JV with a client. The client liked the property and requested we shared the documents requested. Waiting for a proposal from the client,\nMade follow up calls to the clients in my CRM as updated.\n','2026-01-06','','2026-01-06 15:33:07','2026-01-06 15:33:07'),(426,20,'I had a viewing along Kilimani 8am with a client for the 1.6acre where the client liked but requested to consult to the other businesses partners where he will give feedback on Friday \nI later went for a viewing at Westland raphta road with the same client where we viewed 1acre and he liked but some documents were missing where he requested when the document are available to be informed \n12noon I held a meeting with a foreigner client where she was in need of a bank that can finance her in order to purchase a piece of land in Kenya,we consulted from cop bank where they agreed and requested the client to move on an identify the property where she will view tomorrow as I shared options ','2026-01-06','','2026-01-06 16:41:27','2026-01-06 16:41:27'),(427,17,'\n\n- Attended the morning meeting at the office at 8:35am and participated in discussions\n- Coordinated with  to prepare for monthly shoots, awaiting confirmation on project managers, scheduling due to team member still on holiday.\n- Collaborated with Paddy and Rashid to create three office videos, which were shared and posted on social media platforms to boost followers and engagement\n- Updated the leads Excel template and shared it on Beke Marketing and Beke Business groups for team access\n- Prepared and shared the morning meeting minutes on the Beke Business group for team reference\n\n\n','2026-01-06','','2026-01-06 16:59:16','2026-01-06 16:59:16'),(428,27,'1.Early morning BEKE staff meeting where we discussed about our hot leads, their offers, targets for the month, and our plans for today.\n2.Followed up on the specific sourcing of a stand alone house or a villa on 1/2 an acre for rent in Kileleshwa and Kilimani.\n3.Went for viewing with a client at Shangri-la apartments who was interested in a rental of either a1- or 2-bedroom for the purpose of setting up an air BnB unit.\n4.Went for sourcing in Dik Dik gardens in Lavington for the villa, but found none.\n5.Went for sourcing along Owashika road for the Villa, but found none.\n6.Back to the office to follow up on my allocated leads, but I was only able to follow up with three of them as I was time bound and the office had to be locked.','2026-01-06','A sale is coming through.','2026-01-06 17:04:05','2026-01-06 17:04:05'),(429,12,'\nToday, I successfully closed and sealed the deal for a Luminara Premium 1-bedroom unit after the client signed the sales agreement.\n\nI was assigned 10 new leads by the media team.\n\nMr. Wilmot showed strong interest in a 2-bedroom off-plan unit for investment purposes. He is comfortable with a completion timeline ending in 2028. I shared details of Luminara along with three additional suitable options.\n\nHilda, an agent, has a client seeking to purchase a 3-bedroom apartment in Kileleshwa or Lavington, with a budget of KES 25M.\n\n\nAdditionally, I followed up with previous clients. Most requested that we reconnect next week once they resume work.','2026-01-06','','2026-01-06 18:05:03','2026-01-06 18:05:03'),(430,15,'After the reset meeting in the morning, \nAssigned a total of 42 leads to the sales team for their persual , a clear spreadsheet will be shared by mia , \nPosted 4 post on Instagram, TikTok and Facebook all which are fun reels for the new year content.\nHad a session with the meta consultant for purposes of strategizing on the year an ensuring our targets for leads and content creation is met.','2026-01-06','','2026-01-06 18:12:39','2026-01-06 18:12:39'),(431,23,'Daily Work Report\nLeads Assigned:\nTotal of 11 leads assigned by Rashid\nLead Status Update:\n4 leads were responsive and require further follow-up\n7 leads pending engagement\nViewings & Client Updates:\nWilliam\nConfirmed a viewing scheduled for this weekend\nThe remaining 3 options are subject to follow-up\nEscada Viewing\nViewing conducted with June\nIssue: Unit is only available from 19th, while the client prefers immediate occupation\nClient to provide feedback tomorrow on the way forward\nWanja\nViewing scheduled for tomorrow, subject to morning confirmation\nClient is interested in Luminara\nNext Actions:\nFollow up with the 4 responsive leads\nConfirm Wanja’s viewing in the morning\nAwait June’s feedback regarding Escada\nFollow up on William’s remaining options','2026-01-06','','2026-01-06 18:13:22','2026-01-06 18:13:22'),(432,29,'After our morning team meeting, I designed two E-cards( one as product placement and another emphasis we are open and prompting bookings). We had three office video shoots point of view being first day back at the office after the holidays. I edited the clips and submitted by close of business.','2026-01-06','','2026-01-06 20:33:01','2026-01-06 20:33:01'),(433,13,'1. I participated in today\'s office shoot , which involved all the colleagues, after we had the morning meeting.\n2. I did a follow up with the developer since there were changes that needed to be made from yesterday, he has made a change on the sales landing page  so far it looks good the images are clearer since they are not stretched. He will do the same on the rest of the pages as well as agreed.\n3. I continued to add data to the already created developer profiles and I am about to complete then I can proceed to the suppliers and contractors as I receive data.\n4. Mia and I did some office duties  just to keep everything in order.','2026-01-07','Dennis and Carol got leads from the website which is a positive feedback, aiming to get more and more.','2026-01-07 13:44:19','2026-01-07 13:44:19'),(434,11,'Today, I attended the morning meeting chaired by Joy. Following the meeting, Rashid assigned me nine client leads, all of whom I contacted. Five clients were responsive, and I captured their feedback and status updates in the CRM.\n\nLater in the day, I went to Lavington to source townhouses for rent and identified two suitable options. These listings were shared with Diana for posting and also forwarded to the respective clients who are actively house-hunting.\n\nI then returned to the office to continue client follow-ups and ensure all interactions and updates were accurately logged in the CRM. ','2026-01-07','','2026-01-07 15:47:36','2026-01-07 15:47:36'),(435,24,'Held our morning meeting with the team. We discussed each one\'s schedule for the day.\nWent for my 1st viewing with the client at Kilimani for a rental at 9a.m.\nHeld my second meeting at Lavington with the Landowner and Developer for 1.8acres JV Property.\nMade calls to the new leads from tiktok that was shared by Rashid.\nMade follow up calls and messages to my previous clients.\nUpdated the CRM and weed out the cancelled deals.','2026-01-07','','2026-01-07 16:33:55','2026-01-07 16:33:55'),(436,17,'\n\n- Attended the morning meeting and actively participated in discussions, providing updates on ongoing projects and tasks\n- Prepared and shared the official meeting minutes on the Beke Business page for team reference and information\n- Collaborated with the sales and marketing team on an office shoot to create engaging content for social media and marketing purposes\n- Made significant progress on the 2-month shoot plan, ensuring timely execution and alignment with marketing objectives\n- Updated and shared the lead template on the Beke Marketing group, ensuring team access to current lead information and facilitating follow-up activities\n\n','2026-01-07','I will share the leads report tomorrow before close of business.','2026-01-07 16:58:20','2026-01-07 16:58:20'),(437,23,'Leads Assigned:\nReceived 6 leads from Rashid.\nLead Engagement:\n2 leads were responsive.\nClient Updates:\nJamal: Scheduled a viewing for Eternity Heights but has rescheduled it to Friday. He is also interested in duplex options within Kitisuru. All available options have been shared, and the viewing is planned for Friday.\nJenifer: Rescheduled the viewing of a 2-bedroom apartment in Lavington to tomorrow at 9:00 AM.\nSamuel: Expressed interest in Kitisuru duplexes and has scheduled a viewing for Saturday','2026-01-07','','2026-01-07 17:00:31','2026-01-07 17:00:31'),(439,15,'On behalf of the marketing department manager (Joseph) I picked on the TikTok business leads and managed to assign 42 leads to all sales people ,note that the leads are as from 30/12/2025 to today .\nMeta leads were 28 which were assigned equally to all sales team members .\nI had requested for the month of January marketing fee allocation through my team manager, which am still waiting on since as from tomorrow am unable to run ads .\nMyself together with paddy managed to engage in a session where we used 3 photos to make a giant grid In instagram.later I posted 1 engaging fun video.','2026-01-07','','2026-01-07 18:03:52','2026-01-07 18:03:52'),(440,27,'1.Early morning BEKE staff meeting where we discussed and strategised on our offers, along with the hot leads we are following up on and our targets for this month.\n2.I completed following up with all the leads I was allocated by Rashid for yesterday and today. They are yet to be updated in the CRM since I was away viewing with my leads the whole afternoon.\n3.Viewing with Khadija and her Aunt to Canto Apartments in Westlands, Pavo residence in Riverside, and Divine Suites in Riverside too. They liked the Riverside 1-bedroom option and they are going to put an offer tomorrow. Since Khadija’s aunt is heavily expectant, I had to pick them from their residence at Forest Green apartments in Ngara of Prof Wangari Maathai road.','2026-01-07','Pushing for a sale.','2026-01-07 18:47:58','2026-01-07 18:47:58'),(441,20,'10am I had a viewing with a client on a 0.7acres along kileleshwa where he liked the land and requested that his lawyer  will view to give the final word \nI went to kilimani to view a peace of land that is on market for lease  where he liked and requested for documents to do their search\nLater I viewed the 1.6 acres with a client where he liked where the other partners will view tomorrow and book an appointment with the lawyer ','2026-01-07','','2026-01-07 19:10:25','2026-01-07 19:10:25'),(442,12,'\n> Today, I followed up with Mr. Wilmot regarding the 2-bedroom unit he is looking to purchase for investment in Westlands. He mentioned that he will create time over the weekend for a viewing of the three options I shared with him.\n\nI also managed to reach Mr. David via a phone call. He is looking for a 3-bedroom unit in Lavington and is comfortable with an older, classic-style unit. We identified a suitable option shared by Desmond; however, the owner is currently away until next week. The client has expressed interest in viewing the unit once it becomes available.\n\nAdditionally, I was assigned seven leads today. One of them turned out to be very promising—a client looking for a 2-bedroom unit at Eternity Heights, to be financed through KCB Bank. I plan to follow up with her again tomorrow to confirm her availability for a viewing appointment.\n\n\n','2026-01-07','','2026-01-07 19:22:34','2026-01-07 19:22:34'),(443,29,'After our daily morning meeting, We did two office shoot with the team, point of view being emphasizing that we are back and another for a property video introduction. In the afternoon, Rashid and I posted three giant grid posts on instagram for Luminara. ','2026-01-07','','2026-01-08 02:41:32','2026-01-08 02:41:32'),(444,27,'1. Early morning BEKE staff team to work on our targets of closing this month.\n2. Followed up with the Emaar Residence apartments offer and I have been able to schedule a meeting on Monday next week with the owners.\n3. Followed on my 9 new leads as listed below:\nKishore	+254757636773	Rental	C	social	Kenya	Dennis Kimani	8 Jan 2026\nAustin Juma Townhouse	+254723855373	Villa	C	social	Kenya	Dennis Kimani	8 Jan 2026\nSharon Townhouse	+254790649207	Villa	C	social	Kenya	Dennis Kimani	8 Jan 2026\nIkay Townhouse	+254707174357	Villa	C	social	Kenya	Dennis Kimani	8 Jan 2026\nCharity 2Br Parklands	+254780684051	Apartment	B	social	Kenya	Dennis Kimani	8 Jan 2026\nOmwansa Ongeto Rental	+254721574225	Rental	C	social	Kenya	Dennis Kimani	8 Jan 2026\nRaj Kaloo Rental	+254707386587	Rental	C	social	Kenya	Dennis Kimani	8 Jan 2026\nMohamed Amin Rental	+254715627674	Rental	C	social	Kenya	Dennis Kimani	8 Jan 2026\nKhadija Abubakar	+254101121406	Apartment	B	website	Kenya	Dennis Kimani	8 Jan 2026\n4. They are serious leads looking out for rentals, and units to buy.\n5. Today, I spent my whole day in the office following up on my leads.\n6. Sourcing at Colosseum in Parklands.','2026-01-08','I am hopeful for a fruitful week.','2026-01-08 13:33:57','2026-01-08 13:33:57'),(445,13,'1. Today I attended a meeting together with Joseph the consultant and marketing department colleagues; we were brainstorming on new strategies we will be putting in place this month so that we can get more quality leads, increase followers on our different social media handles and also the website bringing in leads.\n2. I uploaded 2 projects for both sale and rent which I received from my colleagues today.\n3. I added data to two developer profiles that I had already created, I included the different projects they have done and also the different units in those various projects.\n4.I  followed up with the developer and reported some challenges which he has already sorted some and we are making a good progress. I will still follow up with those that are pending tomorrow.','2026-01-08','','2026-01-08 13:40:01','2026-01-08 13:40:01'),(446,17,'\n- Attended the morning general meeting and actively participated in discussions, providing updates on ongoing projects and tasks.\n- Prepared and shared the official meeting minutes on the Beke Business group for team reference and information.\n- Updated and shared the leads template on the Beke Marketing group, ensuring team access to current lead information and facilitating follow-up activities.\n- Attended the afternoon marketing team meeting to discuss January monthly shoots and social media strategy, contributing to the development of engaging content plans.\n- Key takeaways from the marketing meeting:\n    - Focus on showcasing investor-friendly projects, unique listings, and lifestyle content to enhance audience engagement.\n    - Prioritize educational content targeting investors looking to buy, aligning with business objectives.\n    - Strategically improve the company\'s social media presence through engaging and informative content, driving lead generation and brand awareness.\n\n','2026-01-08','','2026-01-08 17:20:24','2026-01-08 17:20:24'),(447,29,'Just after our daily morning team meeting, I did an E-card design and edited a Tilisi property video, submitted in the afternoon.','2026-01-08','','2026-01-08 17:25:55','2026-01-08 17:25:55'),(448,15,'Assigned 8 leads from meta and 2 leads for TikTok , lead rollout was low because I was waiting on the allocation of funds to the accounts that I could run new campaign for the month of January, this will happen from tomorrow because again the funds have been a located this evening by Mr Zhu Yi .\nHad a strategic meeting for resitting for the year and the month of January with the consultant caro and marketing department as a whole  I wrote the content of the Meeting down and I will be sharing after the consultant has adjusted on few things in it .\nPosted 1 video and 1 ecard from paddy on all social media platforms .','2026-01-08','Engaging with the consultant and setting up fresh new ad campaigns for the month of January.','2026-01-08 17:33:58','2026-01-08 17:33:58'),(449,23,'Daily Report Summary\n• Leads Assigned\nTwo (2) leads were assigned by Rashid. Both are pending follow-up to confirm property viewings over the weekend.\n• Client Meetings\nConducted two (2) physical meetings with two different clients.\n• Client Updates\n– Jenifer: Interested in Grand Premier for rental with the intention of setting it up as a BnB. Requested a follow-up tomorrow.\n– Jane: Viewed Valley Heights and showed interest in a three-bedroom rental. She will discuss with her husband and revert with feedback on the next steps','2026-01-08','','2026-01-08 18:49:05','2026-01-08 18:49:05'),(450,12,'I went for a viewing appointment with Mr Sam ,at Sunstone, unfortunately we didn\'t find a 3 br availability on sale ,but we\'re following up on one that the owner is considering to resale \nToday, I followed up with the seven clients assigned from TikTok leads.\n\nEvalyne is looking for a one-bedroom unit to rent and plans to move in within the next 20 days. I shared available options with her and will follow up tomorrow.\n\nSarah Kibe expressed interest in viewing the Kitisuru Eternity project. She requested that I call her on Monday to schedule a viewing appointment.\n\nNur Abdi mentioned that he is looking to purchase a penthouse in Riverside or Westlands. I shared an option located in General Mathenge and will follow up with him tomorrow.\n\nI followed up with Patricia, who confirmed that she is open to viewing Eternity Heights on Saturday.\n\nI also confirmed a viewing appointment with Mr. Kush for tomorrow at Muthangari Drive, where he will be viewing a three-bedroom unit for sale.','2026-01-08','','2026-01-08 19:40:50','2026-01-08 19:40:50'),(451,20,'I had 2 viewing today midmorning we Viewed with a client for 1 acre along raphta Westland which was booked last year where he booked a meeting with the owner next week  \nI viewed a property in kileleshwa with the lawyer of the buyer today where the client viewed yesterday which was about confirmation for the lawyer where he will meet the bank next week\nAfter viewing I made fallow up on my previous clients physically in their offices and most responded positively and requested','2026-01-08','','2026-01-08 19:41:18','2026-01-08 19:41:18'),(452,11,'I started my day at the office, where I chaired the morning meeting attended by the entire Beke team. During the meeting, we reviewed the clients each team member is currently handling, discussed their plans for the day, and followed up on progress toward their weekly goals.\n\nAt 11:00 Am, I attended a session with the marketing team. We discussed content ideas to be rolled out on our social media platforms, as well as strategies for marketing projects and running advertisements.\n\nAt 12:30 pm, I went for a site visit with a client, Zacharia, where we viewed several two-bedroom rental options. He expressed interest in one property, Zanzi Courts, but would still like to view additional options. I am therefore scheduled to meet him again tomorrow for further viewings.\n\nIn terms of leads, I received two clients today. However, both were unresponsive as their calls were not picked.','2026-01-08','','2026-01-08 20:39:04','2026-01-08 20:39:04'),(453,27,'1. Early morning BEKE Staff meeting chaired by Mr. Ken and Zhu Yi.\n2. Spent the whole day following with my A and B clients and pushing for site visits and it has resulted to three site visits tomorrow. For Eternity and Wilma','2026-01-09','My scheduled viewing for today was postponed to tomorrow.','2026-01-09 13:46:13','2026-01-09 13:46:13'),(454,13,'1. I uploaded  two projects  for sale, given to me by Dennis after I took his consent letter for approval and he provided the necessary details.\n2. I uploaded two contractors but the images are not yet displaying since they are still showing only the fallback images, I have spoken with the developer to sort the issue as soon as possible.\n3. I continued adding data to the developer profiles which still were incomplete only few are remaining.\n4 . I prepared excel sheet indicating suppliers and contractors requirements as requested by Mr Ken and shared with him.\n5.Mia and I assisted in restocking some of the office shopping  before they run out.','2026-01-09','','2026-01-09 13:57:55','2026-01-09 13:57:55'),(455,11,'I began the day with a morning meeting chaired by Mr. Ken and attended by the entire Beke team. \nAfter the meeting, I proceeded to Kileleshwa to take photos and videos of a stand alone house on Mandera road which i have shared with Leo and are interested in viewing it tomorrow at 9;30Am.\nI then proceeded to Westlands to meet my client, Mr. Sala, we had an appointment at 12 noon where we viewed Diplomat Residence. The client did not prefer the project and requested to explore alternative options.\n\nI later returned to the office and focused on client follow-ups. I made over 10 calls to pending clients and updated the CRM with feedback from the responsive contacts which are 5. (From the calls i made i have managed to get one viewing for tomorrow.','2026-01-09','aiming to close 2 deals this month','2026-01-09 15:11:14','2026-01-09 15:11:14'),(456,24,'8/1/2025\nStarted my morning meeting at Mirage 8a.m with HK Developers for pre-proposal presentation. \nProceeded to meeting with the land owner for 11acres Limuru Road and HK Developers at 9a.m in Aspire for final presentation of the project, the landowner requested for a few clauses to be changed on the NDA in our last meeting on 13th Jan Tuesday.\nWent for another meeting in Lavington with the Developer of 1.8acres and landowner at 11a.m. The landowner requested for a POF from the Developer which will be presented in the next meeting on 13th Jan Monday.\nMet with the Developer for Two Rivers 30acres at 2p.m. where the Developer verified the documents of the land and presented his proposal but it was turned down by the Landowner and he was adviced to make changes before the next meeting on 20th Jan.\n\n9/1/2026\nHad a site visit with a client at 8.30a.m where he like the property but the price is too high. The landowner adviced him to table his offer his to give a chance for negotiations to begin. \nHeld a meeting with the client in the office for the Muthithi Road property and gave an offer for 490Million but it was declined. However he requested for a sitdown with the land owner to start the negotiations. Meeting on Monday 2pm to discuss further.\nHeld a meeting with agents with various properties that they shared and organized for viewing on 13th  Jan.\nMade follow up calls to various clients and leads shared by Rashid.\nTook a client to view Muthithi 42 possible JV Option. Client requested for a meeting on 10th Jan  with  the landowner.\nWorked on the CRM to fill in the new clients and update customer follow up list.\n\n','2026-01-09','','2026-01-09 15:26:48','2026-01-09 15:26:48'),(457,15,'No leads as the strategy in place aims at running new fresh campaigns as from Monday after every sales team has input and evaluated the pending leads that have been assigned this week\nPosted two content from paddy \nDid a report on the previous month report concerning lead generation and ads spend for both TikTok and meta ads ','2026-01-09','Aligning every content for the purpose of next week advertisements and campaigns.','2026-01-09 17:59:14','2026-01-09 17:59:14'),(458,17,'\n- Attended and wrote morning meeting minutes, sharing them with the team for reference\n- Compiled and submitted a two-month shoot plan for January and February 2026 for review\n- Updated and shared the leads template with Mr. Ken Huang\n\nKey Highlights:\n- Meeting minutes were shared with the team, ensuring everyone is informed about discussions and action items\n- The two-month shoot plan outlines key objectives and strategies for the upcoming period\n- Leads template has been updated to reflect current sales pipeline and opportunities\n\nNext Steps:\n-The review of the two-month shoot plan was approved ready for execution.\n- Continue to update and share leads template with the team\n- Prepare for upcoming meetings and presentations as required.','2026-01-09','','2026-01-09 18:15:56','2026-01-09 18:15:56'),(459,17,'\n- Attended and wrote morning meeting minutes, sharing them with the team for reference\n- Compiled and submitted a two-month shoot plan for January and February 2026 for review\n- Updated and shared the leads template with Mr. Ken Huang\n\nKey Highlights:\n- Meeting minutes were shared with the team, ensuring everyone is informed about discussions and action items\n- The two-month shoot plan outlines key objectives and strategies for the upcoming period\n- Leads template has been updated to reflect current sales pipeline and opportunities\n\nNext Steps:\n-The review of the two-month shoot plan was approved ready for execution.\n- Continue to update and share leads template with the team\n- Prepare for upcoming meetings and presentations as required.','2026-01-09','','2026-01-09 18:15:58','2026-01-09 18:15:58'),(460,29,'Today we had our General Meeting on Mr Ken\'s arrival. After which I delved into creating a template Brian, sales person of the month. Afterwards I came up with a caroussel design for Events in westlands for those who just landed in the area. In the afternoon I tried coming up with an educative reel and submitted by end of day.','2026-01-09','','2026-01-09 19:07:24','2026-01-09 19:07:24'),(461,20,'I attended a meeting with the client and the lawyer who holds the document of the 1.6acres along kilimani where the meeting took 2.5h on discussion about the land where the missing documents should be available in the next meeting \nLater I went viewing for a land that client made an enquiry on where I viewed and held a meeting with the owner where we agreed on terms and organise for a viewing with the client next week \nLater I made my call fallow up on my previous clients where most of them responded positively and give next week appointment ','2026-01-09','','2026-01-09 19:19:43','2026-01-09 19:19:43'),(462,12,'\nToday, I followed up with my previously assigned leads.\n\nI spoke with Patricia, who expressed strong interest in the Kitisuru Eternity Heights project. She confirmed that she will be available for a site viewing tomorrow.\n\nI also followed up with Evelyn, who is looking for a 1-bedroom unit to let. She mentioned that she will be available for viewing on Monday next week.\n\nAdditionally, I contacted Mr. Nangval, a friend of Mr. Christian, who recently purchased a Luminara 1-bedroom unit. Mr. Nangval will be arriving in Kenya over the weekend, after which we plan to visit Luminara to discuss his potential purchase.\n\nI also worked on updating my CRM, ensuring that all pending clients and follow-up statuses are up to date','2026-01-09','','2026-01-09 19:55:07','2026-01-09 19:55:07'),(463,20,'I had a viewing with a client along forest road where the client viewed and liked  the plot where he booked  a meeting with the land owner \nLater I had a meeting with the advocate and the client where they agreed on terms to pay for the 1.6acres where the client will give feedback on next week ','2026-01-10','','2026-01-10 18:22:28','2026-01-10 18:22:28'),(464,29,'After our mrning team meeting,I came up with a text based educational reel content and submitted by 1pm','2026-01-10','','2026-01-11 03:43:48','2026-01-11 03:43:48'),(465,12,'\nWeekly Activity Report\n\nThis week, I successfully sourced one new property: Cheval, located in Riverside, Westlands.\n\nI also followed up with previous clients from last year who had pending inquiries. In total, I followed up with 10 clients, out of whom 5 responded.\n\nNina mentioned she will be back in February to proceed with her search for a residential one-bedroom unit.\n\nI followed up with Mitchell, who confirmed she will be available from next week to view Luminara.\n\nI also followed up with Nicholas, who had shown interest in Luminara and requested a price update.\n\nMr. Kush scheduled a viewing appointment for Wednesday this week.\n\n\nAdditionally, I was assigned 18 new leads, of which 8 were responsive.\n\nSarah, Evalyne, and Francis were very positive and scheduled viewing appointments for next week.\n\n\nI conducted two viewing appointments during the week:\n\nOne at Luminara, where the client later referred a friend whom I am currently following up with.\n\nAnother at Sunstone, General Mathenge, with a client who was interested in purchasing a two-bedroom unit.\n\n\nI am also working closely with Mr. Christian’s friend, who has shown strong interest in purchasing a unit at Luminara.','2026-01-11','','2026-01-11 19:13:11','2026-01-11 19:13:11'),(466,23,'Lead Generation & Assignment\nTotal leads assigned: 35\nMeta leads: 35 (assigned by Rashid)\nTikTok leads: 9 (included in overall follow-ups)\nClient Engagement & Meetings\nPhysical meetings conducted: 4\n3 rental viewings\n1 sale viewing\nAll clients viewed properties on-site and follow-ups are ongoing.\nActive Client Follow-Ups\nMichelle\nRequirement: 2-bedroom apartment to buy\nLocation: Lavington\nStatus: Viewed 2 options; still under active follow-up\nJune\nRequirement: Furnished 2-bedroom to rent\nLocation: Westlands\nStatus: Option shared; availability from 19th January\nJenifer\nRequirement: 2-bedroom to rent for BnB setup\nStatus: Requested time to consider; follow-up pending\nBol\nRequirement: 3-bedroom to rent\nLocation: Lavington\nBudget: Ksh 100,000\nStatus: Options shared; active follow-up ongoing\nPrevious Leads – Ongoing Follow-Ups\nMina\nInterest: Luminara purchase for investment\nStatus: Will commit upon return to Nairobi in February\nIshane\nInterest: Luminara purchase\nStatus: Currently selling property in Türkiye; will proceed once funds are available\nOverall Status\nContinuous follow-ups ongoing with all active and previous leads\nFocus remains on nurturing prospects and securing closings in the coming weeks','2026-01-11','','2026-01-11 20:08:52','2026-01-11 20:08:52'),(468,13,'1. I was able to upload 3 projects, 1 for sale from Yoki and 2 for rental from Carol and Dennis, I still have others to upload once I have all the information, my colleagues promised to submit them by tomorrow.\n2.I was able to upload 1 contractor and 1 supplier, the supplier part is not yet complete as some data is still missing hopefully I will be able to trace them soon.\n3.I  was sent by Mr Yi to the DTB bank at GTC as the riders could not be able to drop the parcel as the process of getting into the building was hectic to them.\n4. I got in touch with the developers team as they needed to make some small changes, I did follow ups on the same  there are still some small changes being made. ','2026-01-12','','2026-01-12 14:03:34','2026-01-12 14:03:34'),(469,27,'1. Early morning BEKE staff meeting and we discussed on ways to improve our sales and some steps we should take to achieve sales. I came in late today and paid my Kshs100 bob fine.\n2. Followed up with my leads who required the project details that they are interested in and that to them.\n3. Went to Emaar\'s Consult office to link up Sam and Joyce to Hassan and Amina on the offer and the documents required to take a mortgage on. The meeting went on well and all was agreed upon and now what is left is if a mortgage facility would be accepted.\n4. Back to the office and followed up on the following 6 leads:\nGerald 3Br Riverside	+254736635699	Apartment	C	social	Kenya	Dennis Kimani	12 Jan 2026\nJulien Cameroon	+254111506272	Apartment	C	social	Kenya	Dennis Kimani	12 Jan 2026\nChidam	+254721830007	Apartment	C	social	Kenya	Dennis Kimani	12 Jan 2026\nJerusha Shiru Eternity	+254705020997	Apartment	C	social	Kenya	Dennis Kimani	12 Jan 2026\nAlbi Awuor 3Br	+254711623040	Apartment	C	social	Kenya	Dennis Kimani	12 Jan 2026\nJoseph Kabai 2Br	+254781564099	Apartment	C	social	Kenya	Dennis Kimani	12 Jan 2026\nI have reached out to all of them and shared their respective project details.','2026-01-12','All is good especially with the hot leads we are getting from Rashid.','2026-01-12 15:56:53','2026-01-12 15:56:53'),(470,15,'Assigned 34 leads to the sales team this included 13 leads for tigoni and runda land which were also assigned to joy for he persual .\nAccompanied paddy and mia to two shoots thats in amberbay and oasis metricom \nHad an early meeting with the meta consultant to this was aimed to see the quality of leads that flowed during the weekend that is on Sunday .','2026-01-12','','2026-01-12 17:44:49','2026-01-12 17:44:49'),(471,20,'I  managed to have 1 viewing with a client along raphta road where he viewed and liked the plot and requested the bank withholding the document to arrange a meeting next week \nThe rest of the time I was in the office making call follow up on my clients ','2026-01-12','','2026-01-12 18:50:56','2026-01-12 18:50:56'),(472,24,'Held an interview with one potential employee named Rosemary.\nMade introduction calls to the leads shared by Rashid.\nHeld a meeting with Mr.Danish to discuss the progress of the Westlands 57 JV Opportunity and other new properties in the market.\nHeld another meeting with Mr.Vincent for Ahead Architects to discuss various prime properties he has in which he \nshared the write up for each on email.\nLeft the office at 4.20pm for a site visit with my client, Mr.Felix together with his wife where they also shared their details to be addressed in the offer letter.','2026-01-12','','2026-01-12 19:09:02','2026-01-12 19:09:02'),(473,29,'After our Monday morning meeting, we headed to metricon Oasis in Lavington for a shoot. Later on in the afternoon we proceeded to Amber Ray ,still in Lavington.','2026-01-12','','2026-01-12 19:33:23','2026-01-12 19:33:23'),(474,12,'\n\n> Daily Activity Report\n\nToday, I conducted two site visits.\n\nThe first client viewed Riverside One, Marina Bay, and Dolce Vita. She showed strong interest in the 2-bedroom unit for sale at Riverside One, which stood out as her preferred option.\n\nThe second client viewed a 1-bedroom unit for rent at 108 Riverside. However, she did not like the unit due to an upcoming construction project in the vicinity.\n\nI also delegated a viewing to Carol for Mr. Francis, who is looking to purchase a 2-bedroom unit on mortgage. He viewed Eternity Heights in Kitisuru.\n\nAdditionally, I was assigned six new leads. As I spent most of the day out of the office attending site visits, I will follow up with these leads during the morning hours tomorrow.','2026-01-12','','2026-01-12 19:44:49','2026-01-12 19:44:49'),(475,17,'Attended the morning meeting.\nleft the office at 11am headed to oasis metricon project in lavington for a shoot, then later headed to Amber bay project also in Lavington at 15;10pm for another shoot then left at 4;30pm and headed home.','2026-01-12','','2026-01-12 19:56:21','2026-01-12 19:56:21'),(476,23,'Daily Work Report\nLeads Assigned:\n5 leads assigned by Rashid\n1 lead responsive\n4 leads pending follow-up\nActive Lead:\nClient Name: Mariam Hussein\nRequirement: 2-bedroom apartment at Marina Bay\nAction Taken: Shared full property details\nClient Concern: Master bedroom does not have a balcony\nStatus: Client is still interested in viewing Marina Bay within the week; viewing date to be confirmed\nViewings Conducted:\nClient Name: Hibo (previous lead)\nRequirement: 2-bedroom apartment along Riverside\nViewing Done: Riverside 1 – 2-bedroom apartment priced at 18M\nClient Feedback: Interested in viewing more options\nNext Step: Awaiting confirmation of availability for additional viewings','2026-01-12','','2026-01-12 20:39:59','2026-01-12 20:39:59'),(477,13,'1.I was able to add two more suppliers, I created their profiles and added some data too, I  also contacted 1 service provider from Musa to explain to them about the information required for them to be uploaded on the website. He Promised  to get back.\n2.Paddy assisted to resize some logos that I will be using to upload suppliers tomorrow as I was not able to do much in the afternoon since the network was unstable.\n3. I  received a project from Carol but I did not upload it since the photos were not good enough, she has requested for better photos which she will share once she gets them.\n4.  I replaced photos of  2 previous projects with the ones that Paddy took yesterday when they went to the field: Oasis Metricom and Amber bay the photos for these projects are now of good quality.\n','2026-01-13','There is some progress so far in regards to the  website data. ','2026-01-13 13:29:19','2026-01-13 13:29:19'),(478,27,'1. Early morning BEKE meeting with all the staff members and talked about our workplan for today and the offers we currently are pursuing.\n\n2. I reached out to my leads that I was allocated by Rashid and BEKE yesterday, and who are already in the CRM, and shared with them the projects of their interest. One of the leads is interested in an apartment in Riverside of 3-bedroom. He will view it on Friday.\n\n3. Followed up with the following leads that I was allocated today by Rashid:\n1. Johnson Adeyemo - Is interested in Eternity apartments in Kitisuru, a 2-bedroom apartment.\n2. Nitin - Who is interested in an apartment in Riverside.\n\nI have also shared their respective projects with them and waiting for a scheduled viewing with them.\n\n4. I was able to bring YURI, the developer of AMTO and MORVARA apartments in Westlands and they met Mr. Ken and had a chat on how we can partner in selling their units.','2026-01-13','All is going on well.','2026-01-13 13:38:23','2026-01-13 13:38:23'),(479,23,'Daily Work Report\nLeads Assigned:\nReceived 2 leads from Rashid: Shiv and Paul\nLead Updates:\nPaul: Interested in Eternity. Scheduled for a site viewing on Saturday at 10:00 AM.\nShiv: Foreign client. Communication done via WhatsApp; currently awaiting response.\nFollow-ups:\nCompleted 6 follow-up calls with clients.\nClient Requirements & Progress:\nDr. Prableen: Looking for a villa for rent in Kitisuru or Loresho. Still sourcing suitable options.\nMark: Searching for a commercial space with a KES 140,000 budget to set up an IT training institution.\nIdentified 2 suitable options.\nScheduled to view them tomorrow and will share photos and details prior to the client viewing.\nOverall Status:\nLead engagement ongoing.\nViewings scheduled and property sourcing in progress','2026-01-13','','2026-01-13 16:51:08','2026-01-13 16:51:08'),(480,15,'Assigned 17 leads to the sales team , 9 leads  were leads for land this ensures that the lands sales department are also having inquiries for the land properties they have .\nHad a session with Joseph the consultant as usual to give insights on the current trends in marketing and to give feedback on the leads report for the sales department and make necessary adjustments \nSubmit emails to caro for applicants in the sales position.\nPosted 2 videos from paddy , in all our social media handles ','2026-01-13','','2026-01-13 17:05:55','2026-01-13 17:05:55'),(481,17,'\n\n\n\nTASKS COMPLETED\n\n- Attended the morning meeting at the office and participated in discussions\n- Wrote and shared meeting minutes for January 12th and 13th, 2026, on the Beke business group\n- Updated and submitted the leads template for January 12th and 13th with Mr. Ken Huang\n- Prepared content for upcoming shoots:\n    - Wrote two scripts for tomorrow\'s shoot (Lavington and Kileleshwa locations)\n    - Created hooks for tomorrow\'s videos.\n- Prepared for tomorrow\'s shoot:-\n    - Finalized two scripts and hooks \n    - Coordinate with team members on the type of videos we will do tomorrow.\n','2026-01-13','','2026-01-13 19:01:43','2026-01-13 19:01:43'),(482,24,'Held an interview with one sales lady.\nDid a Site visit with a client in Lavington at 11a.m JV Opportunity where the land owner requested for a  60/40 sharing ratio but the client was offering 30/70. I gave the Developer a different property to consider.\n Took a client to site visit at Two Rivers 30acres JV Opportunity. The client gave the  ammended proposal and it was accepted. Waiting for the land documents and negotiations regarding the upfront amount of 600Million to conclude before we proceed. \nTook another client to Two Rivers for a Buy off of 5acres, since they are buying to put up apartments, they requested for official approvals from the county government regarding the height limit.\nSite visit to Coptica Godowns with a client looking for one to buy. They didnt have a purchase option so I shared ones along Eastern Bypass to be considered.','2026-01-13','','2026-01-13 19:20:12','2026-01-13 19:20:12'),(483,20,'I held a viewing with a developer along Waiyaki way where he liked the plot and hold a meeting with  the land owner where the legal documents were missing where he requested for the legal documents for the next meeting \nI later held a meeting with 3 brothers  owning a peace of land on parklands where it took long to convince 1 of the brothers to sale where 2 had confirmed they need to sale but no mutual agreement,we will be back once they agreed all and the client was ready to pay ','2026-01-13','','2026-01-13 19:21:27','2026-01-13 19:21:27'),(484,11,'The day began with a morning meeting, which I chaired. Immediately after the meeting, I conducted an interview together with Joy for a prospective candidate to join the land sales team.\n\nFollowing the interview, I attended a property viewing in Kitisuru with Brian’s client, Francis. The client expressed interest in the house and liked the property. However, his key requirement is a blue zone area, as the purchase is intended for investment targeting expatriates. The agreed next step is to share additional suitable options. The client is available for further viewings on Saturday.\n\nLater in the day, I attended another viewing in Kileleshwa with the Nanchong Group, where Mr. Chairman revisited a house previously viewed on Saturday. We are currently awaiting feedback from the property owner. Communication is ongoing with the owner’s son, who indicated that his mother is the final decision-maker. She is currently out of the country, and we are awaiting her approval.\n\nI returned to the office thereafter, marking the end of the day’s physical engagements.\n\nAdditionally, I received four client referrals from Rashid. I contacted all four clients and captured their feedback in the CRM.','2026-01-12','','2026-01-13 20:51:06','2026-01-13 20:51:06'),(485,11,'I started my morning with the Beke team’s morning meeting, where we aligned on ongoing tasks and priorities for the day.\n\nAfter the meeting, I conducted an interview with a candidate, Mercy, who had applied for the sales agent position. The discussion went well; however, she requested additional time to consider the opportunity. A final decision on her engagement is still pending.\n\nLater in the day, I went to Escada, Westlands, to conduct a site viewing on behalf of a US-based client who is currently out of the country. I took detailed videos of the property and shared them with the client for review.\n\nI then returned to the office, where I spent most of the afternoon sourcing and sharing property options for clients with pending requests. I also followed up on new leads received during the day.\n\nToday, I received two leads from Rashid. Unfortunately, both leads were not responsive: one phone was switched off, while the second lead requested project details, which I shared, but there has been no response so far. All lead interactions and follow-ups were duly captured in the CRM system.','2026-01-13','','2026-01-13 20:59:47','2026-01-13 20:59:47'),(486,29,'- Attended the Morning team meeting.\n- Submitted a talking video of Mia at Oasis Metricon in Lavington apartments.\n- I edited a carousell for a 1 bedroom in Oasis Metricon.\n- I edited a behind the scene video of walking our audience through luxury. Submitted in the afternoon.\n- I started on a property video for a 1 bedroom Oasis Metricon to be delivered tomorrow.','2026-01-13','','2026-01-14 02:37:16','2026-01-14 02:37:16'),(488,29,'- Attended the morning team meeting which ended by 9\n- We then proceeded to Amani residence to do an off plan shoot with Mia.\n- In the afternoon we joined Rashid for an ground breaking event at Berkeley Homes in Kileleshwa that we were invited to.','2026-01-14','','2026-01-14 14:25:18','2026-01-14 14:25:18'),(489,23,'Daily Work Report\nReceived 1 lead assigned by Rashid. Contacted the client (Lulu), but the call was not answered.\nConducted a site visit in Lower Kabete in the morning for a 4-bedroom house valued at KES 20M. Performed a virtual viewing with a client, Ustav. The client expressed interest and plans to schedule a physical viewing over the weekend.\nSourced a new project in Kileleshwa, Berkeley Apartments, located along Oloitoktok Road. The project offers studio, 1-bedroom, and 2-bedroom units and is currently at the groundbreaking stage. One client was scheduled to attend the ground breaking event but requested to reschedule.\n','2026-01-14','','2026-01-14 14:31:24','2026-01-14 14:31:24'),(490,15,'In the morning we had a meeting with the consultant about how and the script for shooting off plan projects which we will be using tomorrow for the off plan projects campaign\n\nassigned 16 leads to the sales team , 8 leads were leads for land which were shared to joy and the rest of the leads assigned equally to the property sales team. There is need ad creatives for off plan projects which is to be used for the January marketing and so in that regard paddy and Mia went to Amani residence in ring roads Westland\'s and later joined me to Berkeley apartments launch along oloitoktok road in kileleshwa with units starting from 3.99M and could be ideal for marketing in January.\n\nlater posted 1 ecard as shared by paddy . ','2026-01-14','','2026-01-14 14:32:51','2026-01-14 14:32:51'),(491,12,' Today, early in the morning, I managed to call the clients who were assigned to me previously, as I was unable to report to work yesterday.\n\nMr. Charles scheduled a viewing appointment for the options I shared with him in Westlands. He mentioned that he will create time either tomorrow or on Friday.\n\nI also followed up with Sarah, who had previously viewed a two-bedroom apartment for sale in Kitusuru.\n\nAdditionally, I contacted Mr. Charles, who is looking to purchase a townhouse in Lavington. I shared nine suitable options with him, and he mentioned that he will create time next week for a viewing appointment.\n\nI also spoke with Mr. Skyn, who has scheduled a viewing for Eternity Heights in Kitusuru next week.\n\n','2026-01-14','','2026-01-14 14:40:55','2026-01-14 14:40:55'),(492,27,'1. Early morning BEKE staff meeting where we discussed about our today\'s workplan and the targets we have to meet this week. We also discussed about our hot offers that we are able to close this week.\n2. Shared more of the project details to the leads who had picked a project of interest from our listings and wanted more information on them. I also called and followed up with 2 leads (Christine and Maureen) that I was allocated by Rashid and one of them, Maureen, would like to view Eternity this Saturday.\n3. Attended the groundbreaking ceremony for Berkeley apartments in Kileleshwa, and thereafter, waited for my own personal leads whom I had invited to come and buy the studios and the other apartments available. They apologized for not showing up because it too soon. They postponed to next week.\n4. Came back to the office and followed up on my pending offers from my leads, and especially, Sam and Joyce, whose offer has finally been accepted, and they will send the offer to Emaar Consult tomorrow.','2026-01-14','All is well for now.','2026-01-14 14:56:01','2026-01-14 14:56:01'),(493,46,'-Attended the office morning   meeting  at 8:35.\n-went for viewing of a land parcel in Lowerkabete with Desmond at 10:35 (I\n-I was taken through the orientation of crm system by Diana.\n','2026-01-14','Greatful for the platform and hope to exceed  sales expectations .','2026-01-14 15:02:22','2026-01-14 15:02:22'),(494,17,'\nEXECUTIVE SUMMARY.\nThis report outlines the tasks completed, including attending the morning meeting, sharing meeting minutes, updating the leads template, and conducting property shoots.\nTASKS COMPLETED.\n- Attended the morning meeting and participated in discussions\n- Wrote and shared the minutes on the Beke business group\n- Updated the leads template:\n    - Received 3 TikTok leads and 13 Facebook leads, totaling 16 leads\n    - Leads were distributed as follows:\n        - Joy: 8 leads (land)\n        - Caro: 2 leads\n        - Dennis: 2 leads\n        - Brian: 2 leads\n        - Desmond: 2 leads\n    - Categories of each lead were indicated  on the Excel sheet to be submitted to Mr. Ken Huang.\n- Left the office at 11:30 am and proceeded to Parklands for a property shoot called Amani Residency with Mr. Paddy\n- Conducted shoot and received project details:\n    - Amani Residency is a unique project targeting residential clients and families seeking spacious homes\n    - Project prices and details documented for promotion purposes.\n- At 2:15 pm, headed to Loitoktok road for the launch of a new project called Berkley\n- Berkeley project details:\n    - Targeting investors with affordable prices and accessible location\n    - Project will be promoted to clients as a more affordable option for investors seeking affordable housing with high returns on investments.\nNOTES.\n- Amani Residency shoot aimed to showcase the project\'s unique features for residential clients and families \n- Berkley project launch targets investors with affordable and accessible units for investment.\n- Videos will be edited and submitted by Mr. Paddy tomorrow as expected tomorrow at the close of business.','2026-01-14','','2026-01-14 15:37:07','2026-01-14 15:37:07'),(495,11,'The day began with a morning meeting chaired by Joy, attended by the entire team. \nFollowing the meeting, I conducted two interviews together with Joy for candidates interested in joining the sales department.\n\nLater in the day, I carried out a land viewing in Runda for a property we are currently advertising. The client is very serious and is specifically looking for a 0.5-acre plot in Runda, with a budget ranging between KES 55 million and KES 60 million. We viewed three different options, and the client expressed interest but requested to see additional options. A follow-up viewing has been scheduled for tomorrow at 9:30 a.m., and I also spent some time in Runda looking for options and i have already prepared more suitable options for consideration.\n\nAdditionally, I followed up with all the clients assigned to me today by Rashid and ensured that all client details and interactions were properly captured and updated in the CRM system.','2026-01-14','Still working on a closure ','2026-01-14 15:40:11','2026-01-14 15:40:11'),(496,13,'1.I was able to create 6 suppliers profiles, I was copying from Alibaba, the alibaba website has photos in a different format, AVIF which I still need to convert to JPG before I can use them on our website. Other information cannot be copy pasted direct, I still need to type manually due to the format used.\n2.I had a challenge uploading the product information, the developer still needed to sort the issue so that I  could proceed, he promised to sort the issue as soon as possible so that I can continue.\n3.I assisted the new staff to understand the CRM since she will be required to use it everyday, I also created an account for her after her company email was shared to me by Mr Ken.\n4.I received some listings from my colleagues but I was not able to upload them as I was still working on the suppliers part. I will upload them tomorrow.\n','2026-01-14','Tring my best to achieve my target for this week.','2026-01-14 17:03:14','2026-01-14 17:03:14'),(497,24,'Held the morning meeting with the team.\nConducted two and interviews but none were successful due to lack of experience.\nAssisted the new team member to settle in.\nOrganized for the properties to be viewed by Carol\'s client.\nMade calls to the 36leads shared for Tigoni. Organized for viewing on Saturday with the six clients that have confirmed viewing.\nSourced various properties for other enquiries from the leads shared,\nWent for sourcing 0.5acres at Parklands for sale for a potential client.\n','2026-01-14','','2026-01-14 18:26:02','2026-01-14 18:26:02'),(498,15,'Assigned 14 leads to the sales team , 7 leads were leads for land which were assigned to the lands sales department and the remaining seven leads were assigned to the property sales team .\nposted  2 videos and 1 e card from paddy after editing  them .\nAs from 10am we we having a session with the consultant and the main focus was to increase the number of quality of our leads and at the same time ensuring that the target for our daily leads is met, and in that regard we launched one campaign which had 3 ad creatives so that the goal can be achieved .\nlater we had a meeting with Mr. haung which we were trying to discuss how we can improve the quality of our content by adding more favorable equipment. \n\n','2026-01-15','','2026-01-15 13:37:27','2026-01-15 13:37:27'),(499,12,'\nDaily Report\n\nToday, I mainly focused on following up with previous clients.\n\nFollowing the rescheduling of a viewing appointment by Mr. Charles to tomorrow due to work commitments, I carried out extensive follow-ups with several clients:\n\nI followed up with Mr. David, who is looking for an old-fashioned 3-bedroom unit in Lavington. He mentioned that he will be available for viewing next week.\n\nI followed up with Mr. Wilmot, who is interested in purchasing a 2-bedroom unit at Eternity Heights. He informed me that he is currently attending a funeral and will proceed with the acquisition once he is settled.\n\nI followed up with Sarah, who viewed Eternity Heights yesterday. She mentioned that she is discussing the proposal with her husband, after which they will make a purchasing decision.\n\nI followed up with Francis, who is looking to buy a 2-bedroom unit through a mortgage arrangement. He confirmed availability for viewing the three sourced options on Saturday.\n\nI was assigned a new client, Emily, who is looking for a 3-bedroom unit to buy along Wangige–Getathuru Road. I am yet to source suitable options.','2026-01-15','','2026-01-15 13:54:04','2026-01-15 13:54:04'),(500,13,'1. I attended our daily  morning meeting, where we shared our plan for the day and what we achieved yesterday.\n2.I  assisted Mia understand the process of uploading product information, how to get the photos and also their details so that she can assist as agreed.\n3.I created 2 supplier profiles from Alibaba, others I  still needed Paddy to assist me resize the logos before I can use them, he was busy but he promised to assist ,I have given him the ones he needs to resize.\n4.I uploaded 1  rental project .','2026-01-15','','2026-01-15 13:59:51','2026-01-15 13:59:51'),(501,29,'- Attended the morning team meeting.\n- I submitted a video of Berkeley homes. (off-plan)\n- I edited a video showcasing snippets of the ground breaking ceremony.\n- I edited a video for Amani residence (off -plan)','2026-01-15','','2026-01-15 14:08:21','2026-01-15 14:08:21'),(502,27,'1. Early morning BEKE staff meeting and we discussed about our yesterday\'s work that we did, and our plans for today.\n2. I had 2 viewings scheduled for today, by Dishon for the Syokimau Villa and Khadija for Elite and Divine residence but they both postponed to a later date.\n3. I had to follow up with all my leads for this week and schedule viewings for tomorrow and Saturday and succeeded in getting two for tomorrow, that is, Gerald for riverdrift apartments in Riverside, and Khadija for Nandwa Ivy and Blossom Ivy. For Saturday; Chidam and Julius for Marina Bay and Eternity respectively. \n4. Today, I also followed up on three leads that I was allocated today.','2026-01-15','All is well.','2026-01-15 14:10:51','2026-01-15 14:10:51'),(503,11,'I started the day by attending the marketing morning meeting to review ongoing marketing efforts and priorities. After the meeting, I followed up on two charts that had been assigned to me by Rashid to ensure progress and alignment.\n\nAt 11:30 a.m., I went to Kilimani to source rental properties for the Nanchuan Group. I identified three potential options; however, after discussions with the respective property owners, none of them agreed to the intended use of the houses by the Nanchuan Group. As a result, no suitable option was secured and further sourcing is required.\n\nLater in the day, I held individual meetings with team members to assess mid-month performance, progress, and their goals for the remainder of the month.\n\nDesmond shared that he currently has four serious clients he is actively engaging. Some of these clients are interested in land, two are interested in Luminara and one client is looking for a two-bedroom apartment for sale, and another is searching for villas along Kiambu Road.\n\n Dennis mentioned that approximately 70% of his leads are responsive. For this month, he has two clients who are actively converting. One is Sam, who is interested in the Emaar Project and has already submitted an offer and completed the booking form, with feedback pending from the developer. The second is Gerald, who is looking for a three-bedroom apartment with a budget of KSh 20 million. In addition, Dennis has two more clients searching for furnished apartments, bringing his total active clients for the month to four. His main challenge has been the availability of suitable options for his clients.\n\nBrian reported that he currently has four hot clients: Anastasia, Nandabi, David, and Sarah. Sarah is interested in Eternity Heights, David is looking for an older three-bedroom apartment, Nandabi is interested in Luminara and was referred by a previous buyer, and Anastasia is looking for a two-bedroom apartment that is ready or close to completion. He noted that about 80% of his leads are responsive, and approximately 40% convert into physical viewings.\n\nBased on this information, I will continue closely following up with each team member and their respective clients, while supporting them in sourcing suitable options, with the goal of closing at least one deal each before the end of the month.','2026-01-15','Ensure at least one deal is closed before the end of the month by the team. ','2026-01-15 14:52:25','2026-01-15 14:52:25'),(504,24,'Held the morning meeting with the team where we shared the daily schedules.\nUpdated potential clients to the CRM.\nHeld a meeting with the agent of HK Developers to discuss the NDA Agreement between him and Beke.\nCalled 8leads shared today by Rashid and followed up on yesterday\'s six unaswered calls.\nPlanned for tomorrow site visit to Tigoni.\nWorked in the CRM for my previous clients.\nWent for a site visit on with Nanchong Team 3properties but they liked only one on Muchai Drive, a JV option. ','2026-01-15','','2026-01-15 15:15:12','2026-01-15 15:15:12'),(505,17,'\nEXECUTIVE SUMMARY.\nThis comprehensive report encapsulates the salient activities and accomplishments undertaken on January 15, 2026. Key highlights include the successful dissemination of morning meeting minutes, meticulous updating of the leads template, and proactive engagement with digital marketing initiatives.\n\nTASKS ACCOMPLISHED.\nMeeting Minutes and Communication:\n    - Authored and disseminated the morning meeting minutes via the Beke business group, ensuring seamless communication and alignment among team members\nLead Generation and Distribution:\n    - Successfully garnered a total of 14 leads, comprising 3 from TikTok and 11 from Facebook\n    - Leads were strategically allocated to team members as follows:\n        - Caro: 2 leads\n        - Dennis: 4 leads\n        - Desmond: 2 leads\n        - Joy: 4 leads\n        - Brian: 2 leads\nContent Development:\n    - Prepared two comprehensive scripts for tomorrow\'s educational video in collaboration with Joy from the Land department, focusing on informative and engaging content delivery\n-Website Maintenance:\n    - Provided assistance to Diana in uploading suppliers\' information onto the company website, with further updates scheduled for tomorrow.\n\nSUBMISSION AND ACKNOWLEDGMENT\nThis report has been compiled and submitted for review and acknowledgment. I am available to provide any additional information or clarification.','2026-01-15','- Continue assisting with website uploads and content management\n- Follow up on leads and scripts for tomorrow\'s video, ensuring timely execution and optimal outcomes.\n-Compile the morning meeting minutes and shared on the Beke Business group.\n-Record the educational content and ensure every detailed is followed to the latter as planned.\n-Submit my report on time for review.','2026-01-15 16:21:52','2026-01-15 16:21:52'),(506,23,'Daily Work Report\n• Received 3 leads assigned by Rashid.\n2 leads were responsive and were sent full property details.\nBoth expressed interest in Eternity Heights and are subject to follow-up to schedule a site viewing.\n• Followed up on previous and personal leads.\n1 lead successfully converted to a viewing.\n• Conducted a viewing with Levi’s, who is interested in an office space in Westlands to set up an IT training institution.\nViewed two office options along Muthithi Road, Westlands.\nClient requested a secondary viewing on Saturday, together with his partner, to make a final decision.\n• Teresia, a personal client, has been scheduled for an apartment-for-sale viewing in Kilimani tomorrow afternoon\n• Ustav, a personal client has also scheduled to view 4 bedrooms bungalow in lower Kabete on Sunday.','2026-01-15','','2026-01-15 19:12:25','2026-01-15 19:12:25'),(508,46,'-Attending the morning meeting at the office.\n-Ruaka viewing of a plot  0.181ha being sold at 70 million .\n-viewed 50 acres at Tigoni,kentimere at 25 million.\n-viewed 16 acres touching limuru/redhill road at 20 million per acre.\n-Viewed Riara ridge  along limuru/tigoni road 36 acres at 18 million per acre.\n-viewed 63 acres touching limuru karirana road  at 20 million per acre.','2026-01-15','Self doubt kills talent...To focus on making sales.','2026-01-15 20:00:34','2026-01-15 20:00:34'),(509,20,'I had 2 viewing along raphta road with client where 1 of the client who was in need of the half an acre need to meet the owners but they were no available they booked on Monday \nThe second client was in need  of 1 acre where the client viewed  by didn\'t like the place ','2026-01-15','','2026-01-16 03:30:41','2026-01-16 03:30:41'),(510,46,'-Most of the viewing were rescheduled to Saturday and next week.\n-Cold calling for the leads shared and 6 out of 10 showed positive intrest.','2026-01-16','','2026-01-16 13:45:21','2026-01-16 13:45:21'),(511,27,'1. We had our usual early morning BEKE staff meeting and discussed about our viewings we have had so far, the targets we have for this week, and the forthcoming viewings we have scheduled for the week.\n\n2. In the office identifying and sharing properties that suites my leads who are looking for an apartment to buy or to invest in especially the ones located along Riverside drive which are Riverdrift Residences, Executive Suites, Oasis Westlands, Cheval RIverside, Aura Riverside and Riverside One.\n\n3. Followed up on the new six leads that Rashid allocated me:\n1.Rami M - Kileleshwa apartments\n2. Walter - Lavington apartments\n3. Fazz - Kileleshwa apartments\n4. Deshal Shah - Westlands apartments\n5. Ann - Kilimani apartments\n6. Yusuf - Who is an agent.\nThe above are the location they were looking for an apartment to buy\n\n4. Went sourcing for a commercial space in Old Westlands road for a rental and found it was already taken.\n\n5. Back in the office to plan for tomorrow\'s site visits.','2026-01-16','All is well and pushing for a closure.','2026-01-16 13:52:56','2026-01-16 13:52:56'),(512,23,'1. Tasks Completed\n\nFollowed up on 3 leads allocated by Rashid.\n\nConducted a site visit at Butterfly Palace, Donyo Sabuk, with a client.\n\nMade follow-up calls to previous clients and re-qualified prospects.\n\n2. Meetings / Calls Made\n\nLead 1 & 2 (from Rashid):\n\nTwo were responsive.\n\nLead 3:\n\nNumber was not going through.\n\nClient: Ian\n\nInterest: 2-bedroom in Kileleshwa (Berkeley)\n\nOutcome: Interested but needs to confirm earliest availability based on his calendar.\n\nClient: Ibrahim Lingo\n\nInterest: Berkeley\n\nOutcome: Responsive and interested; subject to follow-up.\n\nClient: Amish\n\nActivity: Site visit to Butterfly Palace, Donyo Sabuk\n\nOutcome: Project is still off-plan; client to revert. Subject to follow-up.\n\nClient: Eric Omondi\n\nStatus: Currently in Kisumu\n\nOutcome: Qualified to higher priority. Interested in scheduling a visit once back in town next week. Call scheduled for Thursday for further guidance.\n\n3. Key Achievements\n\nQualified Eric Omondi to a higher priority lead. From C to B\n\nSecured interest in Berkeley from two prospects (Ian and Ibrahim Lingo).\n\nCompleted a site visit with a client.  Amish at Butterfly Palace.\n\n4. Challenges / Issues\n\nOne allocated lead had an unreachable number.\n\nSome clients require time to confirm availability or revert.\n\n5. Pending Tasks\n\nFollow up with Ian on availability for Berkeley viewing.\n\nContinue follow-up with Ibrahim Lingo. Congolese client.\n\nCall Eric Omondi on Thursday.\n\n\n6. Plan for Tomorrow\n\nFollow up on responsive leads.\n\n1 viewing scheduled for tomorrow with Levix.\n\nContinue client outreach and lead qualification.','2026-01-16','','2026-01-16 14:00:10','2026-01-16 14:00:10'),(513,29,'- Attended the morning team meeting, this time I was recording a video of the team sharing the plans for the day.\n- I then submitted a video for Amani residence.\n- We did an educative content shoot with Mia and Joy regarding how to due diligence via Ardhi sasa\n- I started editing the video of shot in the morning\n- In the afternoon, I submitted the edited video of the educational content \n- I also submitted the video of the team in the morning meeting.','2026-01-16','','2026-01-16 14:05:38','2026-01-16 14:05:38'),(514,15,'Gained 19 leads which were assigned to the sales team both for lands and apartment .there are currently three campaigns running 1 is a ad campaign for TikTok which i just launched today , this is just to optimize the number of leads for the sales team since the number is increasing.\nposted two videos from paddy and 1 e card on all our social media .\n','2026-01-16','','2026-01-16 14:06:44','2026-01-16 14:06:44'),(515,13,'1.I attended the morning meeting together with my colleagues, we shared our target for the day and we also had an office shoot in the boardroom.\n2.I did some office work at the reception, attending to visitors and also my colleagues as required.\n3.I worked on the website, I was adding the suppliers data after creating profiles for them, Mia assisted in adding the products part, we are still working on it so that we can finish soon.\n4.Caro Paddy and I had a small meeting in regards to the website photos ,we shared ideas on how we can improve the photos on the website, Paddy and Rashid will assist in taking better photos for different projects, when they are free as they still have some work everyday but they promised to try.\n5.Paddy assisted me to resize some of the logos for different suppliers so that they are uniform, I will be using them tomorrow once they have all been resized.','2026-01-16','','2026-01-16 17:08:36','2026-01-16 17:08:36'),(516,17,'\nEXECUTIVE SUMMARY\n\nThis report encapsulates the tasks accomplished on January 16, 2026, including attending and writing morning meeting minutes, updating and sharing leads template, creating an educational video, and assisting with website data entry.\n\nTASKS ACCOMP.LISHED\n- Attended and wrote morning meeting minutes, shared on Beke business group\n- Updated and shared leads template with Mr. Ken Huang, leads distributed as follows:\n    - Caro: 4 leads\n    - Dennis: 5 leads\n    - Joy: 5 leads\n    - Desmond: 4 leads\n    - Brian: 2 leads\n- Created educational video with Joy on due diligence before buying land, the video was edited and posted\n- Assisted Miss Diana with data entry on website  supplier products\n\nLEAD DISTRIBUTION DETAILS\nThe leads template shared with Mr. Ken Huang included a total of 20 leads, allocated to team members as mentioned above.\n\nVIDEO CONTENT\nThe educational video created with Joy focused on guiding clients through the due diligence process when purchasing land, aiming to educate and inform clients.\n\n','2026-01-16','','2026-01-16 18:59:34','2026-01-16 18:59:34'),(517,12,'\n> Daily Report\n\nToday, I accompanied Mr. Charles to Riverside Drive, where we viewed a 2-bedroom apartment available for sale that he is interested in purchasing. He was quite impressed with the unit; however, the asking price was slightly above his budget of KES 16M.\n\nWe later explored additional options along Mvuli Road and proceeded to view Himalaya Horizon. Mr. Charles requested time until next Wednesday to review the options and provide his feedback.\n\nI was also assigned three new leads today. One of them was responsive and has scheduled a viewing appointment for Eternity Heights on Tuesday next week.\n\nAdditionally, I followed up with Mr. Francis, who confirmed his availability to view the three sourced options he is looking to purchase.\n','2026-01-16','','2026-01-16 19:01:26','2026-01-16 19:01:26'),(518,20,'I had a successful meeting with the client añd his lawyer where they agreed to proceed with purchasing 1.6 according to the requirement they need  and the process will begun on Monday \nLater I went sourcing along kiserian as a request from a client where she was in need of a farming land 10acres and above where we got and viewing will be next week','2026-01-16','','2026-01-17 06:02:19','2026-01-17 06:02:19'),(519,46,'-followed up the pending  leads.\n-had two  viewing   today at kikuyu and regen.','2026-01-17','Identify potential in every budget.','2026-01-17 19:27:33','2026-01-17 19:27:33'),(520,12,'\nWeekly Activity Report\n\nThis week, I successfully conducted five (5) site visits with clients.\n\nI was assigned eleven (11) leads, out of which six (6) became responsive and were successfully uploaded into the CRM. Additionally, I managed to take two (2) of the newly assigned clients for site visits within the week.\n\nI also carried out call follow-ups with both last week’s clients and pending inquiries from the previous week.\n\nMr. Sam indicated that he will be available for a site visit next Wednesday.\n\nMr. Francis rescheduled his viewing and expressed interest in viewing a resale unit at Riverside One, Westlands.\n\nMr. David confirmed that he will be freely available next week for a site visit of an old-fashioned unit in Lavington.\n\n\nLooking ahead, I am working towards conducting six (6) site visits next week and sourcing at least two (2) new properties. I also plan to actively follow up with last week’s clients—especially those who already viewed properties—with the aim of achieving at least one closure.\n','2026-01-18','','2026-01-18 19:04:54','2026-01-18 19:04:54'),(521,29,'- Attended the morning team meeting.\n- I then headed for a shoot at Greenview villas in Kiambu with Mia. \n- We then went to Mogotio Oasis in Westlands in the afternoon for a shoot of their available showhouses( 1 bedroom and a studio apartment)\n','2026-01-19','','2026-01-19 14:03:35','2026-01-19 14:03:35'),(522,13,'1.Today I was working on the suppliers data, I have managed to upload on the three pages as required, I will now be working on their products as it is easier since the profiles are already there.\n2. I shared with paddy the supplier  logos which need resizing so that he can assist me to resize them so that I can use them on the website for the different suppliers, he will give them to me tomorrow as he still had a shoot.\n3. I received land listings from Rosemary but I was not able to upload them , I still need to look for better photos so that I can upload them.\n4.I assisted in office duties at the reception.\n5. The sales team shared with me some changes that they need added on the Customer follow up on the CRM, I heve communicated with the developer.','2026-01-19','Trying my best to finish uploading all the information required','2026-01-19 14:10:59','2026-01-19 14:10:59'),(523,24,'Attended the morning meeting.\nHeld a meeting with the Muchai Road representative and Mr.Edmond for NanChong Group where introduction was done and requested exchange of company profile and land documents. All this was shared on email afterwards.\nMade follow ups to the client on the CRM.\nReceived two requests for 1acre each in Loresho and Lavington and did sourcing for the two and planned site visits tomorrow with the client and landowners.\nSourced land on Mombasa Road 36acres to be viewed on wednesday for a request i received.\nContinued training the new employee on her roles.\nSourced two properties in Isinya Kajiado according to the client request of 200acres.','2026-01-19','','2026-01-19 16:12:56','2026-01-19 16:12:56'),(524,15,'assigned leads to sales team members ,a total of 14 leads were rolled 10 leads were assigned to the sales team . 3 leads haven\'t been assigned since they rolled after office hours .\nsince during the weekend we had stopped the ad campaign for land after it had fatigued and was rolling less quality leads only two leads was available for land . as we plan for another rich locations to target \n3 videos was also received from paddy and i managed to post the in intervals to our social media platforms for audience engagement .\nevaluation on the quality of lead and the off plan ad campaign\'s location for better targeting and this engaged  the consultant too.','2026-01-19','','2026-01-19 16:17:16','2026-01-19 16:17:16'),(525,12,'\nToday, I accompanied Anastasia to view a unit at Riverside One. She was in discussions regarding her offer; however, the specific unit she initially preferred was priced higher than her budget. She expressed interest in an alternative unit on the 7th floor and proceeded to make an offer. We are currently awaiting feedback, which is expected before the end of the week.\n\nI later followed up with pending clients as well as those who had scheduled viewings for this week.\n\nSarah confirmed that she will be viewing Eternity Heights with her husband tomorrow morning.\n\nJanet mentioned that she will create time within the week to view Eternity Heights, in addition to another option in Kilimani and one in Westlands.\n\nI also followed up with Wendy, who clarified the type of property she is looking for. I shared suitable options with her, and she indicated that she will create time for a viewing within the week.\n','2026-01-19','','2026-01-19 16:54:35','2026-01-19 16:54:35'),(526,17,'\n- Attended and documented morning meeting minutes, ensuring accurate records of discussions and action items\n- Departed office at 11:20 am for a scheduled villa shoot on Kiambu Road, accompanied by Mr. Paddy.\n- Conducted video shoot at 2:10 pm, capturing key features and amenities of the property\n- Proceeded to Mogotio Road for a site visit and shoot of the Mogotio Oasis project, a promising development in a desirable location.\n- Received comprehensive briefing on project details, including pricing, payment plans, and unique selling points\n- Returned to office at 4:00 pm, whereupon I attended to outstanding tasks and ensured timely completion\n- Concluded workday at 5:10 pm\n\nNOTES:\n- Mogotio Oasis project presents a compelling opportunity for potential clients, boasting prime location and attractive offers.\n','2026-01-19','','2026-01-19 17:37:14','2026-01-19 17:37:14'),(527,23,'Lead Management\nOne (1) lead was assigned today.\nAttempted to contact the lead, but the call was not picked.\nClient Engagement & Sourcing\nConducted sourcing for an office space for Levix, as recommended by Joy, along Muthithi Road.\nShared the identified option with the client.\nClient has expressed interest and confirmed a viewing for tomorrow.\nEngaged with Hilda (personal client) who requested details on a property in Runda.\nConducted sourcing and identified a project comprising 16 villas, priced at KES 130M.\nShared full details and photos with the client.\nClient is interested and will schedule a viewing upon her return to the country.\nTomorrow’s Work Plan\nUpdate the CRM with today’s activities and lead status.\nConduct viewings of two (2) rental spaces in Westlands with a client.\nFollow up on previous leads.\n','2026-01-19','','2026-01-19 19:09:56','2026-01-19 19:09:56'),(528,46,'-morning meeting\n-viewing at two rivers \n-pangani viewing of a plot for sale(0.0254)\n- follow up on pending leads.','2026-01-19','Incorporate more agents and wider search of the highrise.','2026-01-19 19:20:20','2026-01-19 19:20:20'),(529,27,'1. We held and early morning BEKE staff meeting and we reviewed our total viewings for last week and the weekly targets too. Thereafter, we held our departmental meeting and discussed about the way we can achieve our sales.\n\n2. Followed up with the leads that Rashid allocated me today:\nNew Leads:\n1. Moses - Looking to buy land in Runda. I have already shared options with him and he will schedule a site visit.\n2. Eyob - Interested in Berkeley apartments in Kileleshwa. He requested I call him back tomorrow again.\n3. Maryam Institute - Is NOT a serious lead. He reached out to us by mistake.\n4. Mohamed Bashir - Looking out for a 3-bedroom either ready or off-plan to buy. I have already shared options and he will revert with feedback.\n\nPrevious Leads:\n1. Samuel Chasia - Is the lead who gave an offer on the 4-bedroom apartment at 245 Emaar Residence, and I was following up on the same on his behalf. Emaar are preparing an offer letter to respond to his booking form application.\n2. Julien - Was able to view Marina Bay Phase 2 today, because he would prefer to buy a 3-bedroom apartment with a closed kitchen. He would like to view more options.\n3. George Oloo - Is interested in Berkeley apartments and would like to view today. He didn\'t and he postponed to Thursday this week.\n4. Halima - who is my own lead and interested in an investment unit. She will create time tomorrow for viewing.\n5. Khadija - She came with her sister and mother, and we viewed DIVINE residency in Riverside, and Elite Residency in Westlands. They picked a unit in DIVINE residency, and they will prepare their offers.\n6. Sheikh Issa - Is an agent and shared with me his lead\'s enquiries ranging from land for JV and lease to a home to buy in Loresho. I found the land for Jv and for lease from Joy, our sales manager.\n\n3. Went for viewing of Marina Bay Phase 2 with Julien Mbom, and thereafter with Khadija, her sister, and her mum to view DIVINE Residency and ELITE Residency. The viewings ended at 7pm and went home directly.','2026-01-19','All is well','2026-01-19 19:42:26','2026-01-19 19:42:26'),(530,11,'I began the day by attending the morning meeting with Mr. Ken and the entire Beke team. Thereafter, I conducted a second interview with Mercy, in the presence of Mr. Ken and Joseph. This was followed by an internal meeting with Mr. Ken and Joseph held in Mr. Ken’s office.\n\nLater in the day, I met a client at Misty Springs, where we viewed one-bedroom and two-bedroom residential units available for rent. We later visited 4 morw options , Marina Bay, Orchid Residence, Neptune Residency, Alina Habour and Pinecrest. \n\nUpon completion of the site visit, I returned to the office and concluded the day’s activities.\n','2026-01-19','','2026-01-20 03:27:25','2026-01-20 03:27:25'),(531,20,'I had a viewing for 1.3acres along Waiyaki way with a client where he viewed and liked the place and requested for documents and the owner to present him self on the next meeting \nLater  I held a meeting with the owner of 1.3acres along Lavington whereby we discussed on terms and later agreed on where the land is repossessed by a bank and later we presented to a client where he will view on Friday \nLater I went for sourcing along kilimani where I got a piece of land along wood avenue on sale as it was a request ','2026-01-20','','2026-01-20 05:17:06','2026-01-20 05:17:06'),(532,13,'1. I attended the morning departmental meeting and also another one with all my colleagues from different departments as there was some new information that needed to passed to us.\n2.I attended another meeting with Mr Ken, Joseph and the developers, they had come to share ideas in regards to the APP which they had already started working on.\n3. I worked on the suppliers data, creating profiles for them and also adding information on the already created profiles. Paddy assisted to resize some of the logos to be used, he is yet to finish since he was still busy.\n4. I assisted in office duties at the reception.','2026-01-20','Trying to achieve my targets.','2026-01-20 13:41:13','2026-01-20 13:41:13'),(533,27,'1. Early morning BEKE departmental staff meeting and we discussed on our targets and the hot leads we have.\n\n2. I followed up on the four leads Rashid allocated me today:\na. Brian - With whom I shared the Berkeley Homes apartments details.\nb. Victor - He requested I call him back after 5pm today.\nc. John Mogonda - Call him back after working hours.\nd. Siem - With whom I have shared the Berkeley apartment details with.\n\n3. Visited East Vista upcoming apartments along Prof. Wangari Maathai Road and oriented myself with the project. It is already listed in our website.\n\n4. Back to the office and shared project details with the hot leads.','2026-01-20','','2026-01-20 13:56:52','2026-01-20 13:56:52'),(534,29,'- Attended the morning marketing team meeting\n- Afterwards, I did some corrections on the first video of the Greenview villas with Mia talking. Submitted on completion.\n- I then designed an E-card post (light mood) emphasizing on how affordable the Berkeley project is.\n- I edited a property video for Greenview villlas in the afternoon and submitted on completion.\n- I assisted Diana in resizing the supplier logos for the website to fit neatly.','2026-01-20','','2026-01-20 14:01:12','2026-01-20 14:01:12'),(535,15,'Assigned eleven leads to the sales team , for their follow-up and schedule necessary  site visit  , leads are slow since we only have one ad campaign running . \nhad a a brief session we the consultant and this was aimed to start a campaign for townhouses which could blend with the January session and in the same regard we settled on Greenville townhouses in Kiambu road ,tilisi townhouses and Amani residence in wetlands .\nposted two videos and 1 e card from paddy . ','2026-01-20','','2026-01-20 14:05:13','2026-01-20 14:05:13'),(536,24,'Held the morning meeting with my team where I shared various request to assist me in sourcing around Loresho and Kitisuru.\nHeld a meeting with Mr.Edmond to update on the 2.7acres in Kileleshwa where we agreed to have a meeting on Friday at 8a.m at Elite Board room.\nReceived and shared emails for the proposal of 0.52acres and on phone negotiations.\nSourced and organized viewings at Kabete, Nyari for tomorrow.\nFollowed up on the leads shared by Rashid.\nRescheduled today\'s viewings to tomorrow.','2026-01-20','','2026-01-20 15:16:05','2026-01-20 15:16:05'),(537,12,'Daily Report\n\nToday, I accompanied Janet for a viewing of two 2-bedroom apartments available for sale—one in Riverside, Westlands, and another along Golden Street in Kileleshwa. She showed strong interest in the Kileleshwa unit and mentioned she would like to compare it with a few more options before making a commitment. We have scheduled additional viewings for Saturday.\n\nI also coordinated a second viewing for Sarah at Eternity Heights, where she attended with her husband. She indicated that she will share her feedback before the end of the week.\n\nAdditionally, I was assigned two new leads. One was responsive and requested that I share the property details via WhatsApp, after which I plan to follow up tomorrow.','2026-01-20','','2026-01-20 16:52:07','2026-01-20 16:52:07'),(538,23,'1 lead assigned by Rashid.\n1 viewing conducted with Levix at wendy court\nThere is no availability as we found the only 3 spaces remaining were paid for the same day by another company \nViewing 1 office space tomorrow at mid morning in Westlands \nThe lead that was allocated is interested in Berkeley for a unit for investment and also additionally, 3 bedroom apartment for him to live in. Preferred location is lavington, hurlinghum and Kileleshwa. Clients name is Adeel. I have shared options and Im waiting for clients feedback\nMade follow up calls and managed to secure 2 viewings.','2026-01-20','','2026-01-20 17:48:26','2026-01-20 17:48:26'),(539,17,'\n TODAYS ACTIVITIES AND ACCOMPLISHMENTS:\n- Attended and participated in the morning marketing meeting, ensuring alignment with team objectives and initiatives\n- Documented and disseminated meeting minutes to relevant stakeholders, facilitating effective communication and follow-up\n- Updated and shared the leads excel sheet with Mr. Ken, enhancing lead tracking and sales team collaboration\n- Prepared and finalized scripts for scheduled shoots on Mombasa Road and Kilimani, ensuring readiness for tomorrow\'s activities\n- Provided assistance to Diana on data entry tasks related to suppliers\' products, contributing to accurate and up-to-date database management\n\n','2026-01-20','','2026-01-20 18:25:12','2026-01-20 18:25:12'),(540,46,'-Morning meeting in attendance.\n-outsourcing/viewing at Royal homes at lower kabete.\n-viewing of 2 acres at old kitusuru(250 million for both acres)','2026-01-20','small steps leads to big achievement.','2026-01-20 19:02:18','2026-01-20 19:02:18'),(541,11,'I began the day by chairing the morning meeting with the sales team. Thereafter, I conducted an interview alongside Joy with a candidate, Sandra, who was assessed and found not to be a suitable fit for the position.\n\nFollowing the interview, I carried out follow-ups with my clients. \n\nLater in the day, I proceeded to Gigiri to view a property available for rent on behalf of a client. Upon returning to the office, I continued with client follow ups, I also followed up with members of my team to review their progress, specifically to confirm whether they had contacted the clients assigned to them, the outcomes of those engagements, and the level of client responsiveness and concluded the day’s activities.','2026-01-20','','2026-01-20 22:20:30','2026-01-20 22:20:30'),(542,20,'I had several sourcing along general Mathenge Westland where I got 2 properties 1tourching main road and the other second low where both the owner requested for the buyer so they can sign for the concent\nLater I went for a sourcing along muchai drive for a property that a client requested I didn\'t get the owner BT I was asked to be available next week Monday\nLater I fallowed up with the lawyers on Ngong road plot and kileleshwa where by the kileleshwa one we shall take the client for viewing tomorrow and Ngong road 3 quarters  the buyer haven\'t been back from holiday they are NGO\'s  but still communicating with his lawyer where he is very promising on the deal when he is back  on the course of the month ','2026-01-20','','2026-01-20 23:44:30','2026-01-20 23:44:30'),(543,13,'1. I uploaded 3 land listings from Rosemary, I still have 1 of her listings pending since she has not provided good photos yet, I have requested her to take better photos as per the required standard. She will get back.\n2. I uploaded 1 Contractor from Rashid , I was not able to get photos for their gallery, I am still looking for them so that the profile can be complete.\n3. I worked on the products data for the suppliers that I have already created profiles for, I managed to upload some products for 5 suppliers, I am still working on it so that it is complete.\n4. I assisted with work at the reception.','2026-01-21','','2026-01-21 13:49:11','2026-01-21 13:49:11'),(544,15,'Assigned leads to the sale team a total of 27 leads were assigned today , there was no leads for land since currently there is no land campaigns running.\nPosted three videos from paddy in the intervals of the day , \nAssisted Diana using the Adobe Photoshop to help resize the logos of different contractors .\nHad a session with the consultant aimed and analyzing how the compaigns are doing including the one we launched today ','2026-01-21','','2026-01-21 13:56:48','2026-01-21 13:56:48'),(545,46,'-cold marketing  via calls and social media platform.\n-outsourced 3 more properties that am  to view  tomorrow(kiambu rd,limuru rd,tigoni.','2026-01-21','time management between sourcing and marketing.','2026-01-21 14:01:50','2026-01-21 14:01:50'),(546,27,'1. Today, I had a meeting with 88 Nairobi developer along with my own personal lead as he was looking to buy a unit in Upper Hill since he works in a Ministry, and then I was left at 88 being oriented on the project up to around 11am.\n\n2. Thereafter, I went to Emaar Consult to meet with Mr Hassan and my clients Samuel and Joyce. Finally, Mr. Hassan has agreed to my leads\' payment terms since and was assured the 80% balance would be paid within 90 days. Emaar Consult will share the offer letter for the leads to approve.\n\n3. I came back to the office at 2:30pm and followed up on all the leads Rashid allocated me.','2026-01-21','All is well.','2026-01-21 14:06:14','2026-01-21 14:06:14'),(547,24,'Held the morning meeting with my team and we discussed various ways to collect quality land and close leads as soon as possible.\nSourced and organized for viewing at Kilimani for a 1acre lease property but the client didnt like the location. Set to get more options.\nWent for viewing at Lower Kabete with a local Developer willing to do town houses on two acres of land. Waiting for a proposal.\nWent for viewing at EPZ Athi River for 20acres JV with a Chinese Developer representative.\nCarried negotiations for the Muchai Road property and worked on the requested amendments.\nFollowed on the leads shared and updated in the CRM.','2026-01-21','','2026-01-21 14:30:52','2026-01-21 14:30:52'),(548,29,'- Attended the mornina marketing team meeting.\n- Afterwards, I proceeded to Mlolongo with Mia to shoot an apartment at Waybridge garden \n- In the afternoon we went to shoot an offplan content at Lesonia Residency, we were done by close of business.','2026-01-21','','2026-01-21 15:23:03','2026-01-21 15:23:03'),(549,20,'I had a viewing with a client along kileleshwa for 0.75acres where he liked and requested the lawyer to organise a meeting with the bank\nLater I went for a viewing for a land on lease along kilimani  where we shall have a viewing tomorrow with a client \nLater I went to Westland to view 1acre where client requested to view tomorrow when he will be available ','2026-01-21','','2026-01-21 16:56:51','2026-01-21 16:56:51'),(550,20,'I had a viewing with a client along kileleshwa for 0.75acres where he liked and requested the lawyer to organise a meeting with the bank\nLater I went for a viewing for a land on lease along kilimani  where we shall have a viewing tomorrow with a client \nLater I went to Westland to view 1acre where client requested to view tomorrow when he will be available ','2026-01-21','','2026-01-21 16:56:52','2026-01-21 16:56:52'),(551,12,'Daily Report\n\nToday, my client Sam, who had scheduled a site visit, rescheduled the appointment to Saturday.\n\nI was then tasked with handling follow-ups and lead calls. I was assigned six leads, out of which three were responsive:\n\nMr. Muhammad is looking to purchase one acre of land in Tigoni. He is available to view a few options tomorrow from 11:00 a.m.\n\nMr. James expressed interest in the Kiambu villas and will be available for a site visit next Wednesday.\n\nLaurie inquired about a 2-bedroom unit to let in Kileleshwa. I shared several options with her and will follow up tomorrow.\n\n\n','2026-01-21','','2026-01-21 17:54:44','2026-01-21 17:54:44'),(552,17,'\nACTIVITIES AND ACCOMPLISHMENTS:\n- Attended and participated in the morning marketing meeting, documenting comprehensive minutes and sharing with the Beke marketing group to ensure all team members are informed and aligned\n- Updated and shared the leads excel template with Mr. Ken, ensuring accurate tracking and follow-up of leads generated from various channels\n- Conducted a property shoot in Mombasa Road from 11:20am to 1:30pm, capturing high-quality visuals and gathering necessary information for marketing purposes\n- Proceeded to Kileleshwa for an off-plan property shoot at Lesonia project, a premium development located on Tendret Street off Gatanga Road, arriving at 3pm. The project boasts excellent location, amenities, and features, making it a highly marketable property.\n\nOUTCOME AND NEXT STEPS:\n- The property shoots are expected to yield engaging content for social media and website updates.\n- Follow-up actions include sharing shoot outcomes with the team, pursuing leads generated, and updating marketing materials accordingly.\n\n','2026-01-21','','2026-01-21 19:02:51','2026-01-21 19:02:51'),(553,23,'Daily Report\nReceived 4 leads from Rashid.\nSuccessfully contacted 3 leads, out of which 2 were responsive.\nLead Updates:\nSammy: Responsive. Scheduled a viewing for two properties tomorrow.\nFidilia: Budget range 10M – 13M. Shared suitable property options along Mombasa Road. Awaiting feedback on preferred viewing date.\nViewings Conducted:\nConducted 2 viewings along Kiambu Road with different clients:\nHilda: Viewed Paradise Residence. She is interested, though the price is slightly above her budget. She requested time and will give a final response by the end of the month.\nNana: Viewed Greenview. She expressed interest and would like to return for a weekend viewing with her husband.\n1 viewing was facilitated by Brian along Muthithi road for a rental commercial space.','2026-01-21','','2026-01-21 19:55:56','2026-01-21 19:55:56'),(554,11,'The day began with a morning sales team meeting. Thereafter, I conducted a second interview with Anthony, who was assessed and found not to be a suitable fit for the company.\n\nI received six leads from Rashid and proceeded to follow up on them. One client, Alice, was responsive and requested more information regarding the Kiambu Road villa, which I shared accordingly. Two contacts had their phones switched off; I left text messages, but there was no response, and I plan to follow up again the following day. The remaining contacts did not pick up their calls, and I also plan to follow up with them the next day.\n\nIn addition, I followed up with a previous client and successfully secured a viewing appointment with Ifrah, scheduled for 9:00 a.m. the following day. I also updated my client list to reflect all responsive clients.\n\nI ensured to follow up with my team regarding their daily activities and achievements based on the action points agreed upon during the morning meeting. Dennis successfully secured an offer letter for his client. Desmond attended two scheduled property viewings. Brian’s client cancelled a scheduled viewing; however, he proceeded to conduct follow-ups with other clients.','2026-01-21','','2026-01-22 05:38:33','2026-01-22 05:38:33'),(555,13,'1. I uploaded a listing for sale from Carol after she provided all the requirements.\n2.Mia and I worked on uploading products for different suppliers, we agreed to upload at least five products for each supplier, we are still working on this data.\n3.I assisted in office duties at the reception, Mia and I helped visitors at the reception and also our colleagues.\n4.I received  some listings from Rosemary but I requested her to bring quality photos as per the required  standard so that I can upload them.','2026-01-22','','2026-01-22 13:50:15','2026-01-22 13:50:15'),(556,27,'1. We started the day off with a brief BEKE Staff meeting led by Mr. Joseph, and we talked about our workplan for today and also, we were informed that CFC Stanbic will come to our office tomorrow to open bank accounts for us.\n\n2. I then followed with all the leads Rashid allocated me yesterday and today, and 70% of them responded and I have shared the project details of their interest. I am updating them by today evening in the CRM and the notes remarking about their enquiries.\n\n3. My viewings for today have been postponed for Saturday and next week. Because of this, I had to follow on more of my leads and probed them on their enquiries.','2026-01-22','All is well.','2026-01-22 14:03:19','2026-01-22 14:03:19'),(557,29,'- Attended the morning marketing team meeting\n- I then finished up editing a video of the 3bedroom apartment in Mlolongo I shot yesterday\n- I then designed an e-card post (Berkeley residency)\n- In the afternoon, I edited an off-plan video for Lesonia Residency and submitted by close of business.','2026-01-22','','2026-01-22 14:06:13','2026-01-22 14:06:13'),(558,15,'The better part of the day was spent in a session with Joseph. We were basically reviewing the quality of leads for the past two weeks of January and focusing on the locations for the targeted leads, and this was summarized with one more creative added on the off-plan property campaign.  \nassigned leads to the sales team, and a total of 35  plus leads were assigned today .\nposted 2 videos and 1 carousel post to the instagram to boost on the daily posting strategy.\nCreated a LinkedIn account for the company. This would help filter our application for the current salespeople the company is looking to recruit.','2026-01-22','','2026-01-22 14:06:32','2026-01-22 14:06:32'),(559,24,'Started viewing 14acres at Nyari with Joe Kinyajui. Client is interested with 10acres the ones next to Enaki. To give a proposal as soon as Tuesday next week.\nConducted three interviews but only one candidate for land is qualified, Brian Mawanda. He is ready to start in February if he is approved.\nHeld a meeting between NanChong and Stanchart Lawyer and representative. They requested for us to go through the agreement for the commission before we proceed with the rest of the agreement.\nHeld another meeting with the agents from Reagents regarding 80acres they have on peponi road upfor JV. Requested another meeting for Monday 10a.m at their office in Upperhill.\nFollowed up with the pending enquiries for lease where i got one property in Lavington for viewing tomorrow.\n','2026-01-22','','2026-01-22 15:40:24','2026-01-22 15:40:24'),(560,23,'Daily Activity Report\nLeads & Follow-Up\nA total of 8 leads were assigned by Rashid.\nSuccessfully contacted 6 leads.\n2 leads were responsive: Mark and Shazia.\nLead Details\nShazia\nRequested property details to be shared via WhatsApp.\nInterested in options along Kiambu Road with a budget of KES 35M.\nSpecifically looking for ready units.\nDetails have been shared, with plans to engage further tomorrow.\nMark\nRequested alternative property options.\nOptions have been shared.\nFollow-up planned for tomorrow.\nReason for Delayed Follow-Up\nDelay was due to a lengthy viewing in Westlands with a personal client, Levix.\nBy the time I returned to the office, it was already 5:00 PM.\nProceeded with property sourcing and met the landlady of a property shared by Brian.\nLater conducted a viewing with the client.\nClient Viewing Update (Levix)\nThe client liked the property.\nAsking price: KES 200,000.\nClient’s offer: KES 150,000.\nThe client will consult with other shareholders to determine if they can stretch the budget to KES 200,000.\nFinal feedback expected by Monday next week','2026-01-22','','2026-01-22 16:32:11','2026-01-22 16:32:11'),(561,17,'\nACTIVITIES AND ACCOMPLISHMENTS:\n- Arrived at work punctually and promptly commenced duties, ensuring a productive start to the day\n- Provided assistance to Miss Diana with data entry tasks specifically related to updating suppliers\' information on our database, contributing to accurate and up-to-date database management\n- Attended to various other office duties as required, including  handling administrative tasks, ensuring smooth day-to-day operations\n- Updated the leads excel template with the latest information and shared it with Mr. Ken at the close of business today, facilitating effective lead tracking, follow-up, and sales team collaboration\n\n','2026-01-22','','2026-01-22 19:06:14','2026-01-22 19:06:14'),(562,12,'\nDaily Report\n\nToday, following the cancellation of the scheduled viewing appointment by Mr. Muhammad, I conducted follow-ups and contacted the leads that had been assigned to me.\n\nI was assigned a total of seven (7) leads. Most of them were unresponsive, after which I proceeded to share details of the Kiambu villas with them via WhatsApp for further engagement.\n\nMr. Martin was responsive and requested that we stay in touch tomorrow after he has reviewed the information that was shared with him.\n\nI also accompanied Desmond to source for a property. I am in direct contact with the property owner, and the property is available for commercial use. Upon viewing, Desmond’s client expressed interest in considering the commercial space.\n\nAdditionally, I followed up with Letty, who is looking to purchase land in Tigoni. I shared several land options with her that had been provided by Rosemary.\n\nI also shared the same parcels of land with Mr. Muhammad, who mentioned that he will create time on Saturday for a viewing appointment','2026-01-22','Follow up with this week\'s leads ,\n\nArranging for viewing appointment on Saturday with booked clients ','2026-01-22 19:07:51','2026-01-22 19:07:51'),(563,20,'I had a viewing with a lawyer along parklands jalalam road where he viewed and liked the plot but the price was too high for the plot where he gives an offer where we are waiting for a report \nLater I went to view the 5 acres along ringroad Westland where he liked the plot but the developer requested time to give feedback \nI later held a meeting with the client representative and the land owner regards to 1 acre parklands where we are waiting for the client to confirm his availability to view ','2026-01-22','','2026-01-22 19:18:29','2026-01-22 19:18:29'),(564,11,'I began the day with a site viewing at 9:00 a.m. with my client, Ifrah, who is seeking to purchase a three-bedroom apartment with a staff quarter in an off-plan development, preferably with a minimum three-year payment plan. Three project options were viewed, and the client expressed interest in two of them. She indicated that she would like to bring her brother to view the shortlisted options and committed to providing feedback before Monday. The viewing was productive, as the purchase is intended for her mother.\n\nThereafter, I returned to the office and followed up on client leads assigned to me by Rashid. Out of eight leads, I managed to contact four clients, as detailed below:\n	•	Carol\n	•	Inquiry: Greenview Villas (townhouses along Kiambu Road)\n	•	Action Taken: Shared detailed project information, including photos and videos\n	•	Next Step: Awaiting feedback to confirm interest and schedule a site visit\n	•	Rachel\n	•	Inquiry: Greenview Villas (Kiambu Road)\n	•	Availability: After next week\n	•	Action Taken: Shared project details and photos\n	•	Next Step: Scheduled a follow-up call for next Friday to plan a site visit\n	•	David\n	•	Inquiry: Villas along Kiambu Road\n	•	Additional Request: 50×100 plots along Kiambu Road\n	•	Action Taken: Shared villa photos and project details\n	•	Follow-up Action: Liaised with Rosemary to assist in sourcing suitable plot options\n	•	Next Step: Awaiting plot options to share with the client','2026-01-22','','2026-01-22 19:59:04','2026-01-22 19:59:04'),(565,46,'-sourcing /viewing of 20 acres in Redhill at 35  million per acre(1\\2) acre at 17.5 million.\n-outsourcing/viewing of Redhill bustani garden 4 acres at 25 million per acre.\n-Commercial plot along redhill at 50 million per acre touching limuru road \n-kinganjo viewing of 4 bedroom house sitting on a (50 by 100) at 10 million.\n-following on leads assigned to me.','2026-01-22','for success,attitude is equallyas important as ability.','2026-01-22 20:25:54','2026-01-22 20:25:54'),(566,24,'Started the morning meeting with my team where we discussed the various leads we have and I assigned them other enquiries to follow up on.\nConducted an interview with one candidate that didn\'t seem suitable for the position of a sales agent.\nWorked on the leads shared to make follow ups.\nHeld online conference calls between the TAA and Stanchart to negotiate further on the terms of JV in Kileleshwa  2.7acres.\nUpdated to the CRM all the clients followed up.','2026-01-23','Report on the Team is as follows:\n\n1.David.\nHe has been following up on A clients this week and had promised to close one client for 0.75acres in Kileleshwa but was not successful and was pushed to 27th of January.\nMost part of his especially in sourcing hasn\'t been to our standards either because he is not in direct contact with the land owners.\nIn terms of getting clients, he gets most leads from Agency Whatsapp groups  that in most cases are not reliable.\nIn conclusion, after careful examination of the clients he has listed in the CRM, they are not from reliable sources.  \n\n2.Rosemary.\nShe has started well especially in sourcing  and managed to get 9parcels of land .\n I gave her 10leads  and has all of them she posted to the CRM and followed up.\nShe got a serious client, Patricia Odhiambo on the 5acres in Tigoni ready to commit after two weeks.\nShe has another client, Damaris who is going to view the villas at Burudani tomorrow. \nI can recommend that we got a good employee. We only need to guide her in the upscale market and learn how it works.\n\n3.Joy\nI have managed to engage 2new clients this week with 5Viewings completed so far.\nThe areas of interest successfully engaged are in:\na.) EPZ Athi River 20acres JV-Chinese Developer.\nb.)Muchai Road 0.5Acres-Nan Chong Developers.\nc.)Lavington 1acre for sale-Somali Developer.\nd.)Two Rivers 30Acres JV-Markem Developers. \n\nThe projects that have been able to get offer letters I have clearly indicated the progress on each lead for HK Developers and Westland 57 who are the main clients I am about to close.\n','2026-01-23 13:37:03','2026-01-23 13:37:03'),(567,15,'- I assigned 21  leads to the sales team for their review and follow-up. These leads were selected based on their potential interest, and the team was tasked with engaging them promptly to maximize conversion opportunities. The assignment aimed to streamline the sales process and improve overall team efficiency.\n-I replaced one ad creative in the off-plan properties campaign to improve performance and better align with the target audience, with the objective of increasing engagement and lead generation.\n-I posted one e-card and two videos as submitted by Paddy, one of which was an office fun video intended to boost page engagement, increase reach, and create a more relatable brand presence.','2026-01-23','','2026-01-23 13:58:57','2026-01-23 13:58:57'),(568,13,'1. I uploaded  2 listings  for sale and rent from Carol and 1 for sale from Brian since they had provided all the requirements.\n2.I uploaded 3 land listings from Rosemary as she had provided all the requirements, I still have those that are pending since I asked her to retake the photos.\n3.I uploaded products for one supplier ,I uploaded at least 5 products , Mia and I were not able to continue since the system had challenges , I communicated to the developer to make the necessary  adjustments so that we can have easy time.\n4.I assisted in office duties at the reception ,assisting my colleagues and visitors as well.','2026-01-23','Pushing to achieve my targets for the month.','2026-01-23 14:00:15','2026-01-23 14:00:15'),(569,27,'1. Today, we had our own departmental sales meeting headed by Caroline and we talked about the feedback of the viewings we had this week, our plan for today, and the viewings we will have this week.\n\n2. I had to be in the office and to follow up with all my hot leads and also the ones who needed their specific project details shared to them. It is from this follow up that I have been able to get 4 confirmed viewings for Greenview Villas: Victor Muriuki, Michael Obit, Anne N, and Caroline Mbatia.\n\n3. I followed up with my pending sourcings and especially AMTO and MORVARA developers who are still in discussion with Mr Ken. I am still hoping to have two listings today.\n\n4. In the afternoon, I was still following up on more leads and familiarised myself with the projects.','2026-01-23','Pushing for a sale.','2026-01-23 14:11:51','2026-01-23 14:11:51'),(570,29,'- Attended the morning marketing team meeting where we shared our plans for the day. Also, we discussed on some ways to enhance some adjustments or rather make our videos better.\n- After the meeting, Rashid and I shot two office videos, one fun video and an educational content with Joy. \n- I then designed a carrousel cover for weekend plans that actually hit. I featured the museumofillusions in Westlands.\n- In the afternoon I edited fun video and submitted. Then started brainstorming ideas for the app cover image to be displayed on our website, a video on the same and Billboard designs.','2026-01-23','','2026-01-23 15:51:44','2026-01-23 15:51:44'),(571,23,'Leads Allocation\nA total of 4 leads were allocated today by Rashid.\nLead Engagement\n2 leads were responsive:\nOne client was looking for a rental unit along Kiambu Road with a tight budget of KES 80,000–90,000.\nThe second client requested a location pin of the project but was unwilling to disclose a preferred viewing date. This behavior is commonly associated with agents. Upon further probing, the lead went silent.\nFollow-ups\nConducted follow-up calls with previously handled clients.\nOne client has confirmed a viewing for tomorrow:\nClient Name: Teresia\nRequirement: 1-bedroom apartment\nPurpose: Purchase\nLocation Preference: Westlands','2026-01-23','','2026-01-23 17:48:27','2026-01-23 17:48:27'),(572,46,'-following up on leads\n-social media marketing','2026-01-23','explore every aspect of marketing.','2026-01-23 18:33:12','2026-01-23 18:33:12'),(573,12,'\n---\n\nDaily Activity Report\n\nToday, I was assigned a total of five clients, out of which two were responsive.\n\nNjeri expressed interest in the Greenville Garden Villas and mentioned that she will create time next week for a site visit.\n\nMercy showed interest in purchasing a 2-bedroom apartment at Mogotio Oasis. I shared detailed information with her via WhatsApp and will follow up accordingly.\n\n\nI also carried out follow-ups with existing clients:\n\nFaith, who viewed Eternity Heights earlier this week, informed me that she did not consider the option but remains open to alternatives in the Westlands and Lavington areas. I shared several options with her, with a follow-up scheduled for tomorrow.\n\nMr. Sam confirmed his availability tomorrow from 11:00 a.m. to view available sale options in Westlands, once shared.\n\nJanet, who intends to compare more options with Golden Street, Kileleshwa, confirmed her availability for site visits on Monday.','2026-01-23','','2026-01-23 18:49:13','2026-01-23 18:49:13'),(574,17,'\nACTIVITIES AND ACCOMPLISHMENTS:\n- Wrote and shared the morning marketing meeting minutes on the Beke Marketing group, ensuring all team members are informed and aligned\n- Compiled and updated the leads excel sheet, sharing it with Mr. Ken Huang. Notable highlights include:\n    - 17 leads generated from Meta platforms\n- Assisted Miss Diana with data entry tasks related to suppliers\' product information, contributing to accurate database management\n- Participated in creating a fun reel with team members, which was edited and posted on social media platforms, boosting team engagement and online presence','2026-01-23','','2026-01-23 18:58:26','2026-01-23 18:58:26'),(575,11,'I began the day by chairing the morning team meeting. During the meeting, we reviewed the viewings conducted throughout the week, and each team member provided updates on the outcomes of their respective viewings.\n\nFollowing the meeting, I participated in an interview for a sales position together with Joy and Joseph. The candidate was assessed and determined not to be a suitable fit for the company.\n\nLater in the day, I attended a site viewing at Brookside, Grevillia Grove with my personal client, Greyson, who was interested in viewing a specific villa on the road, Taj Prestige, i shared the property with Diana for listing. I returned to the office immediately after the site visit.\n\nThereafter, I followed up with all clients allocated to me by Rashid, including those I was unable to reach the previous day. Approximately 50% of the clients were unresponsive, as they did not answer calls. Clients who were reached requested alternative property options, which has been challenging to source, particularly within the same or lower budget ranges.\n\nAdditionally, I experienced challenges updating the CRM with the clients I followed up with during the day, which I reported to Diana for support and resolution.','2026-01-23','','2026-01-23 20:24:08','2026-01-23 20:24:08'),(576,46,'-attended morning meeting.\n-had 3 viewing for greenview in kiambu that were scheceduled for next week.','2026-01-24',' filter as much as possible [A,B,C}Client.','2026-01-24 16:25:08','2026-01-24 16:25:08'),(577,12,'y Reports\n52 reports found\n\n\nFilters\n\nNew Report\n\nExport CSV\nDate	Staff	Visited Projects	Remarks	Actions\nJan 23, 2026\nBZ\nBrian Zachary\nNo projects visited\n—\nView\n\nReply\nDelete\nJan 22, 2026\nBZ\nBrian Zachary\nLantana road commercial unit\nFollow up with this week\'s leads , Arranging for viewing appointment on Saturday with booked clients\nView\n\nReply\nDelete\nJan 21, 2026\nBZ\nBrian Zachary\nNo projects visited\n—\nView\n\n2\nReply\nDelete\nJan 20, 2026\nBZ\nBrian Zachary\nGolden Street kileleshwa\nRiverside one\n—\nView\n\nReply\nDelete\nJan 19, 2026\nBZ\nBrian Zachary\nRiverside one\n—\nView\n\nReply\nDelete\nJan 18, 2026\nBZ\nBrian Zachary\nNo projects visited\n—\nView\n\nReply\nDelete\nJan 16, 2026\nBZ\nBrian Zachary\nRiverside one,Dolce vita\n—\nView\n\nReply\nDelete\nJan 15, 2026\nBZ\nBrian Zachary\nNo projects visited\n—\nView\n\nReply\nDelete\nJan 14, 2026\nBZ\nBrian Zachary\nEternity height Kitusuru\n—\nView\n\nReply\nDelete\nJan 12, 2026\nBZ\nBrian Zachary\nRiverside one\n108 Riverside\n+2 more\n—\nView\n\nReply\nDelete\nJan 11, 2026\nBZ\nBrian Zachary\nNo projects visited\n—\nView\n\nReply\nDelete\nJan 9, 2026\nBZ\nBrian Zachary\nNo projects visited\n—\nView\n\nReply\nDelete\nJan 8, 2026\nBZ\nBrian Zachary\nSunstone, General Mathenge\n—\nView\n\nReply\nDelete\nJan 7, 2026\nBZ\nBrian Zachary\nNo projects visited\n—\nView\n\nReply\nDelete\nJan 6, 2026\nBZ\nBrian Zachary\nLuminara\n—\nView\n\n2\nReply\nDelete\nPage 1 of 4 (52 total reports)\n\nPrevious\n1\n2\n3\n4\nNext\nDaily Report Details\nBrian Zachary - Jan 18, 2026\n\n\nProjects Visited (0)\nNo projects visited.\n\nTodays Report\n\nWeekly Activity Report\n\nThis week, I successfully conducted five (5) site visits with clients.\n\nI was assigned eleven (11) leads, out of which six (6) became responsive and were successfully uploaded into the CRM. Additionally, I managed to take two (2) of the newly assigned clients for site visits within the week.\n\nI also carried out call follow-ups with both last week’s clients and pending inquiries from the previous week.\n\nMr. Sam indicated that he will be available for a site visit next Wednesday.\n\nMr. Francis rescheduled his viewing and expressed interest in viewing a resale unit at Riverside One, Westlands.\n\nMr. David confirmed that he will be freely available next week for a site visit of an old-fashioned unit in Lavington.\n\n\nLooking ahead, I am working towards conducting six (6) site visits next week and sourcing at least two (2) new properties. I also plan to actively follow up with last week’s clients—especially those who already viewed properties—with the aim of achieving at least one closure.','2026-01-25','','2026-01-25 20:24:05','2026-01-25 20:24:05'),(578,27,'1. Early morning BEKE staff meeting and we discussed about our viewings and the plan for this week.\n2. Followed up with all my customers with whom we went viewing with and to get their feedback. Victor will come again with his parents to view Greenview Villas; Mr. Gerald is still in need of a ready 3-bedroom and Khadija is considering the options I shared with her.\n3. Emaar Consult are delaying with the offer letter therefore my leads have no choice but to source for another one.\n4. I followed up with all My BEKE leads that I was allocated on Saturday and today and shared with them their respective project details. One, Mrs Jane, would like to view it today, and as well arranging on the same.','2026-01-26','','2026-01-26 13:31:01','2026-01-26 13:31:01'),(579,13,'1. I uploaded 2 properties, 1 land from Rosemary and 1 property from Brian he gave 1 listing  in Mombasa Road.\n2. I uploaded product data for 2 suppliers I added at least 5 of their products to their profiles.\n3. I worked with Paddy to come up with some new detail ideas to be used in the APP home page by the developers, I shared what he has already completed working on, what is remaining is the video for the website homepage, he has promised to submit it tomorrow so that the developer can do the exchange.\n4.I assisted in office duties at the reception as required, I received visitors and assisted them\n5.I communicated with the developer on the new changes as requested by my boss,I explained to them and they started working on thee changes.','2026-01-26','','2026-01-26 13:59:21','2026-01-26 13:59:21'),(580,29,'- Attended the weekly general meeting, where we reviewed what we did last week and shared our work plans for the week ahead.\n- After the meeting, we were to head for a land content shoot in processional way, but there were some adjustments to be made on our APP, that is revamping the icons for the product section, supplier section and the contractors section.\n- I managed to finish up on the product icons bit by afternoon and forwaded to Diana\n- In the afternoon I proceded to create icons for the suppliers and contractors bit, which I managed to to complete by close of business. I forwaded the relevant folders to Diana.','2026-01-26','','2026-01-26 14:01:15','2026-01-26 14:01:15'),(581,15,'- A total of four 42leads were assigned to the sales team for follow-up. The team was tasked with engaging the prospects, providing detailed property information, and actively pushing for physical property viewings. The objective of this assignment was to assess buyer interest, nurture the leads through the sales funnel, and convert qualified prospects into potential buyers.\n- One (1) video featuring the property voted for the week was created and published across the designated marketing platforms. The video highlighted the property’s key features, location advantages, and unique selling points, with the objective of increasing audience engagement, enhancing brand visibility, and generating interest from potential buyers and investors.\n-Collaborated with Joseph in the creation of one (1) TikTok Business advertisement aimed at increasing brand visibility and lead generation. Additionally, developed and uploaded an ad creative for a townhouse located on Brookside Drive available for rent. The property’s unique features and prime location position it as a high-potential rental, which, when strategically and consistently promoted, is expected to attract qualified and serious prospective tenants. ','2026-01-26','','2026-01-26 14:04:59','2026-01-26 14:04:59'),(582,24,'Attended the morning meeting.\nHeld two interviews where one candidate qualified for the role of Apartments Sale.\nHeld a conference meeting on call with the client for a lease property with the Knight Frank Agent and land owner but the client didn\'t agree to the terms. He requested we source a different property for him.  Sourced two options for him and planned for viewing on Wednesday afternoon.\nMade follow up calls for my previous client regarding Tigoni and planned for viewing on Thursday 2p.m.\nUpdated the CRM.\nSourced properties for the existing enquiries that I have on Muthithi Road 0.25acres and planned for viewing tomorrrow.','2026-01-26','','2026-01-26 16:52:59','2026-01-26 16:52:59'),(583,12,'\n\nDaily Report\n\nToday, I was assigned 8 leads, of which 2 turned responsive.\n\nMr. Joshua expressed strong interest in the Greenville Garden project. He mentioned that he will confirm his availability for a viewing appointment on either Friday or Saturday.\n\nSavannah is looking to purchase a one-bedroom apartment and is open to off-plan options. She indicated that she will communicate later in the week to schedule a viewing appointment.\n\nFor the unresponsive leads, I shared detailed information about the respective projects via WhatsApp and will follow up with them tomorrow.\n\nAdditionally, I followed up with Sarah, who viewed Eternity Heights last week. She has decided to proceed with purchasing a unit. However, she noted that the currently available units are not on her preferred floors, and she is therefore open to purchasing from Phase 2, which is yet to commence construction.\n','2026-01-26','Follow up with last week\'s clients \nCRM updates ','2026-01-26 18:26:59','2026-01-26 18:26:59'),(584,17,'DAILY ACTIVITY REPORT\nI  accomplished the following tasks today:\n- Prepared and disseminated the Monday review meeting minutes to the team, ensuring all members are informed and aligned\n- Updated the daily leads template and submitted it to Mr. Ken for thorough review and feedback, facilitating seamless follow-up and tracking\n- Provided comprehensive assistance to Miss Diana with uploading supplier products on the website, ensuring accuracy, timeliness, and optimal presentation\n- Rescheduled the planned shoots due to unforeseen priority tasks that necessitated Mr. Paddy\'s immediate attention, ensuring efficient resource allocation and prioritization\n\n','2026-01-26','','2026-01-26 18:55:06','2026-01-26 18:55:06'),(585,23,'Received 9 leads from Rashid\n3 were responsive\n1, Kirimi to confirm tomorrow morning if they can view green view in the afternoon. Subject to follow up in the morning.\nPurity and Jennifer asked for options to be shared then advise further\nLevix was to confirm if they had a meeting about extending their budget for the commercial rental they saw but was unreachable on phone. Subject to follow up tomorrow.\nMade follow up calls to previous clients. Sammy wants to view Greenview and Ruiru options on Thursday ','2026-01-26','','2026-01-26 19:45:49','2026-01-26 19:45:49'),(586,46,'-morning meeting in attendance.\n-3 viewing in parklands ngara.\n-follow up on 7 assigned leads.','2026-01-26','For every 100% leads assigned i must get one positive buyer.','2026-01-26 20:21:26','2026-01-26 20:21:26'),(587,15,'1. 31 new leads were allocated to the sales team to ensure prompt follow-ups, proper lead nurturing, and detailed engagement with potential clients. The objective is to qualify buyer interest, address inquiries effectively, and guide prospects toward scheduling site visits and eventual conversion.\n2. A carousel post featuring educative content on common mistakes buyers make when purchasing property was published, alongside one video showcasing a rental property, across all our social media platforms. This content was aimed at educating our audience, increasing engagement, and driving interest in both investment and rental opportunities.\n3. I further engaged with the consultant, who requested an in-depth analysis of the performance of the currently generated leads. As a result, the majority of the day was spent analyzing lead performance, compiling insights, and preparing a detailed report that included both performance findings and the proposals put forward by the sales team for improved lead quality and conversion.','2026-01-27','','2026-01-27 13:51:21','2026-01-27 13:51:21'),(588,29,'- Attended the morning team meeting where we shared our work plans for the day.\n- After, I made adjustments on the APP\'s product, supplier and contractors icons. I finished by midday and submitted to the developer progress group.\n- In the afternoon I edited a property reel for Brookside Drive in Westlands, submitted to the marketing group on completion.\n- As we neared the close of business, I began on the billboard designs .','2026-01-27','','2026-01-27 14:02:32','2026-01-27 14:02:32'),(589,27,'1. Today, early morning I was not feeling well and went to the hospital and was treated.\n2. I visited Tatu City for sourcing since the hospital was close by and I am in the process of getting consents for five of their projects. Probably tomorrow.\n3. Came back to the office and followed up on the 9 leads allocated for me and got a viewing tomorrow in the afternoon for Greenview.','2026-01-27','Nothing for now','2026-01-27 15:55:58','2026-01-27 15:55:58'),(590,24,'Attended the morning meeting with my team. We came up with a spread sheet to enable us collect properties in a systematic manner. I assigned Rosemary Kitisuru, Loresho, Tigoni and Kiambu Road to be filled by 17th Feb in addition to getting clients.\nWent for a meeting with the Developer and Landowner of the Kabete 4acres I had sourced last week. The Developer   requested for more documents to enable him do search before we proceed. To meet on 5th Feb to discuss further.\nOrganized for viewing tomorrow with the lease client at 2pm, Peponi Road and Manyani East Road.\nFollowed up the Muchai Road project where we organized a meeting at 11a.m.\nFollowed up on the StanChart  property where they accepted the offer of deducting 1% from the 5% facilitators fees and requested for a meeting on Thur 29th to further the negotiations.\nPlanned site visit to Tigoni on Thursday 10a,m with a developer who wants to take up the 10acres.','2026-01-27','','2026-01-27 16:16:45','2026-01-27 16:16:45'),(591,23,'Daily Work Report\nLeads Allocation\nTotal leads allocated: 8\n6 leads from Rashid\n2 leads from Joseph\nLead Engagement & Progress\nOut of the 6 Meta leads, 3 were responsive.\nClient Updates\nShamba\nRequirement: Rental townhouse in Lavington\nChallenge: Client’s budget is not feasible for Lavington\nAction Taken: Advised accordingly\nStatus: Client to consult with her husband to see if the budget can be adjusted\nClient – Townhouse (Lavington, Budget 6M)\nRequirement: Townhouse in Lavington at 6M\nAction Taken: Sourced options later in the day\nStatus: Options to be shared tomorrow during working hours\nElizabeth\nRequirement: Studio apartment for investment\nAction Taken: Shared available options\nStatus: Following up to set a physical meeting and site visits\nPurity\nPlanned Activity: Viewing at Green View\nUpdate: Viewing postponed to Saturday\nClient Feedback: Wants to compare Green View with other options\nStatus: Will advise after viewing Green View\nFollow-Ups conducted include purity who wants to view on Saturday. And Sandra who also wants to view on Saturday. Ustav also wants to view some options in kiambu road but is traveling until 8th Feb so he will confirm availability once he is back in the country.The rest are still subject to follow up so as to secure the right number of viewings','2026-01-27','','2026-01-27 17:30:25','2026-01-27 17:30:25'),(592,13,'1. Today after the morning meeting Paddy and I had a session to brainstorm on ideas of the APP cover since the one for yesterday was not very good, we came up with two ideas which he implemented and shared to the group\n2. I uploaded a listing for land  from Rosemary after she provided all the details as required.\n3.I received a listing from Rashid, I tried to upload it but I had challenges since the system was a bit down today, I will re do it tomorrow since it couldn\'t submit.\n4.I uploaded data for 1 contractor, he came to the office Yesterday  and shared information about his company via whatsapp.\n5.Mia and I assisted with duties at the reception to ensure smooth running of the office .','2026-01-27','','2026-01-27 18:17:05','2026-01-27 18:17:05'),(593,17,'\nDAILY ACTIVITY REPORT\nI have accomplished the following tasks today:\n- Prepared and disseminated the minutes of the morning marketing meeting to the team, ensuring all members are informed and aligned\n- Updated the leads template and submitted it to Mr. Ken for thorough review and feedback, facilitating seamless follow-up and tracking\n- Prepared two comprehensive scripts for tomorrow\'s shoot, ensuring clarity and alignment with our marketing objectives\n- Provided assistance with various office duties and supported Diana with data entry tasks, contributing to the team\'s overall productivity and efficiency\n\n','2026-01-27','','2026-01-27 19:08:08','2026-01-27 19:08:08'),(594,12,'\n---\n\nDaily Report\n\nToday, I was assigned 6 leads and later an additional 3 TikTok leads.\n\nI contacted the 6 assigned leads, out of which 3 turned responsive, and 2 successfully booked viewing appointments:\n\nMr. Paul scheduled a viewing for the first weekend of February to explore an off-plan one-bedroom project with high returns. I recommended Luminara as a suitable option.\n\nMr. Rodgers confirmed a viewing appointment for Saturday at Mogotio Oasis.\n\n\nRegarding the 3 TikTok leads, they were assigned late in the evening; therefore, I plan to follow up with calls tomorrow morning.\n\nI also followed up with Mr. Aden, who mentioned that he is currently in Mombasa but will be able to plan and attend a viewing by Thursday.\n\nAdditionally, I followed up with Azure Developers, where I successfully sourced information on their upcoming project.','2026-01-27','','2026-01-27 19:44:53','2026-01-27 19:44:53'),(595,11,'I began the day by chairing a morning meeting attended by Brian and Desmond. During the meeting, we reviewed the client leads allocated to them the previous day by Rashid. The discussion focused on lead responsiveness, conversion outcomes, client requirements, and challenges encountered while handling the assigned clients.\n\nThereafter, I participated in an interview with Isaiah alongside Joseph and Mr. Ken. Following the interview, a decision was made to proceed with Isaiah’s engagement, and he is scheduled to join the company effective 1st February.\n\nSubsequently, I attended a meeting convened by Mr. Ken, which was also attended by Joseph and Tasha. The meeting addressed internal matters relevant to ongoing and upcoming initiatives.\n\nLater in the day, I conducted a site viewing in Brookside with a client, Marcy, who had inquired about a townhouse for rent in the area, Taj prestige. We viewed the available unit, which she liked; however, as only one option was available, she requested additional alternatives for comparison. I will be sourcing and sharing more suitable options with her the following day.\n\nAfter the Brookside viewing, I proceeded to Tatu City together with Tasha to review a new residential project currently in its early stages. The project is located within a controlled gated community and offers integrated amenities, including a shopping mall, making it a potentially strong product for marketing. Due to the length of the presentation and the distance involved, I was unable to return to the office thereafter, and this marked the conclusion of the day’s activities.\n\nI also managed to check of my team\'s progress in their daily activities ','2026-01-27','','2026-01-27 20:38:16','2026-01-27 20:38:16'),(596,46,'-01/27/2026  Report.\n-8:30 attended the morning meeting for debriefing.\n-followed on the leads assigned by media team.\n-Had one  viewing with a client in search of one bedroom unit in kilimani and we have scheduled for 2 more viewing  before she can conclude. ','2026-01-26','-Approach each customer with the idea of helping him /her solve a problem or achieve a goal,not selling a product or service.\n','2026-01-28 06:42:41','2026-01-28 06:42:41'),(597,13,'1. I uploaded two listings for sale, from Dennis and Rashid since they provided all the requirements ,the photos and the project details.\n2.I added product data for 1 supplier as I was able to get the information about the products, product photo and the description as well.\n3.I did a follow up with the developer in regards to the changes he was working on, I shared with him the changes he needs to make on the APP , he is working on them.\n4.I assisted with office duties at the reception, attending to visitors and also my colleagues, for smooth running of the office.\n5.Paddy and I brainstormed on new ideas in regards to the homepage video. ','2026-01-28','','2026-01-28 13:55:29','2026-01-28 13:55:29'),(598,29,'- Attended the morning  marketing team meeting, shared on our work plans for the day.\n- I then went for a shoot at Muthithi road next to Hyatt regency with Mia.\n- After that, we headed to Brickwood in Kilimani for the captital vista ground breaking.\n- In the afternoon, we proceeded to a scheduled shoot at Loresho springs. we did land content then back to the office.\n- I edited a video for Diamond Mango and submitted to Rashid for posting.','2026-01-28','','2026-01-28 13:58:08','2026-01-28 13:58:08'),(599,15,'1. Assigned 8 leads to the sales team for follow-ups, with the objective of nurturing prospects, addressing inquiries, and moving potential clients closer to site visits and conversion.\n2. Posted one video highlighting the off-plan project I attended today. The visit was facilitated by the developers, who invited me to gain early insights into the project’s market positioning, key selling points, and investment value, enabling accurate and informed promotion to potential buyers.\n3. engaged with the consultant in order to figure out a way of incorporating more performing reel into paid lead campaigns we currently running .','2026-01-28','','2026-01-28 14:14:17','2026-01-28 14:14:17'),(600,24,'Attended the morning meeting with my team where I advised Rosemary to ensure her report is submitted daily and on time to ensure she doesn\'t get to the last minute rush.\nHeld a meeting with Mr.Edmond and Mr.Vincent, 0.5acres Muchai Road where the proposal changed from a Jv to a sale of 170Million. We are waiting for the offer letter before we proceed by 29th Jan 2026.\nTook a client for viewing at Peponi road 0.8acres lease going for 1.3Million. Client is interested in the property and requested to meet with the landlord by 29th Jan.\nOrganized for two photoshoots of my properties along Muthithi road and Loresho with the media team.\nTook the client to Manyani East but he didnt like the office structure.\nSourced 1acre at Ndemi Road off Brookside Drive going for 550Million suitable for high-rise Apartments.\nFollowed on the requests for Runda 10acres for Townhouses and shared the options I got along Glory Road.\nUpdated the CRM.','2026-01-28','','2026-01-28 16:52:02','2026-01-28 16:52:02'),(601,12,'\nDaily Client Report\n\nToday, I was assigned two clients, one of whom turned responsive.\n\nMr. Felix is looking for a studio unit to let in Westlands or Kilimani, with easy accessibility to Upper Hill, where he works. He is ready to move in next month.\n\n\nLater in the day, I attended the ground-breaking ceremony for Capital Vista in Kilimani, a prime development that is especially attractive to clients seeking investment-focused units.\n\nI also followed up with Mr. David, Charles, Mohamed, and Faith, all of whom successfully booked their viewing appointments, scheduled between tomorrow and Saturday.\n','2026-01-28','','2026-01-28 18:53:35','2026-01-28 18:53:35'),(602,17,'\nSummary of Activities:\n- Updated and shared the leads spreadsheet with Mr. Ken Huang, ensuring all leads are up-to-date and follow-ups are scheduled.\n- Conducted site visits for land properties:\n    - First shoot: Muthithi Road - inspected land and captured necessary photos for listing.\n    - Second shoot: Loresho Spring - assessed land and gathered details for potential clients.\n- Returned to the office at 2:30pm and complete some few pending tasks.\n\nLet me know if this fits or if you need further adjustments! ? Want me to add anything?','2026-01-28','','2026-01-28 19:51:35','2026-01-28 19:51:35'),(603,46,'-8:30 attended morning meeting.\n-attended capital vista ground breaking with the marketing team.\n-cold marketing for leads  assigned and referrals .','2026-01-28','prioritizing relationship with clients rather than transactional connection.','2026-01-28 20:04:22','2026-01-28 20:04:22'),(604,11,'I began the day with a morning team meeting attended by Dennis, Desmond, and Brian. The meeting focused on team coordination and ongoing assignments.\n\nThereafter, I conducted a second interview with Purity in the presence of Mr. Ken and Joseph. The interview was completed as part of the recruitment process.\n\nLater in the day, I proceeded to Tigoni with a client to view Joy’s 10-acre parcel of land that is available for sale. The potential buyer expressed strong interest in the property, and a follow-up viewing has been scheduled for Friday, during which he will be accompanied by his business partners.\n\nFollowing the site visit, I returned to the office and carried out client follow-up calls. Due to the distance involved, I arrived back at the office later in the day but ensured that necessary follow-ups were completed.\n\nAt 5:15 p.m., I attended a meeting at Taj Prestige in Brookside with a landlord who is planning to sell their townhouse. The property is priced at KES 85 million. We reached an agreement on the engagement terms, including a commission rate of 3%, and I took photos of the unit for marketing purposes.\n\nI concluded the day after finalizing the agreement and documenting the property details for marketing.','2026-01-28','','2026-01-28 22:25:05','2026-01-28 22:25:05'),(605,23,'Leads Assigned\n2 leads assigned by Rashid\n1 lead assigned by Joseph\nClient Follow-ups & Meetings\nA Somali client called back expressing interest in purchasing a house in Karen.\nClient requested a brief meeting at the office on Friday afternoon for an overview of properties in Karen.\nStakeholder Engagement\nMet with Levix to discuss feedback from other stakeholders.\nFeedback received indicated that the proposed rent is significantly above their budget.\nAdditional concern was the cost implication of required partitioning, making the option less viable.\nSite Visits\nVisited Capital Vista in Kilimani.\nClient Requests / Viewings\nJenifer expressed interest in viewing a studio apartment at Wilma Towers.\nViewing scheduled for Thursday, subject to confirmation.\n','2026-01-28','','2026-01-29 06:01:15','2026-01-29 06:01:15'),(606,27,'1. Today, we had our usual BEKE departmental staff meeting, and we discussed about our viewings done and the ones scheduled, possible closures for this week, and how to source for listings.\n\n2. Followed up with all the leads allocated by Rashid and Joseph and 50% of them responded on their enquiries of rentals and properties to buy.\n\n3. Thereafter, I went with my clients for the following site visits:\n1. Viewed Oaklands Residences with Michel on the 4-bedroom apartments available for rent.\n2. Viewed Runda Paradise Phase 2 on the fully furnished Villa available for rent.\n3. Viewed Palm Valley for the 4-bedroom unfurnished Townhouse available for rent.\n4. Viewed Oak and Ivy on the 4-bedroom spacious apartments available for rent.\n5. Went to Luminara for viewing with Mr Ben Ireri, after visiting our office, and he liked the project.\n6. Went for viewing with Ibrahim Hussein to view to plots of land which were provided by our very own Joy Kemunto.\n\n4. Thereafter, came back to the office and followed up with my pending leads and office work and errands to complete.','2026-01-29','All is well for now.','2026-01-29 15:44:04','2026-01-29 15:44:04'),(609,23,'Daily Work Report\nLeads & Follow-Ups\nReceived 2 leads from the marketing team.\nKavu:  Interested in a 2-bedroom rental in Lang’ata. However, we currently do not have rental listings in Lang’ata as it does not fall within our up-market focus.\nSecond lead: Not responsive. Follow-up call to be made.\nClient Meetings\nHeld an office meeting with Ben, a client referred by Dennis.\nClient is interested in real estate investment opportunities.\nPresented ideal investment options and discussed alternative real estate investment opportunities.\nProperty Viewing\nConducted a viewing at Luminara.\nClient selected a unit and made an offer.\nRequested a second viewing on Sunday with family before making a final commitment. Ben also wants to view Greenview next week. Will confirm on Monday on the day that will be ideal to view\nFollow-Ups & Upcoming Activities\nMade follow-up calls to clients.\n1 site visit confirmed for tomorrow with Jennifer for a Kilimani studio (rental','2026-01-29','','2026-01-29 16:44:30','2026-01-29 16:44:30'),(61