,'\n\nDaily Lead & Client Report\n\nToday, I was assigned two leads.\n\nRachel is keenly looking to purchase a 3-bedroom apartment in the Lower Kabete area. I shared two suitable options with her and will follow up tomorrow.\n\nMercy expressed strong interest in the Greenville Garden Villa. I shared detailed information with her via WhatsApp and will follow up with her tomorrow to get her feedback.\n\nMr. Mohammed called to confirm a viewing appointment scheduled for tomorrow to view available options in Kileleshwa.\n\nCharles also rescheduled his viewing appointment to tomorrow afternoon.\n','2026-01-29','','2026-01-29 19:32:57','2026-01-29 19:32:57'),(614,46,'I attended the debriefing morning meeting at 8:30am.From 9:00am i did follow ups on pending clients and also engaged with the leads clients assigned to me by marketing team which were 5 in total.Three out of 5 are interested in a 4 bedroom villas .Mr.Empire Adis was travelling to Uganda today and will be back on 12 /2/2026 and we can plan on site visit from then.Patel Krushant(client number 2) will upadate when his available for viewing of the 4 bedroom.Client(3)Mrs.Esther ,requested i remind her tomorrow.Client(4)Is an agent and was looking on behalf, i adviced him in regards to onboarding his client   and he will update on the viewing date.Client(5) Mr.Mshai stated that the price is above his budget and i shared more options  of what\'s available per his preferences.By 12,i  went for land viewing /sourcing at kiambu for a 100 by 100 plot,the agent in contact with the owner will share the pricing tomorrow.Around 3 pm i met up with my client(Teacher Biene)who viewed greenview villas liked them but skeptical about Kiambu road traffic jam,due to her work schedule and kids pick up zone,she requested i share more options with in runda,paradise place,Iguta estate and Rosslyn she might extend her budget if she\'s satified with what we offer  that aligns with her preferences.Later  outsorced for 1.2 acreas in Runda and viewed,will meet with the owner tomorrow and he will update on the pricing.Also outsorced for two more properties along runda/ruaka road ,3 bedrooms though they aren\'t completely done and the owner will advice on the prices once complete by next week.\n\n','2026-01-29','work smart not hard.','2026-01-29 22:08:14','2026-01-29 22:08:14'),(615,13,'1.I assisted in admin duties at the reception, I assisted my colleagues and visitors as well.\n2. I uploaded two listings for land and sale, from Dennis and Desmond, they provided all the requirements.\n3.I prepared PPT for January review as requested by Joseph.\n4. Paddy assisted me to resize photos that I used to create profiles for new suppliers.','2026-01-30','','2026-01-30 13:33:46','2026-01-30 13:33:46'),(616,29,'- Attended the morning marketing meeting, we shared our various work plans for the day.\n-After the meeting, I worked on our social media handles and submitted the file to Mr. Ken\n- We then had office fun and educational content with the help of Rashid, we managed to do three videos.\n- I managed to edit to edit the first vide where Carol was doing comparisons of popular neighbourhoods in Nairobi and submitted by close of business.','2026-01-30','','2026-01-30 14:08:59','2026-01-30 14:08:59'),(617,15,'- A total of 33 leads were assigned to the sales team for follow-up and engagement.\nThe objective was to ensure timely contact with potential clients, assess their level of interest, and guide them toward property viewings or suitable alternatives based on their preferences. The sales team was instructed to prioritize responsiveness, proper qualification of leads, and consistent follow-ups to improve conversion rates\n- Helped  Paddy and Mia during a content shoot for the Friday Fun Reels, focusing on creating engaging and relatable video content to boost audience interaction and brand visibility across our social media platforms.\nLater in the day, collaborated with Carol to produce an educational content piece, aimed at informing and educating our audience on key real estate insights, positioning the brand and increasing views .\n- The posts were scheduled and shared to maintain consistent brand presence, increase engagement, and support ongoing content campaigns aimed at audience growth and lead nurturing.','2026-01-30','','2026-01-30 14:11:12','2026-01-30 14:11:12'),(618,24,'Attended the morning meeting where we discussed the various schedules for the day.\nWent for viewing at Nyari 14acres sale with the client. He liked the property  and is going to give an offer letter but for 10acres.\nI took him to another property  behind Village Narket 1.6acres selling at 400Million but the client didn\'t like it.\nCame back to the office and held a meeting with agents who have properties  for JV and Lease at Redhill road. Planned for viewing next week on Tuesday,\nHeld a monthly meeting with the boss where we discussed the progress so far.\nAt 3pm took Mr.Mumin for viewing at Lavington James Gichuru road . Client liked the property and promised to give a feedback by Monday\nWorked on the CRM to update clients.','2026-01-30','','2026-01-30 17:05:43','2026-01-30 17:05:43'),(619,27,'1. Early morning BEKE departmental sales meeting where we planned our today\'s work plan and the viewings we have had so far.\n\n2. Followed up with all the leads I was allocated today and one of them, Mr. John viewed Greenview Villas today and put an offer for a 4-bedroom villa.\n\n3. Before the viewing I went for sourcing at Diamond Bay, and Misty Springs. I got availables at Diamond Bay.','2026-01-30','All good.','2026-01-30 17:30:59','2026-01-30 17:30:59'),(620,12,'\n\nDaily Report\n\nToday, I was assigned three leads, all of whom I am scheduled to call tomorrow for follow-up.\n\nI conducted two site visits with Ahmed and Faith, during which we reviewed the respective property options.\n\nLater in the day, I updated and worked on my CRM, ensuring all client interactions and lead details were properly recorded.\n\nIn the afternoon, I followed up with clients who have confirmed site visits for tomorrow:\n\nBurhan confirmed a site visit at Eternity, Kitusuru, scheduled for 2:00 PM.\n\nBrian confirmed a morning site visit at Oak & Ivy Villa.\n\nI also have an office meeting scheduled with Saloni.','2026-01-30','','2026-01-30 19:37:28','2026-01-30 19:37:28'),(621,46,'-Had the morning meeting with the sales team at 8:30 am,after that i followed up on  pending leads.By 12:00,went to pre-view Anaya 4 bedroom villas in paradise lot  and shared with my client but she couldnt manage to come for viewing immediatelly and she will reschedule either Saturday or from next week,she was atleast able to view palm valley and later Rossyln lone tree but still not content .While at it,i sourced for 1/4 plot in kasarini in runda,and the agent will advice on price tomorrow.Later outsourced for another 1/4 plot in mutitu ridge going for 25million.\nLater update the crm.','2026-01-30','it\' s the zeal to grow and attain financial freedom.','2026-01-30 20:16:13','2026-01-30 20:16:13'),(622,46,'-Attended morning meeting debriefing 9:30 am.\n-From 10:00 am, i followed up on assigned leads for villas .\n-From 11:45,went to the field for sourcing and was able  to get 2 more plots in Rossyln Trio Estate(0.6 ha) selling at 125 million and (0.1965ha) selling at 100 million.\n-Also viewed for a 4 bedroom  villa with my client(teacher Biene) in Rosslyn Trio Estate but she didn\'t like it cause it needs more furninishing and that\'s an extra  cost on her budget  so,will out outsource for more options for her.\n\n\n\n\n-','2026-01-31','schedule and implement as many  viewing as possible.','2026-02-02 04:49:55','2026-02-02 04:49:55'),(623,15,'-Assigned a total of 53 leads to the sales team. This higher volume was a strategic allocation to ensure all leads generated over Sunday, when assignments were not conducted, were promptly followed up on, maintaining momentum and maximizing conversion opportunities.\n-Posted two videos across our social platforms: one focused on welcoming the new month and the other highlighting Nairobi’s top neighborhood insights. This was further reinforced by an e-card, rounding off the content with a cohesive and engaging brand message.\n-Collaborated with Mia, Paddy, and the Meta consultant to develop strong video hooks for content scheduled to be shot today. The focus was on crafting compelling openings that are optimized for both paid ads and organic posting, ensuring the videos are engaging, relevant, and conversion-focused from the first few seconds.','2026-02-02','','2026-02-02 14:04:29','2026-02-02 14:04:29'),(624,29,'- Attended the morning general meeting, where we shared our goals for the month, plan for the week and the day.\n- After the meeting, we headed for a land shoot at processional way with Mia\n- In the afternoon, we headed to the cube to do an offplan shoot','2026-02-02','','2026-02-02 14:04:56','2026-02-02 14:04:56'),(625,24,'Attended the morning meeting where discussed how to handled and categorize various clients.\nHeld a training with James the new employee to show him how to do reports. He is more inclined into selling of apartments than he is of land.\nConducted an interview with one candidate but she wasn’t a good fit to the company.\nMade follow up calls to the existing clients to follow up progress of the purchase so far and updated in the CRM.\nCalled the 3leads from Tiktok. One was off, the other was way below the budget and didn’t want any other options and the other one wanted property in Uganda. Reported the same to Mr.Joseph.\nReceived enquiries for Kitisuru 2acres sale for Townhouses and Spring Valley, 1acre for apartments to which I did sourcing and planned to view tomorrow.\nWent for viewing at 88Kikuyu 10acres Townhouses development of 3,4&5Bedroom. It’s a good project I can recommend to our portfolio. The Developer to visit the office tomorrow for further negotiations on commission.\n','2026-02-02','','2026-02-02 16:03:26','2026-02-02 16:03:26'),(626,27,'1. A new week and we had our vibrant BEKE staff meeting for all and a presentation on how to manage our leads and the sales.\n\n2. Today, I had planned to spend the whole day following up with my leads and the ones allocated by Rashid. I managed to get scheduled viewings for this weekend.\n\n3. Mr John, today viewed Royal Green Villas in Kamangu, Kikuyu and he liked it he will give a feedback tomorrow on which house he has liked.\n\n4. Projects details sharing to my leads and responding to their enquiries.','2026-02-02','New year. New blessings.','2026-02-02 16:29:27','2026-02-02 16:29:27'),(627,13,'1.I attended morning meeting . Joseph presented to us  new information about clients categories  and their different needs,we were encouraged to do regular follow ups with our clients.\n2. Mia and I did an orientation to our our new colleagues,we encouraged them to always keep time since at Beke time management is Key.\n3.I created accounts for the new colleagues and shared with them their login credentials and also their company emails.\n4.I assisted my colleagues and visitors at the reception for smooth running of activities.\n5.I created 1 supplier profile and also added their products to make the information complete.\n6.I received listings from Rosemary but she is still to provide quality photos so that I can upload them,she agreed to do so tomorrow.','2026-02-02','Learning from all my colleagues so that I can become even better.','2026-02-02 18:36:16','2026-02-02 18:36:16'),(628,12,'\n\n> Daily Report\n\nToday, I conducted a site visit with Mr. Andrew at Adorn Homes to view the available three-bedroom unit for rent. While he appreciated the visit, he was not satisfied with the space. He remains open to alternative options, which I am currently sourcing.\n\nAdditionally, I was assigned eleven clients, all of whom I successfully contacted and updated accordingly in the CRM system.\n\nI also followed up with Saloni regarding an offer she received for a unit at Luminara. She indicated that she would like to compare this option with two other properties before making a final decision on the Luminara offer.\n\n','2026-02-02','viewing appointment with a client looking for the 270k rental unit in Kiambu ','2026-02-02 19:12:17','2026-02-02 19:12:17'),(629,17,'\nTasks Completed:\n    Leads Update: Updated and shared the leads Excel sheet with the sales team, ensuring accuracy and timely follow-ups\n   New Employee Orientation: Conducted a comprehensive orientation for new employees, covering company policies, team introductions, and job expectations\n    Land Shoot: Attended the land shoot at Processional Way, capturing high-quality visuals for marketing materials\n    Office Duties: Completed outstanding office tasks.\n','2026-02-02','','2026-02-02 19:25:25','2026-02-02 19:25:25'),(630,11,'I began the day by chairing the morning team meeting, which was attended by the full team. Following the meeting, Joseph delivered a PowerPoint presentation focused on client handling, during which we discussed best practices and areas for improvement in managing client engagements.\n\nThereafter, I conducted an interview with Catherine alongside Joy. The candidate was assessed and found not to be a suitable fit, as we are seeking an individual with experience in the upper-market areas, which the candidate was not sufficiently familiar with. Consequently, we will not be proceeding further with the application.\n\nSubsequently, I joined a meeting with Desmond and his client to assist in refining the client’s property search. The client was initially open to villas along Kiambu Road but later indicated that his colleagues were also interested in options within Kilimani and Westlands. I supported the discussion by providing suitable alternatives within the client’s criteria and budget. As a result, we successfully secured a site viewing, which Desmond will conduct on Saturday.\n\nLater in the day, I attended a site viewing in Lower Kabete with a client, Suresh. The client had initially inquired about townhouses for rent in Brookside; however, the Brookside option was above his budget. We proceeded to view an alternative in Lower Kabete priced at KES 270,000. While the client appreciated the pricing, he found the unit to be older than his preference and requested that I continue sourcing more suitable options.\n\nAfter returning to the office, I later proceeded for another site visit in Parklands. I am currently assisting a client who is looking for a two-bedroom apartment for rent near MP Shah Hospital and Aga Khan Hospital, with the intention of furnishing the unit. I visited three properties and successfully secured one suitable listing:\n	•	Property: Skyway Apartments, 6th Avenue\n	•	Type: Two-bedroom\n	•	Rent: KES 85,000\n\nI shared the details of this listing with my client and will also forward the information to Diana.','2026-02-02','','2026-02-02 20:22:09','2026-02-02 20:22:09'),(631,23,'Leads Assigned:\nTotal leads received: 10\n8 from Rashid\n2 from Joseph\n1 repeat lead: Jenifer\nClient Engagement:\n3 clients were responsive\nLead Updates:\nMomo – Interested in properties for investment purposes. Shared multiple investment options for consideration.\nJoseph – Interested in Greenview. Actively pushing to schedule a property viewing.\nMeetings:\n1 physical meeting held at the office with Ehsan.\nInterested in viewing Greenview on Saturday.\nHe represents a company with multiple directors who are also interested in purchasing units, mainly in the Kileleshwa area.\nThe directors are Pakistani nationals currently living in Kenya.\nEhsan will share my contact details with his colleagues so they can provide their requirements and receive a detailed breakdown.\nNext Steps:\nFollow up with Joseph and Momo to progress viewings and investment discussions.\nPrepare Greenview viewing for Ehsan on Saturday.\nAwait contact from Ehsan’s colleagues for further engagement','2026-02-02','Viewing at Greenview\nLead follow up sourcing along kiambu road','2026-02-03 04:56:47','2026-02-03 04:56:47'),(632,49,'I did report to work and being the first day My collegue and I ,who reported yesterday for the first time were take through an orientation about the company\'s expectation of us. We were also taken through the CRM and taught how to input details and write reports . We were also informed about the importance of writing reports on a daily and time keeping at the office. I did receive 3 leads yesterday. I called the 3 and i have updated on the CRM. I am arranging viewing with the 2 and 1 hasn\'t picked up yet. We also visited Mogotio Oasis and Luminara projects in the afternoon to converse ourselves with the projects . ','2026-02-02','','2026-02-03 07:34:48','2026-02-03 07:34:48'),(633,27,'1. Early morning BEKE staff meeting and we talked about our offers, the leads we received, and what are our plans for today. We also shared amongst ourselves the listings we are in need of in order to close a sale or a rental.\n\n2. Followed up with all the new leads I have been allocated by Rashid and Joseph, and their response is as below:\na) Zaira Rasool is interested in a studio or a 1-bedroom apartment and with a budget of Kshs3M,\nb) Stella is interested in a ready 1-bedroom apartment in Westlands to buy,\nc) Lavin is looking to purchase a 4-bedroom apartment in Kilimani or Kileleshwa and has a budget of up to Kshs30M.\n\n3. I still followed up with my previous leads and shared their respective project details via Whatsapp.\n\n4. Today, my viewings were postponed, and I had to keep on familiarising with the new listings in our website.','2026-02-03','All is well','2026-02-03 13:43:39','2026-02-03 13:43:39'),(634,51,'Made calls for the 4 given clients, leads shared from Social Media \nGetting acquainted with the CRM, listings and the work systems \nManagerial meeting from 2.30 to 4pm regarding the team\'s discrepancies\n\n\n','2026-02-03','','2026-02-03 13:49:47','2026-02-03 13:49:47'),(635,29,'- Had the morning marketing team meeting, discussed our work plans for the day\n- After the meeting, I began working on a carrousel design for Brookside Drive townhouses in westlands.\n- I also did a compilation a behind the scenes video for our January video contents, both office shoots and scripted shoots.\n- I began editing a property video we did yesterday at Processional way, a 2acres parcel of land.','2026-02-03','','2026-02-03 13:51:25','2026-02-03 13:51:25'),(636,49,'Today I got 3 leads :2 via meta and 1 via tiktok. The 2 are interested in purchasing villas ,Greenview Villas. on e of them had earlier indicated he may get time to visit but unfortunately it wasn\'t possible. I\'ll continue following up . The 3rd client was looking for an Apartment to sell,however she is yet to respond to calls or text. we also managed to visit Golden Mansion Apartments in the afternoon ','2026-02-03','','2026-02-03 13:58:20','2026-02-03 13:58:20'),(637,50,'made initial calls with two clients from leads received. \none was not picking after several calls. the other, we had a conversation and I shared details on their inquiry. he is to be followed up tomorrow.\nalso sourced a unit for a client. will be doing a due diligence on the same before presenting to the client.\nalso had several calls with my contacts in regards to inquiries that we have. have a received a positive feedback on availability of land in spring valley. am in the process of vetting before further engagements,\nalso managed to visit golden mansions to familiarize with the project.','2026-02-03','','2026-02-03 14:00:15','2026-02-03 14:00:15'),(638,24,'Had a client meeting in the morning with HK Developers at 9a.m in there office. The director wanted exact timelines of when the property is going to be available and ready for use. By 16th February the property should be ready.\nHeld another conference call with the lease property client and landowner regarding the new property on General Mathenge for lease at 1Million per month. Organized for viewing on 4th Jan at 11a.m.\nOrganized for viewing of 0.75acres at spring valley for apartments sale with a Developer.\nReceived emails and sent some with the Muchai Road property Architect and offer letter for 57Westlands road offer.\nFollowed up with my previous client on their requests and upcoming requests that I worked on.\nGuided my team on how to do a proper sourcing and how to select suitable properties.','2026-02-03','','2026-02-03 15:20:31','2026-02-03 15:20:31'),(639,13,'1.Today I uploaded 3 listings from my colleagues,Brian and Carol they provided the required information making the process smooth.\n2.Mia and I assisted in duties at the reception,we assisted our colleagues and also visitors.\n3.I did an orientation for Tasha ,I assisted her understand the CRM,I also shared with her our company policy of keeping time everyday since it is very important.\n4.I got in touch with the developer to assist us in linking our CRM to our Meta account,he got in touch with Rashid,and he has started working on it.','2026-02-03','Learning each day.','2026-02-03 15:26:29','2026-02-03 15:26:29'),(640,23,'Leads Assigned\n3 leads assigned by Rashid\n1 lead assigned by Joseph\nLead Follow-Ups & Engagement\nFrom the 3 Meta leads, 1 lead was responsive.\nClient name: Hudo\nRequirement: 4-bedroom house for rent in Brookside\nAction taken: Shared property details and videos\nProperty quoted at: 400,000\nTikTok lead\nClient name: Lauryn\nRequirement: 2-bedroom apartment for rent\nPreferred locations: Mombasa Road or Thika Road\nStatus: No suitable listings available as the areas are not upmarket\nCRM & Admin Updates\nUpdated the CRM system\nAdded several previously pending clients\nLead Revival & Follow-Ups\nRevived old leads still subject to follow-up\nIncluded leads obtained from Village Market','2026-02-03','','2026-02-03 17:49:56','2026-02-03 17:49:56'),(641,17,' Tasks Completed:\n   Marketing Meeting Minutes: Shared minutes of the morning marketing meeting with the Beke marketing group, ensuring all team members are informed and aligned\n Leads Template Update: Updated the daily leads template and shared with Mr. Ken, providing an accurate record , meta we had 14 leads and Tik Tok  5leads making it a total of 19 leads.\n    Lead Assignment Report: Prepared an Excel sheet detailing total leads assigned to each sales agent (Oct 2025 - Jan 2026) and submitted to Mr. Joseph for review and analysis\n   Office Support: Assisted Miss Diana with office duties, ensuring seamless operations and supporting team efficiency\n   Shoot Preparation: Prepared for tomorrow\'s shoots as required, ensuring all necessary materials and equipment are ready.\n\n','2026-02-03','','2026-02-03 19:20:47','2026-02-03 19:20:47'),(642,12,'\nDaily Activity Report\n\nToday, I was assigned one client from TikTok who is seeking a commercial space in Kitengela. She did not respond to calls but replied to messages. I will follow up again tomorrow.\n\nI also re-engaged most of my previously inactive clients from last month via WhatsApp and updated their current status in the CRM.\n\nI managed to speak with Mitchell, who confirmed her availability to view Luminara later this month. She mentioned that she will reach out once she returns to Nairobi.\n\nAdditionally, I contacted Savanna, who indicated that she will be available next week to attend a site visit together with her husband.\n\nI followed up with Saloni, who viewed Luminara over the weekend. She requested additional options for comparison and expressed interest in viewing Golden Mansion within the course of the week.\n\n\n','2026-02-03','','2026-02-03 19:44:23','2026-02-03 19:44:23'),(643,15,'- A total of 14 leads generated up to 10:00 a.m. were assigned to the sales team. Ads were subsequently paused due to insufficient balance in the Meta Ads account.\n- Prepared the January leads performance report and shared it with the consultant. In the same regard, I also submitted a request for the February ad spend allocation.\n- Posted two engaging video contents and one carousel specifically promoting the Brookside townhouses for sale. The content was designed to highlight key features, location appeal, and value proposition of the project, with the aim of driving inquiries, boosting engagement, and supporting ongoing lead generation efforts across our social media platforms.','2026-02-03','','2026-02-03 22:54:58','2026-02-03 22:54:58'),(644,11,'I began the day by chairing the morning team meeting, which was attended by both the Lands team and the Residential Sales team. During the meeting, we discussed various operational matters, including lead handling, sourcing of listings, and overall team performance.\n\nImmediately after the meeting, I proceeded for a site viewing in Brookside with my client, Jay. We viewed a townhouse in Brookside; however, the client did not find it suitable, as he is looking for a newer and more modern unit. He indicated that his children attend school at ISK in Kitisuru and outlined his preferred locations as Kitisuru, Spring Valley, and Lower Kabete, with a budget of KES 450,000 per month. I will be sourcing suitable options within these areas and criteria.\n\nThereafter, I returned to the office and made follow-up calls to several clients. I also continued updating the CRM, focusing on uploading leads that had not previously been captured in the system.\n\nLater in the day, I held a follow-up meeting with the team to address gaps in CRM usage. It was noted that some team members had not uploaded most of their client leads. Following the discussion, we agreed that all leads, whether serious or non-serious must be fully captured in the CRM. A deadline of Thursday, end of day, was set for completion.\n\nAdditionally, I attended a managers’ meeting with Joy, Joseph and Tasha. We discussed the current lead situation and strategies to ensure diligent CRM usage by all agents. We also agreed on key client and deal details that should consistently be captured on the CRM to improve visibility, coordination, and overall team efficiency, particularly for high-value clients.','2026-02-03','','2026-02-04 05:07:38','2026-02-04 05:07:38'),(645,46,'-Attended the morning meeting.\n-updated Diana on the properties i outsourced  for listing purpose.\n-9:30  i had a land viewing /sourcing of 2.5 acres in old kitusuru estate selling at 230 million \n-Followed up on pending and assigned leads for villas \n-Worked on enquiries from my online platforms and still sourcing for more land as per clients enquiries.\n-to update my crm.','2026-02-03','more efforts on sealing a deal.','2026-02-04 07:55:46','2026-02-04 07:55:46'),(646,27,'1. Morning BEKE staff meeting for all of us and we discussed about our plans for today, and any help that we require.\n\n2. Today, I had to spend the whole day in the office whereby I followed up with all the 3 leads I was allocated today by Caroline, and on my previous leads. All the remarks and activities have been captured in the CRM.\n\n3. Familiarization of our listed projects especially the ones in Ruiru, for both apartments and Villas.','2026-02-04','All is well.','2026-02-04 13:37:06','2026-02-04 13:37:06'),(647,50,'new potential clients called today(11). shared all information as requested by clients.\nwas not able to visit the spring valley since was not able to vet the agent who had the land.\nattended the training on Berkeley project.\nfollowed up on yesterday\'s clients.\n','2026-02-04','','2026-02-04 13:44:43','2026-02-04 13:44:43'),(648,29,'- We had a joint morning meeting where everyone shared their work plans for the day. \n- After the meeting, Rashid, Mia and I went for an offplan shoot at The cube in Riverside to do a shoot explaining the Cheval project. We aim to produce three creatives from that.\n- We then came back to the office in the afternoon. I edited a render property for Cheval and submitted to Rashid by close of business.','2026-02-04','','2026-02-04 14:02:31','2026-02-04 14:02:31'),(649,15,'- No leads were assigned today from Meta, as all campaigns remain temporarily paused pending the allocation and approval of the February advertising budget. Lead generation activities will resume immediately once the budget allocation is confirmed.\n- Accompanied Mia and Paddy to the Cheval shoot in Riverside, where we executed and acted on the script that had been earlier brainstormed and aligned with the consultant during the morning strategy session.\n- Successfully published two video posts and one carousel post across all our social media platforms, ensuring consistent brand visibility and audience engagement. The content was aligned with ongoing marketing objectives and scheduled to support active campaigns and organic reach.','2026-02-04','','2026-02-04 14:07:21','2026-02-04 14:07:21'),(650,24,'Attended the morning meeting where we discussed the importance of having all the team members updating the leads to the CRM daily.\nHeld a meeting with my team members where I allocated them tasks of sourcing along Spring Valley and Kitisuru and follow up on leads assigned.\nFollowed up the 5leads shared and updated them to the CRM.\nFollowed up on the previous requests for lease Iin Westland/Lavington and JV in Kilimani.\nHeld a meeting with the owner of Land Muththi Road, Hyatt and Tausi  Lane to discuss how we can partner and push for a sale of her property.\nWent for viewing at Redhill Link road property for lease with a Developer, Mumin where he promised to give feedback by tomorrow.\n','2026-02-04','','2026-02-04 15:15:34','2026-02-04 15:15:34'),(651,23,'Received two leads from Caro regarding the Brookside rental; however, neither lead was responsive.\nUpdated my CRM with the latest client information and activity.\nMade follow-up calls with previous clients who had scheduled viewings for February. One client has confirmed a viewing on Saturday at 10:00 a.m. They are interested in Eternity Heights, Kitisuru.\nMina, who had previously shown interest in Luminara but was out of the country, requested time until the weekend to confirm her return travel dates to Nairobi.\nAttended a meeting in Upper Hill for one of the shortlisted projects that has not yet been viewed, Golf Scape Residency. The project offers 1, 2, and 3-bedroom units. The meeting was held with the developer and attended by Caro, Tasha, and myself','2026-02-04','','2026-02-04 16:28:41','2026-02-04 16:28:41'),(652,23,'Received two leads from Caro regarding the Brookside rental; however, neither lead was responsive.\nUpdated my CRM with the latest client information and activity.\nMade follow-up calls with previous clients who had scheduled viewings for February. One client has confirmed a viewing on Saturday at 10:00 a.m. They are interested in Eternity Heights, Kitisuru.\nMina, who had previously shown interest in Luminara but was out of the country, requested time until the weekend to confirm her return travel dates to Nairobi.\nAttended a meeting in Upper Hill for one of the shortlisted projects that has not yet been viewed, Golf Scape Residency. The project offers 1, 2, and 3-bedroom units. The meeting was held with the developer and attended by Caro, Tasha, and myself\n\n','2026-02-04','','2026-02-04 16:31:35','2026-02-04 16:31:35'),(653,51,'8.30am daily meeting \n9- 10am meeting with team regarding the projects to advertise and made a list of those projects. \n-Sourced some townhouses in Runda. \n-Viewed Golfscape residence along Muchai road, near Ngong road \n- Managed to view a 2 bedroom in Tigoni for rent ','2026-02-04','','2026-02-04 18:20:20','2026-02-04 18:20:20'),(654,12,'\n---\n\nToday, I successfully scheduled an office meeting with Mr. Fred regarding his client, who is seeking a half-acre parcel along Kiambu Road. I shared one suitable option, and the client expressed openness to reviewing additional alternatives and is available for a site visit on Friday.\n\nI also followed up with previous leads. Savanna confirmed her availability for a site visit next Thursday, which she will attend together with her husband.\n\nAdditionally, I updated the CRM with all pending leads to ensure accurate and up-to-date records.\n\nLater in the evening, I received a call from Mr. George, who had previously shown interest in the Kiambu Greenville Garden Villa. He requested a site visit at 5:10 p.m. I referred him to the site, where he was assisted by the site sales representative, Mr. Dennis.','2026-02-04','','2026-02-04 18:27:59','2026-02-04 18:27:59'),(655,13,'1.We had a general meeting in the office, Joseph shared with us about what they discussed yesterday,it was agreesd that all clients need to be updated in the CRM irregardless of their priority A,B,C,D are all important.\n2.I assisted at the reception to ensure smooth running of tasks that needed assistance,from my colleagues and visitors as well.\n3.Today after Annastacia shared a concern that she noticed on the website,the location issue,I tried to sort it out since it\'s important to our clients,I managed to arrange the locations of different projects well,her feedback is good and I am improving,Mia will assist me tomorrow to finish the remaining part as we have already agreed.\n4.I assisted Rosemary sort her agreements and took them for stamping as it is the correct procedure.','2026-02-04','Since it\'s is a new month,I am aiming to upload more listings and also handle the few challenges we have in the website as it\'s still a work In progress.','2026-02-04 18:44:10','2026-02-04 18:44:10'),(656,17,'\nI have reviewed the report on my activities for today and confirm the following:\n\n-Tasks Completed:\n    - Successfully wrote and shared the morning meeting minutes with the team, ensuring everyone is informed and aligned\n    - Attended the off-plan shoot at Riverside (Chavel project) from 11:40am to 3:20pm, capturing essential visuals and marketing materials\n    - Upon return, diligently completed pending office duties, ensuring all tasks are up to date\nPending:\n    - Update and share leads Excel sheet (no leads assigned today, will update as soon as new leads are available)\n\n','2026-02-04','Working diligently to make sure my work is seamless.','2026-02-04 18:57:23','2026-02-04 18:57:23'),(657,11,'I began the day by attending the morning meeting with the full team, which was chaired by Joseph. The meeting focused on general team updates and ongoing operational matters.\n\nFollowing the meeting, I participated in an interview for the sales agent position together with Joy. The candidate, George, demonstrated relevant real estate experience and showed potential; however, he indicated that he is considering whether to join the company on a full-time basis or operate as an external agent. He committed to reverting with a decision after weighing his options.\n\nI proceeded to allocate twelve client leads to the team for follow-up. The leads were distributed among Brian, Dennis, Isaiah, and Desmond to ensure timely engagement and coverage.\n\nLater in the day, I visited Golf Course Residency with Tasha and Desmond. This visit was conducted to assess the suitability of the project for marketing purposes, as it had been submitted as a potential listing. The property is located in a strategic area with limited high-rise developments and benefits from proximity to a golf course. However, the pricing is relatively high considering the location, finishes, and amenities offered. While it may be suitable for select client viewings, its overall appeal for active marketing is still under discussion.\n\nThereafter, we proceeded to Tigoni to view a newly built two-bedroom rental unit, designed in a farmhouse style and priced at KES 120,000 per month. Tasha has the full property details and will be sharing them with Diana for further action.','2026-02-04','•	Attend the morning team meeting\n	•	Attend a scheduled 2:00 p.m. appointment with my client, Ifrah\n	•	Update the CRM with current leads and interactions\n	•	Follow up with the team to review weekly progress and target attainment','2026-02-04 19:50:09','2026-02-04 19:50:09'),(658,46,'-I attended the morning sales meeting at 8:35 to 9am.\n-followed up on pending lead assigned by marketing team and land referrals from 9am to around 11:20am when i  joined the Berkley project  orientation at the office.\n-Once  through with the project debriefing,i compiled  consents and deed plans and  shared with  Diana for listing.\n-12:30 to 2,update the customers follows ups  and reminders of Scheduled viewing pending for this week.\n-Had a physical meeting with Mr.minesh at his office in parklands, 6th avenue in regards to investing with in Tigoni.\n\n\n','2026-02-04','pull up on client pitching for sale as soon as possible.','2026-02-04 20:55:35','2026-02-04 20:55:35'),(659,27,'1. BEKE all staff meeting where we spoke about our work plans and the offers on the table.\n\n2. Today, we were taken through the projects that BEKE will be marketing on a priority basis, and the offers for selling them first and fast.\n\n3. There were no leads allocated to me today, and I spent the better part of the day getting new listings on boarded in BEKE. Namely: Tatu City projects, 88 Nairobi, and Baystar in Kilimani.\n\n4. My previous allocated leads since last year are still looking out for properties and I have shared their respective projects of interest.\n\n5. No viewing for me today, planning for tommorrow or Saturday.','2026-02-05','','2026-02-05 13:34:13','2026-02-05 13:34:13'),(660,50,'attended early morning meeting with the team\nmade cold calls to potential clients to introduce our projects. received three positive feedback.\ndid follow ups of previously contacted clients and we are still engaging. scheduled a visit for next week\ntalked to two developers for projects in Runda and Kiambu road. scheduled a visit for tomorrow for Kiambu road.\nRunda developer will be sharing mandate via email for perusal and consideration.\nThe other project in kiambu road, will be informed of ground breaking date. tentatively next week.','2026-02-05','','2026-02-05 13:43:18','2026-02-05 13:43:18'),(661,13,'1. Today we had a general meeting where we were given the list of the projects that we will be focusing on this month, one of them being the new listing Morvara ,other options were shared too.\n2.I uploaded two listings for land from Rosemary, she had provided  all the requirements.\n3. I created 1 new supplier profile and included the different products the supplier has so that the profile is complete.\n4.I assisted with some duties at the reception , assisting my colleagues and also receiving clients and visitors.\n5. I received consent letters which I took for stamping before I can upload the listings as this is the company\'s required procedure.','2026-02-05','I am learning everyday and challenging myself to also grow as I learn.','2026-02-05 13:57:20','2026-02-05 13:57:20'),(662,15,'-A comprehensive joint session was held involving both the Marketing and Sales departments, focusing on aligning Targeting strategies and marketing approaches. The discussion was aimed at improving lead quality and ensuring the delivery of more favorable, conversion-ready leads to the Sales team. Additionally, content ideas were brainstormed, and the Media team was being guided on how to produce highly consumable content tailored to the qualified target audience.\n-A meeting has been scheduled for tomorrow at 10:00 a.m. to incorporate two creatives for the larger apartment units using existing content. This approach is intended to ensure continuity in lead generation for the Sales team as we await the development of additional content for the fresh new campaign that we have strategized on.\n-Posted two content pieces from Paddy across our platforms to enhance brand visibility and maintain consistent audience engagement.','2026-02-05','','2026-02-05 14:00:47','2026-02-05 14:00:47'),(663,49,'Today I did follow ups and I have managed to arrange a site visit with a client on Tuesday at kahawa sukari . I am also engaging another client who proposed that he is looking for a 3 bedroom apartment to buy in westlands . Today was about follow ups .','2026-02-05','','2026-02-05 14:06:56','2026-02-05 14:06:56'),(664,29,'- Attended the morning meeting, discussed our work plans for the day\n- We had another session of reviewing The January leads given to the sales team\n- I then edited an offplan shoot for Cheval and submitted for review in the afternoon\n- I began editing a carrousel design for Cheval before encountering a minor issue with my machine, planning on completing and submit tomorrow\n- ','2026-02-05','','2026-02-05 14:12:02','2026-02-05 14:12:02'),(665,46,'-Morning debriefing with sales and marketing team.\n-followed up with potential pending  leads.\n-Share and engaged mr.kimani on Tigoni\'s property per his boss request and will follow up for update on viewing. \n-updated referrals on my socials in regards to land.\n','2026-02-05','use every platform to pitch for potentials\n','2026-02-05 14:14:02','2026-02-05 14:14:02'),(666,11,'I began the day by attending the morning meeting, which was attended by the full team. Following the morning meeting, I also participated in a joint meeting with the media team, where we discussed advertising strategies, content planning, paid ads, and properties scheduled for promotion on the company’s social media platforms.\n\nThe majority of the day was spent following up with existing clients and partially updating the CRM with ongoing client interactions and records.\n\nI had a scheduled client appointment at 2:00 p.m.; however, the client cancelled the meeting.\n\nLater in the day, I attended a follow-up meeting with Mr. Ken and Rachel, during which Desmond was invited for a performance check-in. The discussion focused on reviewing his progress over the past five months with the company and emphasizing the importance of increased effort toward closing sales, particularly as this is his final month with the organization.\n\nI concluded the day after completing client follow-ups and internal meetings.','2026-02-05','','2026-02-05 15:41:37','2026-02-05 15:41:37'),(667,51,'Conducted a morning property viewing in Runda for a returning client; awaiting feedback tomorrow.\nShared two property listings with Paddy for Instagram content.\nHeld a progress and daily planning meeting with Isaiah.\nInitiated plans to develop a comprehensive apartment database.','2026-02-05','','2026-02-05 16:09:09','2026-02-05 16:09:09'),(668,24,'Held the morning meeting with my team to polish up on reports and the details expected.\nAttended the training held by the marketing team.\nfollowed up on my leads and sourced more properties from other agents for lease and Spring Valley.\nHeld a meeting with an agent who has Developer looking for land in Kileleshwa and Parklands, 0.5arces not more than 200Million. I provided 4options for viewing tomorrow.\nI went for a meeting with Mr.Mumin in Pronto CBD to discuss the 1acre lease he viewed yesterday. He said he will give an offer on Saturday. We proceeded to view one more property in along Kiambu road for lease.\nUpdated my  CRM and reached out to my previous clients i.e Ms.Ruth for Tigoni who rescheduled our meeting to Tuesday next week.','2026-02-05','','2026-02-05 17:08:54','2026-02-05 17:08:54'),(669,17,'\nTasks Completed:\n    Website Support: Assisted Miss Diana with specific website tasks as requested, ensuring timely completion and accuracy\n    Shoot Preparation: Prepared 2 detailed scripts for tomorrow\'s shoots:\n        - Office shoot: An educational video on the best locations and good projects for investors looking to buy.\n        - Monrovia Project: we will be doing an introductory video on this new promising project located in Westlands along Muthithi road, to attract investors and homebuyers.\n    Office Duties: Completed other office duties as required, maintaining office efficiency.','2026-02-05','Strive to be the best in everything I do.','2026-02-05 17:28:19','2026-02-05 17:28:19'),(670,23,'Leads Assigned\nNo new leads were assigned today.\nFollow-Ups\nConducted follow-up calls and successfully revived 3 leads who are still interested.\nClient Updates\nAudrey:\nCameroonian client interested in viewing Eternity.\nShe will be coming with a friend who is also interested.\nViewing scheduled for Saturday from 10:00 AM.\nVirginia:\nInterested in rental properties in Ruiru or Mugutha.\nIdentified available options within a budget range of KSh 130,000 – 150,000.\nClient is currently traveling and will return to Nairobi on Tuesday, after which viewings will be scheduled.\nSandra:\nInterested in Greenview.\nShe is engaged this weekend and prefers to schedule a viewing next week between Tuesday and Thursday.\nCRM Update\nCRM was updated; work is still in progress','2026-02-05','','2026-02-05 17:59:18','2026-02-05 17:59:18'),(671,12,'\n> Daily Report\n\nToday, my client Solani postponed the scheduled viewing to tomorrow morning. With no new leads assigned today, I focused on conducting follow-ups with existing clients.\n\nI also updated and organized my CRM to reflect the pending clients accurately. Additionally, I had a phone conversation with Palm Court Real Estate, who expressed openness to partnering with us on their ongoing projects in Ruiru','2026-02-05','','2026-02-05 18:35:53','2026-02-05 18:35:53'),(672,51,'Visited Luminara project\nWent for a house viewing in Runda \nViewed land for sale in Gigiri 1/2acre \nSent listings to the media group ; Runda, Tigoni \nTo view a townhouse along Muhuri road today (there is an event) ','2026-02-06','','2026-02-06 11:50:25','2026-02-06 11:50:25'),(673,24,'Attended the morning meeting with my team.\nFollowed up on my previous clients and enquiries given yesterday.\nWent for viewing with the sale client for Muthithi Road 0.25acres but she didn\'t like the fact that its not fronting the road.\nHeld a conference call with my client and landowner for the Reliable Towers Commercial Building for sale and organized for viewing and negotiations on Monday 11a.m.\nSourced 2more options for commercial buildings.','2026-02-06','','2026-02-06 14:17:50','2026-02-06 14:17:50'),(674,15,'- brainstorming the Morvara project, during which one script was developed and two content ideas were shared.\n- Later in the afternoon, we moved into executing the generated idea, with Paddy and Mia featuring in a shoot along Westlands Road to visually communicate the relevance of the content and finally finished at the rooftop with a glimpse of the project location.\n','2026-02-06','','2026-02-06 15:04:22','2026-02-06 15:04:22'),(675,23,'No leads were assigned by the marketing team today.\nCompiled all previously assigned leads and organized them into relevant categories for better tracking and follow-up.\nMade a total of 19 phone calls to clients.\nSome clients responded positively and are currently under follow-up.\nMajority of the clients requested property details to be shared via WhatsApp, which were sent according to their specific requirements, including apartments and villas.\nAll contacted leads are subject to further follow-up.\n I also had a viewing with Sandra who is a client that I have been Pershing at Greenview villas. She liked the project but she said that she needs to have another follow up visit with the family. Monday will not be possible so she asked that I call her on Tuesday to schedule for the week','2026-02-06','','2026-02-06 15:53:12','2026-02-06 15:53:12'),(676,27,'1. We had a morning meeting with the entire sales team headed by Carol Gakuya and we talked about how our week was, the planned viewings we have for today and, the offers we are pushing for that we can close this week. We were encouraged to follow up on our A and B clients to have more viewings. We also shared amongst ourselves the listings we are hunting for to share to our hot leads.\n\n2. Followed up on some of my previous leads and was able to get schedule viewings for tomorrow and Monday next week. Also sourced for more listings for BEKE.\n\n3. Went for viewing with Brian\'s customer to Socian Villas Apartments for the 3-bedroom available for sale. They were impressed by the interiors, but the exterior was not well maintained so they went with Brian to view other options.\n\n4. Later on, I went for viewing with my lead - Charity. She picked me up from the office then we went to view ISRA Residence in Parklands for the 2-bedroom which did not meet her specifics, then we went to view Eternity where she also found out that the units were small especially the bedrooms, later we viewed Angani apartments which was close by and she found the apartments spacious but the prices were too high for her, we lastly viewed Misty Springs but unfortunately we found no 2-bedrooms available for sale. She is still willing to view more options before she picks her choice. I will be following up with her next week.\n\n5. Back to the office and following up with more.','2026-02-06','','2026-02-06 15:54:40','2026-02-06 15:54:40'),(677,11,'I began the day by chairing the morning sales team meeting, which was attended by the full sales team. The meeting focused on alignment of daily priorities and ongoing client engagements.\n\nImmediately after the meeting, I accompanied Brian for a client site viewing. The client is looking to purchase a one-bedroom apartment, with a preference for projects scheduled for completion in 2028. She is a serious and well-qualified buyer, with a specific requirement for unobstructed views and assurance that no future construction will block the outlook of the unit. While Brian is continuing to source additional suitable options, the client’s current preferred option is Luminara, though she has requested to view more alternatives before making a decision.\n\nThereafter, I returned to the office and conducted follow-ups with key clients, through which I successfully secured a site viewing scheduled for the following day.\n\nIn the afternoon, I attended a site viewing in Kilimani with a client who is seeking a one-bedroom apartment for rent. We viewed three available options, and the client indicated that they would provide feedback by Monday.\n\nI concluded the day by continuing to source suitable property options for active clients and sharing available listings and updates with them.','2026-02-06','','2026-02-06 16:53:55','2026-02-06 16:53:55'),(678,13,'1.I uploaded 5 projects from my colleagues: 2 Rentals from Tasha and 3 for sale from Brian,they provided all the requirements as per the company\'s policy.\n2.I worked at the reception,for smooth running of the day\'s activities, assisting my colleagues and also the different visitors who came by.\n3. Paddy  assisted me to resize some photos for different projects,I used them to replace the poor quality ones for some former projects in the website.\n4.I did follow ups with the developer,they were to update us on the new changes in the APP before the end of today,I am still waiting.\n5.I did one follow up with my former client,I engaged her and we are still talking,I am trying to push do that she can come to view Morvara,I am hoping for the best.','2026-02-06','','2026-02-06 17:58:59','2026-02-06 17:58:59'),(679,46,'-8:30 am ,attended morning meeting.\n-9 :00 am ,Luminara orientation  at their office.\n-11:00 am (followed up with Patricia for tigoni viewing on Saturday,Mr.Jeff for Kiambu villas(to  recheck on Saturday morning)Willy and Andrew to verify their availability tomorrow morning.\n-viewed s Ineza 4 bedroom resale with my client(Biene) she will go back with the husband tomorrow afternoon.\n-sourced/viewed a 7 bedroom at Whisper Avenue for rent(owner will advice on commission percentage ) tomorrow.\n-sourced/viewed a 4 bedroom villa to let at Runda(Kiuna rd)opposite 37 Ineza. owner to sign consent tommorrow.\n-updated crm .\n\n\n\n','2026-02-06','financial freedom is the goal..','2026-02-06 18:44:24','2026-02-06 18:44:24'),(680,17,'\nTasks Completed:\n    - Compiled and disseminated the morning meeting minutes to the Beke marketing group, ensuring seamless communication and team alignment\n    - Rendered support to Miss Diana with website data entry and other tasks as requested, enhancing our online platform\'s functionality and accuracy\n    - Conducted a productive shoot at GTC for the Movara project, acquiring high-quality visuals and marketing assets to drive project engagement\n\n','2026-02-06','Make sure I am better than yesterday','2026-02-06 18:50:08','2026-02-06 18:50:08'),(681,12,'\n> Daily Activity Report\n\nToday, following the morning meeting, I conducted a viewing appointment with Saloni at Lesto. We agreed to view two additional options along Lantana Road and Riverside Drive, after which she will be able to make a well-informed purchasing decision.\n\nI later accompanied Mr. Albert for viewings of three-bedroom units available for purchase. We toured three options; however, he expressed a preference for an older, more traditional three-bedroom apartment, which I will continue to source.\n\nAdditionally, I shared two available three-bedroom rental options in Kilimani with Rachel, as per her request. I am scheduled to follow up with her tomorrow to gauge her interest in the shared options.','2026-02-06','','2026-02-06 19:16:57','2026-02-06 19:16:57'),(682,50,'attended early morning team meeting\nattended training on Luminara project mid morning with the boss and the rest of the team.\ndid follow ups on potential clients.\nwent sourcing in Runda and Kiambu road. managed to get two new listings for a rental unit and a project for sale.\n','2026-02-06','','2026-02-07 05:50:51','2026-02-07 05:50:51'),(683,29,'- We had our morning joint meeting, everyone addressed how their week has been\n- I then designed an E-card calling out to partner with who have