a posts. Tasked the team to have a shoot day comprising of 4/5 videos with scripts ready before the shoots(to ensure proper time management and also saving on transport costs)\n- Research on real estate videos that are trending and shared with the marketing team\n-2 leads were shared; called and followed up \n- To visit Amethyst, Kilimani  for property presentation \n','2026-02-09','','2026-02-09 12:41:18','2026-02-09 12:41:18'),(688,27,'1. Today, we had an all-staff meeting held by Joseph, Racheal, and Ken. It was about our last week\'s review, today\'s work plan and targets for this week.\n\n2. Followed up with one lead shared by Rashid, and also a number of my previous leads and realised one lead by the name Jane Wangari had viewed Greenview and was ready with an offer. Will follow up on the same tomorrow.','2026-02-09','','2026-02-09 13:55:38','2026-02-09 13:55:38'),(689,15,'\n1. I was actively managing our social media presence by posting two videos and one e-card across all our social media platforms. This was done to maintain brand visibility, keep the pages active, and continuously engage our target audience with relevant property content.\n\n2.Campaign Monitoring & Lead Management\nI was following up on the campaign that the consultant and I had created on Saturday. During the course of the day, I managed to assign eight (8) qualified leads to the property sales team. There were no leads generated for land at this stage. However, I was working on preparing the next phase of campaigns, specifically for apartments and townhouses, which we are planning to launch as soon as strong creatives and video content are completed.\n\n3.Consultation & Content Development (Morvara Project)\nThe consultant was on site for the purpose of brainstorming content ideas for the Morvara project, which we are currently pushing for the week. In line with this, I was actively contributing to the content strategy and managed to develop one marketing script specifically for the Morvara project to support ongoing promotions.','2026-02-09','','2026-02-09 14:05:36','2026-02-09 14:05:36'),(690,29,'- Attended our morning joint meeting where we had a briefing of the last week\'s reports and gave our work plans for the day.\n-  After the meeting I finished up the Morvara shoot we did last Friday and submitted my midday\n- I then designed company tags for myself, Tasha, Rose, James and Desmond\n- We had a marketing meeting to discuss on how to refine our scripts and understanding our main target audience as investors\n- In the afternoon I came up with a script idea for Morvara and submitted for refining, to be shot tomorrow','2026-02-09','','2026-02-09 14:16:57','2026-02-09 14:16:57'),(691,23,'Leads & Client Engagement\n2 new leads were assigned by the marketing team today.\nPatel who was interested in Amani residency asked that I share details on whatsapp. Still subject to follow up\nThe other one is not responsive so will definitely follow up again tomorrow \nConducted follow-up calls with previous clients.\nTwo (2) clients confirmed property viewings scheduled for this week.\nScheduled Viewings\nMichelle Banju:\nViewing scheduled for Saturday at 9:30 AM\nProperties: Movara and Luminara\nEric:\nViewing scheduled for tomorrow\nProperties: Movara and Berkeley\nCRM & Client Management\nUpdated client information and activities in the CRM.\nQualified clients across all categories to streamline the database and eliminate D-category clients.\nSummary\nFocused on client follow-ups, viewing confirmations, CRM updates, and client qualification to improve lead quality and readiness for conversion','2026-02-09','','2026-02-09 15:33:31','2026-02-09 15:33:31'),(692,17,'\nTasks Completed:\n    - Attended and meticulously documented minutes of the morning general meeting, disseminating key updates and action items to the Beke business group.\n    - Updated and shared the leads Excel sheet, ensuring accurate tracking, follow-up, and alignment with sales team objectives\n    - Actively participated in the marketing meeting, contributing valuable insights and suggestions to enhance content quality and overall marketing strategy\n    - Collaborated with Paddy, Rashid, and Joseph to prepare two comprehensive scripts for tomorrow\'s shoot, aligning with project objectives and brand messaging\n','2026-02-09','Always strive to the best','2026-02-09 16:45:33','2026-02-09 16:45:33'),(693,24,'Attended the morning meeting with the team.\nHeld one interview with a candidate who seemed to have  experience but lacked the necessary touch base technique to fulfil the role.\nWent to source at Kilimani 0.5acres JV for a client  who wanted to view in the afternoon.\nHeld a meeting with Rosemary\'s Agents that have a client for  the Muthithi Road o.5acres to plan for tomorrows viewing with the client.\nTook the NanChong Team to view 0.5acres for sale waiting for a response by 10th February.\nTook another client to site at  Wood Avenue for a JV at 30/70 sharing ratio and sale at 325Million. The client said he\'s to give an offer but at a lower value by 11th Feb.\nCame back to the office to make follow up calls on the requests received over weekend.\nSent emails and property profiles for the RFQ received.\nUpdated the CRM on the sites visited and meeting held.\n','2026-02-09','','2026-02-09 16:47:50','2026-02-09 16:47:50'),(694,13,'1.I started the day by attending our regular Monday meetings, where we set our goals for the week and also encourage ourselves after reviewing our performance in the previous week.\n2. Joseph and I conducted two interviews for the data entry position, Joseph will give a feedback on the same.\n3. I uploaded 4 listings for sale, from Dennis I still have more which I will continue uploading tomorrow.\n4.I assisted at the reception just to ensure smooth running of day to  day activities that needed my help.\n5. I assisted a developer who had registered on our website as a partner to reset his password as he had forgotten it, he needed a new one for him to login.\n6.I did follow ups with the developer as they still have pending tasks that I need to follow up on regularly and test once they are worked on.','2026-02-09','Everyday is a learning day.','2026-02-09 17:23:17','2026-02-09 17:23:17'),(695,12,'\nDaily Activity Report\n\nToday, I was assigned one new lead with an Indian contact number. I reached out to the client via WhatsApp and shared detailed information regarding the Amani project, as per his inquiry. I am awaiting feedback and will follow up accordingly.\n\nLater in the day, I conducted follow-ups with last week’s clients, with particular focus on those I had previously taken for site viewings. I followed up with Mercy, Mokaya, Albert, and Saloni to check on their feedback, address any pending questions, and assess their readiness to proceed.\n\nAll updates and client responses from the follow-ups were accurately captured and updated in the CRM for proper tracking and next action planning.','2026-02-09','','2026-02-09 18:22:24','2026-02-09 18:22:24'),(696,12,'\nDaily Activity Report\n\nToday, I was assigned one new lead with an Indian contact number. I reached out to the client via WhatsApp and shared detailed information regarding the Amani project, as per his inquiry. I am awaiting feedback and will follow up accordingly.\n\nLater in the day, I conducted follow-ups with last week’s clients, with particular focus on those I had previously taken for site viewings. I followed up with Mercy, Mokaya, Albert, and Saloni to check on their feedback, address any pending questions, and assess their readiness to proceed.\n\nAll updates and client responses from the follow-ups were accurately captured and updated in the CRM for proper tracking and next action planning.','2026-02-09','','2026-02-09 18:22:25','2026-02-09 18:22:25'),(697,46,'-Had a debriefing meeting with the sales team.\n-Managed to meet with Jane, George and Joy in regards to a joint ventures.\n-Spoke to my client (Jeff) on all the options shared, he  had chosen a few and were planning to view on Tuesday.\n-followed up on pending clients.\n-Met with Mr. Sighn at his office along Rapta Road in regards to Parkland and Tigoni land.\n-update crm later.','2026-02-09','self drive is important.','2026-02-10 07:08:03','2026-02-10 07:08:03'),(698,27,'1. Today we had our daily sales meeting which was chaired by Racheal, and we discussed about our plan for today, the offers, and the way BEKE is ready to support us in the sales process.\n\n2. I was invited to visit my own personal lead in his office in Upper Hill as he was still interested in 88 Nairobi Condominium apartments for investment. His offer was way below the prices of 88 apartments, and so I had to source for him ready 1-, or 2-bedroom apartments suitable for investment. This led me to source in the following projects today: 88 Nairobi, Serenity Residence, Golden Mango Heights, Lido Gardens, Serene Manor, and Auris residency and did find some ready apartments suitable for his investment. I have shared the projects with him.\n\n3. Back to the office and followed up with one lead allocated by Rashid and the previous ones too.','2026-02-10','1. Results of my work for today is that I was able to source for rentals and for sale of 1-, 2-, and 3-bedrooms apartments.\n2. What I learnt is more of Kilimani\'s demographics and the future it holds in terms of investments, and that sourcing is not easy. \n3. A company car will ease the movement.','2026-02-10 14:00:27','2026-02-10 14:00:27'),(699,15,'1. I assigned a total of 8 qualified leads to the sales team after reviewing and filtering them for relevance. The leads were distributed accordingly to ensure prompt follow-up, effective client engagement, and improved chances of conversion. This was done to support the sales team in maintaining momentum and maximizing response time.\n2.I accompanied Mia and Paddy to Misty Spring for an on-site content shoot, where we captured visual and video material for marketing purposes. The shoot focused on highlighting the property’s features and surroundings to support upcoming promotional campaigns and improve brand visibility.\n3.I posted three carousel contents across our social media platforms, aimed at enhancing brand visibility, showcasing key property features, and increasing audience engagement as part of our ongoing digital marketing efforts.\n','2026-02-10','','2026-02-10 14:05:11','2026-02-10 14:05:11'),(700,29,'- Attended the morning marketing meeting, discussed about the various plans for the day \n- After the meeting I designed a valentine season-themed E-card encouraging inclining our audience to Amani residence.\n- We left for a shoot of an overview of Westlands, started with a backdrop of Misty springs then later in the afternoon headed to Sarit centre to finish the Westlands overview script\n- We came back to the office at 4, managed to design a Morvara carrousel and submitted to our Whatsapp groups as well as Rashid.','2026-02-10','','2026-02-10 14:06:28','2026-02-10 14:06:28'),(701,13,'1. I attended the morning meeting, we shared our targets for the day and also encouraged ourselves to keep pushing ourselves everyday.\n2. We had a meeting with the management team in regards to how we can have more listings in our website, we will be contacting external  to share with them how  Beke intends to work with them, then they can register with us and share with us their listings.\n3. Joseph and I conducted three interviews , we got some good feedback from two candidates, the best from the two will be shortlisted soon.\n4.I uploaded 4 listings from my colleagues , 3 apartments for sale and 1 land listing , I still have more, I am  uploading them in bits.\n5. I did follow up with the developer in regards to the bulk sms system that was to be integrated to our CRM, he will be giving a feedback this week.\n6. I  assisted at the reception.','2026-02-10','I am happy  as I will be having a colleague to assist me, when she reports, we will be sharing ideas on how to improve the website for our clients to have the best user experiences.','2026-02-10 14:07:26','2026-02-10 14:07:26'),(702,24,'Held the morning meeting with my team where we discussed various ways of getting clients and how to close the deals.\nHeld a meeting with the agents that have a developer interested in the Wood Avenue property to discuss the commission agreement.\nHeld a meeting with the Developer for 88Kikuyu. He wants to give us the sole Agency for the project comprising 65-5Bedroom-Villas.\nFollowed up on my clients and requests received yesterday.\nPlanned for tomorrow’s viewing at at Muthithi 33, Kabasiran Lavington and Karen JVA options for the client\n','2026-02-10','','2026-02-10 16:01:53','2026-02-10 16:01:53'),(703,51,'Conducted 2 interviews; 1 person qualified \nStrategized regarding the marketing that can propel BEKE\nFollowed up with clients \nPrepared a presentation on Developer Partnership + Billboard strategy','2026-02-10','','2026-02-10 16:29:49','2026-02-10 16:29:49'),(704,23,'Leads & Follow-ups\n1 lead assigned by Rashid.\nLead was not responsive and is subject to follow-up.\nMade 14 follow-up calls:\n4 clients were responsive.\n2 viewings scheduled for this week.\nScheduled Viewings\nVirginia\nDate & Time: Thursday at 10:00 AM\nRequirement: Rental in Mugutha\nProperty: Mugutha rental going for 150k\nMichele Banju\nDate & Time: Saturday from 9:30 AM\nProperties: Morvara and Luminara\nListings\nManaged to secure a listing from Joy priced at 150k.\nShared the listing with an interested client, Levix, who is planning to view within the week.\nOngoing Actions\nContinuing with additional follow-ups to schedule more viewings','2026-02-10','','2026-02-10 18:42:09','2026-02-10 18:42:09'),(705,12,'\n\nDaily Activity Report\n\nToday, I successfully sourced two viable projects. The first is a 0.5-acre parcel of land located along Njathaini Road, off Kiambu Road. This is a prime property and serves as a strong alternative for clients interested in Greenville Garden Villas who may prefer to develop their own standalone homes.\n\nThe second project is Balkis Apartments, situated in Riverside, which presents a suitable option for clients seeking premium residential apartments in a prime location.\n\nI shared relevant options and detailed information on these projects with Irene and Mercy for their consideration and will follow up accordingly.\n\nI also maintained communication with Saloni, who confirmed her availability for site viewings scheduled for tomorrow.\n\nAdditionally, I conducted a site visit with Moses to view a commercial space. We are yet to view one more option along Lantana Road, after which the client will be able to make a well-informed leasing decision.','2026-02-10','Viewing appointment with Saloni \nCRM updates \n\nFollow up with Savannah concerning here previously scheduled viewing ','2026-02-10 19:19:12','2026-02-10 19:19:12'),(706,17,'\nTasks Accomplished:\n    - Thoroughly updated and disseminated the leads Excel sheet by close of business today, ensuring precise tracking and follow-up\n    - Left office at 1pm to attend scheduled shoots:\n        - Misty and Sarit center for the Westlands area themed video.\n    - Returned to office at 4pm and focused on completing pending office duties, ensuring tasks are current.','2026-02-10','Yet to be my best version ','2026-02-10 19:20:41','2026-02-10 19:20:41'),(707,50,'attended early morning meetings\nwent to view diplomat and Gaia projects in preparation for site visit tomorrow.\nmade follow up calls and cold calls\nwent to source for a villa in westlands kyuna and later to source for land in muthaiga','2026-02-10','','2026-02-11 05:36:14','2026-02-11 05:36:14'),(708,46,'-Morning meeting in attendance at 8:35\n-followed up on leads from last week.\n-sourced for 3 townhouses in Kenyatta road,Superhighway,Ruiru.\n-Updated all my pending clients on their enquiries.\n-sourced for 1/ 2 acre plot in Murera.\n-update crm.','2026-02-10','The more you sweat in practice the less you bleed in battle.','2026-02-11 07:12:29','2026-02-11 07:12:29'),(709,27,'1. BEKE staff meeting and we discussed about our positives and reviews of the most viewed properties.\n\n2. Today, I didn\'t have any site visits and focused on following up on my previous leads. Out of the 13 I followed up on, 4 are responding and will be able to view the projects this Saturday.\n\n3. Project familiarisation.','2026-02-11','','2026-02-11 13:38:52','2026-02-11 13:38:52'),(710,29,'- Attended the morning marketing team meeting, we discussed our work plan for today \n- I then finished up editing and making some adjustments on the Westlands\' overview video that we shot yesterday. After this, I submitted the video to the relevant groups.\n- In the afternoon I edited a 8bedroom in Runda, forwaded to me by Tasha, on completion I submitted to Rashid and our Marketing Whatsapp groups\n- Towards close of business I brainstorm on a carrousel idea of upcoming Valentine\'s events from Friday all the way to Sunday.','2026-02-11','','2026-02-11 14:04:59','2026-02-11 14:04:59'),(711,15,'1.During this reporting period, I assigned three (3) new leads to the sales team as follows:\nCaro – 1 lead\nBrian – 1 lead\nDesmond – 1 lead\nAll three leads were generated through the billboard marketing channel. the billboard has already started showing effectiveness and some descent enquiries as i can report.\nThere were no new leads from Meta (Facebook/Instagram) ads, as the previous ad campaign had been stopped.\nA new evergreen Meta ad campaign has since been created and launched to specifically push:\nMorava\nLuminaria\nThe objective of the evergreen campaign is to generate consistent, long-term leads while maintaining steady visibility and engagement for both projects.\nPerformance tracking will continue in the next reporting period to evaluate lead inflow and campaign effectiveness.\n2. posted three carousel targeted for pushing Morvara  as the property for the week .\n3. As usual i had asession with the consultant aimed at setting one campaign and pushing on high quality leads for the sales team follow up \n','2026-02-11','','2026-02-11 14:05:54','2026-02-11 14:05:54'),(712,24,'Held the morning meeting with my team where we discussed today\'s schedules.\nWent for a viewing at Muthithi 33/31 with a client, waiting for a letter of intent by tomorrow.\nWent for viewing at Kabasiran 1.3acres with the client but he said the property is too steep.\nWent for another viewing at Chalbi 25 JV Property with Mumin, he liked it and promised to give a proposal  on the same.\nSourced at Jacaranda 1acre for sale at 180Million.\nCame back to the office to follow up on my clients and updated them in the CRM.','2026-02-11','','2026-02-11 14:22:56','2026-02-11 14:22:56'),(713,51,'Morning meeting \nFollowed up with my 2 active clients; \nBrian was busy and not able to pick up \nSanjay said he would call in 2 hours , I called back but he did not pick. Left a message to ask when he can schedule for viewing \nFinished a report for billboard advertising.','2026-02-11','','2026-02-11 15:06:30','2026-02-11 15:06:30'),(714,11,'1. Results of Today’s Work\n	•	Attended the morning sales meeting chaired by Tasha for team alignment.\n	•	Secured a new rental listing at Rera One Residency, Kilimani (2-bedroom).\n	•	Met the landlord.\n	•	Took marketing photos.\n	•	Agreed on commission terms.\n	•	Shared property details with Diana for marketing.\n	•	Conducted client follow-ups.\n	•	Scheduled 2:00 p.m. viewing did not proceed due to client unresponsiveness.\n\nOverall, the key tangible result for the day was acquiring and onboarding a new rental listing.\n\n2. What I Learned\n	•	Securing listings directly from landlords strengthens inventory control and improves commission certainty.\n	•	Client confirmations should ideally be reconfirmed earlier in the day to reduce time lost on cancelled or unresponsive appointments.\n	•	Consistent follow-up remains necessary, as some clients require multiple touchpoints before committing.\n\n3. Aspects That Need Improvement\n	•	Strengthen pre-viewing confirmation process.\n	•	Improve follow-up tracking to quickly identify non-responsive clients and re-prioritize active leads.\n	•	Continue building a stronger pipeline of ready-to-view clients to reduce dependency on single appointments.\n','2026-02-11','','2026-02-11 15:35:17','2026-02-11 15:35:17'),(715,17,'\nTasks Accomplished:\n    - Compiled and circulated minutes of the morning marketing meeting to the Beke marketing team, ensuring alignment and clarity\n    - Crafted two comprehensive scripts for tomorrow\'s townhouse shoots in Kikuyu and Kiambu road, meeting project objectives and brand standards\n    - Followed up on uniform enquiries, will share gatherings quotes and options for presentations.\n    - Provided assistance to Miss Diana at reception, supporting her with tasks and ensuring seamless office operations\nNote:\n    - No leads were assigned today due to currently inactive campaigns, they were launched today both on Meta and Tik Tok','2026-02-11','A journey of a thousand miles starts with a single step.','2026-02-11 17:12:49','2026-02-11 17:12:49'),(716,23,'\nDate: 11th February 2026\n1. New Lead Assigned\nReceived 1 new lead from Rashid.\nClient is interested in purchasing a ready 2-bedroom unit.\nPreference: 10–20 minutes walking distance from Sarit Centre.\nIdentified one option at Sunset Park, located approximately 500m from Westgate Mall.\nAsking price: KES 30M.\nViewing scheduled for tomorrow.\n2. Property Viewing Conducted\nHad a viewing with Mark at Banana.\nProperty: 4-bedroom unit for rent.\nRental price: KES 90,000 per month.\nThe same project also has units for sale:\nKES 19.5M (cash purchase)\nKES 20.5M (mortgage purchase)\n3. Follow-ups\nConducted follow-ups with previous clients.\nVirginia confirmed a viewing for tomorrow at Mugutha.\nProperty: Rental unit at KES 150,000 per month.\nViewing time: 10:30 AM.','2026-02-11','','2026-02-11 17:25:23','2026-02-11 17:25:23'),(717,12,'\n\nDaily Activity Report\n\nToday, I conducted follow-ups with Mr. James, Paul, Savannah, and Martin to provide updates and check on their level of interest. All interactions and feedback were accurately updated in the CRM system for proper tracking and future reference.\n\nLater in the day, I accompanied Saloni for property viewings of the options I had previously shared with her. The site visits went well, and she is currently reviewing the options. We are expecting her feedback by the end of the week.','2026-02-11','','2026-02-11 18:31:14','2026-02-11 18:31:14'),(718,13,'1. I attended the morning meeting with my colleagues, we planned our day and shared our progress too.\n2. I uploaded 3 listings from my colleagues, all of them  were for sale.\n3. I assisted at the reception, welcoming visitors and directing them, I also assisted my colleagues where necessary.\n4.I had a meeting with Miss Rachael, she told me to prepare a job description for listing agents as we are going to have them help up have more properties, I was to give a feedback tomorrow.\n5. I had a conversation with Tasha in regards to her recommending listing agents to us, she has suggested we have a meeting tomorrow with Miss Rachael, she is willing to help us get listings since she is well familiar with the up market areas that we focus more on. ','2026-02-12','','2026-02-11 18:42:53','2026-02-11 18:42:53'),(719,50,'attended early morning team meeting.\nfollowed up on the previous clients and made calls to new prospects\nattended a meeting with a client pitching apartments in westlands\nvisited amani project with a client\n','2026-02-11','','2026-02-12 05:35:30','2026-02-12 05:35:30'),(720,46,'-Attended morning  briefing.\n-viewed kentimere south estate with my client(Jeff) waiting  on his feedback.\n-viewed  tigoni land with (charles kinyua).\n-follow up on pending clients.\nupdate crm later\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n','2026-02-11','explore for closure. as soon as possible.','2026-02-12 07:49:29','2026-02-12 07:49:29'),(721,13,'1. I attended morning meeting with my colleagues for a briefing, we shared some new ideas on how to get quality leads, to make us close even more deals.\n2.Racheal, Tasha and I had a session in regards to the property listing ideas, especially for the townhouses and rentals, we are to have another session tomorrow to finalize on the strategies to be followed as we want the best .\n3. Rashid and I did a follow up  with the developer in regards to him linking our CRM to our meta business account , he has sorted the issue and he will train Rashid on what is required, we are still following up.\n4.I uploaded 2 listings for sale, from Tasha and Rosemary they provided all the requirements as  required.\n5.I assisted both my colleagues and visitors at the reception.\n\n\n\n','2026-02-12','','2026-02-12 13:47:16','2026-02-12 13:47:16'),(722,15,'. Lead Follow-Up & Assignment\nAfter reviewing the follow-up reports for previously generated leads, I carefully assessed their status and readiness for the next stage in the sales process. Based on the evaluation, I successfully assigned 11 qualified leads to the sales team for further engagement and conversion. This ensured timely follow-up and helped maintain momentum in the sales pipeline.\n\n2. Office Content Creation\nI participated in planning and shooting engaging office content, specifically focusing on creating fun and relatable videos. The objective was to enhance our brand presence, increase audience engagement, and showcase the company culture in a creative and authentic way. The content captured will be used across digital platforms to strengthen brand visibility and connection with our audience.\n\n3. Meta Developer Account Setup & CRM Integration Preparation\nI successfully created a Meta Developer account and configured the necessary assets to facilitate CRM integration with Meta Ads. This setup will allow proper lead tracking and data synchronization between our CRM system and Meta advertising platform. By ensuring accurate tracking, we can better measure campaign performance, optimize ad spend, and improve overall lead management efficiency.','2026-02-12','','2026-02-12 14:06:42','2026-02-12 14:06:42'),(723,17,'\nTasks Accomplished:\n    - Successfully conducted a Valentine\'s Day shoot at the office, collaborating with Mr. Paddy, Mr. Rashid, and the entire team; footage is currently being edited and will be shared tomorrow for posting on social media platforms\n    - Completed a productive townhouse shoot in Ruiru with Mr. Paddy; the project shows great potential and aligns with our objectives\n    - Updated and disseminated the leads Excel sheet; a total of 13 Meta leads were assigned to the sales team for timely follow-up and conversion\n\n','2026-02-12','Action over words always works magic','2026-02-12 17:18:56','2026-02-12 17:18:56'),(724,12,'\n\n\n---\n\nDaily Report\n\nToday, I accompanied Maggie for property viewings across Riverside, Mvuli Road, and Raphta Road, where we explored several available options that align with her requirements.\n\nI also confirmed tomorrow’s viewing appointment with Savannah to ensure everything is well coordinated.\n\nAdditionally, I was assigned three new leads, out of which two have been responsive so far. I will continue engaging them to advance the conversations.\n','2026-02-12','','2026-02-12 19:15:15','2026-02-12 19:15:15'),(725,23,'4 leads assigned by the marketing team\n2 from meta 2 from TikTok \nManaged to make 2 calls to the TikTok leads which only 1 was responsive and asked for 2 bedroom options for investment. I pitched Morvara and Luminara and sent details via WhatsApp now i am pushing for a viewing \nI had a viewing in Mugutha for a 4 bedroom going for 150k. Virginia came with her family and they viewed but asked to revert once they have had a discussion about it\nAlso sourced for another project around Ruiru called waterfront for villas going for 22.5M to 25.5M. We are in direct contact with the developer and all the leads that had a lower budget than 35M from green view, I want to pitch to them since it is lower in budget.\nMade some follow up calls from which 1 client called Sandra is to confirm a viewing  tomorrow for viewing. We are to confirm availability from 10.30AM.\n','2026-02-12','','2026-02-12 20:13:20','2026-02-12 20:13:20'),(726,11,'1. Results Achieved Today\n	•	Attended the morning meeting chaired by Joseph with the full team present.\n	•	Conducted scheduled client follow-ups; two clients confirmed and honored their appointments.\n\nViewing 1 – Rental Client (Joy)\n	•	Requirement: 2-bedroom for rent in Westlands or Kilimani\n	•	Accompanied by: Rachel\n	•	Properties viewed: 5 options\n	•	Outcome: Client selected Alina Harbour, Kilimani\n	•	Status: Building management has connected the client directly with the landlord\n	•	Next Step: Client meeting landlord on Monday to finalize terms\n\nViewing 2 – Investment Client\n	•	Profile: Foreign investors (South Sudan)\n	•	Requirement: 2- or 3-bedroom unit for investment\n	•	Outcome: we managed to view 2 options, we have planned to meet on Monday to view more \n\n2. Strategic Insights\n	•	Proper follow-up and confirmation improves appointment adherence.\n	•	Showing multiple curated options increases decision speed (client selected after 5 viewings).\n	•	Foreign investors represent a strong opportunity segment and require structured follow-up to convert.\n\n','2026-02-12','','2026-02-12 21:30:12','2026-02-12 21:30:12'),(727,50,'attended the team meeting in the morning.\ndid my follow up calls and  cold calls\ntook client to view Gaia and later on had a productive meeting with them.\nwent to source for properties on behalf of a client in kileleshwa and Riverside','2026-02-12','','2026-02-13 05:58:48','2026-02-13 05:58:48'),(728,51,'Presentation by the Morvara team in the office \nMeeting with Ken and Joseph about billboard meetings \nClient follow ups \nMeeting with managers and Rachel\n','2026-02-13','','2026-02-13 11:35:26','2026-02-13 11:35:26'),(729,50,'attended morning training on Morvara with the team.\nmid morning attended project launch in upperhill.\nmet agents in the afternoon to try to push Morvara.\ntook an agent and her client to Luminara and Morvara.\nfollowed up on previous leads.','2026-02-13','','2026-02-13 13:27:57','2026-02-13 13:27:57'),(730,29,'-  Attended our morning marketing meeting to discuss our work plans for the day\n- After the meeting we had the Morvara Team come to present the project and explain in details what the project is all about, this was very insightful and informative session I must say.\n- Later on, I delved into finishing up the Palm court townhouses shoot we did yesterday, submitted on completion in the afternoon\n- Nearing close of business I managed to edit a property version of the Palm court townhouses in Ruiru and submitted.','2026-02-13','','2026-02-13 14:01:09','2026-02-13 14:01:09'),(731,15,'1. Today, I assigned five (5) new leads to the Sales Team for follow-up and engagement.\nCurrently, the overall lead volume remains low. This is primarily due to the implementation of the lead filtering process, specifically the “Enquiry-to-Lead” form system. While this filtering mechanism has reduced the quantity of incoming leads, it is designed to improve lead quality by ensuring that only more relevant and qualified enquiries are converted into actionable sales leads.\n2.I also conducted sourcing for an old-school apartment in Kileleshwa within a budget of KES 15 million for a returning client from last year. An option previously shared by Tasha has faced challenges, as the sectional titles have not yet been updated on the Ardhi Sasa platform. The matter remains at an early stage, with no transaction initiated at this time.\n3. had the consultant over to evaluate leads and the campaigns','2026-02-13','','2026-02-13 14:09:56','2026-02-13 14:09:56'),(732,23,'We had a training session for Morvara in the morning after the  Morning meeting.\nHad a viewing with a client to 3 different sites. That is Golfscape, Anjoy and Aria.\nLater joined Aria capital residency for an event shortly with the developer and the client is coming to the office tomorrow for a meeting as well as a presentation on Morvara and Luminara.\nMade calls to the people that had scheduled viewings for tomorrow.\n3 clients have confirmed viewing for tomorrow.','2026-02-13','','2026-02-13 14:16:46','2026-02-13 14:16:46'),(733,12,'Today, following the cancellation of the scheduled viewing appointment by Savannah, I proceeded to Kilimani to source for an old-fashioned three-bedroom unit as requested by Mr. Kitawa.\n\nLater in the day, I attended an agents’ event hosted by Aria Capital to gain further insights into their projects and network with industry professionals.\n\nAdditionally, I conducted follow-ups with Mercy and Mr. Paul, who has confirmed a viewing appointment for tomorrow. I also followed up with Savannah regarding the rescheduling of her viewing.','2026-02-13','','2026-02-13 15:36:05','2026-02-13 15:36:05'),(734,17,'Today, I attended the Morvara training session where I gained a deeper understanding of the project, including its key selling points and overall objectives. The session provided valuable insights that will support future engagements and presentations.\n\nI updated the leads template and shared it before close of business to ensure alignment and proper tracking moving forward, we got a total of 11 leads, 5(meta)6(Tik tok)\n\nThroughout the day, I assisted with general office duties as required and supported Miss Diana with several administrative tasks to ensure smooth operations.\n\nThe scheduled shoot for today was unfortunately postponed to next week. However, this provides us with additional time to prepare and ensure everything is well organized.\n\nAdditionally, I followed up with the official shirt suppliers I am still on it.','2026-02-13','Learning is an endless process','2026-02-13 16:23:42','2026-02-13 16:23:42'),(735,13,'1. I attended our regular morning meeting with my colleagues,it was brief as we had visitors coming,we shared our tasks for the day.\n2.I attended the training for Morvara,their team came to do a presentation to us so that we can have selling points for our clients,we were equipped with  important selling points and we also got to ask questions.\n3.I had another meeting with Rachel Joseph Carol and Tasha,we planned on how sourcing would be done and also how we are going to ensure we have quality photos of the new listed projects.\n4.I received a listing from Tasha but I am yet to upload it since she is yet to provid all the requirements,she will be doing so tomorrow.\n','2026-02-13','My week has ended on a very high note.','2026-02-13 16:30:01','2026-02-13 16:30:01'),(736,46,'-Morning meeting  briefing at 8:30 am.\n-viewing/sourcing and met with the authorized agent for Muthangari  drive for a possible joint venture enquiry.\n-Went for viewing of Tigoni  Kentimere  and Tigoni  Limuru land with my client for the 4 and 5 acres.\n-followed up on pending clients, especially those who had re-scheduled.','2026-02-12','work smart not hard.','2026-02-13 18:07:31','2026-02-13 18:07:31'),(737,46,'-Attended sales meeting at  8:30 am.\n-In attendance for Morvara project training at the office.\n-Went  for Aria project training at Upperhill.\n-Had a viewing for a corner plot (1/4) in parklands with an agent on behalf of her client.\n-Followed up on previous clients.\n-cold marketing via calls,what\'s app ,facebook.\n-update crm later.\n','2026-02-13','consistency ,effort, and positive mindset  ,will bear fruits always.','2026-02-13 18:25:46','2026-02-13 18:25:46'),(738,11,'1. Results of the Day\n\nArrived at the office at approximately 11:00 a.m., as the Morvara team presentation meeting was concluding.\n\nConducted follow-ups on three allocated leads:\n\nBenjamin – Call placed; no response.\n\nSospeter – Call placed; no response.\n\nJonas – Call placed; no response.\n→ All three leads were unresponsive at the time of contact.\n\nAttended a managers’ meeting chaired by Rachel, focused on improving property sourcing strategies and increasing listing inventory.\n\nAgreed on a structured sourcing strategy:\n\nTarget: 5 new listings per week.\n\nStrategy: Divide key areas among agents, with each agent responsible for sourcing within designated locations.\n\nKey Outcome: Clear operational sourcing framework established to improve listing acquisition and inventory growth.\n\n2. What I Learned\n\nLead responsiveness remains a major bottleneck; multi-touch follow-up strategies may be required.\n\nSustainable sales performance depends heavily on consistent listing acquisition.\n\nAssigning defined geographic territories increases accountability and focus in sourcing efforts.\n\n3. Areas for Improvement\n\nImplement structured follow-up sequencing (calls + text + WhatsApp where appropriate).\n\nTrack unresponsive leads systematically to determine when to recycle or deprioritize them.\n\nIncrease proactive sourcing efforts rather than relying solely on inbound or allocated leads.\n\n4. Plan for the Next Day\n\nReattempt contact with the three unresponsive leads using a different follow-up approach.\n\nBegin executing sourcing strategy within assigned location to contribute toward the 5-listings-per-week target.\n\nUpdate CRM with all follow-up attempts and sourcing progress.','2026-02-13','','2026-02-14 06:06:26','2026-02-14 06:06:26'),(740,46,'-Morning debriefing for sale\'s and marketing team.\n-Updated  on pending leads and follow ups  via calls and texts.\n-Viewing  at Bustani Garden  for 4 acres,Redhill  12 acres,Kentimere 5 acres and Tigoni Limuru for the 10 acres with Mr Vant and Mrs .Adhiambo,will follow up next week on their feedback.','2026-02-14','what\'s boost my thrive and zeal?...','2026-02-15 17:27:51','2026-02-15 17:27:51'),(741,13,'1. I attended the Monday morning meeting with my colleagues, we shared our progress for last week and also our plans for this week.\n2.I oriented Lydia as she will be assisting me at the reception and also the website, she is still learning, we will be practicing more tomorrow.\n3.I  uploaded 4 listings from my colleagues ,for land and also for sale, they had provided all the requirements.\n4. I assisted at the reception, I assisted my colleagues and also visitors who visited our offices.','2026-02-16','','2026-02-16 14:04:17','2026-02-16 14:04:17'),(742,15,'1. Today, I assigned eight (8) leads generated from Meta Ads to the Sales Team for follow-up. Additionally, I stepped in on behalf of Joseph and assigned a total of seven (7) leads generated from TikTok Ads to ensure timely distribution and engagement by the team.\n2. Today, I successfully published two video posts and one carousel post across all our social media platforms to maintain consistent online engagement and strengthen brand visibility. The content focused on promoting the Ruiru townhouse project, highlighting key features, location advantages, and overall value proposition to attract potential buyers and generate inquiries.\n3.Today, I engaged in content production planning for the week’s scheduled project shoot. This includes preparations for the Amari townhouses in Ruiru and Morvara Apartments, both of which are key projects we will be actively promoting throughout the week. The focus is on developing targeted marketing content to effectively showcase the properties and drive engagement and inquiries. ','2026-02-16','','2026-02-16 14:07:29','2026-02-16 14:07:29'),(743,29,'- Attended the morning joint meeting for last week\'s reviews and discussing work plans for the day and the entire week.\n- After the meeting, I submitted a carrousel for the Palm court townhouses in Ruiru\n- I then finished making adjustments on the terminal 1A banners and submitted to Joseph and Mr. Ken\n- I edited a property video for the townhouses and submitted in the afternoon\n- Nearing close of business, I created an amenities script for Morvara, and one for Royal green townhouses in Kikuyu, Kamangu.\n- ','2026-02-16','','2026-02-16 14:07:51','2026-02-16 14:07:51'),(744,27,'1. Today in the morning we had an all staff meeting and we discussed and shared our previous week report and performance, expected closure for this month, and what we should do to make February a successful month for each one of us.\n\n2. I was allocated 2 leads (Catherine and Kishore) by Rashid today and they are all responsive. They are looking for an apartment to buy for investment. I have shared their respective project of preference with them. More follow ups to follow tomorrow.\n\n3. I have followed up with my previous leads: Peter, Sam, Pamela, and Stephen and there are two scheduled viewings for this weekend. More viewings will be scheduled once I follow up more with my previous leads.\n\n4. I was supposed to give a report on the following:\n1. Total number of leads are 240 ever since I joined BEKE.\n2. The total number of viewings are 10 for last year plus 24 for this year making a total of 34 viewings ever since I joined BEKE.\n3. Up to date, I only have one executed offer for the 4-bedroom in Emaar Consult and the deposit would be paid this week. One closure, a sale, will be for this month.','2026-02-16','Xīnnián kuàilè to everyone','2026-02-16 14:48:47','2026-02-16 14:48:47'),(745,24,'Attended the morning meeting.\nHeld one interview with a candidate but she didn\'t have experience so we positioned her as a sourcing team.\nHeld an introduction conference Zoom meeting with clients wanting the Two Rivers property, they requested for the documents to start the search which I shared.\nMade follow up calls to my previous clients and made follow ups to the new enquiries I got.\nUpdated my CRM.','2026-02-16','','2026-02-16 15:43:57','2026-02-16 15:43:57'),(746,12,'Today, I was assigned four new leads. One of the prospects was highly responsive and successfully scheduled a site visit for tomorrow.\n\nAdditionally, I conducted follow-ups with Violet and Geoffrey to provide updates and maintain engagement.\n\nAll interactions and progress updates were accurately recorded in the CRM system.','2026-02-16','Viewing appointment with Geddy','2026-02-16 18:18:09','2026-02-16 18:18:09'),(747,17,'1. Monday Morning General Meeting Preparation & Distribution\n\nI drafted and finalized the minutes for the Monday morning general meeting, ensuring it clearly outlined the week’s objectives, performance expectations, and key focus areas. The agenda included updates on ongoing campaigns, lead generation targets, content production plans, and team responsibilities.\n\nAfter preparation, the meeting document was shared with the team in advance to allow members to review and come prepared with updates and feedback. This helped improve clarity, alignment, and overall meeting productivity.\n\n2. Leads Management and Reporting\nI updated the leads Excel sheet and ensured all new entries were accurately recorded and properly categorized by source. By close of business, we had generated a total of 15 new leads, broken down as follows:\n	•	8 leads from Meta campaigns\n	•	7 leads from TikTok campaigns\nEach lead was documented with the necessary details to support follow-up and tracking. After updating, I shared the revised sheet with the relevant team members to ensure timely engagement and conversion follow-up. This update also allows for better monitoring of platform performance and campaign effectiveness.\n\n3. Script Development for Upcoming Shoot.\nIn preparation for tomorrow’s content shoots, I collaborated with Mr. Paddy to develop two structured scripts. The scripts were designed to align with current campaign objectives and target audience interests.','2026-02-16','Yet to be the best version of me','2026-02-16 18:35:56','2026-02-16 18:35:56'),(748,23,'1. Kenneth – Morvara\nInterested in a 1-bedroom unit for investment.\nShared detailed information with him.\nOngoing discussions while actively pushing to secure a viewing.\n2. Damaris – Ruiru Villas (KES 25.5M)\nEnquired in detail about the project.\nCurrently engaging her further and encouraging a site visit.\n3. Halima – Revival Client\nHad previously been out of the country.\nArrived in Kenya today.\nRequested a viewing next week together with her daughters.\n4. Ustav – Land Inquiry (Kiambu Road)\nPreviously viewed Aria.\nShared additional land options, including a 0.5-acre parcel along Kiambu Road priced at KES 50M.\nContinuing to push for a viewing.\n5. Virginia – Rental Follow-Up (Ruiru)\nPreviously viewed a rental unit priced at KES 150K.\nSubmitted an offer of KES 130K.\nEngaged the landlord; awaiting feedback tomorrow.\n6. Audrey – Eternity Booking Inquiry\nClient ready to pay booking fee.\nDeveloper initially advised to wait for potential unit defaults.\nFollow-up done; developer to confirm availability by Wednesday','2026-02-16','','2026-02-16 18:42:48','2026-02-16 18:42:48'),(749,50,'attended the morning meeting.\nmid day: took a client to several sites and later attended a meeting with Gaia developer.\nfollowed up with clients via call','2026-02-16','','2026-02-17 05:35:49','2026-02-17 05:35:49'),(750,53,'- Today attended the Monday meeting got to understand the company a little better.\n- Spent the day doing orientation and going through the website. ','2026-02-17','Excited for the opportunity to make a difference and support the team. ','2026-02-17 06:27:56','2026-02-17 06:27:56'),(751,51,'Daily morning meeting \nHad an interview for the sales team.\nFollowed up on clients \nSourcing for properties in Kikuyu and Ruiru \n\n','2026-02-17','','2026-02-17 12:36:46','2026-02-17 12:36:46'),(752,50,'Attended the early morning meeting.\ncontinued with the regular follow ups of clients\nalso made calls to new potential clients.','2026-02-17','','2026-02-17 13:31:57','2026-02-17 13:31:57'),(753,53,'- Assisted with updating listings in the website.\n- Orientation on Listing onboarding.','2026-02-17','','2026-02-17 13:42:23','2026-02-17 13:42:23'),(754,27,'1. Early morning BEKE staff meeting and we discussed our plans for today, and revisited the listings we were to be sourcing per day.\n\n2. Today, I was allocated 3 leads, where 2 of them are serious and have scheduled a meeting for this weekend and one is an agent. In addition, I followed up with my previous leads and also got two more viewings for this weekend.\n\n3. I went for sourcing in Westlands and Parklands and I got several 1-, and 2-bedroom ready apartments for sale and for rent. I am following up on the same with the owners for the consents. Probably would list them this week.\n\n4. Back to the office to follow up on more leads.','2026-02-17','','2026-02-17 13:52:46','2026-02-17 13:52:46'),(755,13,'1. I attended the morning meeting with my colleagues ,we shared our plans for the day and also had a discussion on sourcing ,we came up with strategies to assist us get unique listings.\n2.Carol, Tasha and I conducted an interview with one candidate, she will be contacted once they review her qualification,she might come for another interview as well.\n3.We had a short discussion with Carol and Tasha, they requested I give a report on the listings brought by memebrs of their team,I did an analysis and gave the report based on the average listings each colleague has been bringing.\n4.I oriented Lydia my colleague on how we will be working and also on how to upload listings in the website.We are progressing well.\n5. I assisted at the reception,I recieved visitors and also assisted my colleagues as required.\n6.I contacted one of my previous clients, I shared with him the Morvara project,he said I should call again next week to see if we can have a viewing.','2026-02-17','I am learning each day.','2026-02-17 13:59:46','2026-02-17 13:59:46'),(756,12,'\nDaily Activity Report\n\nToday, I was assigned five new leads and successfully reached out to all of them. Three of the leads were responsive, and I have updated their details accordingly in the CRM system.\n\nFor the two unresponsive leads, I shared the requested information via WhatsApp for their review and will continue to follow up.\n\nAdditionally, I followed up with Savannah and Paul Ekeya regarding their scheduled viewing appointments for this week to reconfirm availability.\n\nMr. Geddy became unresponsive after initially booking a viewing appointment today. I will follow up with him to establish a suitable and reliable date for the viewing.\n\n\n---\n','2026-02-17','','2026-02-17 15:08:54','2026-02-17 15:08:54'),(757,15,'1. Assigned a total of 15 leads to the sales team for timely follow ups to bost conversations rate and even bring potential closings .\n2. Posted 2 videos to all our social media platforms this included the new year wishes to the Chinese new year .this is just bost engagement and visibility of our pages .\n3. Accompanied paddy and mia to the shoot in both Ruiru and Kikuyu areas for the townhouses shoot which can be incorporated in our stand alone paid campaigns.','2026-02-17','','2026-02-17 15:47:32','2026-02-17 15:47:32'),(758,17,'1. Morning Office Activities\nI attended the morning meeting and prepared the meeting minutes, which were subsequently shared with the relevant team members. I also updated the leads Excel sheet to reflect the latest information and ensured it was submitted by close of business.\n\n2. Site Visit – Kikuyu (Kamangu)\nAfter completing office tasks, I proceeded to Kikuyu, Kamangu for a townhouse project shoot. The development is a well-executed and impressive project, showcasing quality design and workmanship. The shoot was successfully conducted as planned.\n\n3. Site Visit – Ruiru (Amari Project)\nLater in the day, I traveled to Ruiru for another property shoot at the Amari Project. The session was completed successfully, capturing the required content.\n','2026-02-17','Trying and failing is better than not trying at all.','2026-02-17 16:42:03','2026-02-17 16:42:03'),(759,23,'NEW LEADS\n\n1. Hector\nRequirement: 3-bedroom apartment for rent\nBudget: 70,000\nStatus: Currently sourcing suitable options within the stated budget.\nNext Step: Shortlist and share available properties with the client for review.\n2. Elizabeth\nInquiry received via WhatsApp requesting property details.\nStatus: Initial information shared.\nNext Step: Continue engagement and follow up to secure a viewing appointment.\n3. Felix\nStatus: Currently unreachable.\nNext Step: Attempt another call and follow up with a text message.\n2. Ongoing Negotiations\nVirginia\'s Offer\nPresented an offer of 130,000 per month to the landlord.\nOutcome: Offer was rejected.\nNext Step: Await further instruction from the client or explore room for renegotiation.\n3. Client Follow-Ups\nConducted follow-up calls with previous clients to check on interest and explore potential opportunities.\n','2026-02-17','','2026-02-17 16:45:46','2026-02-17 16:45:46'),(760,11,'1. Results of the Day\n\n    •	Chaired weekly review meeting.\n	•	Assessed weekly viewings, projected monthly closings, and addressed sourcing gaps with agreed corrective actions.\n\nLead Follow-ups\n	•	Contacted three allocated leads:\n	•	Two unresponsive.\n	•	One seeking investment property in Kileleshwa options but wants to invest in 3 - 6 months. \n\nClosings \n	•	Rental Closed: Alina Harbour, Kilimani – payment completed.\n	•	Sales (Advanced Stage): Client selected Oasis Metricon; 14-day offer secured (expires 2nd March), awaiting deposit.\n\nOverall: Strong performance with one confirmed closing and one high-probability sale in progress.\n','2026-02-16','Hopefull for a Sale closure this month .\n(Apologies for sending yesterday\'s report late)','2026-02-17 18:34:29','2026-02-17 18:34:29'),(761,11,'1. Results of Today’s Work\n\nMorning\n	•	Attended team meeting chaired by Joseph.\n\nLead Follow-Ups (4 Leads)\n	•	Nasib: Seeking rent-to-own near Westlands; no viable options available → unable to proceed.\n	•	Thomas: Investment client (KES 7M budget); options shared → awaiting feedback.\n	•	Raymond: Unresponsive after calls and message.\n	•	Ruiru Villas Lead: Pending first contact due to schedule constraints.\n\nClient Viewing – Westlands (Investment)\n	•	Viewed 3 properties.\n	•	Client reviewing options → active lead\n\nRecruitment\n	•	Assisted in two interviews:\n	•	One disqualified (inconsistent information).\n	•	One under review (limited experience but potential).\n\n2. Key Learnings\n	•	Rent-to-own demand exists but is limited in prime locations.\n	•	Budget-sensitive investors require precise option matching.\n	•	Fast response time improves lead control.\n\n3. Areas for Improvement\n	•	Increase speed of first contact for new leads.\n','2026-02-17','Hopefull for a closure','2026-02-17 18:51:35','2026-02-17 18:51:35'),(762,46,'-Attended  the morning sales meeting.\n-followed up on pending clients/leads.\n-sourced for properties along Maasai lodge and Ruiru upon enquiries for clients.\n-Pre-viewed paradise losts on behalf of the client to get more equipped with the property before taking my client next week .\n-Sourced for a 3/4 plot in Kitusuru for sale at 90 million.\n-Sourced for Aria property at Upperhill(off-plan).\n-Later update crm.','2026-02-16','persistent..','2026-02-18 04:57:22','2026-02-18 04:57:22'),(763,46,'-Managed to go for a site visit with Mr.Kinyua at Tigoni at around 8:23 am,his interested in investing on 1 acre for now.\n-Went back to the office and followed up pending clients and leads assigned.\n-Joined the marketing team for pre-view of a townhouse in Kamangu.\n-Sourced for a 3 bedroom bungalows at Nova (15.3 million)sitting on a 50 by 100 plot.Great investiment for the outskirt lovers.\n-Previewed 2 more properties in Mugutha (selling at 20 -25) million.\n-later updated crm.','2026-02-17','True nobility is being superior to my former self.','2026-02-18 05:19:50','2026-02-18 05:19:50'),(764,53,'- Worked on the Internal Property Listing that will be essential to the team . Handed over by Tasha.\n- Contacted some Property Listings and Contractors to get accurate and more details on some of the listing.\n- Did some research on ways we could improve the companies Outreach activities, this was to se on how Marketing could also be done from a personal level. \n- Uploaded some Listing on the website.\n- Learnt How the company Marketing team works and strategies the put in place to reach more people in the market.','2026-02-18','It has overall been a good day, However I would really appreciate if the laptop issue could be sorted to avoid any future problems.','2026-02-18 13:52:32','2026-02-18 13:52:32'),(765,29,'- Attended the morning marketing team meeting, shared our various work plans for the day\n- I edited a talking video of Mia in the Kikuyu townhouse we shot yesterday after the meeting and submitted\n- I then started creating billboard samples for purposes of marketing and submitted in the afternoon\n- In the afternoon, I edited a property video for Royal green and submitted by close of business\n','2026-02-18','','2026-02-18 13:54:02','2026-02-18 13:54:02'),(766,13,'1. I attended the morning meeting as required, Joseph encouraged us to call our previous clients, as they might be ready by now.\n2. I oriented Lydia on how we will be working, she is doing well and she is also learning fast.\n3. I uploaded 2 listings for sale from Carol and Dennis, they had provided all the requirements making the process easy.\n4.Lydia and I assisted at the reception, attending to both our colleagues and visitors as well.\n5.Tasha shared with us an excel with a lot of listings where we will be confirming the listings that we already have and the ones that we still don\'t have, for the  ones we don\'t have we will  be uploading them . We will also share the excel with our colleagues so that they can have options to share with their clients easily.\n','2026-02-18','I am glad to have a new colleague, now we can work together and also share new ideas .','2026-02-18 13:58:19','2026-02-18 13:58:19'),(767,15,'1. A total of 19 new leads were assigned today, including 15 from Meta campaigns and 4 from TikTok, ensuring continued pipeline development across key digital channels.\n2. A promotional reel featuring a newly designed e-card for the currently marketed townhouses was published. The content generated two organic leads, reflecting improved social media visibility and growing audience engagement.\n3. Additionally, a substantial portion of the day was dedicated to evaluating campaign performance and consulting on lead quality, targeting effectiveness, and optimization opportunities to enhance overall marketing efficiency.','2026-02-18','','2026-02-18 15:05:31','2026-02-18 15:05:31'),(768,27,'1. BEKE staff meeting in the morning and we talked about our week\'s activity and the plans for today. We also shared our hot enquiries and how we can close.\n\n2. Mogotio Oasis came and presented their project to us, and we interacted with them especially on their selling points. We shall embark on more enquiries to them.\n\n3. Viewing with Brian\'s client at Morvara. She is a hot lead who might close on Monday.\n\n4. I sourced for 3 projects this week; Golden Mango Heights, Serene Manor, and Auris Residency. Diana has uploaded them.\n\n5. Today, I started following up with all the TikTok leads Joseph allocated me in the month of November and December. I am halfway and by tomorrow, I shall have a report ready.','2026-02-18','','2026-02-18 15:44:19','2026-02-18 15:44:19'),(769,24,'17/02/2026\nHeld Morning meeting in Tigoni with the land owner, Lead Agent and Client to discuss how we are going to do the subdivision for the property for the clients interested to purchase. The landowner requested the surveyor for a quotation to do the same.\nViewed Lavington 2properties with a client for JV option, Moses at Kabasiran and Mumin at Magenta.\nIn the afternoon  took a client to EPZ Kitengela to view 20acres JV, Waiting for his proposal. \n\n18/02/2026\nHeld an in-depth morning meeting with my team where we discuss progress so far for the team and shared the current enquiries.\nHeld another meeting with the Developer for 88Kikuyu to discuss the project the commission and sole agency partnership, he shared the relevant documents for us to begin the search process.\nMade follow up calls to the existing clients and updated my CRM.','2026-02-18','','2026-02-18 15:55:47','2026-02-18 15:55:47'),(770,51,'Attended the presentation from Mogotio Oasis team\nMeeting with 88Kikuyu developer and managers regarding sole agency\nFollow ups ','2026-02-18','','2026-02-18 16:13:14','2026-02-18 16:13:14'),(771,23,'Leads Update – Marketing Team (3 Leads Assigned)\n1. Regina (Ruiru Buyer)\nMost responsive lead.\nInterested in purchasing a property in Ruiru.\nIndicated that Greenview is above her budget.\nPalm Court is within her budget and a viable option.\nShared project details and currently pushing to secure a viewing.\n2. Elizabeth (Ruiru Buyer)\nInterested in purchasing property in Ruiru.\nRequested project details, which have been shared.\nFollowing up and pushing to schedule a viewing.\n3. Regina (3-Bedroom Apartment Buyer – Currently in Mombasa)\nInterested in purchasing a 3-bedroom apartment.\nCurrently in Mombasa.\nShared available options.\nWill arrange viewings once she returns.\nFollow-Ups (10 Calls Made to Previous Clients)\nKadhra\nInterested in a 4-bedroom villa for rent.\nSourced a 5-bedroom villa for rent at KES 185,000 and recommended it.\nShe will discuss with her husband before scheduling a viewing.\nEric Mbai\nConfirmed physical meeting at the office tomorrow morning.\nScheduled to view Morvara thereafter','2026-02-18','','2026-02-18 17:16:11','2026-02-18 17:16:11'),(772,17,'Daily Marketing Activity Report\n1. Morning Marketing Meeting Minutes\n\nThe minutes of the morning marketing meeting were accurately documented and subsequently shared with the Beke Marketing Group for reference and alignment. The report captured key discussions, assigned responsibilities, action points, and timelines to ensure clarity and accountability among team members.\n\n2. Leads Generation and Performance Update\nThe leads tracking Excel sheet was reviewed, updated, and circulated at the close of business to reflect the day’s performance metrics.\n\nA total of 18 leads were generated today, from meta and Tik tok \n	•	TikTok: 4 leads\n	•	Meta (Facebook & Instagram): 14 leads\n\nThis update ensures transparency in campaign performance tracking and allows for continuous monitoring of platform effectiveness. The data has been properly recorded to support ongoing analysis and strategic adjustments where necessary.\n\n3. Lead Follow-Up – Village Market Contacts\nFollow-up communication was initiated with selected leads acquired from Village Market outreach efforts. Initial contact has been made, and responses are currently pending. Once feedback is received, further engagement and follow-up actions will be implemented to progress these prospects through the conversion pipeline.\n\n4. Supplier Engagement – Official Beke Team Shirts\n\nCommunication with the supplier for the official Beke team shirts has been finalized. A meeting has been scheduled for Saturday morning to discuss pricing, material specifications, design details, production timelines, and delivery schedules. This engagement is aimed at ensuring quality standards and timely availability of official team apparel.\n','2026-02-18','Journey to success is not a walk in the park, you have to step out of the comfort zone and make things happen.','2026-02-18 17:29:24','2026-02-18 17:29:24'),(773,12,'\n\n---\n\nDaily Report\n\nToday, I was assigned a client, Muthoni, who is actively looking for a 5-bedroom house for rent along Kamiti Road or in Ruiru. The available option had already been rented out; therefore, I am currently sourcing alternative properties that meet her requirements.\n\nLater in the day, I accompanied Saloni for a viewing of Morvara from the Broadwalk Mall rooftop to give her a better perspective of the development and its surroundings.\n\nAdditionally, I took Maggie to view units at Sky Valley as part of her ongoing property search.\n\nI will continue sourcing suitable options and following up with the respective clients accordingly','2026-02-18','','2026-02-18 17:53:39','2026-02-18 17:53:39');
/*!40000 ALTER TABLE `daily_reports` ENABLE KEYS */;
